text: I took my car to this dealership to get a diagnostic test done to see what was wrong with my car. I told them that my brake/parking light and engine light was on as well another mechanic telling me I had a transmission problem (my car was making noise) . I was told that because I informed them that three things were wrong with my car that they normally charge $89.99 per problem (yes I said PER PROBLEM) but since it was three things they were only going to charge me $129.99 to look at (first sign). So while I'm waiting on my car to be checked out I start looking at used cars. The sales rep comes over to help me and we start the process of purchasing a used car. He comes back with a price of $500 for my car (which is a 2013 ford c-max energy limited edition) because he was told that the transmission was bad. I asked for the diagnostic test results to show that and he never showed me (he told me that a certified tech informed him). I said let me take my car out of here only to come and find out that it was a water-pump. I will never be taking my car to another dealership.
Kim is the shit!!! Talk about bottomless mimosas... this is the spot damnit!  Food needed salt but everything else was perfect!!!

I was searching for a salon in Philly and came across Salon Bass since it had such good reviews and let me tell you it did not disappoint! I had an appointment with Joe for a cut and color and he is amazing. Freshened up my color and gave me a fresh new cut and I am in love! I will definitely be coming back to Joe from now on and I highly recommend him.

I waited 35 minutes, and Gina never showed up for my appointment. The receptionist was unable to contact her, and said she was also a no-show earlier that day. I hope Gina is okay and don't want to make any harsh judgments, but I wasted my time and money regardless. Hoping to get a refund :/

Dr. Davidson did cataract surgery on both of my eyes. It was done quickly and with absolutely perfect results. I couldn't ask for better results in a better attitude from him. I have and will continue to recommend him to anyone I know that needs cataract surgery.
Lots of running room for my big boy and his little sister. They come home clean and tired after a long day of play and I couldn't be more pleased with the customer service!!

The sushi here is amazing! Tonight was the second time I've eaten here. Although the food is great, the staff is horrible! The first time I went we got the same waiter who did not introduce himself so I couldn't get a name. He was not attentive or friendly. He didn't bring out our waters for 20 mins. We ordered sushi rolls that are suppose to be $5 each after 10pm and he rang up two meals instead. Our bill came out double the amount! We told him and he didn't make the changes. I will never return to this place and it's sad cause the sushi is so good :(
The best sushi restaurant in the Tampa Bay area (well, it's my favorite--and I eat a lot of sushi).

After my daughter graduated from the University of Arizona in Tucson, I needed to figure out a way to move all her things back to Illinois.  As she has a compact car, renting a UHaul and driving it across the country was not a viable option. I also looked into packing everything up and shipping via UPS or the USPS.  Once again, way too expensive and not a viable option. I looked into one-way truck rentals (Penske was reasonable), but then reconsidered when I factored in the gas, hotels, meals, and 2+ days of driving across the country in the middle of winter.  I finally found U-Pack and knew it was the way to go. The online reservation was simple. I called their 800 number to have some questions answered and found out they even offered a student discount.  The price was very reasonable. I chose to drop off and pick up our belongings to save quite a bit of money. They gave me step-by-step information on how the move would be handled and what I needed to know to prepare for the move.  I knew this was the best option for us.  I had everything boxed in Rubbermaid totes so transporting our belongings into the U-Pack pod was very simple and quick.  They said there was enough room for a one-bedroom apartment and we had room to spare.  We loaded everything into the U-Pack in Tucson (it took about 15 minutes from check-in until we drove out of the parking lot).  Within an hour, I got an email telling me that our pod was loaded onto a truck and had left for our destination.  We expected our pod to arrive 5-7 days in Illinois.  It arrived in 4.  I got a phone call and an email informing me that it was ready to be unloaded. I drove out to the facility in Sauk Village, IL, the following morning.  The unloading process took about 15 minutes from checking in with the office to getting our pod delivered (via forklift) to my car, unloading the pod, and driving out of the trucking center.  I still am amazed at how convenient this was.  I am very thankful that I found U-Pack.

Another thing to consider:  Rather than taking several trips back and forth to load/unload the U-Pack, I rented a moving van from Home Depot in Arizona and again in Illinois to be able to make one trip to the U-Pack facilities.  They charged $19.95 for up to 90 minutes (plus return the gas tank filled). Home Depot doesn't charge a mileage fee.
I recently relocated from Tampa and was thrilled to find Nathan at La Bella. I got a gel manicure and a spa pedicure. Very pleased with my experience and the services I received.

From out of town,

It was our last full day/night in NOLA, so we were just walking around and we happened to pass this place after we finished eating brunch cause I saw the happy hour sign.

The happy hour is amazing. I can't even explain, you just gotta go see it to believe me lol. 

So we started off with a few beers/well cocktails. And we ended up playing some pool, and then ended up playing a couple rounds of beer pong. Then my husband and our other friend started playing flip cup with the bartender, and it's going to kill me that I cannot remember name! But she was super fun! * the bartender won the flip cup LOL* and they both had to spin the wheel on the wall, hilarioussss!

After awhile, she gave us some shots that were called green tea shots? I was super hesitant to take them, I don't do shots like that. And surprisingly it legit tasted like green tea! Then the bartender told me to get on the bar, kind of freaked me out a bit lol. I ended up doing my first body shot! Eek. Was super terrified! But I'm hella ticklish so the liquor kind of went everywhere lol.. oops! After that me, my two girlfriends and another girl ended up on the bar doing BJ shots. My god. It was just a wild time!

Def a new type of bar experience for me and I liked it! If you want to have fun without burning your pockets then go here! It's def a good time and youll def leave feeling amazing!
My family and I love Uno's. Pizza is great. Would give a 5 star review if the servers were consistent with their level of service. It's hit or miss with the server staff.

This new Tunisian-based BYO is a complete makeover of the Thai operation formerly here. The new decor is awash in soft, light blue (what else?) executed with exceptional taste. The overall effect is delightfully romantic, especially for Doylestown, which can use something "date night" like this even though the mellow vibe was diminished by a bright sconce light over our table.

The owners are obviously anxious to please, and could hardly do more to make folks feel welcome. We were warmly greeted, well taken care of throughout, and even given a complimentary after-dinner degustation.

Our appetizers -- octopus and a meatball special -- were absolutely spectacular, fully worthy of a great restaurant. The latter was spicy in the best sense, with heat used to enhance flavor using a delectable mix of herbs and spices from the owner's mother in Tunisia.

Were the meal to end there, Blu would qualify for a major detour and a solid five stars. Alas, the warhorse mains -- lamb couscous and moussaka -- were ordinare, albeit using superior quality lamb and other ingredients. Couscous was too dry and lacking in flavor complexity, while moussaka came off as little more than pleasant comfort food. If you want worthy moussaka hereabouts, try someplace like Philly's Estia.

The dessert of superior baklava and dates fared much better except for tiny portion size. If you're more than a nibbler, you're better off walking down the block to excellent Nina's or even Nonno's.

The owner has had long experience as a chef, and given the investment he's made appears to be playing it safe and predictable with menu offerings. Yet, he obviously has talent worthy of much greater things, so in time the main courses may expand to approach the quality and creativity of the apps we enjoyed. In the meantime, best bet is probably to steer clear of predictable menu choices and spring instead for the specials.

Worth mentioning is how clean this place is, and not only to the eye. We noticed that when a table was cleared off where a family with children had been, the floor area around that table was also wiped down.

We got out for under $45/person, plus tip and wine.

First of all, I am never one to leave negative reviews; I have never felt strongly enough to leave one until now.  At this point, we are beyond frustrated and extremely disappointed in United Van Lines, and I think it's necessary for others to hear our experience before choosing a moving company.  

We used them for our recent move from Kansas to Texas and ran into problem after problem.  The first issue was that they gave us a one week window in which they would deliver our belongings, then did not deliver them until 6 days after the window closed.  Upon arrival, we had several items damaged.  

Just to name a few:
-Our washing machine is completely broken.  The knob snapped in half, and parts are loose inside of the washer itself.
-A large chunk is taken out of our antique, wooden buffet table from England.  There is also a piece completely missing on the front.  This upsets more than most since it is impossible to replace.
-A chunk of the wooden leg on our couch is missing.
-The bottom drawer of our wooden filing cabinet is completely broken and appears something got knocked through it.

Note that the people who loaded and unloaded our belongings at our homes were all wonderful and careful.  They were not employees of United Van Lines but third party moving companies.  
United told us that everything was unloaded off of the original truck and then loaded into large wooden crates before bringing them to Texas for our local company to move.  It is obvious that the United employees who loaded/reloaded our belongings were completely careless.

While we are able to make claims for these items, it is extremely frustrating and not all of the items can be replaced.  

I strongly advise you to choose another company.

I have to give 1 star because they almost ruined my experience at Tampa. I finished a Bush Gardens and called to know the closing time, they said 9 pm, so I got at 8:30 pm and the 2 ladies in the front said kitchen was closed and they can't even take to go orders. I called back and asked again and "Cristal" said it was opened. The ladies continued in the same attitude, even saying there was nobody in the restaurant with that name. I know it is Christmas Eve, I work in a restaurant too and totally understand, but you should never do that to a customer. It's so irrespecutful  from these two ladies playing and lying just because they want to go home. The guy in the bar took my to go order kindly.

Decided to try somewhere new for sushi this week and decided to go here. The inside is very clean and well decorated. I called the day before for a reservation, which they subsequently forgot to write down but they still took us sense it wasn't full. All of the staff was very nice and courteous. The rice to fish ratio was off, to heavy on the rice and the rolls were not as tight as we would have liked and did fall apart fairly easily. Some of the sushi rolls were cut so big they barely fit in your mouth. Over all taste was quite yummy though. The spicy tuna was mushy but the rest of our fish was very good and fresh. The absolute best thing on the menu however is their dessert rolls. So amazing! The OMG was totally OMG good! Would recommend for dessert rolls!

We stayed at the Hilton during the Christmas holiday and were happy to have a well known restaurant right in the hotel! My sister had also recommended Drago's to us when she was here this past July. This restaurant was very busy and they had plenty of staff which can be good or bad depending how you look at it. In our case our waitress was very nice but didn't come around as much. My husband only had one Bud Light the entire time. On to the food we all know the "Star" of Drago's is the charred oysters and they didn't disappoint at all. I ordered the stuffed shrimp with boudin and it was very delicious. My husband ordered the Shucky Duckey the duck was tender and moist, the oyster were good but biting into his pasta you also bit into shells which was a little disappointing he didn't finish it. Overall great restaurant for Oysters and the food was good too.

This would be five stars if it were just for the food. These were some amazing pancakes. The buckwheat ones were maybe my favorite pancakes ever (and I've had many in my 46 years, believe me). We ordered sweet potato pancakes to share, and they were also fabulous. Even the yogurt with granola was better than it had any right to be. Kids both loved their chocolate pancakes.

We didn't mind waiting 35 minutes in the cold for a table. That we expected. We didn't expect to have to wait nearly an hour for our food once we ordered. The waitress apologized and said the kitchen was having issues. Kind of slowed down our day. All told, we spent two hours here to have our 15 minutes of eating. Not sure it was worth all that time. They need to work on their service.

Cons: 

Very strict policies. Read the fine print. 

One day I had completed a workout and got into the locker room only to find that they had plumbers just started working on both showers after a class in November. They could have had them work on only one shower at a time or wait until after everyone had left the locker room. 

Almost impossible to understand the instructions over the loud music. If you are new or don't attend regularly, you may be completely lost. 

Pros: very clean studio and great workout. Easy attached parking. 

NOTE: BB studios must be independently owned. Pricing is different depending on location and you can't share passes between studios.

They are open very late at night. Pizzas by the slice was good, freshly made and good variety to choose from. You get a pick up copule of slices to go or you have dine in, they a good extensive menu. Great place to go to if your in the area late at night and need a bite after drinking.

The better bodega. A nice assortment of groceries. Wine bar and coffee bar and a few tables out side where you can meet friends for a bite or conduct business. Staff is very well trained , always courteous and the owners are AWESOME! I have requested items to be stocked and they did immediately. Ask about their loyalty program. I have received a 10% discount a few times.

I was here for the American Geophysical Union (AGU) conference this December, my first time at both the meeting and this conference center. The staff were generally helpful, but not very friendly. Another problem was that the rooms where presentations took place kept having their lights go off and on, which was highly distracting. The food at the food court was also sub-par and overpriced.

I never usually write reviews. But this place was so terrible, I had to write this one. I will never be coming back to this establishment for these four reasons.

1. Host service was terrible, we were told it would be a 10-15 minute wait tops. We sat at the bar for 40 minutes with no update until our table was ready.

2. Service was annoying. We were left unattended for the first 15 minutes, confused and hungry. We asked the runner that brought us a wrong order to bring us our server. And when we did get him, he had no idea if we were his table. 

3. FOOD. I wish I had taken photos of our table, because all the food was still there! The burger was underwhelming, weird patty, pickled jalapenos, and black shriveled bacon. We also got the french onion soup, wings, and tots. Overall the food was nasty, and overpriced. 

4. Last but not least, the management service was dreadful. We told our server how we did not like the burger w/ fries, and french onion soup (which we hadn't eaten). And the manager took off 10% of the burger off because the burnt bacon was apparently 10% of the order. Unfortunately, we drunkenly paid for our check, as we left still hungry by the end of the night.

SAVE YOURSELF THE TIME AND MONEY.

DO NOT GO TO SIX FEET UNDER.
Thai food picked up for the misses. Great food! Very popular spot in my township and they continue to get great business.

Great service from the moment you walk in the building. Very relaxing service. The only thing I'd change is the waiting room area can be a little loud before your spa treatment. But overall great service!

We've been here a bunch of times over the years, and it's always a fun time to walk around! Even though it's basically a bunch of gardens and a big greenhouse, they change up the displays so frequently that it makes it interesting. Most recently, we were there to see a Longwood Christmas, which is always quite the crowd-pleaser!

A few years ago, they did a show called Nightscape during the summer, which was one of the greatest experiences I've ever had in the gardens! At night, they put moving light projections on different plants and played very immersive music. It was a very cool experience, and I was happy that they did it two years in a row. Because they reopened the fountains this year, they focused on that for the summer rather than redoing Nightscape, but the fountain shows were really great as well.

It's always fun to see what they have on display, and it's truly amazing what they're able to do with plants. They have plants that defy what I thought was possible!

Food there isn't amazing, though. Mushroom soup is good, but nothing else we've tried is worth getting again. Maybe some of the ice cream. Anyway, you're there for the plants, not the food!
Really nice outside dinning. Great service and good food. Perfect for a big gathering or loud party!

Service started out ok and then apparently our server had plans after work bc as soon as our food came out, she brought our checks and we didn't see her again except for cleaning the restaurant,  even as new patrons were walking in! Terrible customer service,  particularly for a Fri.  Night, and it was only 9pm. I will not return to that location. Owner/ manager was nice and I would have said something to him if we hadn't been with 6 other people

Food was ok. They do offer gluten-fee options which is always nice. As far as ambiance, hard to say. We were seated at a table, which was a little crowded. We notice 3 booths nearby, which were open and asked to be moved there for a little more elbow room. It was only 2 of us, so it should not have been an issue. When the host came back, he proceeded to take us to the "back" of the restaurant  It was cold, no heat,no TVs , etc. They sat us in a booth for 6. It was quite obvious that they did not like our asking for a different seating arrangement   Needless to say I lost my appetite and only my son ate. We will not be coming back here. No one likes to sit with a jacket on and eat. It was quite unpleasant   It seems customer service is not their strong suit.

First time here! Service was very friendly, fast and great! The wings were very good and the barmaid gave great recommendations for drinks. I would definitely come back. Nice positive vibe and atmosphere!

Only 3 stars is a travesty!

Solid beer collection. Got dogfish 90 minutes on draft

The pretzel appetizer was on point as was the short rib sandwich with special fries
Great service, kind and respectful staff--I love it here!  I bought my 2015 Lexus RX 350here, and I haven't let anyone else touch my car and won't in the future!

Everything about this place was awesome! Great service, great food and great drinks. My son had a burger medium and it was perfect! I had a Korean pick belly sandwich which was full of flavor.

Couldn't recommend it enough - 5 stars all the way

Stopped here when I was shopping over the weekend for a yummy hot chocolate and a latte. Expensive, the same price as Starbucks - maybe more because the sizes are smaller here. Nothing to write home about. I'm sure some people love it but it wasn't what we were looking for. It was a nice little storefront to sit in.
I couldn't believe how pleasant the lady was here! Great pizza! Hard to find good pizza other than imos around these parts. This place delivers!

What a wonderful shop! They have an excellent selection of yarn - I especially liked their variety of Malabrigo. This certainly seems like a great place to go if you need a specialty yarn, or help on a project. The owner, Tim, is incredibly friendly and helpful too. Thanks!

In my pursuit to find a warm, flavorful soup, on the first snow day of the season, I came to Cafe Nahn. It seems many other people shared my idea because the tiny the restaurant had a 20-30 minute wait.

Well, the wait well worth it. I ordered the beef brisket stew and the caramelized pork belly, with boiled egg and rice.

The stew was hearty and very flavorful. This place clearly doesn't rely on a pile of salt for seasoning, like I've experienced at other places that serve headache-inducing, overly salted broth. And the beef was so tender that it fell apart. The rice noodles were also cooked to perfection with the ideal bouncy texture.

While the pork belly was good, it was well-seasoned and tender, I was expecting something a bit more grand. When caramelizing a protein, I thought the outer portion should be, at the very least, browned with a light or very light crisp on the surface.This pork didn't have the desired color or texture, it looked like it was stewed. Also, the pork belly lacked the star feature of this particular cut: the tri-layers comprised of skin and meat that are joined together by a nice layer of fat. And depending on how it was cooked, each layer lends a contrasting texture. At Cafe Nahn, it appears the chef removed the skin, which was a mild disappointment.

 Despite this, the dish wasn't the worse thing and had many other redeeming qualities like the aforementioned amount of flavor and tenderness. Another delicious touch was the boiled egg that was stained the color of the pork brother because it was most likely boiled in the broth.

I will definitely comeback to Cafe Nahn. The customer service and food were both great!

Chicken Tenders. I ordered chicken tenders. I got three stretched out nuggets. The S'maweome sauce was a poor attempt at Zackby's Zax sauce. What did it for me though was the lady's attitude at the drive through. I got rushed at the speaker, and when my fiancé asked for a spoon for her frosty... "I PUHT DAT IN DA BAG ALREADY HAVE A NICE DAY BAI." Taco Bell is across the street. Peace out.

Go here and get the brisket.  Staff is wonderful, polished and professional.  Food is excellent, and unlike so many other places, the portion sizes are correct for a human with one stomach.  The kitchen is run by someone who clearly knows how to organize, the atmosphere was quaint.

If you want to know if Ale Emporium is good, try going in there on any given evening, weekend, or during a sporting event of any significance and try to find a table. My husband loves this place for their wings and pizza. Both are excellent. The deep dish pizza is fantastic and incredibly filling, so order less than you think you'll need. Great beer selection, pretty good service. The only thing that keeps us from going here more often is the lack of a host. The whole place is open seating like a bar usually would be, but this place is huge so it seems to me there should be some kind of organization. When we drive by, if the lot is full and we're really hungry, we usually go elsewhere. But if you have time to stare down fellow diners to steal their table when they're done, it's worth it.

Good side: Everyone was very polite and helpful. I asked someone about the price on some tea and he didn't know but went and found out and then found me again to tell me. I could tell some people were still being trained but even they were polite and speedy. This restaurant is adorable. The artwork on the back wall is cheery and very pretty. I love the gold chairs. I love the benches. It's a great look. You walk in, order and then find a seat which seems to keep things speedy. I ordered the hand pie and it was absolutely delicious. I devoured it. In about 2 minutes. I even wanted to finish the gravy with a spoon. Which leads me to the bad side . . . 

Bad side: The portion was so small. They were so good but I finished lunch super quickly and was still hungry. For the price, I expected a little more food. I ended up getting a croissant on my way out because I was still so hungry. The croissant was flakey and delicious but that plus my lunch was kind of pricey. It was good but this is going to be more of a "special occasion" lunch spot rather than a quick everyday lunch spot.

I've never had shrimp & grits! I am glad I had it at Mack & Kate's! 
Ambiance & decor are beautiful but there's still prejudice in the South. Sadly it's felt at Mack & Kate's!

This is hands down, the best breakfast burrito you will find in Nashville. When my coworkers told me they were going to Postmates breakfast burritos from a place named 51st Deli, I was skeptical to say the least. I have spent the last 6 months trying to find some Arizona-status Mexican food and this was the last place I expected to find it. Pastor Spicy Pineapple Pork burritos, the Barbacoa Brisket burrito, and of course the classic breakfast burrito- are all great choices. They have the best salsa, you get a choice of red or green. I haven't ventured to trying any of the amazing looking sandwiches or salads that they also offer. I have had friends order food with me that say they make the best Reuben in town... but, I will probably never order it. The burritos are just so amazing that nothing can compare. I like what I like. See you tomorrow 51st Deli.

Stopped here quick on a road trip- totally worth it! Not too far off the jersey turnpike, about 10 minutes. The staff were all very friendly. I got a fried pickle chicken sandwich and it was one of the best sandwiches I've ever had. The Mac and cheese was so creamy and a large portion! My boyfriend got the truffle mushroom chicken sandwich and he still can't stop talking about it. Definitely check them out out if you have the opportunity! A tad on the expensive side but quality makes it so worth it!!!

Noooooo. So sad to have to update my previous 5 star review after my visit to "new yards." I had such high hopes and I was totally underwhelmed. The industrial decor was bland and had no nods to Philly. It reminded me of an iron hill. Nothing really wrong with that but nothing really special about it. I got a Bavarian pretzel which was very meh. Seemed microwaved and not quite heated up enough. My friend had the fried chicken sandwich which was good. The three stars are because I actually do love the beer and that was just as good as remembered.

Service was great! They greated us by name when we would come in. House keeping saw that there was six of us amd immediately brought extra towels and shampoo without us asking. 
It's older and rooms are on the small side. Near the airport, which is both good and bad.
Full menu at the bar. Apps and salads are ON POINT. Of course the 'za is to die for. Wine list is as creative as the quail egg pizzas. Brava, Martha!
Excellent food and live music.  I had the baked chicken and others had the burger and fried chicken. Food was great and a good selection of beverages.

My daughter, a student at UCSB rents a property managed by Wolfe and Associates.  After a recent tenant call, the property manager found a water leak under the floor in the crawl space and as a father I was pleased that the property manager took immediate action by having a remediation contractor check for mold, having some internal dampness treated with Tilex (just in case), and scheduling to have carpeting removed and replaced (and subfloor if necessary) within a time frame conducive to the tenants who were finishing up finals. An option was even extended for the tenants to move into a vacant apartment on Del Playa (on the beach) for the week if they wanted to, or to have the new carpet put in over the holidays when the tenants were away on break.  You can't ask for much more than that.  Bear in mind that a property manager is often constrained by the demands of the property owner.  Fortunately, our Winders property owners see the long term value of doing right by good tenants and providing a safe environment for student tenants.  I was very pleased how Tom at Wolfe & Assoc. and the property owners handled this situation.

I would recommend not going here. The sushi is average and the costumer service is horrible and the manager names Martha should not be a manager. 

My boyfriend and I went there for dinner and he ordered muscles. He was eating a muscle and spit one out and cut it open and inside there was a disgusting spider looking thing inside the muscle. We immediately both lost our appetite. The way the "spider looking thing" was inside the actually meat of the muscles made us uneasy. We called over a manager and we're very polite. We showed her the "bug" and all she had to say was "oh yeah sometimes that happens, it's fine." After looking it up on the internet it looked exactly like a parasite. Were we just supposed to believe her? That it's just fine and sometimes that happens?? How were we supposed to know that. After arguing with her for 10 minutes she refused to do anything about it. We didn't even touch the sushi and finally just paid for our meal because we wanted to leave. She said she doesn't care if everyone knew this was in there food and she didn't care if heath inspection found out about it. I just wanted to share this with everyone because not only is this disgusting, it's dangerous.

This place might be the cute Hyde Park setting you are looking for, but i wont have dinner here again!

I ordered their crispy chicken and it was below average. The food is overpriced and the quality is below average. For a little more you can go to a fancier place and get much more for your money. I suggest that they review their menu and their value. 

Their old fashioned is the one good thing on their menu!

Absolutely awful experience. 
I ordered a washer/dryer combo online on Oct 17, 2017. The following day I received an email that only stated that a refund had been issued, not what had been returned. I had to call to find out that the dryer had been credited back due to unavailability. At this point, I canceled the entire order since I wanted the combo. Just before Thanksgiving 2017, I received my credit card statement and the refund had not been returned. I called the Sears Customer Service 800 number, they said that they would have to email the store and notify them to return the item so they could refund the money and would email me in approximately 48 hours. 
I allowed a week to go by but didn't receive an email. I called the 800 number again, and told the same thing as before, so I asked to speak with a manager who then told me the same thing. 
At this point I attempted one more time, and went to the University Plaza location and spoke with Darius, told me that he'd help me and email me within 24 hours. I have yet to have any email from him, and it's now 4 days later. I have attempted to call the store number, which was on Darius' card and listed online, it just rings and rings without answer.
I've filed grievance with the Attorney General, and the Better Business Bureau with hopes of getting this resolved. 
Sears owes me a refund of over $700 and It's been almost 60 days since I canceled my order. 
SHOPPERS BEWARE!

The pictures should explain how much I didn't like my nails they don't care about details.. Plus I really didn't like their personalities I was trying to say what I like to do with my nails and the lady said it's my job and let me finish before you tell me what you want ... never going there anymore for sure ..

Plenty of parking!  Called in order, minimal line to pickup order.  Enjoyed the numerous side options and wish I would've tried more.  

Ribs.  Delicious. My favorite item here. Tender. Fall of the bone. Tasty minus sauce.  Very good with the sweet hope sauce, my favorite. 

Potato salad. Not a big fan in general but this was good.  I would definitely order again.

Cole slaw.  A bit watery but very tasty, a good slaw.  

Burnt ends. Definitely a tasty option. My second favorite meat. 

Pulled pork.  Tasty and moist.

Baked beans.  Good but a little sweet. 

Smoked turkey.  Just ok flavor wise.  

Brisket chili.  Good but not my fav flavor. It was sweet and spicy. 

A great neighborhood BBQ place. Plenty of options, and the ribs were amazing.

It smelled like a fish market as soon as we entered the place. Overly sauced food. Service was good. It wasn't dark but our table was poorly lit somehow. I don't think this is what authentic Thai food tastes like.

It is clear to understand why other reviews yielded a 5 star review.  The facility meets the high standards of other Extra Space Storage but it is the exceptional client service provided by Mike that adds the extra shine to this 5 star rating.

If I could give negative stars I would. STAY AWAY from this horrid nightmare of a catastrophe. From the moment I walked in with my elderly mother, who is disabled, they mistreated us.  The guy doing my mom's pedi was so mean to her, pushing her around. I even fell off their rolling chair onto their floor, & they did nothing to help. No discount, nothing. What a nightmare. We were going to get manicures too, but decided to leave without.

Super great restaurant!! My family and I love to eat here because It's right in Sylvan Park and really easy to get to! There prices are affordable and the quality of the food is great. I have ordered the BBQ taco and The Cuban sandwich so far and I have been pleased with both of them! Honestly if you're looking for a variety of food (good BBQ, sandwiches, etc) and a friendly atmosphere this is the place to go!

After living in Tucson for a year, I finally got the chance to check this place out.

Being vegan in Tucson is difficult- you don't have too many options for going out to dinner, and when you do, they're not great. 

My co worker had dinner here a few weeks back and absolutely loved It. She isn't vegetarian or vegan, but couldn't stop raving about this place. Me and my friend went to have dinner on a Friday night, to catch up on life. The ambiance is very relaxing, the owners come and chat with you as you're waiting for your food. Our server Jesus was fantastic. Very knowledgeable, and sweet. He was constantly checking up on us. If I had my own restaurant, I'd definitely hire him. 


The food was fantastic. The menu is very limited, but all the options sound amazing. You also have the option of doing a four course meal. Soup, salad, main course, and dessert. They were also running a trio special, appetizer, main course, and dessert. 

I had the trio which had jalapeño poppers, pumpkin cranberry pecan tamale with rice and beans, and then dessert was some kind of banana loaf (don't quite remember). 

I highly highly recommend this place, if you're vegan or not. The flavors are fantastic and vibrant, and the presentation is amazing too.

Cantina is my family's favorite go to Mexican restaurant however the service is always poor. Today, my party of three decided to go for lunch and my wife made the comment how bad the service has been over the years. I waited 5 minutes at the hostess station and was told there was a 1 hour wait while there were plenty of tables. The two other people behind me made the same observation regarding their poor service. My rating reflects not able to get a table due to their poor planning and lack of staff. Great food....consistently bad service!

A decent yoga studio in the eastern suburbs of Nashville, where this are a limited selection of options. We encountered this when we moved from Wisconsin to Middle TN. However the services are somewhat overpriced but generally good quality. After a few years we turned to another source for our yoga. 

They offer Hatha, Relaxation and other varieties of yoga practice. Nashville seems focused on hot yoga.

Our automatic payment permission was revoked multiple times, with emails that went unanswered by the owner and then after we revoked the credit card authorization they continued to charge us $80 per month...for 3 more months. Despite trying to reach them they continue to charge. I'm disputing this currently as fraud. 

Beware Unity Yoga! As consumers we have a choice and this is not the fulfilling mindful expertise any yogi deserves

I love Nothing Bundt Cakes!  I actually live near the location on Oracle, but I was driving home today and saw that this second Tucson location has opened.  It's nice to have this second location open up on the other side of town.  I stopped by and got 2 dozen Bunditinis for a work potluck. The store is very nicely decorated and welcoming.  The cashier was very friendly.  The bundt cakes are very cute and tasty.   There are the usual flavors - red velvet is my favorite for sure!

One star off just because I wish it wouldn't close at 6 PM!
It's our first time in Tucson. Friends recommended this place. It's a perfect blend of meat and fruits. Very dark and moody. Five stars!
Thank god for this place. I live down the street and when I'm out of food and coffee, which is often, I come here. Food is always fresh and tasty.

This place is unique. The decoration was cool and the restroom was "sassy". Food and drink tasted very good. I had a Tropical fruit smoothie and Gingerbread chai latte. My boyfriend has Pecan Latter and Waffle parfait. We loved it. Wished the portion is a little bit bigger. They also had outdoor sitting for whoever has pets.
Love the specials Chef whips up! Nice breakfast menu and really enjoy the coffee on draft and kombucha on tap!!!

Hellas -- the "go-to" place for tourists visiting Tarpon Springs. Fantastic Greek menu in an excellent atmosphere. We make a point to bring our out of town guests here if they are wanting the Greek experience.
Since parking can sometimes be tricky down on the docks (or at least cost you $3 in one of the parking lots), it's nice to know that Hellas has a parking lot behind the restaurant. If you ask the waiter for a parking pass, you get to park for free :)
Tonight we went in for a late 8:30 meal. There were a few other diners in the restaurant but not overly packed. I ordered Pastitsio which came with peas and rice - $14.50 and plenty to bring home for left-overs. Very good flavor. Peas were canned peas seasoned with a few spices and tomatoes but to me, still tasted like canned peas - not my favorite. The pastitsio was very good, however. The hubby had a chicken souvlaki ($8.25) which he devoured and a glass of wine ($10.50). With my Coca Cola ($2.95) our bill came to $38.74 with tax. Plentiful portions, reasonably priced - plus a parking pass!  Opa!

THE WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE I HAVE EVER GOTTEN IN MY LIFE! The cashier Karla and the barista Rachell gave us so much attitude! Lied to us about only serving hot drinks when 5 minuets later we see people coming out with cold drinks. when we finally got to order they made faces kept complaining that we ordered too many cold drinks as if it isn't their job to make them. so rude the entire time!
So I went to get an appliance package (fridge,stove, dishwasher and microwave) and Craig (salesman) and Annette (manager) made it happen!

Bob Cooper and Brian Guest along with their service team did a great job with my 2018 Charger Hell Cat.  Ferman CJD Service Department really stepped up and took care of the customer. Bob Cooper is truly an asset to Ferman and I really appreciate what him and his team did to take care of me. 

Thank you.

The park is always very clean and is staffed with friendly and helpful employees. The concessions include everything from cheesesteaks, ice cream, and pulled pork sandwiches to vegetarian options. Chickie's and Pete's crab fries are a big deal here in the Philly area, so be sure to grab some in the stadium! There is not a bad seat in the whole house, and the Phillies succeed in making the park family-friendly and fun for all ages. I always like to get to the stadium a bit on the early side in order to get a good parking space and so that I can get my food and eat it up in my seat before/ as the game is starting.

I could not find a dang negative thing to say about this place if I tried! 

Came in on a Tuesday evening at about 7:30 pm to a packed house- luckily we were able to be seated at the last remaining table. The space is small, dark, and intimate- perfect for a date night, not so great for a group dinner.

Our waitress was so sweet and accommodating, & happily gave us extra chips and salsa and tortillas when we ran out. She also expertly mixed the tequila we brought with their homemade margarita mix.

Two of us shared chorizo queso fundido, nachitos and steak fajitas. Loved it all. The queso fundido was SO good- just make sure to eat it all before it cools down. Love that the fajitas come with rice and beans, also. 

We were able to use a Groupon and get out of there for under 20 bucks, including tip. Would highly recommend and will definitely return, with or without a Groupon!

Was happy to hear that New Orleans has a number of restaurants open during the Christmas holiday. My fiancé and I came here for Christmas dinner and really enjoyed ourselves. We ordered 1 appetizer, 2 entrees and 1 cocktail. 
Appetizer was Gnocchi which though decent, the sauce it was dressed in tasted like pizza rolls from my childhood. Definitely pass on those next time. 
I ordered shrimp and grits - very flavorful and well seasoned. My fiancé ordered the rib eye which came with fries. We were happy when the food came out because the portions were appropriate. Cocktail was great and definitely strong so worth the cost. 
Overall really nice time and good ambiance.

Haslam's was fun. Surprisingly enough, this was my FIRST visit. I know, I know, you're thinking, "what's WRONG with me?!?" 

So, I was in the neighborhood and decided to stop in and look for some books rather than driving all the way out to Barnes & Nobel. Thankfully Haslam's had one book out of the four I was looking for and I also picked up a random book as a gift. 

I totally forgot about the infamous Haslam's cats though. I AM VERY VERY ALLERGIC TO CATS. I immediately started sneezing after a couple minutes in the store and then, while I was walking the aisles I saw it... a cute, fluffy, disapproving kitty. It gave me the evil eye and I decided it was time to go. 

The staff on site were very friendly and chatty.

Arrived at 6:45am to welcoming warm smiles. Biscuits are amazing!!! Even the pickiest biscuit eater will love Biscuit Love. Tried the spicy bacon based on other reviews. Not a real spicy person, so it was not for me, but it was unique! Great place to indulge on biscuits!

Before my friends and I were about to leave New Orleans, we had to stop and get some fried chicken!

We looked on Yelp for the best chicken in NOLA and came across Willie's Chicken Shack.

We decided to order the regular fried chicken but after placing our order, the waitress brought out chicken tenders?

I'm guessing she mistaken our order so we told her the mistake and they quickly prepared the order that we had asked.

Honestly, this was probably some of the best fried chicken I had! The skin was super crispy and the meat inside was super tender and juicy as well. It was seasoned perfectly and they even had a bunch of sauces that you can lather your chicken with.

I'll definitely stop by Willie's again if I'm in the area!

This was my first ever exposure to pho, and it was not a good one. Bland broth and the noodles were over done. I couldn't believe what everyone was raving about. Thank goodness my friends convinced me to try it again elsewhere.

First time trying this place after hearing so many good reviews & I definitely wasn't disappointed!! I ordered the noodle bowl & it was amazing! So fresh & flavorful. The staff was so helpful & explained everything that came in it & gave great recommendations. A little pricey, but it's worth it for the freshness & overall quaintness of the spot! 10/10 will come again :)
Very pricey. Cute clothing, but the sunglasses I purchased broke the day after I bought them. The store didn't seem willing to do anything about it when contacted.
My family and I love this place. The thai food is excellent and the owners are super nice people.

This place brings out the best memories of earing chicken with my family growing up in South Carolina. I just love the simplicity of really good fried chicken paired with delicious sides, served family style or individually.  The cocktails are also fantastic and not overpriced. 

The only thing I would knock this place for is how incredibly noisy it is. I don't mind dining room chatter, but invariably there is a horde of drunk, shrieking harpies near your table.

I wanted to love this place. We had actually driven out to visit King Wok, but decided to try here because we've been wanting Indian food. The garlic naan we had was great. The sauces for both the Saaglamb and the lamb vindaloo were both delicious. For me, the problem was that both dishes' lamb had shards of bone and were chewy with fatty or bad cuts in it. I ate around the meat, which is tragic to me when the lamb should be the best part. I'm not sure I'll come back. The photos of the buffet look great, and they probably do chicken just fine, but apparently not lamb, or at least not tonight.
Long Island Iced Tea is a total fraud!! Watered down mix already prepared!! But, the bartender was excellent and attentive and the Won Ton Tacos were delicious!!

My husband & I love this cafe! It's so cute and I love how community oriented it is. We always see someone we recognize. Only critique is that it tends to take a really long time to be rung up and the drinks & food take a while too. One time we waited for 45 minutes and it turned out they had forgotten to put our order in. Overall, great place!

Horrible manager, mixed up our large Uber eats order. Called to resolve the issue with him. But he refused to acknowledge the problem and yelled at me over the phone. Very rude. Will not return. TBH, the food isn't that impressive anyway.

I come from New Jersey, so I always pass this place whenever I'm going to sports stadiums or other things in the stadium area. I kept telling my girlfriend and a friend of mine how one if these days I'm going to try this place. Well, last night was one of those days as I was in the area and decided to stop. 

Have to say, I really loved it there. My girlfriend and I split a cheesesteak and fried pickles. The cheesesteak was very high quality and had very good taste. I felt the steak on the sandwich was a higher quality than the other notable Philadelphia cheesesteak spots. The roll was also very good which overall made the sandwich a home run. It was also cheaper than the other places as well. 

The fried pickles were very very good. The pickles were the chip type and they had a lot of breading on them. They were bigger than usual and very crispy. I have been thinking about them all day.  

They have a very big menu so next time I stop we are going to try more stuff!

Tip: They don't have a bathroom, so don't come on a full bladder. They also accept credit cards, which I found quite convenient.

This is a pretty cool local bar. Went there on a Monday night, not a lot of people there at all. Bartender was good. We just had a few beers. They have a takeout beer section too. Highlights: 2 small size pool tables which were really nice. All the cues were pretty beat up though. They also had a shuffleboard table and dartboard. I didn't eat there, so I'm not sure how the food is. My experience was average. Since then, I've been here about 4 more times, pretty much only to play pool. It's a dive bar but the upstairs is pretty cool when it is open. (Usually after 7pm) They have another pool table up there too.
Update- we come here all the time now, honestly, the experience is hit or miss depending on the the bartender. Most are cool and do a great job, but some are so terrible it makes me not want to come back.

Absolutely love this place, my son is a VERY picky eater and I ordered him a fish plate and he ate every bit of it then asked me to go buy him another one. The breakfast is the best. Those grits are so creamy and delicious. And lord let's not forget about the sweets

This little coffee shop surprised me. We have seen white some coffee shops in Boise but always tried to stick with what we were familiar with, Starbucks, until we tried this little local owned coffee shop 3 months ago.

The coffee is rich and perfect to the taste.  I always like mocha or latte type of coffee.  Doesn't matter what flavors I ordered, they were just perfect to my taste.  The flavors will not overwhelmed nor too sweet than the coffee itself.  I just ordered a holiday special "Snowball Mocha " (I think).  Marshmallow melted on to of the hot coffee, it is rich but the bitterness of the coffee underneath it just make the coffee perfect (although I am not a big fan of marshmallow, I think this combo makes them perfect together).

I had a chance to stepped inside and it is such a cozy welcoming coffee shop.

Give this little place a try.  You will love it!

Ice cream, near the beach. What more do I need to say. This little shop has a tremendous amount of flavors and is a skip hop and a jump from the sand. 

I came in during off season and they were not busy. Was offered samples if I wanted but decided to opt for a $3 milkshake. Man was it worth it! Mint chocolate chip milkshake was just what I needed. It was soft serve with syrup but still delicious. 

Not a whole lot of seating inside so grab your treats and go!

I have heard mixed reviews about Massage Envy. I tried it out for the first time a few days ago over the holiday my family all bought me gift cards to Massage Envy. They all went at once to get the massage card and apparently the promotion that has been running this month if you buy $125 worth of gift cards you get a free 30-minute upgrade on a massage an hour or longer. Well, my family all did by more than $125 worth. However, they did not give them the 30 minute upgrade because they all bought their cards individually although at the same time. You would think an establishment understanding it is all holidays and that a family was there buying gift cards individually to give to one person they would honor that special. I was told about it whenever my gift cards were given to me so I ask about it when I went in. Well, the representative messaged her manager and apparently the excuse that we got was the corporate office was writing them hard about who the issue the gift cards to. I would think the corporate offices main objective was to retain and leave a customer satisfied and wanting to return. I was buying gift cards the same day as well because prior to this experience I had agreed with another co-worker to get one of our co-workers a gift card to Massage Envy and I was picking up the $125 gift card to give them and get the promotion. They were fine giving me$125 gift card to give to someone else. However, even though they could clearly see that all of the gift cards were purchased at the exact same time and they were over the $125 value the management of this establish willing to honor a request that could have encouraged a customer to switch to Massage Envy as their primary therapist agency. However, I am going to finish out my gift cards and I'm going to continue with the same Spa I've used for years. I get one massage a week and I have been getting that for years. I did however decide to use one of their other promotions since I had such a high-value and gift cards they were offering a membership for 90 days and I decided to do that membership and buy it with the gift cards I bought 125 where I could use the upgrade given for myself I'm future massages and the gift cards that were given to me I'm going to gift to our co-worker and the amount of $125. The sad thing is the reason my family chose to try Massage Envy was the fact that that promotion was running and they know I typically get a two hour massage and they thought it would be beneficial. However, when they refused to honor at they worse kind of SOL because they had to buy the gift cards because a spot I typically use a closed already for the season. I can tell you that once my gift cards expires and this 90-day deal I will not use Massage Envy again. However, I can say that my therapist was amazing his name is Arnie yeah and he was very good with his hands he did what he describes as sneaky deep. I like a mixture of deep tissue and relaxation massage Swedish type combined together. He did it better than anyone, I have ever met. If this was the only factor in my decision I definitely would have stayed with Massage Envy. However, it is important for Massage Envy to know a great therapist is only one factor when a customer chooses to become a long-term customer of their business. Also, my friend Christian  and I went to have a massage at their sister location days before and he made to request that they work on his legs in his glutes because he was having severe pain and muscle spasms and they work on his feet and briefly work on his back. The therapist didn't work on his glutes at all just skimmed past his weights did not do his feet I'm focused almost 100% on the massage on his back and shoulders when he asked for that to be the least. Plus, he is slightly a larger man and he was forced to hold his head up during the massage because they wouldn't give him a pillow after he requested hello twice. What he did was pull the headrest off an attempt to use that and that didn't even reaches head that kept falling off and the therapist would just leave it in the floor so when I would look over at him he looks so uncomfortable because he was holding his head off of the bed and he was clearly uncomfortable I could tell from my bed and His Hands kept moving and the therapist would put his hands on his hands and tell him to relax. He asked for a Swedish massage and they gave him more of a deep tissue I swear to God he said how or ouch 15 or 20 times during that 90 minute massage. The put us in a a couple's room which was not requested we were just request that they schedule is at the same time and I am assuming that they thought we wanted a massage together and that was far from the truth. So, this made my massage awful even though my massage therapist was decent not as good as Arnie however still very good. Christian ask that a manager follow up,  he said  manager never called. Honestly, it was a complete waste of $100 for each of us.

By far my favorite spot for baked goods. I decided to be brave and check out their vegan main event cookie, OMG! If no one had told me it was vegan, I would've never known. The cookie wasn't dry, it was so gooey & tasted just like if not better than a regular cookie. I am ordering a cake for my birthday and I'll share that review too!
Didn't realize I had to wait hella long just to get a hamburger. Waited 15 minutes and had 7 people in front of me. Kinda ridiculous.

The first time I tried B&B, I was in love with their chicken nuggs. They were juicy and tender and all of the sides were delicious. Perhaps the best time to go is after the busy lunch hour or right before dinner, when the kitchen isn't rushing and food doesn't sit out for long periods. 

Last night, we went during dinner time and I overheard a few people complain about the amount of time it took to get their appetizers. The servers took a while to take our order and get refills, but they were friendly. My chicken was so dry and the batter was burned. I'm assuming they made a bunch of nuggs ahead of time and maybe reheated them in the fryer, because they were so over cooked it ruined it for me. My tots were stale and cold. I could tell the servers had a rough day so I wasn't going to complain. Like I said, the first time I went the food was to-die-for and it wasn't during a busy time.

Love going here greatest scones ever but 15 minutes getting coffee today.  Staff making coffee had to run food to tables.  Not acceptable especially this time of year when more crowded than normal.  Would rather support local business but can't wait 15 mins to get cup of coffee.

Four bottles of the wrong drink delivered. They said they will exchange and never did. The pizza was stone cold! The sides were stone cold! First time trying pizza hut in a long time and huge regret. Shut down already.

My medically military retired son (comprehension problems due to Iraq injury) thought to surprise me with a new microwave. When I came  home there was an over the range microwave oven sitting on the counter.  We have no way of using an over the range as our oven is freestanding with no cabinets or anything to install it. I tried taking the microwave back to get a refund as it was over $350 (which was ridiculous for them to sell that to him to begin with) but was told there were no refunds or exchanges. The owner suggested I try and sell it on eBay or Craigslist. Later our AC unit got a busted freon line and my son called Atlas repair out to fix it. They came and charged my son around $500 to fix it. Although it is running, it was barely blowing and after running continuously for a day and a half, it was still 76 degrees in the house. I called them to tell them it still was not working. Its now been 4 days and they still have not come to fix it!

Ice cream in December? When it's OwowCow, the answer is always a resounding YES. 

This place prides themselves on their locally sourced product. Everything is made or procured locally, and it really makes a difference. Sure, you're going to pay a little more for a cone here, but you're supporting multiple local business and getting a delicious, organic treat that's free of the extra garbage corporations will add in. It is SO.WORTH.IT. 

They are always trying new flavors, so you can easily try something different every visit if you'd like. The kids behind the counter here are super friendly and will happily give you a tasting of any flavor before you get stuck ordering something and don't like it. 
They are peanut free here, which is cool for all the peanut allergy folks out there. 

Let's just say, I don't think you can go wrong here. The house vanilla is still my favorite, but I also have not been disappointed in any other flavor they offer. They have a ton of topping choices as well- my fav being the chocolate "chips". I don't know what planet these hunks of shaved chocolate would be considered chips, but they are the perfect pairing for the vanilla. 

Bunch of fun cone options here too. Waffle cones with fancy dipped treat edges- from cookie pieces to candy bits. I usually just go with a cup because I can't finish the regular size on my own, but if you want a challenge, go for the waffle. 

The fridge at the counter is also full of local drinks, pints of their ice cream, and various to go treats depending on the day. They offered ice cream pies and ice cream sandwiches on my most recent visit before Christmas. 

Owowcow, I love you. I wish I could pack you up and take you home to South Carolina with me! I will, however, stop in here every time I'm in the area!!

You might see me giving a lot of five or four stars but I only like to write about places that I honestly think about when I'm looking for a great eat. This place can rival its counterparts in dog town and the hill. Great flavor and wonderful variety.

The menu changes so check before you go. So far nothing has stood out as something that I could not do myself at home. Average at best, ok service overall very small plates even compared to other small plate restaurants. Rather expensive for such small plates.

We found this center while passing through Reno for a short stay. Looked solid and experienced from the reviews and they were right. Needed therapeutic massage after a very trying flight experience that left us crunched up. They were able to book us in with short notice with Bill and Karen- best thing we ever did for ourselves. Good work and good information to take home and follow up. Will stop there anytime we are back in town.

Called Service One on Wednesday and talked to Pam. She had an opening for service at 12-3PM Thursday, the next day. I took it. Elvis, the excellent technician showed up on time, diagnosed our ice maker as worn out. Elvis replaced the ice maker and wraped up the appointment in 30 minutes. It doesn't get much better than this. Thanks!
Gave me price with over inflated prep and delivery charge. Bought bike at dealer that gave true pricing up front. Sales manager is a jerk, salesman just as bad

Got bad food poisoning here from eating a turkey sandwich  on Friday 12/22.  Reporting this incident.  Have ruled out all other sources.  Really put a dent in christmas plans!  Last time I was here, I found a long black hair in my sandwich.  You guys need to check your cleanliness procedures.  Will not ever be coming back.

This pizza place off of US 30 is one of the best New York pizza places that is not in New York. The customer service was top-notch, and the food was made very quickly. I ordered a cheese pizza and it was very flavorful overall. The sauce had a spicy flavor, and the portion size was very good for the price. Overall, I would definitely return to this pizza place for New York style pizza.

Good park mostly for summer water activities. We came in the winter time, not much open, but they still charge for 6 dollar entrance fee which is a little upsetting. But the park bathroom was open which is a plus. We walked in few trails, just normal park trail not the kinda hiking trail I'm looking for..

They are great. Expensive. But really good.... 

There delivery had been on time and they don't do anything you wish expect them to do.

The pepperoni pizza is delicious and probably the best thing in their menus.... 

Nothing else I've tried stands out, but the pizza is better than good enough.

Our wait was 55 min not the 30 we were told.  Our wait for food was 48 minutes and the wait for the bathroom when we went to leave was 15 minutes.  Even the blueberries for my husbands oatmeal came out late and he'd just about finished the oatmeal by the time the blueberries arrived. The food was great but all the waiting was not.  Felt bad for our waiter who could have turned the table twice.

EOS is a great place to hang with friends and dance the night away. We had our company party get together here, staff was very accommodating and made sure all people in the party were taken care of. Big shot out to Nelson, such a great bartender. Thanks Nelson!

I love Quiznos, but I hate this location. I've gone here multiples times and have been very displeased every time. Customer service is very mediocre, seems like everyone just wants you to leave. Quiznos in South Reno and Damonte Ranch is 100x better.

Blueberry pelmeni - yes please. Gotta love dumplings for breakfast!! Loved the coffee and the prickly pear iced tea. So refreshing!! Great little courtyard it back - loved the vibe. Only issue was with the tip jar - had to vote between Harry Potter and LOTR. Gah!!! But I love both. Ha! What a nice little cafe.

The ham and Tri tip roast were unquestionably delicious and savored by my fam, but the experience was uncomfortable.

Last minute holiday dinners are always a tough dish to palate, and I am used to chain establishments such as Boston market and honey baked where the order can be prepared and heated ready to serve. Perhaps I miscommunicated my expectation that this would be the case while on the phone with them yesterday morning. I ordered for a late afternoon pickup figuring I could serve the meal as soon as I returned home.Unfortunately, I arrived to find the ham and tri tip roast I ordered were not only unheated, but in the case of the roast partially frozen. 

The person who helped me explained this was normal and reheating would be a simple matter, the work of about 30 minutes at 300' oven which I verfied with the detailed written heating instructions. (Nice)

I arrived home and immediately set to the task of reheating the items following the instructions to the letter. Sadly the time allotted was not sufficient and the meat was not 140' internal even 45+min later. I had to serve after a full hour when the thermometer showed the correct temp. However the meat was chilly in places and I was embarrassed in front of my guests. :( My oven is an efficient and well serviced machine utilizing both convection and regular bake settings so I doubt this was the issue.

I would definitely consider using Boise bistro again as the taste was awesome. I would simply suggest more friendly help and more specifics during phone order placement.

Thank you for reading :)

I tried this place because of the reviews on here and a friend referral, I am very picky when it comes getting my nails done but this place was amazing! The salon was very nice and well decorated and clean, after signing in they offered me tea, coffee, or water and gave me a warm neck roll while getting my nails done. They were very friendly and talkative which I loved and my nails look amazing! They were much more professional than a lot of other places and they offered 25% off until New Year's Eve. Definitely my favorite place and I will for sure be going back.

Called in a carry out order last night. Employee was friendly and helpful over the phone so no complaints with the service. However the pizza was one of the worst I've had at a Pizza Hut. Crust was extremely dry and hard like cardboard and next to no pizza sauce didn't help. Ordered a large but they had no large boxes so it came in two medium boxes. Unfortunately it was bad enough that I won't be going back anytime soon.

I hate to leave a one-star review because I love Hot Box, but the customer service is so bad at this location that I had to share.  The place closes at 10 PM, so we called twice at 9:35 and 9:40 to try and order some breadsticks.  After no answers on both calls, my wife went to the store at 9:50 and got a bunch of flack for coming in so late and ordering breadsticks...some guy with a nose ring walking around all huffy completely being rude because we came in 10 minutes before close.  I get you don't want to stay late, but maybe he should have answered the phone 15 minutes earlier.  I wonder how much business they lost due to this disgruntled employee.

Just had the best message I've ever had. I highly recommend Anna. She hit all my problem areas and stretched/helped my flexibility. 

I will definitely be a regular... I'd call to schedule in advance ...because Anna is very popular and well worth it.

Great burgers and selection. Usually good service. Go hungry because there's bottomless steak fries (there's even many varieties of fries too) with an assortment of dips instead of having only ketchup. Also, the onion rings are wonderful.

We liked it here.  We started with the hummus plate.  It was very good.  Both ordered burgers, mine came out as ordered...his came out well done (he asked for medium).  Server was efficient and pleasant.  My one complaint is that another couple was seated so close to us, we might as well have been a four-top.  I'm used to tight quarters, but this was very uncomfortable.
Taking train to Doylestown from 30th street station.  It's an hour and fifteen minute ride for only a dollar ( senior citizen). What a bargain. The staff are efficient and helpful.

Jonathan Plasky was a fantastic salesman. We got a great deal and he was very communicative throughout the process as we arranged to get the car. We drove an hour to their dealership and were not disappointed. Everyone was so nice. He spent time going over all of the car features in great detail. No high pressure sales or games. I am very happy with my experience. I will definitely return here the next time we buy a car (I love Hondas). Check out Crown Honda. It's worth the drive!

I had an emergency situation where I needed something altered ASAP for a wedding reception. Saji not only did the job in time but she did an exceptional job for an extremely reason price. I will definitely be seeing her again in the future!

I'm not a regular in the sense they know my name, but I come here at least 2 - 3 times a month, so it's time I return some love. 

My fiancé is not normally a big tapas person - but I lured him in with the promise of pork belly baos, and he never looked back. 

It's not common to find a place where I have so many options as a vegetarian, and even more difficult to find places that have great options for both of us. 

Whenever we have out of town guests, this is a go to spot, so you should go too.
I was surprised to see that this place didn't have more 5 star reviews. Solid local joint. Nothing fancy but sometimes that's good. I come here to study a bunch. Always a solid choice.

Good/ slightly above average for a week hotel stay. A rewards member so some of the amenities I receive are extra but overall at base a good experience. Happy and engaging staff, clean common facilities and room was spacious and equipped with a full fridge, microwave and stove top. Hotel gives all guests free breakfast and happy hour (with wine or beer). Neither of which is the greatest but both can double as whole meals meaning during your stay if you plan right you'll only have to pay for lunch! Gym and pool are small but both serve their purpose. Great location on the edge of the French quarter and walking distance to everywhere worth going. Not sure on parking charge but when you're this close to the action we only rented a car to go OUTSIDE of the quarter on a couple tours. Lots of games in the lobby and a convenience store on the block behind hotel. Overall pleasant and although on the pricey side still worth it.

I've been to Bell Beverage before and it is a place I like to go if I'm looking for something special.  Today, they knocked it out of the park.  I've been diligent in my search for Founders CBS and from the get go Bell told me they would let me know when it arrived.  I received my email yesterday, and picked up my bottle today.  No hoops to jump through, no "we are only selling one bottle an hour".  What you see is what you get, and for a reasonable price.  Excellent beer citizens!!!!

Thanks 
Best and the best around to USF. hi recommendation for this place. Professional people from the owner of the bar tend to the waiter. I have this girl she super sweet and kind and so helping.

Came back for my 2nd & 3rd visit over the past week. I will say, those zucchini fries just keep getting better and better! I've also tried the tots, potato salad and the tomato and cucumber salad, all were fantastic. Last week I tried the prime burger again and it was MUCH better than my first visit. I had the French burger the next visit and it was okay. I liked the prime burger better. The flavors of the French burger just didn't suit me quite as much. But it was juicy and cooked well, regardless. Service has been good!

We had a great stay at the Nashville Downtown Hostel. I had a group of 30 people and they made great accommodations for us. The staff was extremely helpful. Our rooms were very clean. It was amazing how close we were to downtown Nashville in the strip. This is a great place to stay.

Barbacoa with jackfruit and amazing spicing made this my favorite dish of the week. Vegan dishes have a bad reputation of being bland. Well? There's nothing bland in this amazing little jewel. I'm so glad to have found it and will become a regular. The menu changes daily and is always "colorful even on the palate." That's the best I can do to describe the amazing flavors and textures of this food. And they utilize local produce to make everything fresh. Down to the bowl of soup du jour that is "gratis" and your first taste of the unique spice blends and freshness that will explode into your senses. I look forward to my next visit.

Coming from California, I had a high bar set for good Mexican food and Suegra cantina beat it for sure. The staff was so knowledgeable about their menu and their insane tequila list (The El Jefe margarita was awesome), on top of being genuinely nice and attentive, but not overly attentive. The food was delicious, authentic, and high quality. 

It wasn't packed on a Saturday night, which makes me worried it won't last long because people don't know about it. So GO!!

I took a pair of jeans in to have the zipper replaced. I went to pick them up and they weren't ready yet and was initially disappointed with the responsiveness of the girls working. When I called a few days later and discussed my issue they jumped through hoops to get my jeans done (even took them somewhere else since their seamstress wasnt in). They definitely redeemed themselves with how seriously they took me and wanted to resolve my issue. I will definitely go back!

I love my visits to Philly because I always find spots that are authentic with cultural vibes. Cafe Nhan was no exception. 

I landed in Philly and before visiting family I needed Pho. Literally needed it. I flew up from GA, and I was cold and felt a cold coming on. I searched Yelp per usual and decided on the place with the best reviews that was in my direction of travel and stumbled upon this place.

I was greeted promptly and told I could sit where ever I wanted. Nicole was my server. She was great and super attentive and if I heard correctly it was her birthday!  She worked on her birthday and was in the best of spirits. It made my day. 

The restaurant was small, but very cozy, super clean and the service was quick.

I ordered Pho with shrimp. I requested veggie broth but this restaurant only has beef :(. I have to admit, this threw me off. Only beef broth? Don't get me wrong it was still good broth, but did not mesh will with the shrimp. Speaking of the shrimp, they were not deveined (in case you are that person like me that doesn't like to see the inside of the shrimp while eating it). Also, I do believe the shrimp might have been frozen (they were not as flavorful as fresh never frozen shrimp usually are). Aside from that, all of the fixings were set out nicely and Nicole made sure that I had everything that I needed. 

Upon departure, I was asked about my experience. The team seemed very interested in what they could do to make their customers experience better. I inquired about the fact that they only have one type of broth for their Pho and it was explain to me that they did not want to compete with their next door counterparts which cater to vegans and vegetarians. I completely understood, yet thought to myself, its not competition when you're doing your thing. Give people what they want ;), I want veggie broth in my Pho this season.  

Overall great experience. If they ever get veggie broth or if I become a regular meat eater I will return. 

I do recommend this place, the experience and service were both great.

What a great find! I had been looking for some good Middle Eastern/Greek food while working in the area and had struck out several times. Driving by I spotted the Jaffa Street food truck in its new 'home' and pulled in. Tried the falafel, hummus, and lamb shawarma, and they were all great! And at great prices, too.
I look forward to making this a regular stop. Thanks, Hannah

It's wings and fries. Standard tasty wings but the fries were not crispy :( 
Got them to go by ordering online. Not very well staffed. Soda machine was low on syrup (water) and the straw dispenser was stuck. It took a long time to get a cup (cashier is the only one who can distribute the cups).

Just your basic chicken teriyaki bowl.
What disappointed me the most was I substituted noodles instead of rice for a dollar and it was just spaghetti noodles... wasn't expecting that.
I'll get the brown rice next time.

I set up an appointment two weeks in advance of needing my house's locks changed. He gave me a quote on the phone and I was prepared to pay that amount. Adam was professional and responsive. Showed up right as scheduled and re-keyed 5 locks and gave me 8 keys in 10 minutes! He was extremely honest and didn't charge me the quoted amount as the job was not as labor intensive as anticipated. He left and I found that a few of the keys didn't work. He walked me through fixing the issue on the phone and was VERY patient, then all keys now work. He was super professional and answered all my home security questions. All my neighbors and friends now have a great, honest, and reliable locksmith! Thanks, Adam!

We stopped for lunch at the Shoreline Cafe after arriving in town for a recent weekend stay in Santa Barbara. We found the service and food to be very good, as was the sandy scenery. There's nothing like enjoying the open air and being right on the beach while enjoying a good meal. We'll certainly be stopping in again the next time we're in town.

My husband and I bought a home in November of 2017 and used the Schoenhouse and Manter team. They are extremely knowledgeable of the Bay Area real estate market, as well as attentive and super responsive/accessible. Also, Lisa and Miles are incredible negotiators and found us great value at a good price in a very competitive housing market.They are easy to work with and we would 100% recommend/use again.

Ashley M

If your looking for a huge calzone and massive tasty salad sauce on the side is your place! You can't beat the prices and you won't leave hungry! I think I have had all of their salads, every one was fresh and had lots of flavor. The pesto chicken you can add is a great addition the the Italian salad. I think their homemade dressing is what makes it delicious. As far as calzones my husband loves the meat me in St. Louis! Perfect for dining in or take out.
New to the area and we eat out A LOT... Ordered delivery and the crust was soggy and flavorless.  Will try again in the resturant before making a final decision but the first impression was not good.

A few of the staff are hottish... and this is Jersey... area is lame, so this place is an oasis.  I feel so depressed, but what else is there to do around here.  Selection way less than Walmart, but they do have some nice stuff.  Most important is it's clean and well managed.

Just had lunch, great cocktail, ordered my burger medium rare, came out raw in the middle, sent it back, the next one was medium to medium well. I told bartender perhaps she could tell the chef about the temps. Got a "look". Asked me if I wanted her to take it off the bill? It shouldn't even be a question.
