Btw we were charged although I only ate part of it. Pretty disappointing at a place that specializes in burgers.

Honestly love this place for a casual drink. It's a nice low key place in the heart of the city. Not the biggest selection of food so if you're looking for a hearty meal i probably wouldn't come here, but I've had a cheesesteak and quesadillas here and they were decent. It's really the atmosphere that i love, just a no frills bar which is my kind of place. Love the brick!

If you've never eaten here you're in for a treat!!!  This is by far my family's fav BBQ place EVER!!!  Been eating at 4 Rivers since the beginning when they only had one restaurant!!!  Everything I've tried on their menu is top notch and NEVER disappoints. A MUST TRY!!!

One of my favorite places in Seminole Heights!   The inside of this place is just so cute.  There are plenty of tables inside and a couple benches outside if you want to eat here.  

As far as the food goes, I am seriously addicted to their acai bowls.  I think I probably stop in once a week for a bowl.  I loved all three of their bowl options.  I usually gravitate towards the Whatever bowl which has light and fruity base, although sometimes I will get the cacao bowl which has a hint of chocolate in the base.  They have a lot of different toppings which are all are spot on - fruit is fresh, granola is crunchy and the honey is local!      

I will also come in here for some gelato or a pop.  My favorite pop is the earl grey lavender lemonade.  So yummy!  Whatever pops is a great place a sweet treat or a light breakfast/lunch acai bowl!

My boyfriend and I checked in last night and left within the first 3 minutes. He opened the refrigerator and 5 ROACHES came crawling out. nOt only that but he went looking for the outlet near the bed and the bed itself was covered in roaches all along the side. THEY WERE EVERYWHERE! The manager at the front desk seemed to be already aware of the issue and immediately refunded us. DO NOT STAY HERE!

We had just finished up at The Wilson County Bank in Gladeville having pictures with Santa along with all the cousins. I have an idea! Let's go to Providence in Mount Juliet and eat burgers! Yeah, let's just hop on over there and have dinner real quick...

It is about 5-ish, so we head that way from the Gladeville community. We zip along on Stewarts Ferry Pike to South Mount Juliet Road. Cool! But THEN we hit rush hour traffic along a lonely two lane highway - well not THAT lonely as traffic was backed up almost from Stewarts Ferry Pike to Central Pike. I'll wait until you pull up Google Earth before typing any more...

Done yet? It's a long way isn't it? It takes about thirty minutes until we crest the hill after Central Pike and see the lights of civilization. We get to the restaurant around 5:45 - again - ish. I put in our name, give my phone number and await the anticipated text message which I was told would be 20 minutes. They appear short on servers at this burger place as several tables become vacant. Eventually others are sat - people that appear to have come in after us. I approach the host - "I'm sorry, I entered your phone number wrong - we have been trying to get in touch!" Someone in the 615 area code just asked his wife, "Did you order a table? It's ready!"

This turned out to be a blessing in disguise. Our daughter notices the man behind the bar as someone she knows - one of the managers. She knows his wife and knows that just yesterday he was suffering from an extreme stomach bug.  So I'm trying to get us a decent table and my wife says, "We are leaving!" Wait? What?! I'm about to score us some free food!" We get outside and they explain why we are leaving. 

What now? Mexican, Chinese? Me, "What about Cori's Dog House?" Silence. Again, "What about Cori's" No response. "I said what about...." "We heard you - just hoping you would get the hint."  Someone mentions Indian. "Cori's has an Indiana Hot Dog!" My lip stopped bleeding in a few minutes, good luck getting that blood stain off her coat sleeve, though. 

This was our first visit as well as our daughter to Persis Biryani Indian Grill - you probably forgot by now which restaurant I was reviewing. My son-in-law had been along with our one year old grandson about two years ago - just seeing if you were paying attention. Were it not for the food and obvious ethnicity of the staff, you would not know you were in an Indian restaurant. The inside is sleek and modern with lots of stone, modern chairs and white laminate - bright, but pleasing. We were sat immediately. Indian food has flavors that appeal to a certain palette. Or if you are like my wife you had some really bad Indian food a few decades ago and never gave it another shot.

This time she goes WAY out on a limb and orders the Saag - just kidding - she gets this every time - she also locks her car when it is in the garage - so go ahead and analyze her. They have butter chicken AND chicken tiki masala which I had thought were the same, but were different here. Here they use ghee instead of just run of the mill butter. It imparts a nutty flavor - slick, huh? I read it on their wall. Our daughter orders the butter chicken - now it is her favorite to date - and Indian food is now her favorite. If you follow my reviews - and who doesn't - you know that she or my wife thought they wouldn't like it. There is the aforementioned reason in regards my wife and then there is her negative influence on her daughter all these many years. I am surprised DHS didn't pull her from our home, but she is almost 30. Daughter's husband orders the avocado curry, medium spice. He loved it! Now me - I tried to explore and decided to order the restaurant namesake dish - biryani. I get it with chicken and find that they don't have degrees of heat when preparing this dish. A slight language barrier with the server and he was finally able to explain that to me - I was asking what spice level - he was saying no spice eleven. He assured me it was spicy. It comes with riata yogurt and pepper gravy on the side. It is a large portion of basmati rice and lightly breaded chicken.  Good, but I would probably not order it again. I find I prefer the dishes that are sauce heavy. Good, but different. We ordered garlic and bullet naan. Bullet naan is very spicy! The garlic was delicious as well. Our daughter loved dipping the garlic naan in the sauce of her butter chicken. I did too, until my wife told me to leave her (our daughter) some...

Kid's meal is basically boneless tandoori chicken served with either white of fried rice or noodles. Lots of green onion so you might tell them to lighten up on that - otherwise the one year old ordered that - spicy level 3 - kidding. We said we might get the kid's meal next time. Our daughter had to tell her husband to leave him (their son) some...you women! It was that good. They leave a carafe of water at your table which is good and our server was great, but MORE WATER!

My husband and I recently eloped so my boss gave us money to go out to a nice dinner. We love any restaurant by Stephen Starr so we thought what better way to celebrate our new marriage by coming to his new restaurant the Love! We had reservations and they were t ready for us so we waited at the bar. I splurged on the "$20 Manhattan" which was $19 which is a little ridiculous because I don't even think they cost that much in Manhattan but the drink was delicious. My husband had mad elf to start and he tried their wheat beer which was pretty good. To start I had the duck salad. Thank you. The flavors went so well together and the duck was cooked perfectly. My husband had the coconut curry soup and the scallops. I tried both and they were delicious but the real winner was the short rib stroganoff! So amazing! The place has a cute atmosphere. We came on opening weekend so it was a little busy but we hope to come back many more times!

This hotel is run down and has poor customer service. I found a cockroach in my hotel and the front desk was not helpful at all. All I was offered was another room. No other accommodation. I clearly don't want to stay in a hotel if there are bugs in my room because they are probably in other rooms.

This was my first time here and it definitely won't be my last. My margarita was great and the price wasn't bad..$8. I had the fish sandwich and it was  quite tasty. Upon first look I honestly thought it would be just ok but I was pleasantly surprised. We came here to see the band Fat Pocket and the place was packed. The bartender was nice. This was an over overall great experience. I hope I have fun like this each time I come!

This review is only for the charbroiled oysters!!  We  came here for a few drinks and some oysters, the wait time was about an hour or so. We were starving...they did give you 1 drink ticket each for the bar upstairs. We were able to snag some seats at the oyster bar. Now be prepared, you may end up smelling like charcoal but Greg, who prepares and cooks the oysters is AMAZING. 
The restaurant is definitely understaffed. No question. We were on our second dozen of the oysters before they even came over to take our drink orders. 
We ordered po' boys and some char broiled oysters for dinner. Po boys were fine, nothing to write home about ! We had the BBQ shrimp po boy, it's a huge sandwich and they literally scoop these little
Shrimp into a hero.  No lettuce or anything, but the sauce is good. But the oysters were AMAZING! They are by far the best ones I have had in NOLA. Just come here for those around lunch if possible but skip the dinner here ! Not worth the wait time 
If it were just a review on the oyster bar, I would say 5 stars but the service and po boy were a 3 star.

Nothing I can say, the food is not quite good. Third times I try to eat here but the food is getting worst each time. Well, I hope they are doing better. For me, the price is not an issue as long as the food is great. Huge disappointment!  They missed one item from the to go order, but I'm okay because they gave some french fries instead of french onion soup.
Delicious menu - we tried several appetizers which were creative.  Great atmosphere and service!

Great place to chill and have a brew. Massive selection. Bike logo reminds me of the Eagles album covers.  Very clean. So if you remember the old bars, this is a complete turnaround. Smells like popcorn instead of piss. Well done guys. A foosball table would be nice. .

A great little airport. Never a line for TSA, it's a breeze compared to Phoenix airport. A short walk to car rentals right on site. A few small shops and decent choices for grabbing a quick bite to eat like Noble Hops and a couple little chain bakeries. Highly recommend Flying into here over phoenix airport in the area.

Hubby and I just tried this cute and cozy restaurant tonight. Wonderful selection of wine and the service was great. We had the cheese plate (choice of four) with homemade fig jam and olives. It was a perfect starter. Hubs had the filet and I had the French Onion soup and a salad. Soup was delish. Steak was good but not great. We were both satisfied with our meals-- 4 stars for sure- close to a five. The restaurant is quaint and cozy but could benefit by a tiny bit of an upgrade (like framing the 70's mirror on the wall in the dining room). Overall I definitely recommend this restaurant but with a few tweaks it really could be a straight up five star experience.

What a great store!!! I would have never thought to get kids watches from here...I would have never thought to get any watches here because I'm not a watch person. But they are affordable, durable and unique gifts!!! I thought I've only seen Swatch stores in expensive malls, so I automatically assumed it's an expensive and overpriced brand. But I learned so much today. The saleswomen were informative and super helpful. Swatch is an international brand with stores all over. They replace your watch batteries for life and the batteries last 2-3 years...awesome! For the kids watches, the parts don't come off and the surface of the watch can always be  buffed out if they get a scratch on them. The kid's watches are essentially waterproof cuz they can take baths in them and you can even throw them in the washer if they have the cloth bands and need a little extra cleaning. I walked away with two different watches for my son and two watches for my two nieces. Great priced gifts for the holiday season!!!

I typically enjoy Pei Wei and have been eating here for years. I ordered a salad for the first time off their menu. I wanted to try their Ahi Avocado salad (~$8) because I love tuna. The tuna was underwhelming. It was diced into small pieces and the fish had too much moisture. I think the fish retained a lot of water. Despite this, the salad was nicely dressed and the fried wontons add a good crunch to the salad. The service is good and food comes out quickly. I will stick to my noodle dishes. For quick Asian food, I eat here for convenience.

Neal and Chris really make you feel like family here. Even though you have to travel a little bit to get to the attractions and the airport, the hotel is very comfortable and a good value for your money.
Low quality service and bad attitude all around from staff. I'd recommend driving further and going to a place that will appreciate your business.

I would definitely recommend Dean's Service. My heater wasn't working on a Sunday morning. I reached out to Dean's, left a message and Daniel called me back quicker than any other company. He was able to send someone out a few hours later. I was very thankful since most companies were closed on Sunday. Coby actually arrived sooner than originally planned. He was very knowledgeable and explained why the heater wasn't working. I appreciated that he took the time to show me different parts of the system and answered every question I had. The level of communication and service from both Daniel and Coby throughout my experience was top notch.

The bar is owned by Mac and Dee from "It's always sunny in Philadelphia" when it first opened, they used to swing by every so often, but I have not heard of that happening in a while.
The bar has absolutely nothing to do with the show, so if you are going in for nostalgia, I suggest going to the actual "Paddy's Pub" on Race st, which allows smoking and is almost divier than what is depicted on the show.
That being said, this is a fine little bar. Very basic, good beer selection, decent food. Nothing special, but a nice change of pace in old city where most locations are sports, food, or more high-end oriented.
Great food, good service, friendly people! The portions are a great size for the price. I look forward to coming back!
A bud of mine lives here and it's awesome. I am looking for a place and plan to move there when my lease ends. The apartments are super fancy and totally updated. I can't wait until next month!

Omg!!!!!! I'm NOT a fan of breakfast food usually but this was soooo damn good. Like how y'all? How???? And (unpopular opinion) I'm also usually not big on NOLA food. So I'm extra picky when I'm in town but (popular opinion) I do LOVE New Orleans. 

Important note: I don't eat meat and my husband is vegan. So we both had an array of meatless options and loveddddd it. The breakfast potatoes were amazing and the coffee and the tofu scramble. And the espresso was great. 

The service also was awesome and everyone was really helpful and welcoming. We loved it overall!

We recently moved into a house where the sprinklers had to turned on via the bleeder screws at the valves outdoors. Chris and Tim came by and diagnosed the problem to a cut sprinkler wire by the swimming pool. Apparently the pool contractors intentionally cut the wire to make way for the pool but neglected to re route or reconnect the sprinkler wire. It's been this way for a decade. Now it's just a matter for picking the most cost effective option to hook up an irrigation controller to the valves.

The team at for my family has been a great addition to our cleaning routine. We have been using them for over a year and have never had a bad clean. Oliver is super responsive and helpful! The add ons like carpet cleaning are a bonus! One of the best parts of having FMF clean is that it forces me to "defat" my home and get rid of clutter and extra things! I love coming home to fresh!

They have made a lot of efforts to ease scheduling by adding an app!

Not very good pizza for way too much money.  $3.50 delivery charge when on the phone they said $2.50.  then they charged another dollar for using my credit card that they didn't tell me about.  By the time I gave the driver a modest tip it was over $36 for 2 medium sub par pizzas.  Would say the donair pizza would be 1/5 and the cheeseburger 2/5 stars.

This was my first time trying South Philly pizza, and it was something special. We ordered a plain cheese pizza and sausage/mushroom pizza. Both were good, but I'll always remember the sausage. Loved that it was sliced sausage rather than crumbled or ground. It had so much good flavor. My friend patted her sausage with napkin, but I thought it was just fine--a little grease adds flavor :)

Worth a visit!  The entrance fee was fairly inexpensive and the extra garage tour is worth the money as well.  They said they typically change the showroom cars every 6 months, I think.  This time they were showcasing micro cars.  Loved how the showroom was set up.  No overwhelming and so many cars to look at.  The garage tour was also very informative.

If you love European cars, this is the place to go!

I've been going to Cynthia for a few years and I've always had great experiences with her. She's a color genius especially with high or low lights. I always receive compliments on my hair when I've had her do it and I LOVE the blonde she brings out in my hair. I've gone to other stylists on occasion only to be disappointed with the color. With Cynthia I know I'm always going to get great color.

My headlight and tail light were out. I went in and immediately was greeted by Ty. Luckily they weren't busy so he was able to ring me up and change my lights. Very friendly, and I was on my way in a flash. They change wipers, and batteries there as well, but I'm sure everyone knew that except for me. Excellent customer service.

This place has the worst service you could possibly imagine. I went in there to get 1 bagel with butter and it took 30 minuets. There was literally 1 person in front of me and 3 people sitting down waiting for their order. When I finally got my bagel they put cream cheese on it instead of butter.... zero chance this place will be able to stay open much longer

Not many choices to hrab a bite in concourse C, but this place seemed to have the most selection.  Erenie took my order and was very friendly & polite, made sure to ask if the items that came on a chicken club were ok and they were.   Overall very pleasantly surprised,  it took about 10 minutes for my food but, it was all hot and fresh.  Chicken Club & Chicken finher basket were very good.   For being in a  airport it was a good value.  Honey mustard sauce was awesome!

I don't know why I keep eating the food here. Not many choices in this dumpy airport. ACME was such a good eatery, and they were replaced by a garbage restaurant, Dooky something. 

I ordered red beans, no rice and gumbo, no rice. The read beans were delicious. The gumbo was awful. Looked like they put cornstarch in it. Had some kind of slimy red globs all floating around that I had to fish out. 

It should be against the law to serve bad gumbo in this town. 

Cost me $23 for this poor meal. 

I tried one of their biscuits. Bland. Dry. Terrible. They should taste a biscuit from Popeye's.

After a 10 year absence, I went back for dinner. And I'm so glad I did. This is not the same old place. Yes, it's the same but the vibe is totally different. It's alive and it's awesome. 
I got lucky with timing as it was a last minute decision. Called them and a wonderful person answered. Engaging, pleasant, funny. 5 minutes later I was walking through the front doors. 
The staff is different and the atmosphere is a mix of old South Philly and East Passyunk. A GREAT mix. 
Food was on the spot. Service was outstanding. This was a fun dinner. 
What a transformation. Wow. 
South Philly deserted its Italian roots sadly. And the proliferation of good Italian eats is but a thing of the past. 
If you're in South Philly, forget the wannabe great Italian like Tre Scalini and come here. 
Highly. HIGHLY recommended.

Was there last week they had a special on pork roast and pork chops. Went to self check out, special wasn't working, floor manager Jeff W. Was non-communicative and clearly annoyed with me. 
My husband and I are in the store all the time and the customer service from Jeff W. Was rude and extremely unfriendly. Thinking of going to Giant for my food may be farther away but at least employees are nice.

This place is honestly not that great for the price we payed 75$ for 2. We went around 3 rounds wasted so much food nothing was good except the soda. Most the seafood was very fishy almost anything fried was soggy. The pizza tasted like cardboard and felt like biting wood. Prime rib was full of fat tri tip was like rubber even the desert sucked don't come here downtown Reno has a better selection and better price this place taxes for trash food and don't even think about the line we had to wait through. Best advice go somewhere else to eat.

I'm a Reno native and came home for the holidays and wanted to check out a new restaurant in downtown that I hadn't been to. We choose Sierra st. The appetizers were fantastic! Loved the caprese salad, Thai chicken wraps, and bacon wrapped dates were to die for!! great place, stop in for yourself!
Best challah in . . . well, anywhere I've been outside of Europe and Israel. Don't tell anyone. ;-)

**I ordered through Ubereats. It took about 10-15 minutes to get to me** 

I ordered the dragon bowl with half sushi rice and half mixed greens. The dragon bowl comes with tempura shrimp, avocado, tempura crunch, cucumber. It also comes with siracha, but I requested that it be left out.

The tempura shrimp was cold, which wasn't a surprise since it did take a while to get to get to me and it was on top of cold rice and veggies. It tasted fresh though and still had some crunch. 

The rice was cooked perfectly and tasted great with the mixed greens. The only complaint I had was that they mixed teriyaki sauce in with the rice and veggies, making some of the lettuce inedible. Next time I will make sure to ask to have the soy sauce and other sauces on the side. Other than that, I would definitely order here again!

Incredible food incredible service!!! 
Can't wait to come back again!!! I walked in, had a great recommendation and the food came out quickly!!

I recently went to Pueblo Radiology for a vein procedure.  The staff and doctors are great, but their billing procedures are not. I never received a statement in the mail or via email for the amount that I owed beyond what I paid at the time of my visits and on my procedure date. To my surprise, they quickly sent my account to a collections agency which I paid once I received the bill from the agency. Their billing dept is in LA and the person I spoke to there did not have any information for me.   I still have not received an itemized statement from them.  Very frustrating experience on the billing end, but my procedure was successful and again the staff and doctors are wonderful.  Hopefully they will improve their billing process.

Started with artichoke dip and small wing with bbq sauce (bad choice as I will explain).   Artichoke dip definitely star of appetizer round. Definitely worth it.  The chips are homemade which are ok, but dip was creamy with good flavor.  Wings, as I ordered ribs, I should have tried a different flavor.  They were heavily sauced.  Sauce is sweet with heavy vinegar base.  Reminded me a little of Tony Romas.  For entree, my wife had tri-tip and I had ribs.  Tri-tip came sauced, same as wings.   Smoke ring was ok, but meat a little dry.  (Happens with smoking)   Ribs reminded me of backyard ribs.  Same sauce with blackened flat side and fall off bone.   

Mac and cheese was homemade and star of sides.  Cole slaw was a little sweet, but balanced.   Beans have a strong ancho chile flavor, but are also sweet.  

Service is attentive.   Will be back to try pizza.

Classic Society Hill bar and restaurant. Was in on a very chilly Friday evening. The bar was warm and cozy, and there was live jazz! Enjoyed a well-made cocktail made by a very professional and friendly bartender. Ordered the Philly classic fried oysters and chicken salad, which was wonderful, and salt cod fritters which were crispy and delicious! Refined atmosphere but neither stuffy nor overly fancy. In short, this would be my neighborhood go-to for classic food and warm service!

I highly recommend Sew Perfectly. I have taken maybe 20 items to them in the last few months so I can speak to their excellent skill and customer service. I got simple things done like hemming or adding a slit or repairing a tear and I feel like my clothes got rescued for a very low cost. I have also gotten more complicated things done like replacing a band on a skirt with an elastic band, and getting a faux fur collar on a jacket completely replaced (I brought them the new faux fur fabric, which I purchased separately), the items look amazing. I really can't praise this place enough.

The food was fantastic , the broths delicious and savory. Service was great.

I have one main concern that will keep me from returning . The ventilation is terrible, and based on the space layout , there is not good air flow. As a result, your clothes and jacket and anything you bring in will absolutely reek of potent Mongolian spices for a very long time. Do not wear anything that can't be washed in a standard washing mine here .

Again food was great , but not worth the Hassle for me.

Let me start out by saying that I have stayed here several times and have given this Courtyard a positive review in the past. I have always loved this Courtyard due to its out of the way location and absolutely beautiful interior, I truly love the lobby area!

I am witnessing a trend at this hotel though and that is with the room cleaning staff. I know that they have a job to do, but I have never stayed at a hotel that matches them for aggressiveness. The last time we stayed here they kept bugging us about when we would be out of the room, we finally just requested a late check out to try and solve the issue.

We stayed here last night, didn't get in until pretty late due to a flight delay. By 9:00 this morning they were knocking on the door trying to get in to clean the room. I guess they thought my Wife was the only person in room so as I was trying to get in the shower, she just walks into the room, no knocking just opens the door, I thought it was my Wife coming back into the room it was that quick. I honestly don't know what the deal is with the room attendants here! They truly need to knock before entering a room, don't assume that there is just one person staying in that room.

I guess if I stay here again I will have a "Do not disturb" sign on the door the entire length of my stay!
Drunken noodles with beef were delicious!! Be aware, of you order the food Hot, it is not scorching but get your nose runny :-) The Thai iced tea was amazing as well. Very light and casual setting.

First time was okay but the second time back was a different story. The bagel sandwiches are pretty on point; however, the drinks were a disappointment. My girlfriend got the iced coffee and I got the iced latte, 1/4 of a way through our drinks we started noticing a weird taste. The drinks started to taste like rubbing alcohol or so we think that's what they tasted like. We threw the rest of the drinks away. I recommend they check their equipment or their entire drink making process, something was fucking the drinks up.

We went to carlucci's for my father-in-law's birthday. It's one of those restaurants that just seems to attract old people but despite its old-people-vibe, the food was quite yummy. I had the seafood carnavale in the white wine garlic sauce, my partner had the crab cake and father in law the red seafood canavale. It was soooo goood! Additionally, we had the house Pinot noir for $26/bottle. With desserts and coffee - our total was $170 and then 20% off through Yelp!

Dr. Neville and the entire staff at Clymer has provided superior support, guidance and treatment to my 19 year old daughter.  She was diagnosed with fibromyalgia and chronic fatigue syndrome at the age of 16 and we had been given very little direction and or understanding of this condition at a very large hospital system. Dr. Neville spent considerable amount of time learning her history and then suggesting the appropriate testing.  Adrenal Fatigue can be treated with much success if given the right treatment plan.  The Clymer Healing Center has gone above and beyond to respond to our many questions and concerns throughout the healing process.  The suggested options over time has resulted in significant improvement.  The key here is a comprehensive plan customized for the patient.

IKEA gives you exactly what you're looking for ... inexpensive furniture that lasts relatively long. This is a great place for contemporary starter furniture for all ages. We have purchased furniture for all three of of our children's dorms and first apartments. It has held up relatively well and has even been handed down. 
They are also very forgiving with their return policy. Quality is a 3. Their business practices push them to a 4 Star.
I heard this place was closing down and all I have to say is, good riddance. Bye Felicia.

As a foreigner, this is my first time taking greyhound. I know that the bus price is really cheap especially for student budget, but this bus has a bad service ever. How can you tell us "the bus late 4 hours " without any reason. There is no alert text or email so you need to check it first by yourself. Zero star.

Possibly my favorite lunch spot in Nola. Walkable from the quarter or just under Canal Street as long as the weather is decent. 

We went with the lunch buffet and the fried chicken was the sh!t.  Fried just right, not greasy, seasoned and juicy. I could have had that everyday. The Mac and cheese was really good and the beans with ham was amazing. 

You get sweet or unsweetened tea with the buffet and the unsweetened tea was even good.  

Lastly, the bread pudding is crazy good.  We would stop there just for the bread pudding good to put it in perspective.  

Nice little spot with nice people and good home cooked food.

If you're in the mood for great Wings hot or mild, cold beer this is the place. I don't understand all the negative comments about this location. This Buffalo Wild Wings has always been great. I tried the new Thai ginger boneless wings. They were mild at first bite but had a gentle heat. I recommend pairing any wing choice with a local brew. My server Jill deserve credit as she was fast and friendly.

I love this place. It's only a couple blocks from Banker's Life Fieldhouse so it's great for a pregame/ concert meal. The Pour card allows you to pick and pour your own beer. The food is really good. The adult milkshakes are amazing perfect combo of alcohol and shake. There isn't a ton of seating so it can get crowded but it is worth the wait.

On Wednesday we like to go there,it is called Wednesday special.
Buy whole chicken and get half chicken free.

Great grill chicken
Best refried beans
Fast service
Place has outdoor seating
Drive thou

I have been to other places and their refried beans is really good!

During fall time take seat outdoor but during summer time take out,kindly hot at that times.

Talked to Mae in the pharmacy, needed to get a medication ASAP. Gave her the phone number for my RX plan.... Mae called back a couple of times within the next few hours with every excuse under the sun... Oh 'they hung up on me', 'they didn't answer', I verified the number & it was correct. 
After hours of waiting I told her to forget it... I'll go somewhere else. When I called the number got right through no problems.... wouldn't waist my time with this place!!

I really enjoy going to Katie's PPO. This is my first time visiting this particular location, and I have to say- I like this location more than the Rock Hill one. For one, it's closer to me. But overall, I just think it's so dang cute. It's more spacious too, which is a bonus because I think the Rock Hill location gets a little cramped. 

The food here is just as good as the Rock Hill location. I hate to not be adventurous, but I always get the arugula reginette. I had it my 2nd time at the Rock Hill location, and I have been getting it ever since. It's a delicious choice if you are a mushroom lover. I typically always have a little bit leftover for a light lunch the next day too, so that is a bonus. 

My one complaint is just the prices. I personally just feel like the pizza and the pasta are pretty pricey. Pretty pricey pizza & pasta (say that 5 times fast). But in my honest opinion 18-20 dollars for a pizza just is high to me. I guess if you were splitting it with someone, that's not bad at all, but if you're out to eat with people you're not spilling a pizza with, 20 bucks just seems crazy. Obviously, people are willing to pay it. I mean, I am paying $20 for pasta with mushrooms. But whatever. I look at somewhere comparable like Pastaria, where there pizzas hit around the 13 dollars mark and the pasta hits around the 16 dollar mark and I wonder why the prices are so high here. 

Overall, I can't complain about the quality of food and service though. They are always really on point every time I have visited. I hate spending 20 dollars on a pasta for myself, plus and drink or app you really start to get into around 50 bucks just for 1 person. KPPO does't blow me away, but I'm sure I will be back.

I really REALLY wanted to like this place, especially after reading all the great reviews on Yelp. Unfortunately, it just wasn't so. The food wasn't terrible but it also wasn't great. If I had to sum up the meal in one word it would be SALTY. I'm not a bland food type of person, but all the food that my husband and I ordered today was pretty salty. 

My husband and I arrived to the place around 1:30 and luckily it wasn't super packed. The place is really tiny but very well decorated and very clean. We were able to get a table right away and we were greeted right away by the host to ask if wanted tea or water.  The servers were very friendly during our entire time there, and they were great with all customers from what I could see. 

We ordered the cha gio for appetizer and the regular bun bo hue and the banh mi dac biet for our main meal. The cha gio looked really good, and they didn't use much (if any) taro as a filler unlike a lot of other places,  and I really appreciated that. They tasted really fresh and pretty good although a bit salty. The spicy fish sauce vinaigrette that they serve with it was also on the salty side. The banh mi was OK--surprisingly small, not a lot of meat filling, and they don't put the pickled veggies on the sandwich which I thought it desperately needed. The bun bo hue was what I had high hopes for, though, since it seems like everyone raves about it. As soon as it came out I tasted the broth--great pork flavor but other than that it was salty and didn't have enough lemongrass. My husband though the meat was a little over cooked and on the soft side. I was a little let down since bun bo hue is one of my most favorite noodle soups.  

I'm not sure if we went on an "off" day but I just wasn't won over by any of the food. Props for the great decor and excellent service though.

I was in a hurry to get some business cards printed and David called me back as soon as he saw my email which happened to be AFTER he closed the store on Friday evening and did everything he could to get me the business cards.... staying after hours! I called at least five other print stores in town every single one of them said it was asking way too much (which is funny because it took david less than an hour) and since it was Friday they were closing early (even though I called around 1:30..???) Super sweet guy and definitely reasonably priced. Thanks buddy!

Save your time and don't shop here. I went in to purchase a bedroom set for my daughter first time I went in to look and get prices then I had to go home measure and talk to my husband.. I went back and the lady who quoted me all my prices which she wrote down in detail everything she told me was off. The manager said why didn't you buy it the first time you were here then and basically told me he dosent know what to tell me so I said I was going to shop elsewhere and he said OK. I was blown away from the lack of professionalism. The furniture is cheaply made anyway. Ended up going to ashley furniture the same day, got my daughter a 5 piece bedroom set for 1,800!!!! Including mattress box spring warranty delivery mattress protector everything !! WAY BETTER quality than bobs and I saved money at ashley

By the way the link the "bobs representive" posted under my review is not a legit link.
She's old but she's fun to look at. This place is pretty cool if you're obviously into antiques, lots of retro 50s post war flashbacks..I love just walking around this place..

What a gem!! If you're looking for really great wine in a great spot next to the river, this is the place. The viognier was different in the best way possible. It was complex and subtle and really is a red lovers white wine. Their flagship red, Turas, was also really good! The staff was super friendly and knowledgeable. The patio looks like it would be perfect in the summer. Also, their wine club is a great deal! Try the wine flight!

We ended up here after seeing the ridiculous line for Hattie B's. We are so glad we did.
Simple but very tasty food. Most importantly the staff was very friendly (especially to my kids).

This is a great pizza place. We bypass other pizza restaurants to eat there.  Their Italiano sub is as good as it gets.  All in all excellent customer service, quality and pricing. Free movie as a bonus!

Exemplary customer service, very courteous and respectful staff!

The electricity went out at the apart on Christmas eve (awesome I know) and we were in quick need of a contractor to come out. Fortunately, as everyone was home for the holidays, we were able to wait until the day after Christmas to try and get someone to come out. I left a voicemail on Christmas just to be sure.

Within 15 minutes of them opening, I received a call back from Cindy to schedule someone to come out. Cindy was amazingly nice and explained the whole process to me with how their services work. They DID NOT charge a service fee to come out to look at it which was great, especially with the various contractors our there charging an arm and leg just to come out. They were able to get someone out within one hour. 

By some miraculous event, the power was on as I came to the house to meet them. The house must have hear Generation 3 Electric is coming to town. The inspector was still kind enough to look around and try to diagnose what may have caused it. While there was no apparent reason for what may have caused it, he still did a thorough walk through. 

I am usually uneasy about working with some contractors as I feel many try to get the most money from you and up charge for services. This was definitely not the case. I cannot speak for pricing as we didn't have anything done but am definitely using them again if I have any electrical issues (hopefully never).

Best place you've never eaten at in St. Louis. The food is outstanding. The only reason for the 4 star rating is for service, not for poor service but rather for a lack of servers causing our server to be under a stack of pressure. The food is just amazing it eclipsed the shortage in staff.

We went on Christmas Eve to grab a meal. We were seated and waited 15 minutes before a waitress took our drink order. My girlfriend had to go ask the hostess twice to send over a waitress. When the waitress finally came over she said the hostess never told her we were there! She offered a free appetizer so we asked for a queso and pulled pork dip and chips! About 20 minutes later the manager came with a plate of tater tots and said they were all out of pulled pork . The tater tots were dressed with green onion which I won't eat and bacon my girlfriend won't eat. She ask us if there was anything else we would like. We asked for a different plate with green onion and one side and bacon on the other . About 15 minutes later they brought out a new plate. Our food order arrived about 10 minutes later. After we finished eating the waitress came and picked up our payment. When she turned to the table she tried to inform us that the restaurant isn't a seat yourself restaurant. My girlfriend told we didn't seat ourselves the hostess did ! She started to argue with my girlfriend. The management needs to pay closer attention to the operation on the restaurant. Food was mediocre at best ! Will be along time before we return.

I have been cutting my hair at this barbershop for an year and a half. The ladies laura, naline have been doing a really impressive job since I decided to come to this new location. $14 for a haircut with shampoo included. You guys rock and I am fabulously happy. Keep up the good work ladies as I love you all a lot and I will continue doing business with you for future

Preservation Hall is a magical musical place.  I felt like I was transported back in time as the Jazz music flow through the venue.  They are opened nightly at 6pm, 8pm, 9pm and 10pm.  Ticket price varies and costs about twice as much online.  The show I attended was during a week night and online pricing about about $35.  However, you do get a reserved spot on the bench.  I waited inline for half an hour and bought ticket the door for $15.  It's standing room only, but that's great since it's easier to dance.  

The venue is much smaller than anticipated with 3 rows or bench seating and the rest is standing room.  You can bring in outside beverages since they do not serve alcohol.  There is no restroom, but you can use the ones at Pat O'Brien's next door.  You won't want to leave for the hours or so of music that you'll experience here, so make sure you go before the show.  You can take pictures before the music start but not during.  The music was amazing!!  It was raw and pure and intimate.

My favorite place to eat besides the tacos right next door to them. I think I come here everyday they know my face now and what I order every time I come in lol. I love their food and good customer service. :)

Amazing place. Heard of it on Sunset magazine last year and finally went this year. Backyard to a river. Atmosphere is amazing for any occasion. Loved it! I heard it was closing but I hope that's not true.

Disappointed. Came in on Monday 12/11/17 around noon. Name was put on the list. Wait was short. Was helped by Jesse. Told him I needed a cell phone for my daughter, as well as insurance, and a cover because she broke her screen and phone was glitching.  (Problem 1) A lady walks in the store and interrupts us. Rather than telling her to sign in and wait for the next employee to help her, he leaves me standing there while while he assists her with her question.   After the interruption, he proceeds to ask me how old my daughter is. I said 22. (Problem 2) He said "well tell her to buy her own damn phone."  I explained to him that was not an option at this time. Then we started looking at phones.   I asked him about buying the phone rather than installments. He looked annoyed at me and said "well we don't do that you have to buy it from Apple."  My husband texted me about an offer for BOGO on IPhone 8. Jesse said that was only for adding a new line. My husband did not see where you needed to add a line to get the BOGO offer. Said that to Jesse. He said "listen I have been doing this for a long time and I know what I'm talking about."  I told my husband via text again.  My husband said tell him to put it in writing  I told the rep what my husband said. Oh boy. Things got uncomfortable.  (Problem 3) Jesse became impatient and angry. I apologized for any problem I was causing. (mind you at this point I was also frustrated with my husband, but as much as that frustrated Jesse, he failed miserably in basic customer service).  (Problem 4) He put the IPhone back he had taken out for me and just walked away. I told him I wanted the phone. He said "well I put it back and need to wait on other customers."  Coincidentally at that point someone walked in he clearly knew he said "Hey" and started taking with them. Apparently that was the customer I was holding up (or maybe a friend he was going to have lunch with ). I told him "clearly this is not working for you."  I left the store. No sale.  His customer service skills are unacceptable.  Even if a customer is challenging, you should never just blow them off. He was condescending right from the "tell her to buy her own damn phone" comment. I have been an AT&T customer for over 10 years and felt like I was such an inconvenience for this employee.   I won't be going back to this store.   Frankly I don't think I will stay with AT&T. No longer under contract.  They can lose my phone sales and wireless business at 185.00 a month. There are many other wireless companies. I will try another place that hopefully won't get upset if I am not an express transaction.  FYI. I truly don't believe I was in the store for more that 20 minutes from stepping in and waiting to walking out.
Not impressed, sushi burritos from the bay area that ive tried were way better quality and taste.

While participating in the Whole 30 diet, my husband and I visited the Block. Since it is very restrictive (no sugar, grains, dairy, beans, etc) we have dreaded eating out. The Block was a totally different experience!! Our waitress was very willing to accommodate us and spoke to the chef. Both Chef Brian and his wife Lea prepared an amazing, clean and healthy dinner for us! And it did not lack any flavor or make us feel like we were missing out on anything at all!!
We started with the beet salad. (Omitting the cheese) which included an awesome vinegar-based dressing!
We both had amazing entrees as well! The Fish special and Amish Chicken were absolutely delicious! They were happy to omit the butter and even topped the roasted vegetables with a quality truffle oil!
We will definitely return again! And bring all of our friends!

I've definitely had better experiences staying at other hotels, and I think this may be the last time I make the effort to stay at a Holiday Inn Express.

We arrived pretty late on a Thursday night and made our way into town.  My wife navigated us to the hotel, where we found parking out back.  The part of town didn't seem that rough until we realized we couldn't get into the hotel because the doors had locked and you needed a key card to get in.  Small problem-- we hadn't even checked in yet!

There was an unexpected parking fee of $30/night added to our tab, which we were only informed about after we checked in.  This got us off to a rough start with the whole trip, but being 11pm and not being familiar with the area at all, we just went ahead and opted in for the parking.

The elevators are really slow, and it seemed like only one of them was operational.  The room seemed clean, but unnecessarily small, with the bathroom sink right next to the bed.  The bathroom door slides shut without a lock.  It's an odd feature that I'm not a fan of at all.

There are a few notable pros to this place, namely the short walk (about 10 city blocks) to the French Quarter, the free Wi-Fi in the rooms, and complimentary breakfast, but on the whole they can't save what's otherwise a mediocre experience.  While we were having breakfast, some lady was arguing with the concierge because they changed her reservation without telling her and were trying to move her to a smaller room that wouldn't accommodate her family.  It was really disappointing to find out.

I didn't encounter any of the bed bugs that other people reported, but I wish I'd read some of these reviews beforehand, because I would have avoided this place.

Amazing place! Was recommended by a friend to see Saji to get some pants alternated that were tad too big and wanted them to feel more fitted for a wedding I was going to attend and did not want to spend lots of money on a new pair a pants. Saji was very friendly and very attentive in what I wanted and was very reasonable on time she could get it done and the price was unbeatable. Could not recommend her enough. I will be visiting her for all future alteration I have.

If i could give them no stars I would. HORRIBLE SERVICE from start to finish Molly is the absolute worst person to have at the front counter, very nonchalant the phones not working she's like oh well... asked for a refund

Good food, great service, great selection of food and sauces. We were looking for something new to try and thought we'd give this place a shot, and it did not disappoint! Considering the atmosphere and decor, I was a little surprised at the higher prices, but everything we ordered tasted great and the portions are good sized. We would definitely go back. 
We tried, and would recommend: the meat sampler, the vegan potatoe salad, Cole slaw, and bread pudding.

The steak was not quite medium, a little tough. The mill old fashioned was really good. My wife did not like the shrimp and grits they were too spicy. Might come back for the brunch but dinner was a just ok. The place looks nice kind of a mill look on the inside with chains and gears on the wall. Service was good the waiter made recommendations for wine that was spot on.
Fast and courteous service. Had the Salmon Lover Roll and Miso Soup which were both very good. Menu has many options.

I finally found a coffee shop near me that I love!

 I want a place I can go have a good cup of coffee where I can relax at. Well now I have it. It's such a warm place. You feel like family! Plus food is good! I love that now when I go in They know just how I like my  the question is just if I need a large that day !

Thanks you guys!

Welcome to Bensonhurst, Brooklyn! Mazzaro's is an Italian neighborhood under one roof. You got the Pork Store, the Bakery, the Bread Shop, the Wine Shop, the Butcher, the Cafe, the Deli, the Grocer, the Coffee House and a Gourmet Pizzeria all within walking distance. Always busy, a daily visit, can't find parking, loud and long lines. Everything I miss from Brooklyn! There is just too much to describe here. Suffice it to say, it's a must visit to fully appreciate. From warm fresh made mozzarella to fine Italian appetizers to fresh breads, cookies, pastries and coffees, it's an adventure to visit. I can spend an hour or more every time I go in and always see something I didn't see the last time. One warning, it is expensive, so check your available balance before going in. I can quickly spend a hundred or more in minutes, but that's exactly the way it was in Brooklyn as well. It's nice to know there's a place I can go to get ANYTHING I desire as an Italian food junkie.

This place is a perfect all night dinner and entertainment stop.  The show was great, nice shops to walk around and the haunted house was a uniques experience and a must see! The food was excellent but why topped off all these great amenities and the food was the service. Even waiters who were not our own stopped to talk and chat which was very nice! Love this place!

I went here looking for ferret food and cat litter and found a decent selection of pet products, pet advice, and pet specials.

There's stiff competition, from online to huge big barn strip mall chains, but it's nice to see specialized pet smarts in a small local store. This might be the place I head to first for info and stuff when the pets need attention. Prices are somewhat competitive but still a little high. The great service makes up for it tho.

The Frist Is such a wonderful place and it's existence makes Nashville so much richer. The people that work at Frist bring in wonderful exhibits and have fabulous events.

Today I was there to just get my kids out of the house over Christmas break. There is a great kids area on the upper level called Martin Art Quest. There are so many fun educational activities for kids and adults to do! You can make screen prints, paint, create reliefs, sketch, read, build, use magnets to make cool wooden creations, etc. my kids range from 2yrs-6yrs and all three were able to find activities. 

Frist also has some amazing exhibits. There is one now about WW1 and I look forward to returning without my kids to view it. 

Frist has some really neat events. Last year I went to their Prohibition gala and we got to dress up in 20's Garb and they had all kids of yummy food and adult drinks and music. So fun! 

I need to take an architectural tour of the Frist one month. The building is Art Deco and amazing! I can't believe our post offices use to be that beautiful. 

Go visit, become a member, this place is amazing and I hope all will support it.

This is not my usual movie theater but I went to a screening of The Shape of Water. Amazing movie with a little bit of errythang - romance, suspense, comedy, and beautifully created. The theater itself, though, was just average. Nothing too special to mention. It was decent and clean and finding parking was not an easy feat!

Finally went to Short Hills Deli since the fire. It was finished almost exactly the way it was before the fire and year plus being closed. The menu was very close if not exactly the same too. The only addition was the pickle bar. It wasn't all that great. The health salad was chopped finer than cole slawbut had a good flavor. I would have preferred the old deli way-sliced cabbage, red and green pepper and onions. The cole slaw was too creamy and definately not made in house. The pickles were just a little too overdone for my taste. The bowls and plates were so small that you either could only get two small pickles on the plate or go back for multiple helpings. I had a pistrami sandwich labeled thick sliced New York cut. They need to take a trip to NYC to see what hand sliced pistrami looks like. The rye bread was too soft almost white bread. The good news was the flavor of the pistrami was well above average. The pepper rim was just right with a fine grind and very slight peppery taste. My dining partner had the turkey with gravy, stuffing and potatoes. The turkey looked to me like sliced deli turkey breast. Not a fresh in house cooked breast. The gravy was certainly out of a can and very salty. My companion said the plater was just okay. He like the barley mushroon soup.
The waitress was extremely pleasant and several levels above the staff I remember. Prices have gone up considerably. The Sunday breakast is now over $50 and says it's for three people. I could do better in Harolds at exit 10 of the NJ turnpike 
Probably will go back but not very quickly or often.

Drinks: I had their alcoholic cucumber melon drink, which was amazing! I had asked for recommendation and our server was on point. 

Price: not cheap by any means but worth it. 

Ambiance: relaxing with a great view of the water. 

Service: real attentive. Made sure we always had a drink. Great service. 

I didn't have food, but drinks with friends made for a great evening.

Sometimes when you go to a popular restaurant that all your friends have recommended for a must visit, you already have high expectations and most likely you won't be super-impressed. That's not the case with Commander's Palace for us. Having just eaten a big breakfast at the French Quarter, we decided to take the streetcar over to the Garden City area for a stroll. Receiving a tip from a streetcar passenger couple that we could get three 25¢ martinis with our lunch entrée, we decided to drop in to check out the menu. We were quickly roped in to sit down after receiving jingle necklaces on our neck by the very hospitable and lively hostesses welcoming visitors for the holidays season. Despite insistent warnings to our waiter, Argyle, that we were not hungry and would like to split our order, the level of service by him and his crew (Julien & Jamie Lynn) remained as courteous and attentive as ever. We observed a very well-organized and well-communicated operations by the restaurant staff on the second floor. Our split orders of turtle soup and pork loins lunch special were tasty and plenty for us to share. Best of all we got to try all three of our 25¢ (melon, cosmo & commander's) martinis with our lunch order. No wonder this place is an institution in the beautiful Garden City residential neighborhood.

From the moment entering this unassuming exterior, this restaurant has nailed it from atmosphere to terrific staff to amazing food and margaritas. 

My wife found this from a quick Google search as we had just arrived in Tucson for the first time ever. We drove from our AirBNB and were delighted by everything we experienced at this place.

The menu changes everyday and the servers have it down pact!

Our plates were excellent. The only area I'd suggest for improvement is reduce the portions.

Please note its a bit higher end, and they welcomed us with our shorts and flip flops (well, mine, my wife was considerably better dressed). 

Bon Appetite Cafe Poca Cosa! Very well done!

Trying for the first time. I had 2 soft chicken tacos,rice,chips. Tacos great. Rice tasted funny. Didn't like at all.hubby had chicken Nachos no onions. Large amount of food. Pretty good.my son had the fajita burrito chicken very large. Way to much rice. Pretty good. Friend had ground beef nachos very greasy couldn't even finish. Wasted most of it. Liked the different choices of sauces to try. We won't go back.

Excellent Breakfast Burrito at a reasonable price.
Nice and friendly folks.

You order at the window of the small Mobile Home, Wait a bit, and a woman comes out of the house next door with your food.

Only reason I did not give them a 5 Star is because they did not have egg whites.  High Cholesterol Yellow Eggs only here.

They explained to me that they are not yet set up for egg whites. 
They are hoping to expand in the future. 

I know it's complicated to separate the yolk from the whites, but hopefully they will figure it out soon and we will all be healthier.

It's in a neighborhood right off I-10 and Speedway that looks unsafe, where many people have bars on the windows of their homes--it's the Barrio of Tucson.  But during the hours they are open--6 am to noon, you should not have any problems--the bad people are usually strung out sleeping at those hours.

They have a gravel parking lot and a few tables outside.

Nice entrepreneurial hardworking folks that deserve your business. 

Check them out.  Unique thing.

Star cleaner is a Great place to get your dry cleaning done the staff is friendly and very helpful Terry can get out almost any thing  stain wise great prices too and the guy that has someone elses  shirt bring it back it maybe mine
The whole team was amazing. Tubes were explained procedure explained. Whole experience was AWESOME.   And I can see.

Wanted to like this place. I love a good burger joint with a nice beer selection. Went there on a Saturday and found the place relatively busy, but we were seated right away. The restaurant was clean, inviting, and the wait staff was very nice and attentive. The menu had several delicious sounding burgers and appetizers. We ordered the fried pickles and the pretzels between 5 people. There were maybe 12 total pickle chips to the order. Most restaurants serve you a giant basket. That's what I've come to expect from a fried pickle appetizer. There was only -3- pretzel sticks in the order. Not impressed by this. 

4 of us ordered burgers, each chose a different one. No one was particularly impressed, but I'll keep this review to my order. I had the Pacific burger which had an Asian slaw, a couple of sauces, and some nice sounding fresh veggies. I upgraded to the wagyu beef and had them cook it medium rare. The order came with my side of onion rings... exactly -3- onion rings. In what world is that a side of onion rings? The plate looked half empty. 

Took my first bite of the burger, about 1/3 of the patty broke off and tumbled out the back and onto my plate, along with a stream of various sauces and juices that turned my plate into a sloppy mess. I realized at that point that i was committed to completing the meal with the burger in my hand, because there was nowhere to put it down that wasn't a swimming pool of sauce and grease. The patty was extremely bland. My guess is zero salt was added to the patty before grilling. By my third bite, the bottom of my brioche bun had disintegrated into a moist sloppy mess and completely fallen apart. At that point, the meal is basically ruined. 

There are at least a half dozen better burgers within a 3 to 5 mile radius of this restaurant.  All that potential in the menu is wasted with the lack of attentiveness in the kitchen. Had the patty been seasoned properly, the appetizers and sides been the proper size, and my burger constructed properly, this would have been a completely different review. Such a shame.

Stopped here for a late lunch before our flight home and we were so glad we did! We were worried about getting a table butt there were plenty available in their beautiful dining room. I had the Brandy Milk Punch (sooo good!), the Huckleberry Blintz, and of course you must try the Bananas Foster if you come here! It is to die for!! My parents also got Irish Coffee which was also good. Wait staff was very professional, attentive, and nice. If I ever get back to Nola, I will definitely come here again!
Incredibly slow service and they charge a 20% gratuity for groups larger than five...even though the food came out a half hour apart and we paid with separate checks. This will be our last visit!

Staff is very friendly and playful with the dogs. Brought our pup here for the first time in December and he loved it. Decided to bring him for doggy daycare couple days each week. The only negative we have is that he came him with his skin broken out red bumps all over here not sure if it's a coincidence or what doctor says it may be allergies. Either way we will bring him back.
Good times!! Mocha Manhatten and the Mexican martini are really my go too drinks.  New area is real nice. Same vibe but different. They did a good job!

This is my favorite hotel in New Orleans.
The service is top notch from the valet, to check in, to bell service, to maintenance being prompt when our toilet was clogged, the restaurant, everyone was courteous and helpful.
Oh and the hotel is exceptionally beautiful at Christmas time! I haven't had a bad experience with any facet of this hotel.

I've been here about four times now over the years, and the staff never disappoints. Very little waiting time (if any), and well qualified friendly people at every step of the process from being greeted to being measured for your frames. The Techs know what they're doing, and the doctors are informative, caring and professional. I wouldn't consider going anywhere else. As for price, they can't be beat, and they aren't pushy about adding on extras. They offer them, as of course, they're expected to do, but zero pressure. Every one of my visits has been outstanding.
Great food and a low key atmosphere. I've never had a bad meal and customer service is always great. Prices are as good as the portions. You can't go wrong with having a meal or get together here.

My wife and I were visiting Tucson and stopped by this place for breakfast. The first impression as we stepped in was how clean the place was. The staff were very friendly and we loved the food. So much so that we went back for lunch the very same day before leaving Tucson. Their fish tacos were the best we have ever had.

the place is pretty unassuming in a strip mall. when we walked in it was pretty empty, but it was a monday night so that's to be expected I feel like.

they have happy hour 4-6 and it's $1 off beer, wine, and appetizers and they have a pretty great selection too. 

here's what we tried:

half order nachos with tri tip- YUM! they are totally living up to the hype. piles of good chips with cheese and jalapeños, olives, tomatoes, and tons of meat. it was a very generous portion. unless you're sharing with 8 people I don't recommend the full size!

meat platter with tri tip, ribs, pulled pork, mac and cheese and corn bread...I got bites of everything and it was delicious. the corn bread was really tasty as well! they give you honey to drizzle all over it...heaven.

smoked tempeh sandwich with vegan mac and cheese- I didn't get to taste this one but our vegetarian friend said it was really tasty. it's cool that they cater to every kind of diet here. 

the service was really friendly and everyone we met was super attentive and kind. I honestly am looking forward to coming back here and trying more stuff on the menu! if you come for anything, get the tritip! that was my favorite...

11/24/17

No trip to New Orleans is complete without a meal at the Commander's Palace, the quintessential restaurant.

Here, excellence isn't just about food, but really about the entire experience from the moment you walk in the door until you walk out.  The servers attend to you with Southern grace, and every detail of your seating is to create that special ambiance and romance.

I will say that despite their best efforts, there were flaws.  For one, drinks took an eternity to come, and luckily arrived just before the first course.  Our dessert and nightcap drinks also took more than a 1/2hr to come!  And moving on to the food and drinks, clearly some are better than others...

1. Tequila Mockingbird 2 $13 "an original creation of Commanders... we liked this drink so much we named it twice. tequila and lemoncello combine to create a tart treat you so nice you'll order it twice":  Refreshing and very tart.  Smooth.  Good tasting though not complex.  7/10

2. Kessler Riesling 6oz $11.50

3. Garlic Bread (complimentary):  Soaked in butter.  Did not skimp on the garlic, and there's tons of spices and cheese.  7/10

4. Cast Iron Seared Redfish Cake $13 "blackened redfish cake with shaved winter vegetable salad, peppery argula & rum barrel hot sauce aioli":  Resembles a high-end crab cake, but substituting fish.  Soft, yet many textures including julienned vegetables.  Creamy consistency, with some horseradish. 8/10

5. Turtle Soup $8.50 "a Commander's classic finished tableside with dry sherry":  Can't come here and not get this.  Just do it.  No, it is not amazing tasting.  The turtle is really dry for one.  Though, that sherry does add quite a bit of complexity.  Well, just gotta try it.  7/10

6. Caramelized Pumpkin Salad $9.50 "Covey Rise Farm pumpkins with petite greens, Belgian endive, pecan tuile, brandy soaked grapes with artisan cheese and Satsuma-cane syrup vinaigrette":  Delicious!  Crisp vegetables against sweet pumpkin and fruit.  Love all the sweet crispy things on top too!  10/10

7. Pecan Crusted Gulf Fish $39 "a Commander's Palace classic with crushed corn cream, spiced pecans, petite herbs and prosecco poached Louisiana blue crab":  Well, I'd have to say, it's a ton better than I was expecting.  Often nut crusted fish just ends up with a dry and hard breading.  But in this case, they kept the pecans light, and was not offensive.  The sauce is a bit sweet and very rich.  The fish flesh was pretty good, but was just a tad tough and could stand to be cooked less.  8/10

8. South Louisiana Seafood Stew $36 "a rich seafood stew of Gulf fish, poached local oysters, wild white shrimp, a popcorn rice boudin cake, with a charred tomato-chili broth and roasted trinity garnish":  Well, I kinda object to the name--this wasn't a "stew" at all.  I mean, I guess they can say the sauce is a stew.  Anyway, the fish is savory with a crisp skin.  Some flavorful mysteries in there too.  Loved how perfectly the oysters were cooked, nearly raw but just enough, and ultra tender.  The oysters paired really well with the rest of the dish.  6/10

9. Sweet Potato Milk Punch $9.50 "we combine milk and vanilla to a perfect balance of creamy goodness. next, house-made spiced rum spiked with sweet potato is the kick you won't want to miss":  AWFUL.  Cannot taste of that sweet potato whatsoever.  Tastes pretty much like sugar and milk mixed with alcohol.  Perhaps a super watered-down egg nog?  2/10

10. Limoncello $5

11. Lally's Praline Parfait $8.50 "hand-crafted vanilla ice cream layered in an old fashioned parfait glass with candied pecans and sticky praline syrup, Lally Brennan's favorite dessert":  OH GOD... perhaps best sundae I've EVER had!?  So luscious.  That house-made ice cream is decadently luxurious, and paired with the pralines... heavenly!  10/10

12. Commander's Bread Pudding Souffle $9.50 "all the richness of Creole bread pudding whipped up into a light souffle, finished tableside with warm whiskey cream":  Hmm, this one is tough.  It's not really a "souffle."  More like bread pudding with meringue on top.  Really mushy bread pudding.  My gf didn't like it.  But personally it worked for me.  It was served really hot, and the sauce clearly had plenty of alcohol.  Most bread puddings are too... bready.  But I think this dessert made good use of the bread.  8/10

So, there were mishaps, and not everything was the best example of cooking.  But overall, it was a beautiful night at a very special restaurant.

5/5

#neworleans #creolecooking #gardendistrict

Super nice, super helpful. 
Allergy testing done and walked away with recommendations.  
Thanks Dr. Tubiolo

I enjoyed hearing famous Nashville celebrities tell me to keep my luggage with me at all times, and to watch out for strangers with strange bags.  I really enjoyed all the art as well when touring the terminals between flights.  Great atmosphere here, and plenty to keep you entertained during a layover.

Great little hole in the wall bar. Several pool tables, dart boards and even a small stage for live entertainment or karaoke. There's no food served here which means by law they allow smoking inside. Definitely takes you back to the days of old when you would come home smelling like an ash tray. Prices are decent and offer several shot specials for $2-3, even on Fri and Sat night. Because of its proximity and prices it definitely beats a lot of the other bars in the area but could stand to eliminate the indoor smoking or offer outdoor alternatives.

There ain't no f'ing way. I ordered a shrimp and oyster platter. The shrimp platter is 15 dollars. The oyster platter is 17 dollars. The 1/2 shrimp and 1/2 oyster platter is 24. WTF. Every other place in the city just charges you the more expensive of the two. I was not  expecting it to be 24. If you are going to charge me 24 dollars for fried shrimp, you should at least butterfly them. Danny and Clyde's does just as well for half the price.

To start with, I wish I had read the reviews, especially the one's about the customer service. 
We purchased (among other items) a dining table with 4 leather chairs. We only used this table/chairs a few times. 
Unfortunately three out of the four dining chairs had developed rips/tears on the seats. 
Like so many other dissatisfied customers, we were told that they would take care of the problem, but never came thru. They told us that the company they got the furniture from is out of business, BUT they would help us get to a satisfactory solution. 
We asked either to have them replaced or repaired. 
Unfortunately they did not do either. - the best they could do is sell us replacement chairs at their cost!!!!! (The offer was; chairs, that would cost more than we originally paid for the chairs!!!!) Of course we declined!!! what a sham!!!!
Neil the manager, was obviously not interested in a satisfied customer.

This fresh market is nice and clean. I like the most are the ready to eat food by pound. It make life a lot easy. When you walk in, it is timber like covering floor which make shopping like home. The first section is flower just reminds you do you have love one to buy the flowers for love or forgiveness. 

The ready to eat food just need to reheat or simply eat them. These food included scampi shrimp, preassemble sandwich, Korean salmon, and more. I like the coffee bean by weight. The wine selection is a bit less choice but good enough for the evening. 

Pastry is freshly made for your pickups. Many organic item in the fresh produce includes the veggies. The aisle is wide enough to maneuver your card. Most of the cart is a lot smaller with two layer of container.

First time here and it was pretty good! Right off the bat I was a little surprised that they do not bring out waters, you have to buy drinks from a cooler if you want one. Even asking for tap water, they do not give any. You must buy a bottled water. The food was pretty good! The loaded fries were tasty. But we had to ask for forks, I was surprised they expected us to use our hands for messy fries? But they gave us some and it was fine. The falafel gyro was good, but the falafels were a little hard. Still tasted good though! It's probably a popular take out place, and I would do that instead next time!
I got the Poke Tacos and Crazy 2 roll and neither one had much flavor. I would never spend money on this place again, waste of money.

Me and my family visited Bubblefish many times. It is a great place for sushi and bubble tea. The raw fish within the sushi and sashimi were very fresh and the drinks were refreshing. I think the sushi and drinks were, in my opinion, fairly priced. It was a comfortable and relaxing place to hang out. The waiters, waitresses, and the cashier was very nice. I like both sushi and bubble tea so that's a bonus.

It's definitely a place fit for these 5 stars!

We loved everything about Boulevard Burgers.  The food was very good, the drinks were great,  our server was prompt and helpful and the trumpet player was fantastic.  We loved the feel of the deck and the high tables.  The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars was the location is just ok.  The street wasn't  the most appealing ambiance but I guess that they did their best with the location.  We would recommend it and when back in St. Pete's beach, we would visit again!

If I'm ever having a bad day, this is the place I go to make it better. The waitresses are always so friendly, kind, and want to make sure everything is correct for you. The spicy fried rice with tofu is my go to dish, and has been consistently good every time I order it. The interior is pretty, and I can't stress enough how lovely the waitresses are. A very good Thai restaurant on the west side of Indy!

We ordered a drier and it was delivered Monday but was damaged when we finally got ahold of someone to see when a new one was going to be delivered it was set up for Wednesday of this week, Tuesday afternoon we get a call saying the delivery day had been changed to December 31. The drier was in but they were just backed up.  The delivery team that had the damaged drier told us Monday that since it was the stores fault that they would put us ahead of others and get it to is fast.  Now was are to wait 2 weeks?  Very poor customer service. The general manager wouldn't ever talk to us.

I've come here a few times most recently after some jerk decided they didn't know how to pull away from a parking area and destroyed the left side of my fender, at the park mind you. I dropped my car off Friday and they had my car back to me Monday morning. Which is great because I work 30 minutes from where I live and I have a son that needs to go to school, so needless to say I need my car back asap. It looks brand spanking new and I can only thank Michael and his dad for taking great care of me. I'd highly recommend them to anyone.

I asked that they leave my dog's hair long and just trim the face.  My dog received a cut made for the summer time, in the dead of winter.  It's ok, his hair will grow back.  Just need to keep him in jackets much more often.

Came here after hearing glowing recommendations from some locals while we were on vacation. Food and service definitely lived up to the hype! Try the pineapple Pickers vodka and the fries - you won't regret it
It has an awesome environment, high quality coffee, and good music. It is a lovely place. I will come back here again.

I love this place. I live in Columbus OH and we do not have a Yard House but I've been to the one in Cincinnati many time and now this location once and I've never been less then very satisfied!!! The food is great and if you like variety in beer this is your place. I recommend the Mac N Cheese. It's so good and I actually prefer the regular (with chicken) over the Lobster Mac. They also serve food late which is a huge bonus.

As far as Mexican food for the everyday gringo is concerned, Union Taco is the tits! I'm so happy they deliver to my place of employment, however their exorbitant prices mean I shall only order on payday. $5 for a singular taco is just silly.  Since I can't in good conscience pay that much for a taco, I opted for a chicken burrito. It was damn delicious, and well worth the $9. 
And the insistence of my coworker I also ordered the Mexican street corn. Also delicious! I've never had this delicacy before but it is very tasty.  Union Taco gives you a very nice portion (three corn hunks) for your $5. Definitely big enough to share. 
My delivery experience was most enjoyable and I certainly intend on dining in one of these days!

First time here and never coming back. Baristas loudly complained that 15 US Navy service men that came in this morning didn't tip. Then said they are glad they don't give military discounts because members of our service have an entitled attitude about receiving discounts. Then said "Fuck our country, honestly. Let us all die."

Never heard such open disrespect for the United States from an employee at any establishment. Sounds like the girls working at 12pm on 12/9 feel entitled to freedom and tips while disrespecting those who sacrifice their lives for our great country.

I live in Arizona and ordered from them over the phone to have 2 bottles of wine shipped to Ohio for my Mother in Law. I didn't receive an email about my order, shipping, charges.........nothing. I looked at my account online and it said pick up in Florida. What??? I called and the guy said "it's being shipped today". When I spoke with them to order, he even said someone at our hotel can sign and they have to be over 21. I told him I have no email of the order I placed or charges. He said they don't charge till it's shipped. My account said I was picking up in Florida but the employee said it was going out today. Which is it? I couldn't believe how disorganized this company is. I called another co and ordered from them and got an email within 10 minutes! I will give all of my business to the other company I ordered from from now on. And when I told him to cancel my order, he just said "ok". Not "what can we do to make it right", nothing. He just said ok. Wow!
