Walking through the Christkindlmarkt will definitely get you in the Christmas spirit! They have vendors, a skating rink and a performance stage nestled in Carmel City Center. There were about 35-40 boots selling food, German trinkets and Gluhwein. Gluhwein is a warm mulled wine. I'd definitely recommend getting some; it will warm you up on a cold night and at $5 a glass (or more if you want a souvenir glass), how can you say no! Walking through the market, sipping Gluhwein, watching people skate while listening to a band play Christmas music was a great way to spend an evening! 

I went on a Wednesday night and it not overly crowded. We waited in line for about 10 minutes to order dinner at the Joe's Butcher Shop Booth. There were not very many booths selling food. For next year, I'd recommend having less booths selling trinkets and more booths selling food. 

Christkindlmarkt is a great addition Carmel and the other holiday festivities around Indy! I'll definitely be coming back next year!

I had an issue with the order through the Pei Wei app but when I got there the store manager Martin quickly made things right while still in the middle of the lunch rush. Thanks for the great service....and the food is good too!
Reliably good tacos. Got a few and then dived into the free chips. Shredded beef and asada was good. Multiple sauces available and the handles of the ladies met you know how spicy the salsa is.

I come here for their trivia night on Wednesdays, which I mostly look forward to, except when I want to have a beer. I've taken to coming 15 minutes early, and it's still only about a 50% chance I actually get served at the bar before trivia starts... It's really frustrating, standing there as time ticks away, watching the bartender pass you by again and again.

On one such occasion (not the first, and not the last), I finally tried an 'excuse me' to get the bartender's attention... She took great offense at this, as she had been very focused on her phone at the time, and threatened not to serve me at all if I was going to be rude.

Seriously, that happened. Just like that.

But, I love trivia enough to put up with it. So joke's on me I guess.

This place is fantastic. Being a breakfast connoisseur and avid food critic, I happen to come across this Pancake House in the center of Indianapolis. As I walked in, I was greeted by a smile and the greeting of the day. I was then ushered away to my table by a nice young man named Dung Tran.  While we waited for our food, I noticed that all the workers were constantly walking around asking the patrons how their food was and even engaged in conversations. Not one worker was sitting down. 

Our waiter, Mr. Tran, was quick on his feet to get our drink order and even answered questions swiftly as if though he was the cook himself. 

Our food, even though it arrived quickly, was  lacking certain ingredients. Upon arrival at the table, our waiter, Mr. Tran, quickly recognized its deficiencies and apologized. Mr. Tran summoned the manager and the manager quickly corrected the problem. 

Even though I told the manager and waiter that nothing should be done, the manager insisted on giving my breakfast free and even came out with additional sausage patties.

I highly recommend this restaurant for any meal due to the service and professionalism of the workers and leadership who run this establishment. 

PS: the food is also pretty delicious!! (Country Lady Platter)

Outstanding atmosphere with an eclectic vibe.  The bar is fun and welcoming with the curved design encouraging conversation.  Despite a wide variety of upscale Southern Living style entree options ordered by our group, the food feedback the same: very average with unassuming flavor.  One note,  the server indicated there were no chicken entrees I the menu which was a disappointment to some. It would be a nice to catch a drink or appetizer around the bar.  The service at the bar and table are good.

TIP: If you enjoy Bern's steak tartare, you can order it here in a shorter dining experience.

My fiancé and I love coming here. We drive all the way from Philly to visit the Qmart and Video Bananza is one of the main reasons why. The selection is great. We are huge horror fans and we always find rare and obscure films that you don't see everywhere. We have always gotten superior service. The staff is knowledgeable and you can tell they love what they do. Highly recommend!

Don't waste your time going anywhere else. Great work at a fair price. Completed the work a day earlier than they said. Not a big job--just a hood repaint--but they treated me like I was in there for a $5,000 job. The paint job was perfect and the entire car looks new. They also did a lot of little things like cleaning the headlamps so they are now nice and clear, cleaning the car inside and even putting tire conditioner on the tires!  I drove away feeling great. Everyone is friendly and nice. Really -- this is the place if you need paint or body work. And NO, I don't work there! Just a very satisfied customer!

These brand new apartments are gorgeous and very conveniently located.  They used all high end finishes and really made the apartments feel like high end condos.  I ended up going with another property in the same area due to price but would definitely recommend the Hanover.  This part of North Broad is very safe and there is a lot of proposed development.
My wife and I love this place... Steaks are good service is great!! Definitely a once a month spot to visit!

One of the best things about St. Louis, IMHO. I was never really into calzones until I ate the food here. 

Fatty B - like a deliciously cheesy, meaty inside out pizza with twice the flavor. The red sauce (always on the side! Haha) adds a nice little spicy kick. 

The Duke - smoky chicken and bacon nicely offset with the sweetness of corn all wrapped up in a warm, hearty pocket of seasoned dough. 

Caesar salad - surprisingly enough, I have yet to find a better Caesar salad in this town. Like for reals. 

The calzones are all huge and I usually save half for another meal the following day. You're basically getting 2 meals for $10! 

Haven't dined in at this location, but I've gotten delivery from here plenty of times. Of note, it does take 45 min to 1 hour for delivery since calzones are made fresh and have to bake. They charge a small delivery fee of about $2 that's not a tip for the driver, but the food is so delicious that it's worth it. 

Phone service has always been very professional, and we've never had a wrong order after all this time. Delivery employees are super friendly too. 

There's no greater feeling than having a nice, hot calzone fresh out of the oven delivered to your door!

I ordered a pizza, wings, and breadsticks using the Yelp app Eat24 service. I got a call from Eat24 after 20 minutes to tell me that the order was sent to the store but that they were unable to reach the store for confirmation. I tried to call the store several times with no answer. An hour passed without being able to reach the store and no delivery before we cancelled the delivery.

If you cannot be bothered to answer the phone or make your to-go orders in the designated timeframe, don't offer delivery! Thanks for wasting my time, Zpizza.

A lot going on here!
From the street, Gran Caffe looks like a little cafe.  Inside, it's HUGE.  Bar, 2-level seating, gelatos, etc.....The day I had lunch, the place was packed (lots of office parties, I guess).  I had linguine with clam sauce, and my partner had a red crab sauce.  I would describe both dishes as good.  What surprised me was the small portions.  Like pasta is expensive???  I think their objective is to leave you hungry for one of their divine desserts or gelatos.  Well, it worked.  Gelato was lovely.  Only 3-star review, as I could have used another handful of pasta (and I am NOT a big eater!).

This spot is really an "order at the counter and then head somewhere else to eat" kind of place. It's small and gets very crowded easily but is reasonably fast. Bagels are big and yummy, but coffee is very average. I've only been here once and got the rainbow bagel with cream cheese, so pretty basic. They do have breakfast sandwich types of bagels.

Tiny little spot right near the train tracks in Elkins Park. Given the very high ratings, I was surprised it was empty when 2 of us walked in at 6 pm on a Saturday night. Although I think we both liked the overall experience, i would not recommend the clams as an appetizer. They were way over-salted and tiny.  The entrees were so much better: pork Marsala with perfectly steamed fresh broccoli and just enough mashed potatoes and covered with ample fresh sliced mushrooms (cooked) in a divine sauce. Veggie penne also excellent. Apple tart with a crumble topping served warm with a scoop of wonderful vanilla ice cream was a highlight. Great cappuccinos as well. Entrees were around $17. It is a byob. I would definitely go back and highly recommend but I would ask for low or no salting and I'd bring my own wine glasses because the ones they provide are large and clunky fake cut glass and are cumbersome and distracting (especially if you bring a nice bottle)

By the time we left a few more tables had been seated.

The food and pizza are really great.  Unfortunately they advertised two pizzas for $17.99 and afterwards charged us full price.
We tried to correct our bill and although they did make an adjustment the owner came to our table and admitted that the waitress was new and not trained properly. 
She went on and on about the cost of her dishwasher payment 
Should have just given our money back and said "Sorry". The above problems with the restaurant are not my concern

Tried Farm Burger while in town and it was good. It reminds me of BellyAcres in Memphis. Everything is local and fresh. I had the #5 which come with bacon, a fried egg, pepper jack cheese, and  salsa verde.  That paired with the Parmesan fries was delicious. My wife did the build your own lunch combo and she enjoyed it. Overall a really good experience!

Loved the sushi here! It was fresh and delicious and very reasonably priced. We tried every roll here except for the California roll and garlic roll. Great atmosphere and the wait staff were very attentive and food came out in a reasonable amount of time even though they were quite busy.

The worst service ever. We lease a home that the natural gas fireplace was not operating correctly. The landlord called, a gentleman came out, cleaned the pilot light area with a brush and left. The next morning we tried to enjoy what we thought was a working fireplace, and the repair was unsuccessful. We called the company to inform them of the same issue, and the lady who answered the phone stated that repair man was not even authorized to perform work on fireplaces. They send out another gentleman who stated a $213 part needed replaced, and said it was fixed. So here we sit waiting for a third gentleman to arrive to finally fix the issue. This is a company that continues to take your money............Wayne

Delicious authentic and bright! I Loved finding this little gem today. The menu was true Hawaiian and extensive. If you want a quick bite to eat then this is your stop with at the counter ordering and friendly welcoming staff! Fun!

This used to be one of my favorite places to eat. And I dont know if they switched owners or what but it has gone down hill. The food is still good but no nearly as good as it used to be. Also today when I stoped to get a salad the cashier asked me if I was Pregnant!!!! No I am not!! I dont even look it thank you! The old people need to come back and run it again.

Really hungover on this fine Sunday late morning/early afternoon and looking for something besides my typical greasy Mexican breakfast (my go-to). Hopped on Yelp and typed in "ramen". Now, Lee House does not have Ramen but they have some amazing Pho. We ordered online (through Yelp) and for $27 we were well on our way to receiving Pho Tai, Kung Pao Chicken, and Pho Dec Biet (I'm butchering this). They do not deliver to my area, even though it's Brandon, but we saved on the $3 delivery fee and got some fresh air! Walked in about half an hour after ordering and the woman was very confused and said they did not have any outstanding takeout orders. After a few minutes, we were able to clear this up that we had ordered online. About 10 minutes later, we were on our way with a ton of hot spicy food! I like that you can order the Kung Pao to your spiciness specifications - we went with Medium just to try it out. The to go Pho was packaged in three separate containers. One for the broth, one for the meat/noodles/onions, and one for the bean shoots and other fixings. The Kung Pao was a rather large portion that also came with white rice. For $27 we have several meal's worth of food, which is great. With so many great options in our area, we really need to get out and explore more and I'm very glad that Lee House made the cut! They have Thai, Chinese, and Vietnamese options so there is something for everyone. Looking forward to trying some dim sum next time!

Today I visited hair world at this location Iris Cedric the beautiful blonde African American woman and Peter they are absolutely fabulous they took very good care of me and hair world today I suggest everyone in East Nashville come to this location so they can take care of you too
Great atmosphere and service! Chicken wasn't my favorite but all the sides were delish. Definitely try the Mac n cheese and the chili!
I love this place! Great food and good service! The Cubans are the best and you can't beat the devil crab!
Great service and even picked me up and took me to my car when fixed everyone was polite and professional

How many times has this place changed ownership in the last year? It was fantastic and with each change of ownership it has gone downhill.
The food is much blander, the service is not good at all... even comes with a little attitude .
The restroom were out of order... both of them ... 
are you allowed to open with no restrooms?
This place was very delicious 2 or 3 owners ago..

My family and I have been to Tony's for several special occasions and it has never disappointed. I LOVE the pepperloin for dinner and the Asiago cheese dip for an appetizer. I love the $5 appetizer deal on Wednesday's, perfect for lunch or dinner with friends. It's a great place for dinner reservations in Alton. I have only had unpleasant service here one time and it was due to a bitchy waitress. Other than the one occasion, the service has always been great. I love the separate bar and dining areas as it makes the dining area feel more upscale and makes the bar area feel a little more casual.
I got their Linguini Alle Cozze and it was amazing! It was full of mussels and I asked to add shrimp and mushrooms. Really good authentic Italian food and will be back. Plus it's BYOB!!!!

Well that was a pretty sad experience. Service was fine, though that's not necessarily of much import. The ambiance was stuffy. I was surprised but it looked like a place built in the 90s to be avant garde. I ordered a Sazerac at the bar. I get that they didn't have any herbsaint, but really any anise liquer works fine. It's just a rinse, really. Anyway I ended up with a shaken ouzo/jack Daniels concoction that was more ouzo than whiskey. One sip and I was done. Anyway the food. That's what matters. I had the foie gras, which was fine but unmemorable. I can't really describe it, but it didn't have that melt in your mouth quality decent foie gras has. That was followed by overcooked smallish scallops served over a tasteless risotto.

This place is more expensive than good. Seems like the kind of place which stays busy by catering to locals pretending to be "in the know." Not worth the trip.

This is a trendy place and it can be tasty, but fewer points for cost and customer service. 

I've been a few times, and I agree everyone should experience it once. It's great how you get to pick your base, flavors, and mix-ins. When they turn on the science and the fog rolls over the counter - so cool!!!

Recommendations: professionalize staff. When they are not working on an order, they are very loud sometimes talking and laughing amongst themselves - loud enough it disrupts patrons who are sitting and trying to enjoy ice cream. 

Also: I asked for a cup of water. The dude asked me if I wanted the thimble-sized water cup or regular. I said regular. He filled it up. Began placing a lid on it. Then asked his co-worker if this costs money. She said yes and he began ringing it up. Like, what?!?!? I said no thanks, and he just didn't give it to me. Please teach your people to inform the customer of the prices on water, for crying out loud, and train them better.

I had my daughter's Sweet 16 there last night.  The atmosphere was amazing.  The food was delicious.  We had the Penne Alla Vodka, Chicken Fingers, French Fries (delish), Roast Beef and green beans. Everyone loved the food.  The manager Melissa was extremely attentive.  The Christmas decorations were beautiful.   We had looked at renting a banquet hall in Newtown Square and when I worked out the numbers it would have been $20 per kid and then I would have had to pay for the food and drinks. I highly recommend having an event there.

The worst chicken ever. Not fresh like they advertised .
Cooked in advance and flash fried to bring up to temp.
Can't believe restaurants like this are actually in business. No passion/no care in the world. The south side location went under and now everything is starting to make sense as to why. If I want reheated chicken then I can buy this at the grocery store for a fraction of the cost for probably a better product. Won't be going back there.

I caanot say enough great things about Levi and the entire staff at the Egg Connection.  Today I had the Chicken fried steak and it was outstanding.   We were a party of 7 and everyone raved about their meal.  I heard "the best eggs benedict ever" and "loved the Huevos Rancheros".  Used to come here in the 1990's when I lived by the U of A.  Now I will make the trip across town to enjoy the experience. Especially if Levi is our server.  Great place for a big group breakfast.

I received an in-home massage as a gift from my husband, such an appreciated gesture. Impact Wellness and Chris provided one of the best massages I've ever had. I especially enjoyed that I didn't have to drive anywhere, deal with traffic, worry about timing. That made the experience all the more relaxing.

Heard great things about this place. Went Christmas Eve and yes it was packed. We arrived 30 min before our scheduled reservation of 7:15pm and waited 40 minutes to get seated, no issues. We ordered two steaks and two salads to start. Waitress was okay, not very personable, but kept drinks filled. Salads came out immediately and were nothing special but good. Steaks came out 50 minutes after the salads. Got one apology very quickly. 50 minutes! The steaks were good but very salty. We saw several customers send theirs back to be recooked. We may give them another shot in the future but this was not a very good experience.

Had a great experience with the whole process from start to finish. Great people, hard working, great attention to detail. Would recommend to anyone looking for quality design/work/service. Even after the job was done I have called back with questions and given expert advice.
Nice clean environment. Good choice of sandwiches and toppings. They weren't as swift but that didn't take from the tasty food. On SLU campus so their a little more pricey than most but good.

Seriously need to work on customer service. Although we were greeted after walking up to the coffee register, both employees then turned away--one to go chat it up with people at the other side of the bar, and the other to tidy up the counters and get beers. 

When my friend finally ordered, the one employee AGAIN turned away and started doing menial tasks while I stood there waiting, trying to get anyone's attention. My friend went to the bathroom, came back, and I still hadn't been helped. She was finally given her order and then the employee turned away from me yet again, but my friend was able to get his attention to let me order. 

It's a shame because the chai latte was quite good--subtle and not overpowering. 

But I'm not going to stand at the register for 10+ mins, being ignored while the bar people get special treatment. Getting coffee should be a fairly quick process. 

(Also: there's no food. What gives?)

I did not like the mayonnaise they put on the burger. It made it taste too salty. The fries are great and they give you ranch. I ordered a Moscow Mule and they did not serve it in a copper cup as described but in a glass.  My fiancé had fish and chips and loved it. I might come back for a basket of fries and another Mule if served in the correct cup.

An early entrant into the microbrew trend, UC is now known far and wide, and for good reason.  The brewpub is large enough that you'll never have trouble getting a seat, but small enough to keep a neighborhood bar vibe.  Swing in, try a beer, get a growler, repeat.

As casual breakfast goes this is likely my favorite. I normally have the veggie breakfast burrito. It has eggs , cheese, green peppers, and onions. Great fresh taste. I'd likely add potatoes since I don't eat meat and more salsa. I also had a cake donut with chocolate. Taste very fresh and top 5 donuts in the area to me. 

The inside is nice and family friendly. The selection of donuts is wide as well as the menu. Very pleasant surprise in St. Ann. Staff was helpful enough. I'll continue to go for these items, maybe venture out.
Fortunatos has the best Italian food around!  We always get 2 calzones and an antipasto salad. The calzones are incredible!! The salad dressing is wonderful!!  You must try this place!!!
One of the best dinners I've ever had! We ate the Shrimp and Grits and Luke Cheeseburger.

Obsessed with this place. Food never disappoints. Don't overlook the homemade pop tarts either. YUM! Avocado toast, anything (cream cheese or breakfast or lunch sandwich) on a bagel is delish. I especially love and always buy a half lb of their Waldorf chicken salad every time I go. My favorite. Also love the classic coke bottles. I get a coke every time too :)

So.  You are reading a review of Chipotle?  Ok.  Well then, let me welcome you to the modern world.  I hope your slumber under that rock was peaceful.   We have internet now, and cell phones and Facebook!   We also have build your own assembly line food places.  

Chips toe is one of the best chains at doing the assembly line food.  It claims healthy and fresh and conscientious practices.   and it delivers some really great simple and reasonably priced quick serve Mexican food. 

This particular location isn't as big as others I have been in, but the outside patio is sizable and they have a good sized parking lot outside.  And if you are feeding a picky family this might be a good choice because of a number of other quick serves in the same center.  

Everything was band new, clean and the service was quick and efficient.   

And it's walking distance.  Well to my house at least.  I have no idea where your rock is located.

Enjoyed dinner here last night.  Wait staff was very knowledgeable and provided great recommendations for food and drink.  Gemelli and sausage in vodka tomato cream sauce was excellent.  Just an FYI, the bread is ridiculous.

Update 12/18/17 - had dinner again at Amerigo last trip to Nashville.  Another great meal with equally as good of service.  The wait staff is attentive, but not overbearing.  Nice atmosphere as well, really enjoy this place.

One of my favorite restaurants.   Great service and great food.   I had the Kobe beef sliders and fries.  Sliders were cooked perfectly with a bit of garlic aioli.   Fries lightly seasoned.   Very relaxed atmosphere.   I will return

CWAS cannot be missed! As both a meat and veggie lover, this is absolutely worth the adventure. Snag a res, this place is tight and crowded. Being from NJ, I find myself visiting philly quite often. I have visited CWAS this past September as well as Sept 2016 for a friend's birthday who is vegan. This is some place I would have never chosen on my own but I highly recommend this joint. 
Friendly and attentive staff, sweet environment and decor. If you get the chance to sit in the back sit away from the wall so you can see the cool screen playing old video clips. 
In my recent visits I have tried the Gin cocktails on special and fell in love. They use such awesome ingredients like ginger and rosemary and I enjoyed the creativeness. 
As it is tapas, we chose to order almost everything. Standouts were the Bucatini and meatballs and Korean fried tofu. I could have sworn it was meat! The Tofu was crisp, spicy and so flavorful, i could have ordered and eaten it all night long!  The zucchini crab cake sliders were tasty though I wish there was more filling it was too much bun! Try the Bao buns! They won't compare to some amazing one I've tried in Brooklyn, but hoisin sauce is great!

My son took me here for lunch, his favorite place! I ordered the broccoli and beef lunch platter and it was very Good! Usually the beef and broccoli is over cooked, but they did a great job! The pot stickers were okay, I had better! I kept my leftovers for my dinner at work tonight! Yes I would go back!!

I ordered the gyro sandwich.  I always love eating this at any restaurant that sells these.  This one sandwich was large.  I couldn't even close it.  If your a couple you could share this sandwich.  The sauce was good and so was the meat.  I enjoyed it very much.  Again these are just my opinions but feel free to try for yourself
Stop because I saw the place was packed.  Good reason - breakfast burrito was great and the service was quick and friendly.

We went in with a party of 18 for my daughter's birthday.  The burgers are great and so are the fries.  My wife loved the chicken skewers.  The manager said the skewers are marinated the night before in a garlic marinade so if you aren't a big fan of a lot of garlic, he said to order the buttermilk chicken skewers.
They even have a "Navy Seal" burger that has 4 patties.  It was listed for $25.00  My son-in-law was a big fan of the nachos.
The service was very friendly and despite the party being so large, Haley managed to deal with it and all the chaos that goes with it.  She always had a great smile and was attentive and accommodating.  
The manager came over, just to make sure we were happy.  Great place.
Be aware, it is a sports bar and can tend to be pretty noisy.  That sort of goes with being a sports bar.
I like the fact that it's vet-owned and they give military discount.

Love this place if you are looking great for true authentic Mexican this isn't it, but it is about as close as you get around here. Plus the atmosphere is fun. Nice place for a date night. Very good drinks. The food is delicious no complaints.

So, this is going to be my first Yelp review and I'm doing it because the staff was incredibly awesome and friendly! There's this really nice waitress who was on point with everything she did. I don't remember her name, cause I'm terrible at remembering names, but she's Venezuelan.. so, there's that. I'm Peruvian and it's very hard to find authentic Peruvian food, in Orlando. It's so happens that I was in Tampa and decided to check this place out. Best Lomo Saltado I've ever had in my life and it's enough to say that you can fight a war over it! I also had the House Chicha, which was great! It was missing some little chunks of apple, but that's a dealer's choice preference and up to your palette to decide. The atmosphere is very relaxed and fancy, which is an interesting combination; I enjoyed it! If you're Peruvian, this place will make your heart content!!

I've been to Bearcat about 3 times already and each time I loved it! The servers were so welcoming and nice! This is a great place for breakfast and lunch. They do have a vegetarian and vegan options under "Good Cat!" If you like meat, the "Bad Cat" is for you  my personal favorite for breakfast is the Bearcat Breakfast! It had two eggs (your preference of how it's cooked), bacon or bison sausage ( I chose bacon), and roasted potatoes. I add a blueberry pancake with the order for a $4 upcharge. The pancakes were delicious! You also have the option of paleo pancake too. 

Another favorite of mine is the Hot Chicken sandwich for lunch. It's very savory and decently spicy! My boyfriend got the Chicken Farro and he loved it! 8/10 in his book! 

Recommended drinks: the mango lemonade is my favorite :)

First time going there and staff is very nice but bathrooms were very run down there was tape holding up the sink also popcorn is stale and very little choice of candy (no junior mints, milk duds etc.) the screens are very big and they have reclining seats also assigned seating there ices are old tasting.

Came close to closing time and the two boys working still made us feel welcomed. We drove from New Jersey and my friends enjoyed your subs for the first time! We will be back soon ! Thanks again for a delicious meal and friendly service

So good!  They have the best ribsz and mac
and chesez  Line was out the door but it moves the flow quickly!

The best compliment I can give this restaurant comes from years of travel dining. Having had dinners at Per Se, French Laundry and a list of Michelin started restaurants. I would still choose a Catbird menu and intimate dining experience hands down EVERY SINGLE TIME.

Pretty solid spot located across the street from Arkane - perfect for a beer crawl kind of day. We stopped in after a trip at Arkane to grab some food. The Raven is partnered with Barley Mow Brewing so these are the brews they carry. The beer selection is small but solid and our bartender was very helpful. We ordered the meat lovers pizza and they let us sub the red sauce for garlic and olive oil which was a very good decision. We also had an order of the hot sauerkraut soup - phenomenal! I highly recommend this place if you're in the Largo/Clearwater area!  They have a parking lot and plenty of space inside with a large bar area equipped with TVs to watch the game and more traditional dining options. A brewery with food? I'm in!

So this isn't  a place I would sit down and do a full meal at because it's tapas. But I would come here and get a few plate and try a few things each time. The interior is so beautiful it's perfect for a date night. Perfect for a pre going out spot. The drinks here are amazing I can say that. The food here is pretty good too. Everything is vegan and everything was delicious. The brussle sprout dish was super. I will be back in the future to try more.

Our tourist stop of the morning! To start off, they only accept cash, i didnt see it posted anywhere until after we ordered and it was at the bottom of a small table top menu. Luckily I did have cash on me. 

Also this place looks packed all the time, but don't let it discourage you from waiting, the line goes very fast and there is lots of seating. The table turnover is very quick as you only have the beignets, coffee, and cafe-au-lait. My wait was less than 3 minutes.

The beignets are delicouse, soft, and crisp and the cafe-aa-lait was perfect. Very good, and well worth the calories.

We came here with a large group on Christmas Eve. It was surprisingly busy but we had a reservation and didn't have to wait.

I like the idea of all you can eat meat, but when you are eating it and dining here you generally feel terrible. The food is VERY salty, they say you can order no salt meat but you will have to wait. That doesn't seem worth it when you are here. Our waiter was clearly busy with other tables and we weren't drinking so its possible we weren't the most important group.

A few cuts of meat never made it to our area, we were sitting in a back room and its possible the filets with bacon don't make it that far. It is an experience for sure, but I think Fogo de Chao is the best at this game. 

The beef ribs might be the best thing they have, other than the Brazilian Cheese Rolls.
AMAZING!  A friend just brought a box of assorted pastries over to us... unreal!  Fresh, flavorful, just excellent!

Local family owned pizzeria for gigantic, delectable pizza pies. I'd recommend the buffalo chicken pizza which is absolutely delicious. For locals looking for a failproof cheat meal, this is your best pizza option in Cherry Hill.

Great place to dine , definitely recommend this place if you're in this area of Reno . Staff very friendly and polite. The ambiance is very nice also there are two dining areas which make it really cozy and the decor is very modern.

5 years ago my family and I stumbled on this place looking for somewhere to eat dinner after walking around the city for the holidays. We were beyond impressed with the food, so much so that it became a tradition to come here every year. All of the food is fresh and delicious and the roast pork sandwich is out of this world. The staff has always been very friendly. Over the years, my family has grown and this year we came in with a party of 9. We arrived around 3pm on a Saturday, December 2nd and it wasn't very crowded, however, the hostess was very rude and abrupt with us saying she didn't have a table big enough to accommodate us. There was a large table by the front window which she told us was reserved. We asked about combining two tables together like we did last year and she said that wasn't allowed. We asked how long of a wait it would be to seat us at the large table or if there was any other options and she said no and she couldn't give us a wait time. She was very rude and unaccommodating. Unfortunately this place lost out on our business that day and we won't be returning next year. If you have a large group I would not recommend going here.

Ordered for delivery and it came way faster than anticipated. The food was subpar. The sweet potato tots were ok, but tasted like they were under done. Didn't try the sauce that came with it.

I got the buffalo shrimp wrap and it was pretty bad. None of the ingredients were fresh and there was so much sauce that the entire thing was so soggy, it was hard to eat. Took two bites of the shrimp and it ended up making me sick. They're generous with portions, but quality of the food is terrible.

Came to get some fries, and the guy at that took our order and greeted us at the window gave amazing customer service. His name was Frisbie, and he told us a quality joke & made a quick yet quality conversation. This may be irrelevant to others reading reviews, If anyone even does, but it was just a really nice change of pace going through a fast food drive through and seeing someone that doesn't make it apparent they hate their life. I'd like to see that more often, fast food counts too  frisbie, if you're reading this- can't wait to hear your music!! Thanks for being a cool dude

Workers are extremely rude especially the older ladies. They act bothered by anything. I really dont enjoy shopping here because of the workers. Such a shame because they have good stuff. I prefer babies r us...sells the same stuff pretty much and are way more helpful.

I looked at buying a car at Glanzmann Subaru and their staff was extremely friendly and helpful, but they could not match a price that I had been offered by another Subaru dealer. After buying at the other dealer I returned once to Glanzmann for service. Again they were totally professional and I had no problem with the service they performed. However the accommodations for those waiting for service are sadly lacking. The waiting room is glass-walled and with the sun pouring in 15 people sat there shading their eyes unable to work with their laptops or to see the television screen because of the glare. There was no coffee or even hot water available during the two hours I was there on a Monday morning. Reading material was limited to two copies of The Inquirer. There were no facilities or space for mothers who might have to bring their children with them. From now on when possible I will seek service at another dealer a half-hour further from my home.

If you're looking for a good burger and fries, this is not the place. I would have expected a lot more from the Desi Vega's brand. 

For starters, the burger that we received was not what we ordered. We realized this quickly because our burger was supposed to have blue cheese and fried onions and the one we received had cheddar cheese and raw onions. Our waitress took it back to the kitchen. When she returned with what we thought was a new burger, it was simply a "remade" version of the first one. They added blue cheese and fried onions. So our burger was filled with onions and had way too much cheese. Unacceptable if you ask me. 

The fried pickles were so greasy I didn't even want to eat them. The French fries were not cooked well and the potatoes were so hard. 

Unfortunately, I won't be making a trip back here. Desi Vega's, you've got work to do with this location.

Arana falls squarely in the "not too bad" category, which is not really a rave review. Its hit or miss, and that's the problem. Their guac is yummy. Their chips warm and crisp. Nachos are good. Tortilla soup hits the spot. Drinks hit the mark of fruity, boozey and fun. 

But once you get deeper into the menu, the cracks become apparent. For starters, a lot of their tacos are just not that great. The spinach and mushroom taco was downright bad, greasy and paltry looking. The fried chicken taco was way more breading than chicken. The burritos are pretty forgettable. 

For happy hour, I'm happy to swing by and drink delicious half price margaritas accompanied by an appy or two. But I would never come here for dinner. 

And also their menus - yes, the physical paper menu itself - is truly tragic. Or as my friend said when we sat down and were handed menus, "This is sad." The menus are so old and worn down that they are LITERALLY illegible. They're so faded that you can't read what's printed. Not only that, but they're sticky and dirty. Honestly, a menu like that makes me suspect that management is not enforcing a clean environment and that the kitchen is quite likely filthy. I worked in food service for years, and wiping down the menus was part of the closing tasks that we did nightly. I doubt Arana ever wipes their menus. What they should do is THROW THOSE THINGS AWAY and order new, legible menus. I know this seems petty, but menus are the first thing a customer is handed when they sit down and a sticky, dirty, old menu makes me wary of the establishment in general and whats going on in the back of the house. Seems like such a simple thing to fix!!! Details people, details.

We happened to be Christmas shopping so we stopped in. We had a traditional pizza an a calzon. The food was good the waitress was nice but our drinks did go empty for a while. So I had to get my water to go.

I've eaten at all the Indian restaurants in the St. Louis area and this one is my favorite! Buffet items are always fresh and hot. Service is efficient and unobtrusive. We lunch here frequently and make the drive from downtown because it's just that reliably good. Solid choice!

Service: BVH has given good service and treated me fairly. There was an issue with a poorly done service. When I returned for warranty , MJ went over and above to remedy the problem. There has been a turnover of mechanics. That being said, the current crew, especially MJ and Darrell, are consummate pros. 
Sales: the inventory is excellent. BVH will price match if asked, but don't expect them to eat the tax!
New bike sales are low key. Do you really want to be swamped with high pressure 5 point close b.s.?

Great shop,
MarkinReno
I've seen a few movies here. The seats are pretty comfy and overall it's pretty nice. They offer a pretty good variety of snacks and drinks. The bathrooms are always clean too.
Thank you so much for stellar service! You guys have an amazing staff, amazing products, and amazing prices. My quartz countertop looks amazing!! You've got yourself a customer for life.

I would have used Uber on my trip but my parents insisted it is "unsafe". So, instead I got a driver calling people on the road "fat", got to the airport way too early because I had to share a ride (Uber Pool would have been half the cost), the driver was giving me shit at 3am for being from the state I'm from. He really just needed to talk less or be more tactful. 

I think this place needs to charge way less of they want to compete with Uber and Lift, especially if the service isn't great and there is no tracking of the driver's location on the way to pick up.

Great place for lunch for sure. Looks like they have a great butcher shop inside with fresh grass fed meat selection. Nice salad and other selections to have them heat up or take home. Cookies etc.  I've tried their brisket sandwich and tritip and pretty amazing. The best baked beans I've had anywhere!!!

Not really an outlet priced mall. More like an outdoor regular mall. Good selection of stores, decent food court choices, and very clean. 
I shop here, because there is not much else in the area, but if you are looking for cheaper outlet type prices, you will not find them here. 
There is ample parking, and it is easy to get in and out of the lot. 
All in all, nothing spectacular about this mall, but Ok for local shopping.

The space is gorgeous. I can't wait until it warms up and we can hang out in the courtyard. Beautiful moorish design throughout. We had the man'oushe with za'atar and cheese which was one of the staff's favorite as well. They are about 10" so enough for one person. It was full of flavor and very filling. I was satisfied with just this and a chai latte. It was pricy. 2 man'oushes and 2 coffees ran us $30. Unfortunately it's too expensive to frequent regularly, but we will definitely be back for a special treat. I can't wait to try their dinner service when it begins, and definitely  want to go back for the pastries!

I've passed by Spice Box quite often but had never stopped to try it. I've recently started eating a vegan diet and finding delicious vegan food for lunch during the work day can be challenging. The staff walked me through the menu options that would work for me and were extremely helpful in helping me find something I'd like. They even let me taste some of the rice to help make a decision. The food was ready very quick and it was absolutely delicious. I'm already looking forward to going back and would highly recommend anyone try them--especially if they are new to Indian cuisine.

If you are in the market for upgraded sound system. Tinted windows or security systems do yourself a favor and hit up the guys aty Divine sounds.   They have a premium selection of components.  They do a quick and excellent job. This is my third car and it's been an excellent experience.  They stand begging their work.  We had to get some adjustment done to the sound system and they were able to do so at no charge.

Everything about this place was disappointing. The service was horrible: the waitress was extremely condescending (Excuse me for not knowing what a cauliflower steak is), the table was dirty and she refused to wash it, the food was meh and portions were small and it was expensive. Oh and they didn't have ketchup for the fries that came with a $14 mediocre burger.
Amazing Cuban sandwiches and the pork is great too. This is one of our favorite places to eat Cuban food. It's a small place with big taste.

A wonderful business meal with a party of 11 this evening.  The staff was very attentive, the wine selection was wonderful, and the food was excellent.  We could not have asked for a better evening.  I highly recommend Caffe Aldo Lamberti.

I can't express how wonderful the employees are at Kendall. Rebecca and Nick are top notch! We were on vacation and had a run in with an animal. Damaged the molding and possible bent the condenser. Called on the Saturday before New Years. Not only did they help us out, got us in and out quickly with no charge, they were just awesome. Can't say enough about them. Thanks Kendall for having excellent employees. I would highly recommend this dealership!

First time customer, forever hooked on this place! 

We got the Campechano, which has both perfectly marinated carne asada and the marinated pork combined into a beautiful relationship of flavors.  And the Sonoran Burrito (oh so tasty). 

Ordered both BACON WRAPPED, yes, you read that correctly....Bacon.Wrapped!!  Just so mouth-watering good!

Per a Yelper Tip, we also ordered them with the Cream Cheese (excellent tip, just do it).

1 Star - just for the flavors and the sauces
1 Star - just for the Bacon Wrapped awesomeness (that's some next level shyte!!)
1 Star - for the mouth watering abundant avocado nestled in each burrito
1 Star - for the Size of them - people weren't kidding about how big they are (arm length)
1 Star - Excellent Customer Service - the gal who took our order was friendly, knowledgeable, and just plain adorable (keep her).

Just sad we don't have a place like this in our hometown.

I am going to comment mainly on my 1st and only visit here with a out of town friend of mine who comes to STL 1-2x a year for work trips. She let me pick a place near us both we would like but had not tried before. I took a gamble on this one among others but figured my Italian heritage would not let me down.....it did not!

A busy Monday night for sure. Place was hopping. I had no RSVP but got seated right away as my dining partner came just a bit after me. We got 2 glasses of red wine right away and then ordered from the totally awesome MACRO BOWL menu they have which is a intentionally healthy, macro counted, BYO bowl for the health nuts of the world like me who love to eat well and delicious when eating out. Kudos to Billy G's on this! 

We did 3 bowls. Two 6oz sirloin and one 4 oz sirloin. It was the perfect amount for 2 people as the helping of rice and veggie is a bit slim and we both felt a bit more veggie could be added to the dish to round it out a bit better. You can pick, chicken, sirloin, tuna or salmon as your meat and then brown, white or wild rice as your grain. All cost $12 accept tuna which is $14. You can do 4 oz 6 oz on each as well.

The service is great, friendly, never leaves you hanging and even joked with us when we asked for a picture, great guy but do not recall the name. 

Overall great experience and good food with good prices. From what we say coming out of the kitchen and passing the long table of people next to us, there is some seriously good eats to be had here!

They have HD TV's all over the place as well so you can catch the game as we did during dinner.

In Nashville for a couple days and Hattie Bs was highly recommend and advised to get there early as there is usually a very long line. We arrived an hour early and did not need to, but there was a line at 10:50 am. I would suggest to open maybe at 10 am, versus 11; Good hangover food. It is definitely a must if you are traveling to Nashville. Funny story; while waiting in my car for an hour, a group of guys walked up to the door around 10 am and a few of them fell to their knees in disappointment that it wasn't open yet!
I love love love Terakawa. It's my go to ramen spot. The juice is flavorful, the noodles are amazing, and the service is impeccable. 10/10 would recommend.

Really good donuts! Surprised that it tasted so good.  though I wouldn't recommend the Boston Creme if you're looking for the typical creme flavor but it's not bad.  The place is small and has a few places to sit.  Has coffee and tea to enjoy your donuts with.  Has some good unique flavored donuts.  Would recommend that you eat the right away or soon after purchasing.  The donuts will not taste as good later on if storing them for later.
The waitresses and waiters are perfect the food is great the music is great I love it. Its better than dominos pizza. Very polite people if their were 50 stars i would rate it 50.

Just ok food you find anywhere.  Nothing representing NewOrleans.   The desert bread pounding was at best Average.  

The wine list narrow and ultra pricey.  I would not recommend it given there are so many great restaurants in New Orleans

This is a nice addition to the neighborhood. This place literally moved a few doors down from its original location. Nice renovated.

Food taste is homemade vietnamese food. I had the pho here and it's pretty good. Bun no hue is good.

Staff is attentive and friendly.
Terrible service. Just get the cheapest one if you are just tryna get the snow salt off your car. They do a horrible job vacuuming.
Pretty good food, had it delivered through door dash but wasn't really a fan of the hash browns but overall real good food. Wish I photographed it before I ate it , but I was too hungry.
Mega store has all your sporting needs! I go there for all my outdoor gear from biking to skiing to Headbands! Staff is friendly and Knowledgeable. Sporty Spice Approved!!
My first time at Cracker Barrel, and I really liked it. The food was good, and I could not believe how inexpensive it was.  Our waitress was very sweet and attentive

First off, I'll have to admit to having a bias since my wife and I frequent their sister restaurant in Maple Shade called Yokohama. That said, Tuna Bar is a tremendously hip new addition to the Philadelphia restaurant scene. The food is of excellent quality and presentation, while the restaurant is chic with a New York City vibe. 

I actually ate there two nights in a row so that I could get a true taste of the cuisine.  The Wok Kampachi Ceviche was excellent but my favorite was the Scallop Crudo.  You should try Grandmom's Wonton Soup, which is a creative new rendition of the old time favorite that I highly recommend.  I even had my favorite roll, the Sindy roll, which I eat at the Maple Shade location. It was delicious as usual. 

Though Tuna Bar may borrow some rolls from the Yokohama menu, make no mistake, the food at Tuna Bar is original, upscale, and very creative.  The menu is evolving as it is perfected, and getting better by the day.

I had my wedding party's hair and makeup done at this salon last week on Black Friday. The salon accommodated my bridal party and paid special attention to my self, my mom, and my sweet little flower girl. Karla did my hair and makeup. She is the most talented cosmetologist i have ever known. My hair stayed all night and looked great. My makeup looked stellar despite the wind and 100s of cheek kisses from guests all day. They came in early to accommodate us, brought us snacks and mimosas, and were just all around great. The customer service there was very impressive! All the girls looked great and were very pleased :)

Tyler was VERY helpful when I went in to ask him about a problem I was having installing a new heating element in our 38 year old (!) Kenmore dryer. Within minutes, he solved the whole problem! I went home to put the finishing touches on fixing our dryer and it is once again drying our clothes perfectly. Thank you, Tyler!!!

This is a wonderful theater very clean very new awesome seating full leather recliners in every theater good concessions including alcohol Gastropub attached only issue is no rewards for MoviePass members

I had the Chicago style and was more than pleased.  This was hands down the best Chicago style pizza I have ever had, the sauce and sausage were excellent.  Small cozy dining area, nice big bar in the room next to it.  Excellent selection of bottled and draft beer.  Super waite staff.  The house salad was nothing special.  The Chicago style takes 45 minutes, order ahead or enjoy and beer and the person you are with.  I am excited to return and try the thin crust and New York style.  Parking in the rear, beer garden out front.

Cool Quality is a great company and will always provide you top notch A/C service.  Whenever we have needed an honest assessment of what's going on with our A/C ,I know we can count on Lawrence to recommend what is in our best interest. His customer service is great and he will always go above and beyond to make sure you are a happy customer.  It can be hard to find people you trust but you and your AC will be in great hands with cool quality!!

Ewww!!! I used to go to this location all the time, the staff was always friendly and I could count on it being good. There was also usually always an employee cleaning. However, after the experience I had today, I certainly won't be returning. The place was filthy. Food all over the window in front of where you order, food all over the floor, and food on almost every single table. I bit into my taco and thought it tasted weird, then looked and discovered that the chicken was dark meat with skin on it. Wtf happened to this place? I'm really disappointed. Please fix this store, no place where food is eaten should be this disgusting.
Just ate here, with my wife, for the first time. Chilled at the bar, had a beer, and ate some pizza. Great service and good times!

What an experience! 

My wife and I went on a busy Friday night and staff was overwhelming helpful in both getting us seated and guiding us through a perfect meal. 

I have celiac and the kitchen was amazingly accommodating. 

We had a great time, and even more, a great meal. We will absolutely be going back many times.

I love the cooking classes!  I went by myself the first time not knowing what to expect. I learned some new techniques as well how to improve or be flexible around the recipes, made some new friends and had a great meal at the end.  It was so much fun I've taken my friends with me to other classes, some friends that would typically never go to a cooking class loved it too!  Chef Nikki clearly knows her stuff and cares about your experience.  We've already signed up for more classes in the future. If you are looking to learn and have some fun at the same time - this is the place for you!  
PS.  If you get a chance to try the chicken & waffles from The Heat food truck - do it!  So good!

Been coming here since I was a little girl and they have amazing Greek food. The food gets 5 stars, but service brings the overall rating down to a 3. A year ago I went in with my mom and we ordered a Greek salad for two. A waitress immediately interrupted my mother and I and asked us if we were sure we wanted the bigger salad because the two of us probably could not finish it. At first I was taken aback by such a comment as it is not the waitresses/waiters job to tell me what I should and should not order. However, it never happened before so I didn't make a big deal out of it. All was well, until I went back again with my mother yesterday. Like always, we ordered a Greek salad for two. I proceeded to continue with my order and as I was stating I wanted a chicken souvlaki, the waiter didn't even let me finish before he said well if you are going to order more food maybe you shouldn't get the bigger salad. It'll be too much for you two to finish. Okay, are you kidding me? Is this a rule in this place? A rule that says you need to tell customers how much food is enough? This isn't alcohol we're talking about, you can't cut me off of food. The salad is not even big when split between two people. It is disrespectful that the waiters and waitresses are even making suggestions like that. It is rude, and mind you I'm paying for a bigger salad rather than a small one. Larger bill=larger tip. Better service=better tip. Simple as that. If I get asked this one more time, I might be convinced that it is a rule to tell people how much food is enough in this place. 

P.S. some people enjoy leftovers.

Jewel in the Garden department at the Powell Avenue store was a huge help.  Went out of her way to find what I needed.  She's a Jewel!  If all Home depot employees were like Jewel, they would be the best and most popular store in the country.

Wow. Belly buster breakfasts for great prices. Steak and eggs stood out but pancakes were fantastic. No one cleared their plates even though we all shared. Everything I tasted was yummy and didn't break the bank. Service was great and food came out quickly
This place is great! Bowling, pool, great beer great food and beautiful bartenders/waitresses what more could you ask for?

I really like the idea of the Christkindlmarkt but I don't think it was executed that well this year. The wine was good but I was disappointed they didn't have anymore souvenir cups. The market itself was fun to look around but there wasn't enough to make a day of it. I saw everything I needed to in about an hour and it was a 45 minute drive to get there, from the south side.

I think adding more seating and adding more booths to the area would have made it more enjoyable. I loved the IChe skating rink in the middle, I think it made a great focal pointe. 

Parking wasn't as bad as I thought it would be and the lines weren't that bad for a Sunday afternoon. 

I hope they continue to host this event and work on adjusting it because I think it can be an awesome event !
Best gelato I've ever had and I'm the biggest gelato/froyo/ice cream snob. Seriously the best consistency and flavors!

We had the burrito pazon with asado( steak) and my husband had also the tacos asado , I dont considered them authentic Mexican for me it's Americanized but it better then other places. It was really good and filling. The horchata was not good tasted that it was made out of powdered horchata

Friar Tuck came to my rescue. I was on a search for a particular Bloody Mary mix and they had it. When I recently went to Washington, MO for a day trip I discovered, Tony's Sweet Heat Bloody Mary Mix. I wanted to add it to a gift box I was creating for someone and really wanted to avoid having to make the trip back to Wash MO to buy another bottle. 

Oh, did I mention Tony's is a local brand? It is, it is......Fenton, MO. 

I visited Tony's website and found out who carried it locally. I tried to buy it from small local shops, but they were all out (tells me how good it is), so I had to buy it from a BIG chain. However, I will say the price was $2 lower then what I paid in Washington, MO. Also, I was surprised by the attentiveness and friendliness of sales associates assisting on the floor. 
The cashier was even a pleasant asset to the store. 

Will I return? - They rescued me once, I bet they do it again. 

When: December 13, 2017
Why: On a Mission

I will start with saying the service was ok. I got the steak special with butter and herb topping. The steak was not medium , and I can live with a little overcooked. But it was grey with almost no discernable grilling, no doubt it was microwaved. No crust at all. No flavor. The 1$ long island iced teas were the draw, they were decent, but you could tell you were on a stipend. I know it's cheap, but they don't take any pride in their food. Go for the 1$ long islands, eat somewhere else.

Still new to the area, but found this place and it reminds me a bit of Home (I'm from Seattle). The food is DELICIOUS, and you can taste how "real" it is as compared to something like Panera. So far I've had the grilled cheese with tomato soup, and the southwestern style chicken salad, and a chocolate croissant! Would recommend them to anyone! Quiet, and out of the way, I'm planning on this being my new study spot!

Eight of us enjoyed our evening before the Garth Brooks concert on Saturday the 16th of December. Our food was awesome. Everything was completely fresh. No freezers or microwaves in this restaurant. We were visited by the general manager to make sure everything was to our satisfaction. We don't go downtown too much. But when we do, it will be to this place.

(This is pretty much copy and pasted from my Washington Square West review, but with the addition of one more sandwich and a comment on the interior)

Great quick lunch, not so much dinner. This review is based solely on sandwiches. I've had the:
* Testarossa: thinly sliced roast pork, pancetta, Claudio's sharp provolone, roasted long hots, and pepperoncini aioli
* Italian Stallion: fennel salami, genoa salami, sweet coppa, Claudio's sharp provolone, house-made sweet pickled peppers & onions, and pepperoncini aioli
* Roman Cavalry: Coppa ham, hand-made fresh mozzarella, arugula, olive oil, aged balsamic vinegar

This place is ideal for people who work nearby and want a quick, tasty lunch. I would not recommend coming here for dinner because they don't pack the sandwiches with ingredients. 

The Italian Stallion: This is not the best Italian hoagie in the city, but it's the best in center city (and if you don't have time nor want to go down to South Philly). There isn't (at least the two times I've had this sandwich) very much meat on it. Claudio's sharp provolone is better than regular supermarket or deli provolone, but it's not that impressive, so I don't know why they're making a big deal and telling everyone that's where it's from. It always tastes fresh, so it's better than getting an Italian hoagie from the Wawa down the block...

The Testarossa: This is not the place to go for a roast pork sandwich. Again, there isn't very much meat, although it is still quite tasty, and the aioli adds a nice touch that other places specializing in roast pork do not. The pepperoncini aioli is my favorite thing, and I wish they sold it separately in bottles. 

The Roman Calvary: This is basically an arugula sandwich. I've had it twice, the second with extra meat ($2 extra). The first time (regular amount of meat), it was basically one slice of coppa with a mountain of arugula. The second time (with extra), it was only two slices of coppa, and there wasn't even mozzarella on it. I'm glad I paid $2 for one slice of meat but no cheese... Just stay away from the Roman Cavalry unless you really like arugula with one slice of meat.

The rolls (Liscio's) have tasted fresh the three times I've had Matt & Marie's, and having it toasted adds a nice crunch (highly recommended, although they don't usually ask if you want it toasted, so you might have to request it).

The verdict? If you don't have much time, and you live/work nearby, come here. If you have a lot of time, you're better off going to Reading Terminal or the Italian Market. I'm going to continue coming here for lunch because the Italian Stallion and Testarossa are great (and I plan to try others), but I won't be getting the Roman Cavalry again.
Food here is amazing. The broth in the pho is delicious. It is a small place however always packed with people but the wait time is short.

I go to Frankie & Johnny's quite a bit and I've always enjoyed my meals here.  Their menu offers something for everyone.  I tend to stick with a cup of gumbo and one of the fried seafood platters.  Their special dipping sauce is awesome, so be sure to ask for it if you get fried seafood.

It gets pretty crazy around here during crawfish season.  They're one of the few places on this side of town where you can always find crawfish when they are in season.  You will have to go earlier in the day rather than later because they do run out sometimes.

They can be a bit abrasive on the phone depending on who answers; especially if you call during peak hours on a Friday or Saturday evening.
I like this store, but beware. You cannot return something for a refund, only store credit. It IS overpriced, but the choices are few in Santa Barbara.

I love watching Maneet Chauhan on Chopped so was looking forward to this restaurant. It didn't disappoint. Everything that we ordered was phenomenal and the drinks were on point. I wish this restaurant was in Charlotte. Love the southern twist to traditional Indian flare! Must try!

I woke up on a Sunday morning with a pipe in my basement that burst.  After I turned off the water is called Horizon services since they advertised they are available 24/7.  I spoke to Laura first and gave her the nature of the problem but also included a kitchen sink that had a drain issue (I am already paying for a dispatcher so why not get the drain handled too).  I was transferred to Stephanie who promptly told me TUESDAY between 4 and 8. I stated the problem again advising her I had no water because of the broken pipe.  Apparently she only thought it was a kitchen sink.  She told me to hold and got back on the phone with a TUESDAY between 4 and 8.  Clearly I couldn't go two more days without water and a family.  Very very disappointing response.  The next time I hear a commercial for this company it will remind me of my bad experience and prompt me to tell my story again and again to family and friends.

Mihail is EXCELLENT!  He is very fair and honest, professional and courteous, prompt and efficient.  He showed up as promised, assessed my hot water heater, and gave me fair and honest feedback. This is very refreshing.  He understood that our family needed our hot water heater repaired but advised me that he would and could not leave the heater on as it would not be safe.  I and my family thank him for his honesty and any other services I need in the future, I will be calling him.  If you want someone to come and do repairs for you, Mihail is the person you should call.  Honest, fair, and hardworking.  I am truly happy I found Mihail.

I have yet to find a Mexican restaurant in the U.S that I would term "authentic" until going to Lola's.  Quite simply the best tacos and sopes I've had in the U.S. (and as good as any I've had in Mexico).  It is a simple menu, not dissimilar to a taco stand in Mexico, with limited choices but that which they serve is done exceptionally well.  Even the agua de jamaica (basically hibiscus flower tea with sugar) was a fresh and delicious compliment to the tacos.

This has got to be the worst Whole Foods in the country. Yesterday was the last straw, was treated very rudely by staff at the deli counter. I dealt with the dirtiness and lack of certain items because its a little closer than having to drive up oracle but never coming to this location again. Management needs a serious makeover.

I can virtually see the glow of Thai Chef's sign from my driveway, but I've never had an opportunity to try it. When my neighbor suggested ordering takeout from here, I was so excited to have my chance. 

Their menu can be found online, and it's pretty extensive and what you'd expect from a good Thai place - various noodles, rice, and curries. I had a little debacle about what to order, because it honestly all sounded so good. I settled on the drunken noodles, and I was not disappointed. It was a huge amount of food, and it was DELICIOUS. Like, I-burned-my-mouth-because-I-was-too-hungry-to-wait-for-it-to-cool delicious. Had I any self-control, I probably could have saved some for second dinner, but I didn't. It comes with chicken, and I would stick with it that way. I don't think I would have enjoyed it as much with a different meat. My friend ordered Duck Pad Thai. The duck was delicious - crispy, flavorful skin. We were both thrilled with our order.

Safe to say, I can't wait to eat from here again. Maybe next time I'll opt for dine-in, as the vibe is super cute and cozy. Ideal for a quaint dinner out, with private tables separated by curtains in a dimly lit, quiet setting. However, I enjoyed my food just as well on the couch in front of wheel of fortune. Whatever suits your fancy, give Thai Chef and Noodle Fusion a try.

I was so pleased to get authentic middle eastern food. I had the lamb shish kebab platter. I also had the cucumber lemonade! The lamb was grilled perfectly. The spice was delightful. A wonderful salad side with a grilled tomato and pepper was also served. The hummus was perfect. The lemonade was as refreshing as it was tasty. The saffron rice was on point. I will be returning to dine regularly. This is a culinary delight.

First time visiting  Blok & Co.  I ordered the  Vanilla Latte w/ Almond Milk.  OMG, hands down the best coffee in Boise.  I didn't even know it was possible to get such a creamy texture from Almond Milk.  I wish i lived closer so i could make it a daily event... will have to settle for regular visits.  Keep up the great work Blok!

PS.  While waiting for our coffee they brought us two slices of Banana Cream Pie on the house, very delicious.

We stayed here overnight, just from 9pm at night to 5am in the morning to catch a flight. The shuttle driver was nice and the rooms were clean and big with ample cable. I don't know what else to say...

This place is fantastic! Went here for my birthday and got the Tandoori Chicken Poutine as an appetizer and it disappeared within seconds. I got the Kashmiri Spiced Braised Lamb Shank and was in heaven after the first bite. I tried my friend's dish, which was the Malabari Seafood Cioppino, and it was also fantastic. Highly recommend! I am already planning my next trip back.
Pretty eclectic and creative but delicious. Uncomfortable seating, crowded and loud. It feels too trendy. Like it's trying too hard. Price is also rather expensive.

After a fun filled day in Philadelphia I wanted to get a chicken cheesesteak for the two hour drive back home. So my fiancé and I stopped at Ishkabibble's because they had good reviews. Boy was I disappointed my chicken cheesesteak was dry, the bread was not fresh and I pulled out several chicken gristles eating the first half. The chicken wasn't seasoned and wasn't worth taking a picture of. I will not be returning to this location for cheesesteak.

Is it a good sign when you look at your recent activity, see a place you checked in at, and go, "what the hell is THAT? Was I there?" I had to go look at the pictures to remind myself of my forgettable experience here. While running errands late one night, the misses and I found ourselves looking for something to nosh on. She, being on a healthy kick, wanted no parts of Wendys, and me, for the absolute life of me not understanding how Chic-Fil-A has become the freakin' Studio 54 of fast food spots, having a line, WRAPPING AROUND THE BUILDING, AT EVERY HOUR OF EVERY DAY, we wound up taking a drive over to.....Bobby Chez. After missing THEM closing by about 8 minutes, we FINALLY decided; wait; resigned ourselves to the fact that our only option was, B. Good. Full disclosure, I can't stand these artisanal, free range, gluten free, kumbaya, BURGER joints. Its a BURGER. Its SUPPOSED to be fattening and messy, and delicious. I don't need lettuce that was grown in a temperature controlled field and read poetry every Tuesday by an Amish grandmother. And sweet potato fries can go straight to hell. Having my tomatoes being given honorary degrees from Johns Hopkins is just a way to charge me $12 for a burger. Ugh. ANYWAY, we go in to order and I swear to god there was even talk of just HER getting something here and then going somewhere ELSE for ME to get something edible, but I decided to take one for the team. We order and then go sit down to wait for everything. They call "Matt," but apparently the ONLY other person in the store was also named Matt, so they pump faked me on even giving me food. When they called MY Matt, they had me come get half of my food, as they forgot my wifes sweet potato fries (ugh.) They promised to bring them out and we decide to eat in the mean time. I forgot what she got, and had to just now go check their menu online to remember what I got, which was the El Guapo, but the only thing I DO remember about the food was the the "natural ketchup" was naturally nasty. I'm even willing to concede that I am just accustomed to regular, sugar laden ketchup, but it was a jarring change that I didn't particularly care for. Whatever.

Long story short, I personally won't be back. If you like to pay a premium to have the flavor taken out of your comfort food, heres your place. It wasn't HORRIBLE, or even BAD, but it wasn't anything to write home about.

Best lobster and chargrilled oysters in town!  You have to eat at Dragos.  Worth a cab ride from the quarter.  I know there is one at the Hyatt but this location is the original and I find it to be a better experience.

My favorite place to go eat right down the apartment. It's a mix of new American influences with southeast Indian cuisine. Came for brunch once and had to come for dinner again. You can have a choice of traditional Indian curry cuisines with choice of protein or pick a few dishes from the appetizer section to share with all. Must try the tandoori chicken poutine for dinner! For brunch everything so good! The naan with different chutney and spiced butter spread is great starter for all. You can ask for extra naan too! Friendly staff,  very nice atmosphere, and phenomenal food.

The Erin Rose is awesome but I wasn't a huge fan of Killer Poboys.

The shrimp poboy was good. The shrimp was plump and well cooked and accompanied by a fresh carrot/daikon mix and delicious aoli. The root veggies and aoli are cold though and while I understand it is to add texture and a crispness but instead it is startling and distracts from the warm shrimp.

The braised beef poboy was disappointing. I'm a big believer in finishing my plate but I couldn't finish this poboy. The beef was so dry and there was no sauce to help choke down the sandwich.
The sweet potato fries here are bomb. I have tried the vegan bowl which was kind of bland tbh but I love the vegan option and there's a lot of great toppings. Sweet place to stop when doing the loop.

Good little find. Ordered many items off the menu to try , including the fried fish and fried chicken, the pork belly with rice noodles, and cold sesame noodle dish, and the sweet and sour pork. I'd say the pork belly and noodles was too rich as an entire meal but it was still really tasty. The cold sesame noodles and sweet and sour pork were my favorite and I'd highly recommend. Lots of other good-looking menu items that I will definitely be back to try. Other people's dishes in the restaurant looked great too.

Every so often, I remember to visit Dalessandro's on a visit to Philly. And I am never disappointed with the great steak sub, the down to earth atmosphere, and the general joy of the place......it's all about sitting at a counter with your hands wrapped around the freshest hoagie roll ever and trying not to lose any of those little meat bits as you aim the whole of it into your face.

The Tucson branch of the BBB clearly misses the mark as far as being helpful and honest in dealing with local merchants.  I have submitted complaints several times only to find the BBB unwilling or unable to engage.  Example: when Precision Door left a garage door installation partially completed, BBB contacted them.  Precision stated they would follow up with me, which they did not do.  After receiving another bill from Precision, I followed up with BBB explaining that Precision was continuing to bill me for the complete job yet had not finished the work BBB had been told they would do.  BBB then told me I was on my own.  Some help.  In another instance, I contacted them when I found out the AC company I was dealing with had installed a more expensive AC system than called for by manipulating their Manual J computation rather than using the mechanical engineering firms computations.  So, I spent unnecessary money on an oversized unit, which incidentally is less efficient than a properly sized one, and got virtually the same result from BBB.  So, my assessment is that the local BBB is toothless and not worth the effort to correspond with.

Best tacos I've had in a long time! This will now be my go to taco place when I'm craving Mexican food. The prices can't be beat and whether you get the seasoned beef, chicken, or steak tacos they are all the same price. My wife got the burrito and it was huge and was presented very well! We will definitely be back and I've even told some friends that we will need to go!
Good location and breakfast, but could use updating. The front desk are not very friendly.  Do not use valet parking, but find a parking garage several blocks away for half the price.

I really wanted to like this place since it's so close to my house.
Lucky for me, I really did like it a lot. The decorator needs to get mad props for turning the space into a light and warm environment  It's a slight step from being too fancy but stops just in time. Brilliant.
We stopped for a coffee and the people could not have been nicer.

Now, the thing for me is if I go to a coffee shop, I expect the coffee to actually be good. Their coffee does not disappoint. Rich and robust without being bitter or burned.

I look forward to going back.

Two things I'd like them to change though...bring in hot soups for the cold months and be open on weekends.
Delicious menu, beautiful atmosphere and amazing waitstaff. Very clean and did I mention how wonderful the food is! The owner is an amazing man and we enjoy this place immensely!
This place is awesome!! Authentic food at a great price.  We try to come here once week, its the best.

This was one of the most expensive dinners we have had in St. Louis, and I was expecting better:
- We should have been warned that the salad dressing was spicy hot, more suitable to a Mexican burrito than a steakhouse salad
- The plates had undulating edges, so my knife and fork kept falling off and landing on the table
- I ordered the deep-fried lobster, which was breaded. Each bite tasted like melted butter and breading....with a slight hint of lobster flavor
- The lobster and prawns were sitting on a bed of matchstick potatoes, so my food kept slipping and sliding as I tried to cut it
- I had to say "Please don't take my plate, I am still eating" twice
- Surprisingly, my two dining companions ordered steaks and were asked how they wanted them cooked.  Both steaks came out cooked more than requested
- After spending nearly $300 on dinner, we definitely felt rushed to vacate our table
- However, the onion rings were the best I have had in St. Louis

They were out of so many things. We had to change our order and then we had to change it once more when we drove up to the next window because they discovered they were out of that as well.....but at least the woman was nice about the situation and apologized. I wouldn't hesitate to return here since this was my first time.

What a great surprise. I stopped in here as Vintage and El Vez were crazy full for the holidays. An amazing selection of vegetarian options. The highlight of the night was the punch. Perfect for the holidays, light and refreshing, with a hint of green apple and cloves. It was like a light mulled wine. Yummy! I'd go back anytime.

The deals of products are great. Ill defintely remember these names to avoid them. But the cashier I dealt with was not customer service oriented. She had a customer in front me she was dealing with and took at least a good 5 mins of them about limit of buying a product etc... So when she checked me out she didn't say sorry about the wait. Then the check out reciept guy is not friendly either. He said hi to the lady in front of me, but when he checked my reciept he just threw the ad catalog n that's it.  Well it's a Shame, no wonder people like self check out, you don't have to deal with  them. You can tell by going to Costco they take pride of customer service. Sams Hire good quality employees not those who just thinks there just to their get a pay check.
