There is at least one cat on the property and no where is that advertised online when you book. I'm allergic to cats. That's a bad unhappy situation waiting to happen. The owners said the cat doesn't stay inside at night but guess who I saw at night chilling on the couch in the common area--the cat. Family run, but they acted like it was their first day running the business and they were gruff and anxious. Breakfast was good at least, French cuisine with a side of cat hair. I cancelled all subsequent bookings and went to stay at another place.

Went to look at a 10 oz bar of silver I saw online,the guy told me it would be $167 or about that. Said my goodbyes and went home. 
  The next week I decided to go and purchase it. This time the lady behind the counter told me her boss said it would be $260 for it. I just smiled and walked away. 
 Why would I want to pay $10 over the value.

A few of us came for a few cocktails and meals for happy hour/dinner. We did not have reservations but they got us right in at 7pm. We were sat almost immediately and were soon greeted by our waiter and someone to fill our glasses. 

 Their wine specials were incredible ($5/glass) for happy hour, and they had a large array. I essentially liked their wine list because it wasn't too extensive, but I still felt like I had an impressive number of choices. 

When I went to order - I asked if anything could be made vegan - and the waiter said "absolutely nothing" thankfully he was kidding, and HOOKED US UP. For our meal, we decided to share 5 plates (we needed to order 2 more after the 5th dish came out) and all of which were delicious. My favorite dish was definitely the flat bread with mushrooms. I mean, can you go wrong with some carbs?

After everything was said and done our bill came out to $125 so I was almost floored at that price. We left satisfied and tipsy so I couldn't have asked for anything better.

This was our "go-to" place for many years, but over the past two years we have noticed a real decline in service. At times, the server was outstanding, food arrive at right temperature and all at once and any side dishes or condiments arrived either before the food and right with food so we didn't have to wait to eat until everything was there.  Other times we have and the server was horrible.  Some dishes were right temperature but others at the table were cold or had sat warming until dried out. It really wearing on our loyalty. Either we get great service or terrible service, not worth the drama anymore but the food is good.  Noticed they change "Managers" like people change underwear.  From what I read in the paper, people are not complaining here but with their feet.

Come for the latte and specialty drinks if you're around the neighborhood. They serve only breakfast and lunch. We came here for brunch and ordered: fisherman omelet, hangover hash, and sombrero frittata. They overcooked the eggs as we wanted over-easy for the hangover hash, but the spicy siracha mayo complemented the dish full of sausages and potatoes to add a little flavor. Sombrero frittata didn't amaze me since it has avocados mixed into it and a side of toast that was a like biscotti. The dish was pretty bland and I was expecting avocado slices. Fisherman omelet was a nice portioned meal but a little seasoning would be great my friend asked if it had came with toast, the waiter said yes, but none was served.

The food here is excellent but the service was horrible today. We had to ask for coffee refills and sugar but the worst was my granddaughter wanted to get a pastry and the woman at the counter was on the phone with her back to us she never turned around acknowledged us or offered to get some help. We had to go to the hostess stand to ask for help then the girl was pissy and we ended up leaving without our pastries. Sunday morning they certainly should know how to staff. Too bad because they do have good food but so do alot of other places in Cherry Hill

We've used Izzy Pop for about 2 years now.   I was very nervous as my dogs were used to at home grooming or mobile grooming and I wasn't sure about them spending the day with so many other dogs.   But we took the challenge and they absolutely love it.   It is as much as a play day for the dogs as it is a day for them to get beautiful.   And when my older dog had to have surgery, Rita was very accommodating getting her bathed on short notice before the surgery.  Izzy Pop has been a very positive experience for me and the dogs.

In Chicago or Toronto this is a 1 or 2 star joint but here it's 4 stars.

Why? Because in Chicago or Toronto there are enough Chinese people so that the restaurant doesn't have to pander to non-Chinese people's taste buds. Here they don't have that option and have to be given a pass.

The food is not bad but is sometimes overly salty and overly sweet to suit the tastes of locals. There's no delicacy that you would find in the previously mentioned Chicago or Toronto, but it is what it is.

This place is still better than the countless pizza, burger ("gourmet" burgers), and brewpubs they have in Carmel. Keep it open.

I've been going to this office since 1997 and I have never had a problem ever I mean that ... that's why I keep going there. I had a lapse for three years ( just healthy I guess ) and went this past week. I'm still so very upset by what happened I can't stop thinking about it. Dr.O was fabulous by the way I did meet with her and she was aces. 
So I go because my finger was infected for two weeks the nurse practitioner initially was wonderful and I thought omg this is really nice. I had to get these fmla papers signed because my work did not want me in work ( I work with food ) and told me to stay out a few weeks. Well I don't know what happened between the first visit ( which was wonderful and why I gave it 2 stars plus she DID sign my fmla papers and gave me more antibiotics for my finger ) of this I can't complain. But the 2nd visit she was very wary of signing these fmla papers ( and believe me my work makes it sooo easy they knew I've been having a lot of problems ) I didn't want to delude her with all the problems I had been having ok let me get to the issue that upset me to no end - she becomes so visibly upset about these fmla papers that I was also having severe eye problems I tell her my eyes have been hurting and then she goes from being pretty nice to just out and out treating me like I'm some dirt bag trying to get out of work. I've been working full time for over 30 years I work hard and right now I seem to be running into a lot of physical issues I'm almost 50 I mean it's bound to happen. So again she did sign the papers but after running out of the room like she was on fire and telling me "oh yeah If you're really in pain call me " yeah ok, 
so my eyes are hurting so bad I call an eye specialist and they tell me I have a problem that's going to need LIFELONG treatment that the front lens of my eyes are actually damaged. The eye doctor said most gps tend not to notice this issue but she could have at said maybe see an eye doctor and not been SO concerned about these fmla papers that she took me out of work for literally 3 days 
It was just frustrating I felt embarrassed and I have to find a new gp I LOVED this place for many years since 1997 I've been going !!! They helped me through many things and I've always loved the staff there and the surrounding staff seemed ok it's just this one nurse practitioner should realize that some people are hard working people who like myself have developed a lot of physical issues and I'm trying my best to chip away at them one at a time NOT be looked down on.
The Swedish meatballs and chocolate chunk cookie skillet were incredible. Makes me wish I lived closer... Love this place!!!

An interesting spot. Love the interior. It was a bit loud. The waiter was nice. The menu had a lot of different options. The food didn't fall into one category. Which I loved. Ended up getting the chili and cornbread which was very delicious

The agnolotti with mushroom filling is the bomb...so good!  Had this with the spinach salad (plenty to split between two diners) and walked away very, very happy.  This was a first visit; surely it won't be the last.

The sushi was very well made! Delicious!!! I would def recommend this place for lunch or dinner! 
I will be returning.

After we got our food, we were SO surprised to see this place had 2 stars. The shrimp tacos are flavorful and the steak and cheese sandwich is AMAZING. The bartender is also so friendly, and accommodating. This place hands down deserves more than 5 stars..... 20x better than any of the 3 restaurants we tried in the French quarter.

Any closer to Mass Ave and you'd have to learn how to spell Massachusetts Avenue anytime you needed to give your address. 

I've lived at Circa for about a year and a half. The first unit I had was a bit noisy.. these were built fast and there isn't concrete between the floors, so if you're on a lower floor, you might hear your neighbors a bit. It wasn't bad, but once I found the historic lofts above the office and gym, I moved and never looked back. 

Most of the people who live here are in their Wo's and 30's, but there's a mix of those of us who are older. The pool is nice and relaxing during the week with a lot of people who work from home, and then it gets a little busier on the weekends with people relaxing and having a good time. We've also got a nice fire pit, gas grills and pet friendly grassy areas. 

The complex was recently purchased by another company, but the new group seems just as friendly and inviting as the previous staff. Activities geared towards residents happen on a regular basis, and the front desk staff has always been as friendly as can be when I've stopped by.

I had been wanting to try this place for a while, ever since I passed by it one day. Fast forward to Sunday, we were looking for a quick place to grab brunch and I suggested we try Southgate. We were able to find street parking nearby for free . When we got inside we were immediately seated and were able to identify several menu items that looked really yummy  the prices were all pretty decent (a meal and a mimosa will run you about $20). When the food came out everything tasted great (the fries are AMAZING). And last but certainly not least, our server Dan was super attentive and helpful. Overall it's a nice option for a casual weekend brunch if you're not trying to do a boozy brunch but still want a little booze.
definately great for sure and myself will come here again.it is essentially fresh and having good taste. the sushi here can be counted in. will recommend my friend come here.
Great Bloody Mary's and interesting food selections. Plentiful servings. Good coffee and even better servers.
The best sandwich in Boise accompanied by the worst XM Radio selection in Boise. My tastebuds danced. My ears bled.

I had lunch there yesterday. This is my sixth visit. Will not be my last but I was very disappointed. Last week I ordered the same sandwich and it was so good I thought I would get it again. Turkey, Avocado Pesto, bacon. Delicious. Well, they changed the bread. I could barely bite thru it. They did not have any avocados, they cut the turkey in half, hardly any pesto on the bread. I was not happy. I ordered the potato soup as my side and got turkey noodle. The waitress did bring me the correct soup. It was like water with big chucks of potatoes in it. No flavor at all. Now my two other visits I had the cabbage salad with chicken that is so good. I also tried two different breakfasts and they were amazing. I am hoping they are going thru growing pains and will get the bugs out of their systems. This restaurant is close to my house and it has good food, great staff and a beautiful atmosphere. I am so glad they opened up in Garden City and I want them to do well. I had a Christmas Party there for 15 ladies and they reserved tables for me and were very patient and did a great job with our crowd.
Definitely a good go to burger place. The chicken stew they currently have though.... OMFG! YUM!!
We tried this place while we were in town and really liked all the food. We ordered the burger and wings. You can't go wrong eating here! The staff was very nice and helpful with the menu!

First. Let me say that I love Moriarty's; and I refer a lot of hotel guests there. My husband and I especially like to sit at the bar and have lunch. We have always had very exceptional service by Rachel.

This review is not about Moriarty's but about the extremely rude bartender today named Jennifer. I have never been spoken to in such a rude manner. I sat for lunch and ordered an iced tea (that alone is probably what gave her the attitude). When I politely asked about one of the posted specials, she barked at me that I would have to wait until she could go over all the specials with me. Then muttered under her breath "like I know them off the top of my head". Well Jennifer, if you were any kind of a service professional, you would know the two specials off the top of your head. I paid for the iced tea, didn't touch it, and went across the street for lunch.
I'll definitely go back, just not when this woman is working.

If you're searching for a cheesesteak, John's Roast Pork is the place to find one. We were in town for my wife's work, and during my great cheesesteak tour of 2017, this was a must try. I'm very glad that we stopped here. We grabbed a Lyft over here, and our driver confirmed that John's was the best.

We got in the long line (which moves very quickly) and ordered our sandwiches from John himself. In a short while, we got our sandwiches. I ordered the Cheesesteak with mushrooms, and it was delicious. We ended up sitting outside, which wasn't so bad, because the weather was nice. 

The other popular sandwich there, is the namesake, the roast pork sandwich. It comes with broccolini, and is next on my list of sandwiches to try from here. 

If you're in the area and need a cheesesteak, go here. I will echo the other reviewers that this is the best cheesesteak in Philly.

I live right down the street from this Wendy's but I'm not coming back here again.  I stood in line for about 5 min.  When it was my turn, I stood at the register for another solid 2 minutes with NO acknowledgement.  At least 4 different employees walked by me behind the counter (ie answering the phone, interacting with the other register, going to and from the kitchen, etc...).  I was the only person in line at the counter at this point.  The employees weren't necessarily rude but I was just invisible.

Man, oh man. Had it not been for the great service and the beet and onion salad, I wouldn't have given them any stars. The mac and cheese tasted and looked like it was straight out of a box. The chef salad had sliced American cheese as a topping and the roast beef smelled really funky. The only good things were the beet and onion salad, that marinade was spectacular and the candied yams were good, can't really mess those up. Definitely not visiting again.

NOT what we expected at all.  We had reservations for Christmas Eve.  We got seated right away, with no menus.  Sat for a while until some girl came and asked to take our drink order.  I asked her if we could get menus.  She left.  Waiter came back and said he would get us menus as soon as they were available.  Tried to take our order.  I told him we had NO idea what we wanted.  I asked for an artichoke from the happy hour menu on the table and he simply said "we don't have that".  I asked for a menu again.  A few minutes later he came racing by our table and dropped off a bottle with with items.  He came back and asked for our order.  I told him a small filet and he looked at my husband.  We were confused so I asked what it came with.  He, again, simply stated "rice" and that was it.  
Rice was gross, salad bar was pretty good (could use more items) and the steak was FABULOUS!!!  Steak bites were good too.  We ended up getting a baked potato that was probably the best I've had. 
Overall, it was a mediocre experience.  We probably won't go back until they get more clear on the menu and offer other sides, not just the gross rice.
I was happy that Brad was able to provide his services on short notice. He was very professional every step of the way and we were very pleased with the job he did on our car. Thanks again Brad!

I love coming here for lunch on the way home from El Capitan canyon campground. It's quick healthy and delicious. The hardest thing about this place is NOT getting dessert because the cakes all are as good as they look!! And they look fabulous.

I really like Parc. It is a safe bet. Their bread basket is to die for - my favorite is the one with raisins! Yum!
During my most recent visit I had the french onion soup. It is good, but I think it is a bit overrated. I think the soup lacks a bit of flavor by itself. The cheese is pretty good, tough. 
I had the steak au poivre. I asked for it to be medium and they got it perfectly. It comes with spinach. I love spinach so I liked it! I had a side of fries too that were delicious! Very thin and crispy. 
I didn't have dessert, but they make a good cappuccino!
Also, I forgot to mention this place has an electric car charger! You'd never have expected it, because it took me by surprise!
The food was delicious and the service was amazing. Managers were constantly asking customer if everything was good. Our waitress Ashley was also very attentive and knowledgeable.

Such amazing food!!!! We have always enjoyed the stand at City Market & just found out about the fountain square location. Went for dinner this week and were not disappointed. We started with the Seitan High Fives, which were amazingly delicious & fried to perfection & tossed in our chosen sauce of BBQ. Our party also got the seitan bahn mi, with juicy seitan marinated just right; the tofu rich girl (the orderer of this sandwich wished it had more sauce) and the country style seitan (omg! How do they make that gravy taste just like gravy?!?!) which was fantastically, magically comforting and I want to eat it every day. Our service was great. I really think this is one of the best restaurants - and hooray for vegans; what a welcome and delicious refuge this place is.
Great shop! Great latte! Great vibe! Nice baristas! Def coming back. Particularly like the patio out back. W large fans it wasn't too hot out there.

We had a Wonderful evening last Saturday. They had an open mic with wonderful musicians!!! From Jeff on Classical guitar to Kyla on piano - original  music! The food & service was GREAT ! Bacon wrapped peppers, humas, on & on... wow! Check it out !! Hope they have more live music!!
This place is great! I always sleep well after a cryo treatment and Todd is a super chiropractor as well. I highly recommend it!
Stopped in for a takeout latte- almond milk decaf. If was well-made and frothy. The shop also sells local crafts. There are snacks and bottled beverages too.

Admittedly the 4th star is more for the environment than the actual coffee--although the actual coffee was definitely strong and packed a punch, caffeine-wise. I dig the interior of this place--it has an upstairs loft and woodsy feel, was playing really good music, and during the week, I wanted to find a different spot to work from, and this did the trick. I have driven past on the weekend to always see the place packed, but I think during a weekday, space here is more manageable. Always stoked to find good coffee places in town!

Hands down the BEST car buying experience I have ever had.  I was able to work a deal via the phone with no hassle and walk in and sign papers.  In and out in under 30 minutes with no issues whatsoever.  Amy and Brian were a pleasure to work with, I highly recommend this dealership to anyone looking!!

I've heard great reviews about the food here, so I was eager to try some of their menu. We ordered the candied bacon and the sausage and kale dip. The bacon was cold and too sweet, but the dip was awesome! The ambiance was real casual and mellow, the perfect place to just sit with friends, have some drinks and eat.

Best place to get juice in Nashville. I drive past here everyday and stop in often to grab a juice. The staff is always for attentive and helpful, and they always answer my questions. The price for the juice is a little expensive, but the quality is worth paying for. 

Also, they have a punch card system... so if you buy ten juices, you get one free. It's a great incentive to keep coming in!

I now understand why this place has 4.5 stars, which is far more than just about any Italian eatery. I picked up food to-go, and it still managed to be super hot & delicious! It was even packaged well with saran wrap so it didn't spill. The portions are huge, so I'm looking forward to having my other half for lunch tomorrow. The sauce is sweet and dark like I love! And they had brucioloni! A) That's hard to find and B) Gendusa's is the bomb! It's so tender, garlicy, and completely hit the spot. We lived in Kenner & moved about 15 minutes away & never knew this gem existed til we found it on Yelp. Wish we had known about it when we were even closer, but we'll be back. Open on Sunday til late, gelato & cappuccino, AND the food is amazing. Yes yes yes!!

Skull's was a suggestion by our tour guide 'Big E' who gave the best nighttime monster truck tour of Nashville, more on that in a different review.

It has a lot of nostalgia attached so that was the primary reason we wanted to be sure to check it out. But the bride to be also was interested in checking out the burlesque show so it was a win/win for the entire group!

We were staying right around the corner so we went over to Skulls quite early in the evening and were able to avoid the cover charge which was great (but for $20 cover it is still worth the visit). We had checked for reservations the day before but nothing was available so we had decided to hang out near the bar area. On a whim we asked the hostess if a table was somehow available and there was! They said that as long as we ordered food we could have the table as long as we liked which was amazing. The server was sweet and attentive as was the rest of the staff so it was a great experience. Now for the food rundown:

Crawfish risotto - Yum! well seasoned and perfectly cooked it was a great risotto
Tuna Tar Tar - this came with homemade potato chips and the tuna was great quality
Beef Carpaccio - Awesome beed carpaccio almost as good as some I've had in Barcelone!
Boeuf En Croute - this was a bit dry but was tasty, not my favorite
Chef's featured fish (branzino) - one of my favorite branzinos! It came off the bone and was crispy and salty and just so tasty!

Now on to the burlesque show - the girls did a wonderful job and were just so sweet when we met them after. It was a fun and lively atmosphere and a great experience. And out of the 400,000 bands we saw over 2.5 days this was a great, talented group - we even recognized the drummer from a bluegrass band we saw a few hours earlier at Robert's, he cleans up NICE.

Overall for the service and prices Scull's was a wonderful experience and I would make sure to check it out!

We stopped by for a quick lunch and ordered a classic and the Depot burger, we asked specifically that they be rare, the classic came in closer to medium, and Depot burger had no pink at all, why is it so hard to make a rare burger. Any way the food was good, the grilled onions we're awesome. Our waitress was great and the over cook burger was removed from our bill with an apology. Talk about being a stand up place, we will go again and most likely recommend.

Very good food served fast and friendly,   Meal was hot and beer cold like it should be.  It's in the station so weather effects room temperature it's 18 outside so it's cool in side the station.   Would rather not watch CNN (Fake News) or NFL but little story telling is good to laugh at.  I would eat here again if passing through on train. Had the philly streak, fries very very good very good. Cost with a Philadelphia pale ale (bottle) $20.82

I met up with a group of co workers for a couple of beers and ended up finding a gem of a place! Amazing beer selection and the food menu looked delicious. (I'll be back for food next time!) the staff was extremely friendly and attentive. I thought that being in Seminole Heights parking would've been an issue but there's a huge lot across the street designated for parking for their place. I only wish I lived closer or maybe they can open another location closer to Sarasota?! (Wishful thinking)

I was told the Chef James Malaby worked with/under George Perrier.  I recently moved to the area and had to try it. I'm not sure what I was expecting, but I can tell you I was completely disappointed in the atmosphere. There was zero ambience. It was drafty and cold. The lighting was terrible as it was way too bright. There as no background music.  Looking around, I couldn't tell what this place was trying to be. Is it a diner?   For the atmosphere and the quality of the food, it was WAY over priced. Not what I expected at all. 

I get that there aren't many quality restaurants in the area, so some folks who don't get to Philly much, might think the food was good. For a gourmet Chef, like Malaby, the food was a disappointment.  There is a need for a really good high-end, hip spot for those of us that appreciate great food AND good atmosphere.  Blueplate had the potential to delivery that vibe, yet failed.  I couldn't wait to leave. Unfortunate.

First, this location needs more professional staff. Popped in after doing some Christmas shopping for a sandwich to take home and your employees have an atrocious attitude problem. fwhen I came in at 9:48 they looked puzzled to someone ordering food? Your restaurant is still opened right? You should be able to make orders? CORRET! 

Secondly, let's talk about the inappropriate behind the scenes talk of the employees here. Like can you not save that kind of talk for when everyone is gone. 

Lastly, this is a sincere frustration I've been using your restaurant chain frequently for catering at different locations all over Indiana INCLUDING this one. It was nice to walk into the restaurant and see what exactly the employees do. And how they act. I will strongly reconsider this location for my Community North Hospital lunches.

Great customer service! The staff was short handed but was as efficient as possible and dealt with each customer with care, including us! Shannon and Rolando were both fantastic and super sweet people. Their work ethic and ability to interact with customers should be notably mentioned. Thank you, both! Now we will be customers at this branch from here on in.

Froyo, check
Self-serve, check
Complimentary tasting, check
Tons of toppings, check

As far as froyo goes, Whirled Peace certainly hits many of the prerequisites, but it lacks some of the final pieces to hit a 4-5 star review. The flavors are decent, but very limited (I think only 6 were available) and the cost per oz is one of the highest I've seen in quite some time. My favorite will always been original, but I was kinda disappointed by the peanut butter flavor and definitely not a big fan of the chocolate one, as it tasted much more synthetic than I would have liked.

Food: 3 stars
Price: 2 stars
Free tasting: 4 stars

I was looking for a local IR sauna after moving to the area and even though they don't have a shower in the room, there are plenty of other reasons to sauna here. The new client specials and Axxess deals are unbeatable and I appreciated the cold towel with essential oil of your choice. There's everything you need in the room - water, towels, robe, music, lighting, entertainment; I almost forgot there wasn't a shower. The staff was incredibly kind and made the experience easy, comfortable and very relaxing. Thanks Daisy!
Delicious crepes. We had the Mont Blanc Crepe which had the most amazing cream sauce. Paired with a peppermint white chocolate mocha and I left more than satisfied. Fantastic!

Popped in for dinner after our "Mall Santa" experience and we were not disappointed. Hubby ordered the Ciopinno, I ordered the steamers and we got a Margarita Pizza for the tiny human. Ciopinno and Steamers were spot on! The pizza was good, but they do serve it on a different type of crust (I apologize for not knowing, but I was not concerned with the crust when ordering) that I was not used to, but mini me didn't mind one bit. You could tell the ingredients were fresh and as we ate the place continued to fill up. 
   Our server was a very pleasant man with a sense of humor we understood. Charlotte, the other server who came on the floor about mid way through our meal, was absolutely amazing! She might have a great thing for little humans, and that's ok with us. Charlotte cartered to our little peanut and made her (and us) feel special. 
  We shall return again soon M3. We'll done.

Gave this location a try, all though the Burger of the day was not all that great but good. It was the Amazing French Fries that I loved! They were cooked and seasoned just right and it was a true delight.

Just spent thousands of dollars and the last four years of my life at Belmont only to find out they don't give a shit about me or anyone else. The only reason they got one star is because Yelp wouldn't post this review without one.

Update (4/25/18): 

I was asked to elaborate, so I sent that person the following: 

Part of the reason I choose to get my education at Belmont was because upon visiting campus it was advertised as a "student-centered" university. This may be true in terms of class sizes and staff to student ratio (13:1)- I can confidently say that I had great relationships with my professors and they were always available and willing help with just about anything. However, Bob Fisher and his administration (whom I call his puppets) just want your money and could care less about you as a student. This became apparent to me as a student leader on campus when anything I did just seemed to be pushed back on by the administration, and unfortunately the advisors of the student organizations I served were to scared to stand up for us. As an example, read this short blog written by the SGA President when we was "tired" of not being listened to:
 
http://belmontsga.org/president/2017/2/8/im-tired-of-being-tired

Pay attention to the last line in the last paragraph to understand why I said that advisors of student organizations are afraid to stand up for us. 

As for myself, I did not serve on SGA, but I did serve on the Interfraternity Council. About halfway through my term our rules for Rush were dramatically changed and the fraternities were not happy about it. See here: 

https://www.tennessean.com/story/news/education/2017/05/05/belmont-wants-fraternities-admit-all-eligible-students-they-arent-happy/101306300/

Because we wanted to exist on campus, we knew we had to comply, but we wanted to have an open dialogue and figure out a system that worked for everyone. Unfortunately, the man who would make the ultimate decision (Bob Fisher) refused to speak with us. He would direct us to lower administration members who didn't have answers because what they were saying "came from above." 

Overall, I got a great education from Belmont. I would just love to see some change in leadership so the students are able to exercise their voices. I guess thats just what you get at a private university where your first amendment rights are inapplicable...

Excellent service, excellent food!!! This was my first time at the Collingswood location. I have frequented the Philadelphia locations several times. This location is, by far, my favorite. It's spacious which is different than the other locations. Our server was super friendly and even brought a bowl of boiling hot water so that I could warm my daughter's bottle. We will definitely returning in the near future.

SHORT REVIEW: Meet here. Drink here. Chat here. Work here. Eat (light bites) here. VISIT THIS PLACE.

LONG REVIEW:
I give it 4.5 stars, the knick just due to the nature of worrying about your parking meter while you relax in this place for awhile.

THE STORY:
I love exploring. Driving around the city with my eyes peeled for new spots, watching IBJ for the new real estate deals...it's all fascinating. Armed with intel, I ventured out to HoiTEA ToiTEA because I deserved a break that day.

WHAT'S IT LIKE IN THERE?
-- The first thing you should notice is that this place is clean and refreshing. Simple to navigate, bright, airy, and contemporary. The layout is part retail store/part cafe ala Starbucks. I love the mashup of being able to buy relevant items to the purpose of the storefront I'm in. With a variety of seating areas-and even a private room-your work/chat space should be a part of the conversation just as much as having one. I approve.

WHAT DID I EAT? 
-- Not much, as they're focus is TEA (hence the name), but WOAH. Their chocolate chip cookies are so splendid (TIP: ask for it warmed up). Your taste buds will come running to thank me. They offer lite bites, but their selection of teas and other drinks is fancy, broad, and declicioso!

Ordered tofu Bahn mi and the bbq pork bahn mi. Carrots and daikon need to marinate in the vinegar spiced water longer and the pork shouldn't be as "fatty" and cut into smaller bites. The heat from the jalapeño was on point and the tofu was seasoned well. May try it again.
It is amazing here.  Food is unbelievable no matter what we order. So yummy from the homemade hummus to the chicken shishkabob, so good. And the baklava for dessert is to die for.

Great pizza! We started with pepperoni beignets! Light pastry with cheese pepperoni and a little red sauce. We got the desperado pizza. Ham, pineapple, onion, cheese, jalapeños, and red sauce! It comes with a New York style crust. Really good. Good ambiance-showing Rocky3 on the wall, playing Led Zeppelin for tunes. In a converted warehouse. Prices reasonable. Highly recommend!!

This review is just for happy hour. EDIT: and lunch! 

Happy hour is from 4-7 so if you get out of work early or have the day off definitely arrive early. It's 4:30pm now on a Thursday and there is plenty of room at the bar but I have walked by other times and it was packed.

$3 high life's all day! $4 domestics, $5 wines, $8 citywide.

We tried the fries, garlic parmesan wings, and sliders. Sliders came with a generous pickle and were delicious. Boyfriend said wings were okay. Fries were amazing with the smoked gouda cheese were so good. Did not try the brussels sprouts because we are doing a bang bang and going to eat more at our next location.

Overall, a solid early happy hour. Would recommend bringing a sweater or two if it's cold out because the windows seem to take all the heat away.

EDIT: Stopped in for lunch on 1/25. I made a reservation on Open Table because it's Restaurant Week and I thought it might be busy (not because they participated, but from overflow). They were not busy at all! We got there right at noon and I think we were the only table. The service was slow, though we did choose a table upstairs completely out of eyesight. I ordered the Quack n Cheese which is one of the best macs I have had in my life (duck, dried cherries, scallions, and mushrooms with big shell pasta). My lunch dates ordered the Beet Sandwich and the Burger sans cheese and they both agreed that their lunches were also amazing. Being upstairs, the temperature was perfect. Definitely will be back for lunch here in the future!

I want to have to come back and update my review, and I'm optimistic that will be the case.

Pros:
Absolutely gorgeous location. I would host any event in their space and I really look forward to the whole thing being open. 
Friendly. The staff was genuine, happy, and attentive. They clearly want you to be there and want you to have a great experience.

Challenges:
The food. I ordered the kafta sandwich, side of fries (didn't realize the side was a la carte), and the clementine ginger soda. The drink was tasty and an ok riff on a NA mule. The sandwich was lacking - somehow greasy and dry at the same time, much smaller than anticipated, and tasted ok at best. I'd expect a lot of flavor and spices and it was really just one note. Fries were fries. I enjoyed the seasoning 9n them but they still felt like freezer bag fries dressed nicely.
The price point. I'll pay for good food, service, and ambiance, but I think they overshot reasonable for now. At $12, I expect a whole lot more out of the "sandwich" and at least a handful of fries, chips, greens, something on the side. A $30 lunch (after tax/tip) should be much more than the small, order and take a number style that was experienced. Yes, Fishtown is up and coming, but it shouldn't expect to nor try to be Rittenhouse. I can't concede to paying that much of a premium.

So, as mentioned, I hope to see the food become better and better proportioned, and/or I hope to see the price adjusted for the cafe. I'm pulling for Suraya to thrive once it gets its legs.

I ordered pizza, a chicken cheesesteak and fries. The pizza was very good; traditional Greek style pizza. The fries were soggy, and the chicken cheesesteak was pretty good. This could have been a result of the longer delivery time, but to be fair it was a dinner time order on a Saturday.

We used to recommend Twisted Tail - and its fantastic selection of whiskey and bourbon - to all of our friends. After a recent experience with a rude server who made condescending remarks, we will not be returning.

Ok so I was super excited to try this place. The avocado tacos were amazing. My husband got brisket and the fried chicken tacos, he as well loved them. We also ordered Mexican street corn. ( I was craving it) i was disappointed that the corn I ordered off the cob was canned corn, not a lot of flavor probably due to the fact it can from a can and wasn't roasted. The taco soup was also really good. So if you do get the corn order on the cob to ensure it's really roasted corn. All in all it was pretty good. We will be back for the tacos and try the corn ON the cob next time.
This place serves my favorite steak... the kona encrusted bone-in NY strip. I love their truffle fries and lobster mac! The coconut pie is awesome,  too!

Wow, excellent food and service! I called for delivery, and they were very prompt. Minimum order price is quite low too.

I wasn't sure what size the portions would be and I was hungry, so I overdid it a bit and got three items: falafel, qudsia, and saffron rice. 

It was all delicious. Seriously all of it, and I'm picky about Mediterranean food. There's nothing worse than bland hummus or mealy, reheated falafel. Well, Mona's qudsia--a hybrid of hummus and the fava bean dip, foul--was nothing if not flavorsome, and the falafel was still hot and at the peak of its crispness. The rice was exceptional too--very well spiced, though I couldn't place what was in it beside the obvious saffron.

The prices were fair: $5 per item, so my total before tax was just $15, and the portions were generous. As it was all mine, I had a difficult time refraining from completely overstuffing myself. If I were to order from them again, which I likely will, I'd omit the rice. Good as it was, the dishes are served with plenty of pita.

Yep, definitely a new favorite.

Somehow we ended up going for custard while it was 29°F outside, which is probably not the optimal time to visit an outdoor frozen dessert stand.  But it was worth it to introduce a newbie to Ted Drewes and the world of midwestern custard.

I always try to find out what foods/restaurants are special to locals in an area, and my MO friends swear by Ted Drewes.  So when a new colleague came with us on a business trip and said she didn't know the difference between ice cream and custard... we knew what needed to be done.

There's something about their custard that is the right combination of rich and creamy and flavorful.  I'm a sucker for a concrete (let's face it, plain custard is pretty boring), and they've got so many flavors to choose from!  It's all vanilla custard, but you barely notice once it's been mixed up with all sorts of toppings.  This time I got the Dutchman, because I love pecans and butterscotch.  It was soooo good, I almost forgot I was freezing (almost).

A few things keep me from giving them the last star.  One: I really wish they also had chocolate.  I'm a chocoholic and some concretes would just be better with chocolate as the base.  Two:  I know the walk-up model is popular and classic, but I'd love more places to keep warm if they're going to serve custard in sub-freezing temps.  Three:  the smallest size concrete is still a lot of custard.  I'm not a cheapskate, I just don't want to eat an entire meal of custard.  Calling a size "micro" that's still like 12oz is laughable.  I threw out half of it and would rather have just not wasted that food.  

The lines move fast, and they've got lots of menus and signs posted so you can think about what you're going to order in advance.  They make everything pretty fast, too.

Came here a couple of months back with a friend for a late lunch around the start of happy hour. We opted to sit in the sun room out back which is absolutely beautiful. The decor was spot on and the lighting was awesome. It seemed to be very popular as most of the patrons at the time were sitting there. We got excellent service. They checked up on us, answered questions and refilled drinks quickly. I ordered a flatbread and was pleasantly surprised to get it for a steal at $4. My friend thoroughly enjoyed her meal as well. We really enjoyed being seated near the fountain. Overall, a great place for happy hour and a solid light meal.

Trendy. Tasty. Containers you can keep. Limited fountain drink selection. I've been three times now and I always leave STUFFED! The containers look small but there's some kind of magic that goes on there. Four stars because seating is incredibly limited. The service is good and they're happy to answer any questions.

Amerigo Italian Restaurant in Midtown is a casual dining experience with a comfortable and nice ambiance. They have a few locations in Tennessee and a couple in Mississippi as well although this is the only location I have visited. 

I've been here twice and both experiences have been good. Most recently I came here for a work lunch so they put us in a private room since there were so many of us. I'm always sympathetic for servers which have to take care of a large group but I think that our servers did a great job. They were quick to take our drink orders and get us situated. 

Through my workplace they had arranged for each one of us to pick a salad, entree and dessert. I got a Cesar salad, the chicken acuto and the pecan butter crunch cake. I enjoyed everything that I ordered. If I had to pick a favorite it might be the pecan butter crunch cake. If you are going to get a dessert get this one! It is sinfully rich and decadent and almost tastes like a cheesecake. The Cesar salad didn't have an overwhelming amount of dressing like some places do which I was happy about and the croutons were tasty. The chicken acuto was actually a perfect serving of a grilled chicken breast with a side of black bean salsa and spicy olive oil. It's served with a grilled artichoke and green beans. Everything on the plate was delicious and other people at my table who ordered it agreed that it was a great dish. Most other people at my table got the lasagna which seemed to be a crowd pleaser as well. 

Overall I enjoy Amerigo and have had good meals and service here. It is a perfect place for us to go for work functions so I always look forward to us coming here.

Iron Barley was amazing when it was located in the city. We have yet to try it at it's new location. We expect the same quality of food and menu selection as before and hope they bring their ribfest and tomato festival to high ridge.

I was in town for 4 nights for work.  This hotel was close to our training site, which was our main reason for selecting it.  I thought it would be fine since it's part of the Marriott family.  I should have guessed that you get what you pay for.

Positives: Really positive/kind/helpful staff; free ICE! tickets; shuttle to Opryland and Opry Mills; quiet; ease on and off of Briley

Negatives: REALLY uncomfortable beds; almost no blankets to speak of; no continental breakfast; overwhelming chlorine smell because the pool is in the middle of the hotel; pretty crappy shampoo/conditioner/body wash; inconsistent Wifi connectability; sticky bathroom door latch (I almost got stuck a few times!!)

Oddities: Free Christmas present wrapping station (huh?); light switch positions (you'll see what I mean...particularly in the bathroom area); VERY small bathroom (as in, you can hardly close the door); strange smell in the hotel room itself

I don't think I'd stay here again. I'd probably opt for having my company spend more for Opryland or deal with a longer drive.

Every time I come here, I learn something and I catch a buzz. What more could you ask for? Andrew is amazing. Ask him anything. If you want to drink beer and be left alone--perhaps not the ideal place. If you want to feel like you belong--I have no higher recommendation!

What to get: charbroiled oysters
Service: 3/5
Atmosphere: casual, group sit down
Wait: 30 mins (Friday 9PM for 2)
Parking: parking lot

The Experience: [July 2016]
If you're driving through town, Acme serves the basic New Orleans cuisine affair: oysters, gumbo, po-boys, jambalaya, seafood etouffee, etc. I'd describe it as a local 'chain' as it's primarily in New Orleans. It's open later so it's perfect for a late dinner. I had just finished driving 11 hours, so I just wanted an uncomplicated place with little wait.

It gets pretty busy with groups in Acme, so as a small party of 2, we had to wait awhile. Sometimes you have to nab one of the staff to remind them for anything like water, but you know it's just generally a busy place.

I ordered the infamous charbroiled oysters as a starter. Never had oysters any other way except raw, so this was something new for me. They're heavily seasoned, so if you're scared of the taste of oysters, this will cover it well with the taste of butter and cheese. It's synonymous to having fried fair food, where it tastes so good, but you know it's probably bad for your arteries.

I also ordered the New Orleans Medley: gumbo, jambalaya, red beans and rice, and half of a sausage. It's satisfying and feels like you're fulfilling the pre-requisites of New Orleans food. I'd recommend it if you're new to the cuisine and trying it out. It gives you a small taste of everything, so it's a solid first meal here.

Went for breakfast and was not disappointed!!! Excellent latte, tasty ommelette, and banging hash browns. Portions are generous and prices fair. The staff is friendly and super attentive! We will return for sure!

This was my first time to Whitebox after seeing it in friends posts. Upon walking in I felt that even though it's very white and modern from a design perspective, it still felt warm and welcoming. The employees working all had a smile on their faces and were pleasant to interact with. You order at the counter and then choose a seat and they will bring your food / drinks to you. The best part of my meal was definitely the latte. It was delicious and I liked that you could order a 12oz or 16oz. I ordered the Quiche Lorraine for brunch. It is served with a small arugula salad. The quiche is served room temperature, but mine was cold like it had been in a refrigerator. I asked to have it warmed up and it came back at about the same temperature. It was ok, but there is definitely better quiche to be had in StL. The arugula salad was entirely forgettable. I also ordered one biscuit with gravy on the side to try. The biscuit was a lot bigger than I was expecting. Neither the eggs in the quiche or the biscuit were very fluffy - they were both much denser than I would have expected. While I enjoyed my overall experience I felt the food was overpriced.

I ordered a chicken pasta with Bucktown Alfredo and a side of chicken and andouille gumbo. The pasta was terrible, the Alfredo sauce was rancid. The gumbo was a sauce with rice and two pieces of chicken grizzard that was in edible. This order was delivered to me by a food servicer so the fact that it was room temperature was disappointing but it was the least of my worries. THE FOOD ITSELF WAS SPOILED AND OF POOR QUALITY. I spoke with a manager to refund my money by the name of Devin who advised me to call the food delivery company for an order and I told him that I have only refunded food one other time and on that occasion the restaurant called the servicer and I was given a full refund. He scoffed at me and said "oh you've done this before?" as if I go around ordering unwanted food. He agreed to call them and I asked that he call me to confirm it was done. After an hour and a half without hearing from him I called back. This time the owner Katherine took my call and had very clearly spoken to Devin and was not interested in helping me. She told me that my issue was with the delivery and they couldn't guarantee the integrity of food deliveries. I told her as I am telling all of you THE FOOD WAS SPOILED not cold from a 15min late pickup. She told me that she would call waiter and "Get it taken care of" either tonight (which was unlike because she was too busy and Devin had waited on hold for 30mins with the food delivery service company and hung up) or she would "get it taken care of tomorrow", and suggested again that I call the food delivery company. So I did, within 5 mins the food delivery company had taken my call and needed to get Katherine on the line to confirm that a full refund would be give. Katherine told the delivery company that she had not told me she would give me a refund and instead chose to refund half of my order.  I don't know about you but when someone says they are going to "get it taken care of" I take that as you are going to make things right and give me a refund. So Katherine was misleading and disingenuous. I will never patron this place again. It has been in business for years but apparently the current ownership and food quality is DEPLORABLE. I wouldn't recommend this place to my worst enemy.

Wow!!! It completely lives up to the hype.  This place is dirty. The floors were sticky in the dairy isle?
A very disheveled elderly woman greeted us with such an odder. We at no time felt safe because an odd man followed us around the store. Turned out he was homeless and kept asking us for money. I gave him five bucks and wished him a merry Christmas.  Bad idea because now I guess he figured we were suckers and hounded us when we left. A story I will pick up latter.
It was busy so can sort of understand why it was so hard to find help to open security cases to get electronics out for purchase.
There were so many bags of chips and cans of soda opened and half empty laying around in the isle's.  As Walmart's go, there selection of products was decent but if it wasn't so close to Christmas and it being so close to my home I would never go to and go to either Elkton or Wilmington to there Walmart's instead.
And now leaving. We took our cart after waiting in line for 40 minutes behind a very large woman wearing the tightest spandex and paid. And after showing our receipt to security as we left. The homeless gentleman I had helped out earlier was standing outside waiting to walk us to our car and help us load it up. I told him it was unnecessary and slipped him another two bucks and a merry Christmas. Bad idea number two. Because now we were followed by his apparent henchmen. To shake us down.  I yeld OK enough is enough!!! Back up!!! MERRY CHRISTMAS!!!  It started to get ugly. My girlfriend quickly loaded the car while I held them at bay.  They started to take an aggressive stance so I pulled out my hobo be good stick out of the trunk and said Merry Fucking Christmas assholes!!! And with such a clatter. They took off running with my girlfriend shouting Merry Christmas to all and let's get the fuck out of here!!!!  Were home now and a bit wiser about shopping there. And that is to never return. Be wise and don't go there either!!!

Dr. Brewer is a great Doctor. He's certainly introverted but I prefer a knowledgeable doctor over an overly chatty one that doesn't know what their doing, and this guy knows what he's doing. He came after hours to see my daughter who was running a very high fever and administered antibiotics. I was very thankful and reminded me why I've stuck around since my firstborn was a baby. That's 9 years!!  He's always very kind and has great bedside manner. Thank you Dr. Brewer :)
Glad to see this location revitalized. The portions were large, and the service was good. Recommend their Tao's Chicken.

I love Good Morning Mama's! Always a solid breakfast. Every time I come, I leave full- and it's not super expensive. 

Went here for the first time on a weekday, for a team meeting. So no mimosa for me :(
Not 30 seconds after I sat down, the waitress was asking for my drink order (with suggestions! NICE). I got coffee and she kept it refilled all of the time. Coffee is tasty!

I went a different route and got the veggie breakfast sandwich but I added bacon and got it on a croissant. When I say yummy, I mean it. The avocado, spinach, and tomato gave me a well balanced veggie explosion as my eggs were prepared perfectly and that buttery croissant was *thumbs up*

Of course, we got the Italian biscuits with apple butter and they never disappoint. Soft, sweet, and melt in your mouth biscuits with the slightly tart but sweet apple butter. They are fantastic. 

Service was great- we were a bigger group and she kept up on our demands and was as nice as can be.
Decor is cute- like a 50's gas station/restaurant. Just looking for servers on skates!

This is the place I am going to get live lobster,live crab, oysters, bread shrimp and breaded oysters and all the seafood I am getting in Reno , every month!!!
 Thanks to Sierra seafood!! The only place in town that serving the live seafood! I am not going to Take the fully cooked crab from other store any more since eating from the boiled pot would taste much better. The meat is much tender and juicier. 
 I got a 2.5 lbs live crab in the morning and cooked in the pot for 30 mins after pick my son up from school in the afternoon.he ate all the legs . He is Super happy !
I also got the kids breaded shrimp which was made by the store. No wonder why other customers buy bulk bags of the bread shrimp.. it tasted so fresh and healthy! I bought only one bag to try it out today.. guess what?? Only one serving, My 5 yrs old and 1yrs old eat the whole thing!! That shows that how much they love it!!!
Very impressive and definitely would come back regularly!!!

This place. Has been on my radar since I moved to Tampa in 2013 and sad to say I just never made it.  And I'm disappointed it took me so long because this place is a hidden gem.  The menu is in both English and Spanish so it's easier for those of us who aren't bilingual.  The place is super friendly and the food is sooo good.

I have never been to Florida but my mission was to find an awesome Cuban sandwich because everyone says I needed to have one, I tried 4 different cuban sandwiches at different restaurant's and this one was still good but definitely 4th on my list, the sides and every thing else were still good but I was not impressed with their Cuban sandwich.

We are glad to welcome DelItaly to the neighborhood. Great family owned restaurant and deli. Authentic Italian chef and owner. We tried the meat pizza and it was delicious. Can't wait to try the sandwiches and cannoli. Thank you Felice and Lucas!

Great selection of unique sushi combinations; opting for the Chef's Selection for the evening. We also liked the flavored soy selections. Pricing was a bit steep.....but still an enjoyable experience!

A great dinner out with family.  Large selection of draft and bottled beers- many local.  Didn't try any cocktails but many fun options on the menu.  
Some wanted burgers but they were out at 7:30 on Saturday night.  What?  
So we made the best of it and ordered things we may not have otherwise: 
Coconut Tofu!- spicy and sweet.  Fish and fries!- light sweet fish and crispy fries.  
Pork chop & Cheesy grits- creamy and savory. 
Scallops were done perfectly although a little on the bland side and over priced for the serving size.  
Trout Caesar salad was eaten til last bite.  
We started with a mascarpone tart with pickled/roasted onions.  Interesting flavors- served with lightly dressed greens.  Too full for dessert.  Maybe next time.  I want to back for a burger.

Hot Tin definitely exceeded my expectations! The view is truly amazing, of course, but the interior is beautiful as well. The whole bar has an open concept. You still get an amazing view even if you're not on the balcony. On a Friday night it wasn't overly packed. The crowd was more sophisticated and the music was a mix of old and new jams. The cocktails were yummy. You can lose track of time up there! It's definitely worth visiting if you're on a date or hanging out with friends. I can't wait to return!

Food was fresh and it was excellent!  love the patio seating  with Heaters!!!! however the service was slow thus the reason for the 4 star and not because of the non-smiling hostess.

We went for brunch and not really busy yet it still took us 20 mins to order (5 mins to get our server to acknowledge us and another 15 to take our order).
Do you feel the Hangriness coming out? We did talk about leaving...

 Set my stop watch and 20 mins after she took our order,  our food was on our table.

Very nice "hole in the wall" type atmosphere that is actually fairly family friendly. The outdoor patio is pretty spectacular on warm days and evenings in the spring, summer, and fall. A good array of games and seating/tables outside are available and a great space to relax.

The beers they make are the full spectrum of beers from super light and fruity to flavorful and robust. I'm a big fan of their IPA beer called the "None-the-wiser". It's a great rich and hoppy flavored beer that's smooth going down. If you're not a fan of the IPA, I'd recommend the Hoo-Brew Honey as an alternative. It's a bit more sweeter but it actually has a higher alcohol content than the "None-the-wise".

Food at Blind Owl is great. Simple American a style pub food. Appetizers, flatbread pizzas, salads, burgers, sandwiches, and a few entrees. I definitely recommend you try the chipotle rubbed smoked wings. Good balance of smoke, heat, and flavor while maintaining a crunchy skin as if deep fried and still moist and tender meat. The pulled pork nachos are also a favorite of mine and are great for sharing if you want or as an entree.

One unique men item at Blind Owl is an array of Mac & Cheese dishes. I haven't had them all but the Cajun and Buffalo mac & cheese I have had and they're great. Creamy, cheesy, and definitely not lacking in the flavor department.

I usually get one of two burgers when I go here. First is the "Early Riser" which is a ground beef patty with smoked Gouda cheese, sun dried tomato aioli, and a fried egg with the yolk still somewhat runny (how it's supposed to be cooked). The second burger I enjoy getting is the bison burger. A classic burger but with the unique flavor that bison naturally has compared to beef.

The side dishes are good...I'm really only had their hand cut fries and the tater tots and they're both cooked to the crispy perfection that I like in my fries or tots. 

All in all, it's a great place to eat, socialize, enjoy a drink and relax...for all ages (obviously not all ages can do everything).

Not a good experience.
This is advertised as an upscale restaurant and is priced as such.  Don't mind paying for good food and good service. In this case, didn't get either.  
We went for lunch during the week. They had one lady seating, taking orders and serving. While the place was not busy, it took a long time for everything. There was another lady walking around, looked like possibly manager or owner. She had no interest in helping out. 
The space looks like minimal effort was taken to convert this from a bar to a restaurant. Old tables and chairs placed randomly around the room and on a wooden dance floor. 
Would not go back.

Impressed with this place! Visited my cousin in Indianapolis and he brought me here. 

So I walk in and it looks like a comfy family diner. All the staff is very happy and friendly. Some neat decorations on the wall that look retro. Then I see a sign that says biscuits and "sausage gravy"...this is when I knew they were legit! To many people shy away from putting the sausage in the gravy as it's meant to be! 

My wife ordered the biscuits and sausage gravy. I had crab cakes Benedict. Both were awesome. The food came out fast and was packed with flavor! Great portion sizes for the price. My cousin who brought me here ordered this spicy chicken biscuit that was amazing too. Chicken was juicy and tender and the sauce was so yum. While we were eating 2 different managers made it a point to stop in and introduce themselves and make sure we were happy and food was good! Everyone had a smile on their face which makes it that much better to eat here. My cousin proceeded to tell me it's a chain, so if a big dog reads this, Cincinnati would be a great fit for your restaurant!
Food sucks. Service great. Need to get rid if manager Named Hansel. Not what you we ordered. Go to others there. Didn't get right order. Ordered full serving. Got senior portions. .

Yes! One of my favorite restaurants. The lasagna is good enough to make you slap your grandma! (Metaphorically speaking, granny.) so Tuesday night is my night. The Del Pietro salad is excellent  excellent. Just don't go on Tuesday because I hate crowds and you might slow me down. Seriously, SUGO'S is one of my favorite restaurants. Give it a try.

Second visit to the Parish this evening...and well worth it!    Our first visit was at lunch...which we enjoyed...and our dinner today measured up.   My wife had the Drunken Angel and said it was excellent...she'd give it a 5.   I had the mussels and they were very good.   We'd order both again!
Service was very good and atmosphere is very comfortable and lively.
The reason I didn't give it a 5 is that I've only been there twice.   I feel I'd need to have a couple more experiences at exceptional levels to confirm a 5.
We'll definitely be back...

When we got engaged (!!!!) this past weekend at Dilworth Park, immediately after (in a daze) we started wondering what to do now and decided to go for a drink to celebrate. We decided on Good Dog since it was close by and was always a win in the past. Upon entering I yelled (I think) at the poor girl at the door that she was the first one I'm telling and that we're engaged! If she's reading this, I'm so sorry I yelled. I was overly excited. Haha

She seated us at the table under the front window which I believe they normally reserve for people that are ordering food too, so that was really sweet of her. To make things even more special, our waitress brought us glasses of champagne and a congratulations! Everyone was just so nice and it really made our already awesome night over the top amazing. The night was such a whirlwind but we'll never forget how lovely the people at Good Dog were to us. Thank you!

Friday night. Heard some "Party in the USA" playing, saw the dancing people inside. We hopped in. They played all the old hits--Britney, Backstreet Boys, Pitbull, Kesha, Miley Cyrus...great time for singing along. Much less of a bar scene than other places.

The two entertainers invited people to come up on stage and perform, and they lip-synced along too. They also sorta danced? Lots of to-be brides. Whatever they were doing, it was such a FUN time! Waitresses walked around with shots that you'd do from their mouth. Shots girls could be aggressive. Some wild stuff went on, and it was fun to watch as you tipsy/drunk dance your way through the night. It gets super hot, so make sure you wear something that won't kill you if you sweat in it, in the middle of a crowded sea of people.

Only thing was there was a small roof leak in the middle of the dance floor, so one empty spot on the dance floor.
best thing about the placeWAS THE VIEW. THE food was terrible(crab roll. more like a dry onion roll. it has been closed for a while. the land was bought out.  good

Great food and fresh sushi..great value for the food.
There is a mix of Japanese, korean, and American.

Brought my parents there for a quick dinner. Food tastes good and service is great (given it was right before new year and they were so busy)! Our waiter (I didn't get his name, my bad) was patient and hustling. Good vibe, too!
A consistently good place for lunch. Good salads and good service. Relatively relaxing friendly place. Never had to wait for a table.

2nd time visiting Ale Emporium. 1st time was totally crazy as this place gets packed in the evening! Came for a late lunch on a Wednesday this time. Herman Style wings = FIYAH! Man, those wings were good. They're meaty, juicy, crispy....ah yes. Also ordered the loaded potato skins...THAT WERE HUGE & DELICIOUS !!!
Jeanette was our server & she was very nice. 

Mon, Weds, & Fri are $5 Jack Daniels specials so......lucky us! I had 2 & my bf did as well. Drinks were on point. Had a nice little afternoon buzz. Nothing wrong with day drinking. 

The bar was kinda busy but the service was quick. Total tab with 4 Jack & Cokes, a Blue Moon, 2lbs of wings, and potato skins was 50 bucks. Well worth it to me. Check out Ale Emporium if u haven't

This is the best BBQ place in Tampa hands down. Came  here for the first time a few years ago and did not know what to expect. It's in the middle of a neighborhood next to a no name mini mart. Just three small tables inside. The Yelp reviews were good and my office was only a few blocks away on WestShore Blvd. It was love a first bite. Such succulent meats, such tasty sauce, such incredible sides (especially when they have greens at the end of the week). 
My office has since moved but luckily I now have weekly meetings close by so I decided to come back today, oh so good. My old office mates still speak of this place.
It's a hole in the wall kind of place, no fine dining or fancy drinks here, and also a gravel parking lot (most just eat tailgate style).  Just meat in a styrofoam container in a paper bag. Find a nice patch of grass somewhere nearby International mall and bring a few beers and enjoy!

I'd stay FAR AWAY from this "so called" restaurant! I went there with a group, and we had to walk out. First of all, when you walk in the restaurant, you see live fish barely breathing in the tank. Some were alive, but barely breathing; while some were dead. How can a restaurant served fish in that type of condition? Also, what makes matter worse is that we saw many mice droppings on our tables. Yes, I said, a "plural word!" Mice droppings were on two of our tables, and they were very noticeable! Also, the restaurant was VERY dirty, and seemed as if it had not been cleaned since it opened in Philadelphia! Disgusting, dirty, and just plain gross on every level! If you value your health, go somewhere else!! Phewy!!

My friends and I stopped by for some late night food and snacks and had a great time. It's quite small but very intimate. we got the puffed pork chips and the beef fat biscuit which were so good! The puffed porch chips remind me of a crispier pork rind with this sour cream and onion type dip. The biscuit was perfectly baked with tons of flavor. Overall, I would definitely come back and try their entrees!

We skipped the buffet and ordered a la carte.
We loved the mango lassi, chicken biryani, garlic naan & paneer tikka masala.

The food was really good and so was the service. The only major problem is the design of the restaurant, the main door opens into main dining areas and on a day like today it was freezing at the tables (and we were not that close to the door) they need to install a second set of doors to act as a wind trap or one of those over head heat lamps to keep cold air from entering.

Literally the best breakfast place I've ever eaten! I would recommend it to anybody. We had the Banana French toast, shrimp and grits, and the avacado crab omelette. Everything was amazing! Not to mention it is a cute little place with a great vibe!

I'm glad to have discovered this place after it has been here all these years. Lunch and the staff were great. I loved their hummus-- not too strong with the tahini. Perfectly flavored and light. The spinach/mushroom pie was yum. My husband's shawarma platter was good as well. I'll be returning often.

I am happy to say I've finally found a mechanic I can trust! I will never bring my car anywhere else even if it's for a simple oil change. Ray is an honest worker and has fixed some issues with my car due to very poor work done elsewhere. I know I can trust Ray and everyone that works for him. We need more people like this in the world. I would recommend this place to anyone!

I've had many massages in many different spas but I've always felt the pressure was too intense.  I figured I had a low pain threshold but that didn't change the fact that I have a lot of tightness in my shoulders and neck. Whenever I'd ask for lower pressure though, I felt like the massage didn't do anything for me. So, unfortunately, I just thought I was the only person in the world who actually doesn't feel better after a massage!

But that was before I discovered Spa Terme di Aroma. 

I've only been here twice and I don't know what else to tell you except I believe that their massage therapists are exceptionally well trained. They work out the knots without me wanting to wince in pain (and tense up more). I always feel like a burden has been lifted off of my shoulders (literally!). Friendly staff and yummy treats in the lounge too. You feel relaxed the moment you walk in their cozy Old City spa and inhale the delicious aromatherapy scent. So happy I found this place.

These people are out for blood. They are a ripoff and scam. Don't do service with them. My husband is the nicest easiest person to get along with and they have done nothing, but screw him over. You would think that they would want to make their customers happy. Well don't hold your breath. We will NEVER step foot on that property ever again. I advise others to stay away too.

Airport dinners sometime make me cringe. Cantina Laredo was right across from our gate -- 45 minutes for a sit-down meal here was just the right amount of time to plan for. Our waitress was so kind and accommodating to our toddler. Fresh warm chips and salsa we complimentary upon seating. After we devoured it immediately it was a clear decision to get the table-side guac next. With onions, jalapeños, cilantro and probably something else I  can't remember freshly whipped up infront of us... you can bet we devoured that too. Enough for 2 hungry adults, but probably could entertain 3-4 mouths.

The quesadillas hit the proverbial spot. Pro-tip: you can mix it up with beef/chicken. It was just the right amount of cheese to meat combo. Pair allll of those things with a top shelf marg and your flight will be more enjoyable - guaranteed.

Terrible experience here on a not very busy Sunday night. Had 7:00 reservations and arrived in time. The entrance is on the side of the building and not clearly marked. Then we waited about 5 minutes before anyone acknowledged us. We got our drinks and then sat for 25 minutes never placed our order. We walked out after getting nothing but excuses as to why we were not even acknowledged.
Great pizza! I stopped by for a quick bite while driving through Santa Barbara and was really amazed. Short wait time for some really good pizza.

LOVED the Love. Great ambiance and perfect for groups or special occasions! Went with 4 people and we got a ton of food that included the cheese plate, purist poke, and Caesar salad for appetizers. We got the beef stroganoff, scallops, gnudi, and spaghetti squash for entrees. All were great except the spaghetti squash was just eh. Sides : broccoli & Brussels. Dessert: Carrot Cake sundae with cream cheese custard. Everything was amazing. Gnudi was a personal fav because it came in a delicious truffle butter sauce. We will definitely be back !!

Been here for brunch twice. Can you say bottomless mimosas?!!! And they mean bottomless! I got in a race with my server to see if I could make it to the bottom of the glass before he refilled it again and he won. For sure. The buffet is to die for. Fresh seafood!! Bacon, eggs, grits, etc.. Belgian waffles with whiskey butter. So much deliciousness I can't even begin to describe. The restaurant is very nice. I wouldn't recommend for kids. People are paying a lot of money to eat there and don't want children running around and screaming etc.. dress code is semi formal I would say. They offer valet parking also if you so wish. I went there both times for special occasion with my boyfriend. It's not a place I think I would go for just a random brunch because brunch for two will set you back over $100.00. You get an amazing experience for the money though. Beautiful restaurant, top notch service, and lovely water views from inside. Will be back for our next special occasion for sure, but this time I won't be in a mimosa race!

Great shop, great location, helpful staff, easy parking if you come by car.  Been coming to Cadence for years.  I live in DC now, but I came in for some MTB shoes after switching over the pedals on my road bike to MTB-style pedals.  They gave me a great deal on last season's model.  When I had trouble with the shoes, Cadence replaced them and shipped them to me.

Went in for a Chicago dog and a polish.
Their was one person in the dining area.

I would have thought my items would be out in a minute... it seemed like 5 minutes..... way too long...

I found out these are new owners.
For three people running the place the service would be quick....  

Also, the restaurant carpet looked filthy.

You need to order $5.00 to use a debit/ credit card
$3.00 for a hotdog and $5 for a polish... is what I ordered. 

For someone who lived in Chicago for 30 years, I know hot dogs...

I will not return

Theirs another place down the street... that will be my next review.


 Follow up .... this place is closed ....   been driving down olmerton and every time there is a closed sign...

Time for some new owners who know the business.... 

Make me an offer and I'll take it on..
Excellent thin crust pizza.  Great servers and staff- always friendly and great attitude.

The Catfish St. Peter was amazing! My husband ordered this dish and could not stop talking about it. It was amazing (the little bite he so lovingly shared haha.) Our server Mike was THE BEST! We came for the Reveillon menu and we were not disappointed in the least. Mike gave us his recommendations as we ordered and he did not steer us wrong. Our order was taking a little bit to be prepared so Mike brought us complementary gumbo which was divine. He also made sure we had warm French bread and butter while we waited. I had the chicken espagnole and the chicken just fell off of the bone. It was so good. After dinner my husbands dessert came (part of the Reveillon menu) and he brought me warm brownie pie with a scoop of ice cream since our food took so long. It was completely unexpected and extremely appreciated. He warned us that the pie was rich and that's why we needed the ice cream and he was right. It was rich and delicious. We definitely recommend this restaurant and this place will become one of our regular places to dine when we come to town. Ahhhmazing! Well worth the 30 minute wait outside in the cold on Christmas Eve. Try this place!! You will NOT regret it! 

My husband called every single one of our family members after our meal to tell them about the catfish St. Peter. You HAVE to try it!!

(Also ordered: bread pudding, mashed potatoes, crab cakes. All were delicious.)

Okay this food is DECENT at best. I say that by meaning it's good variety but Circle 7 just down the street blows this place out of the water. Why? Cause the service here is shit. Absolutely horrible. Constantly the servers are MIA. One time I waited over 30 mins for my check and finally left what I thought was close to what the price of my meal was. But what brings me to writing this review is tonight a short stout blonde waitress was MIA again, nothing new. But I saw her in the corner holding hands with what appears to be her boss. Glad she has time for that instead of refilling anybody's drinks or being attentive.

Water street defiantly has the best cocktails in town! The grapefruit gimlet is my personal favorite, and their cocktails are always made nice a strong. I love the ambiance of this restaurant. It's very small and cozy. Perfect place for a date night or cocktail with a friend. Highly recommend the goat cheese stuffed dates and bruschetta trio! Yum! I would give it 5 stars if their dinner menu was a little bit larger. Decent entrees but not a huge selection.
How can I give vivint 0 stars? Worst company ever, go somewhere else, they will put u on hold forever and give you the run around .

All i can say is: DELICIOUSNESS! Great and tasty food! I can't talk about the place because we order takeout but the sushi and rice were amazing. We order a poboy sushi roll and a rice combination. We will definitely go back!

As my tip suggests, this place is like nada's younger, rowdy brother. 

You walk in and your eyes are immediately shocked at the vast colors, graffiti-like artwork, pinatas, and more. Most noticeably, the music and the amount of TVs. The music is LOUD (is this a new trend that's going on? I'm not a fan at all....) and there are TVs EVERYWHERE. 

I can see this place being perfect for two occasions: 
- big sports games going on and you don't want to stay at home and watch them. The amount of TVs ensure that you're covered, no matter your placement in the restaurant.
- Tuesdays! Be sure to stop by this joint on Tuesdays if you're in the area. Specially priced margs and tacos. 

Any other day of the week: this place seems way too overpriced. There are lots of drink options (not your typical marg on the rocks like many other places), so you can choose a variety of ways to drink tequila. Still, I'm not sure that they're worthy of the price tag. The frozen marg I had felt like I was going to get hungover....simply cause of the amount of sugar that was in it. 

I also ordered the chips + guac (which was very good) and the chips and salsa (a-okay). The veggie tacos that we ordered were so oily that the TWO corn wraps were soaked. You had to use a fork to eat them cause they were so oily. This was a massive turn off. 

Pros: 
- Tuesdays
- TVs everywhere
- Great location for walking 
- Fun atmosphere
- Arcade-like games to play
- Open till 3am so perfect for late-night munchies after the bars (which honestly feels like the type of crowd that this place is going for)
- Live DJ at times

Cons/things to improve: 
- Tacos are very greasy and oily
- Food is just a-okay. If you're not here on a Tuesday, I'd suggest going elsewhere as the prices aren't worthy of the taste.
