- Frozen margs are a bit too sugary and the house marg didn't entice me to come back for it again. 
- Music was LOUD when I came here (maybe it's different now or during a different time?)
- Limited vegetarian taco options. 

Nice alternative to what was previously here, I might add. But could use some improvements on the taste to get me to come back here as often as I do with other taco places around Indy.

Worst experience ever. They charged us 3800 bucks for deposit while we provided the docs they asked for(proof of income). I live in LA and my bf lives there. I have a dog, which stays with me most of the time and I bring it with me to visit my bf, like probably once in two weeks, and the leasing office was trying so hard to make us pay the 1000 bucks for a dog deposit. They really made me feel like all they care about is money money and money. Of course we ignored it, and then they emailed us, threatened our roommates "if you don't pay the dog deposit, you will be kicked out". So we paid for it. And then I decided I'm just never gonna come to this community any more, so I asked my bf to take back the check( at that time I was visiting with my dog but I'll be back in 2 days), and the woman in the office said that "you either signed the document or you gotta send the dog away RIGHT NOW". almost forgot to mention that they are so good at asking for money but have not given us the garage keys or the other gym key since my bfs moved in for 1 month:)
Expensive mediocre food. Ham swiss spinach sandwich was okay but wouldn't bother coming here again.

I don't get it.  I really don't.  I know many people absolutely love this place.  I find that everything on the menu is very, very heavy.  
The atmosphere is cool but I just have never found anything special about the menu or the food.

Definitely visit on a Wednesday or Thursday if you want to beat the crowds. If you visit a weekday AND it's cold and blustery, you will really cut down on the number of people standing in between you and a giant puddle of cheese on a piece of bread (also known as raclette). 

We visited on a Wednesday evening, and we were able to just walk up to any of the food stands. No waiting! We got the bratwurst, but we were a little disappointed because it was smaller than the bratwurst pictures on the Christkindlemarkt website. Where are the big weiners? We came for the big weiners and left disappointed. The bratwurst tasted alright, though, and came with spicy mustard on top, with a side of warm potato salad (which was delicious). We also got an apple cider donut. 

There isn't much to do here besides ice skating. But it's nice to walk around and look at all the German-imported goods for sale. There's also a live band playing Christmas music, so that was nice.

Who goes shopping at a mall a week before Christmas? Me... that's who. I needed to buy a couple of tops and some dress pants for work. My husband suggested we try the mall, since they have Macy's and JcPenney. 
Let me start by saying, while I am a woman, I detest shopping. So Christmas was probably not the ideal time to head that way. However, my husband promised me we would stop at the food court and have a fish sandwich. Who could resist? Not me... I'm a sucker.
Overall the experience wasn't too horrible, but it was very crowded, and the store workers seemed a little overwhelmed and tired. Made me feel bad for them, but happy that I wasn't one of them. The racks were mostly disorganized from the multitude of holiday shoppers that are too lazy or lost to find the spot they pulled the item from.  The shoppers however should be ashamed of themselves. They walk into you, push you, step in front of you while you are looking at an item, or just plain show their 'behind' to you. Next year, I resolve to stay away from the mall during this time. Except for the fish... that I will come for, but make it "to go".

Wow, invested and trustworthy customer service. I was dreading coming in bc who likes going in for a phone problem? I was helped by Jeff and Daniel who walked me through my options patiently and offered sincere advice. I came out with an affordable solution to my problem and very happy. There were several other customers in the store and they did an excellent job of keeping everyone satisfied and were focused on meeting everyone's needs efficiently. I was happily surprised by my experience at this location and will come back with any future needs.

This is a very cool little bar with a great concept in the downtown Indy area. I was in town visiting my brother in law who recently transferred here so wasn't very familiar with the area yet, and we decided to check this place out. The area is a little run down, hopefully being updated soon, and it was hard to tell what kind of place this would be. 

As soon as we walked in, we were very pleasantly surprised! They have a pour your own beer wall, a great cocktail list and awesome staff! 

The beer wall allows you to pour your own and pay by the ounce, which is great for when you are trying out new beers. The staff was wonderful with explaining how it works, and the decor is really cool. It is so much bigger than it looks from the outside! 

We have yet to eat here, but the menu looks great and it is one spot we hit up each time we are in town! 

Highly recommended!

I came with my family, a group of 5, close to 5 on a Thursday evening and there was a line forming but it went fast.

My family and I got all got tenders with two sides, except my dad who ordered a sandwich. We tried the baked beans, southern greens, fries, Mac and cheese. I think the girl misheard my dad and gave him the order of white instead. Didn't matter as it was the same price anyway.

Fries were good and I loved the baked beans. I don't know how collared greens actually taste but these tasted better than I thought, though my mom and sister weren't impressed. Mac and cheese had pimento in it. I thought it was light on the pimento and pretty good, my sister said she tasted better.

I thought the chicken was good though not really outstanding. The food took a while to come for some reason...but maybe that's how it is with the tenders since they're more popular to order here.

Sweet tea was fantastic! I loved it. My sister got the lemonade which the make themselves. It was also very good!

The space wasn't that large and the tables seemed kinda close to each other. It seemed like a lot of people get to-go here. It's a long wait though so you've got to be patient.

Otherwise, parking was kinda sucky. Super small lot. Just park somewhere up the street and walk.

This review is long overdue!

Float Nashville is my happy place. It's the first place I ever floated, and one of my favorites!

I have consistently found their venue to be exceedingly clean, and well stocked with amenities. Their staff are friendly, and the booking process is easy. 

I particularly like that they have an open tank option. I find that its larger size and unenclosed format makes the experience less daunting if it's your first time.

I highly recommend this float center to anyone who is looking to relax. If you don't have time to go on vacation this is a great alternative solution - I usually feel the same results as when I've been on vacation for a week! For a busy mom, or a stressed out business person, or a student facing exams, this is a perfect solution.
Service was mediocre.  My steak was over cooked and my husband's was undercooked. Both steaks were over salted.  Maybe it was just a bad night.  I went there before and didn't have any problems.

Super disappointing!! Went with party of 6 the day after Christmas. First the good. My buddy got a pizza and it was very good. Everything else was meh. Wife got the bean soup and Beet  salad. The soup was ok the beet salad was old tasting. Steak salad was over cooked. Two club sandwiches seemed skimpy. Now my real aggravation. I ordered the meatball parm. It comes out and the meat balls are cold. I send it back. 15 mins later it returns . The bread ciabatta was nice and warm but the meatball still are not! Really! The waiter never returned to ask. So they put the plate in the oven and someone in the kitchen thought that would work? By the way they served me the same fries. This is a $12 sandwich. To the waiters credit he took it off the check. So what! I didn't get lunch. By the way the meatballs were not great. The whole bill was $148 with tip. I may return for half price Pizza at happy hour , otherwise I will not be back.

Oh my goodness!!! We ordered for the first time tonight and you just earned new regular customers.  We are vegan and found the menu VERY accommodating to us.  The tofu was PERFECT,  the food was so flavorful and every veggie was fresh. The flavors of the gang Phet......so awesome. We had the gang Phet, the pad Thai with tofu,  the fried rice with tofu and TONS of fresh veggies.  The sauces were amazing, the service was friendly and I cannot say enough good things about this place.

When Woodlands moved, I was sad. I've been wanting to find my replacement Indian restaurant, and dare I say that Green Chili may even be better? Although the inside feels a bit like a cruise ship, it's definitely a comfortable and maaaybe even romantic place to eat. We've found ourselves going fairly regularly. The Gobi Manchurian is a great starter (and somehow better than Woodlands), as is the garlic naan. The service is pretty good and very friendly, they have inexpensive beer, and they apparently have separate kitchens for meat and non-meat dishes. Highly recommended!

I will never go back to nice nails. I am so glad Cindy Diamond is at Andy Nails
 She is awesome along with the rest of the team. Nice nails has become such an angry place to go
I will be a faithful customer now to Andy Nails

Known for his awesome pirate tours, we were lucky enough to have the Captain personally officiate my sister's Pirate Wedding, and it was AMAZING!  Captain Ginty (officially an ordained minister, wouldn't you know...) led a hilarious and touching ceremony for my sister and her groom, complete with rum, swords and the funniest vows I've ever heard.  Our crew of merry troublemakers had a blast storming the quarter with this knowledgable and laugh-out-loud funny Captain.  HIGHLY RECOMMEND.
Food was good. Wait sucked. Will eat here again inside though..... try the most expensive burger they have its worth it.

Terrible food and even worse service. I got the shrimp po'boy with fries. The fries were cold and the po'boy was not tasty. Not worth paying $15 for. No waiter seemed to know what table was their's. I waited 10 mins just for a glass of water, then waited again for the check, about 15 mins. No one checked in and I had to get up and find another waiter to ask for hot sauce. If I could give 0 stars, I would.

Ok....sometimes a place is so significantly good, i have to write about it!! This is the best bbq i have had (and I've been around). Tried the ribs... dry rub, but fell off the bone with a perfect smoke. Wings.... they are whole wings and fantastic!! Pulled pork was a step up from anybody else. Sides.... Mac n cheese, delicious...smoked green beans, so good... baked beans are done right... craft beer with a great bar right inside!! 
All this, and priced right. Don't change a thing peg leg (ask about that story).

We've been to this Ikea store a lot. Sometimes it's for something serious like a sofa, sometimes it's for something for the kids rooms. My most recent trip was to replace the sofa cover I spilled a whole glass of red on, after I was in the doghouse for golfing earlier that same day so a speedy replacement was necessary! 

I walked in the exit like usual and went right to the computer kiosk so I could get my slipcover.  Turns out an employee has to set that up. So Matthew took care of me in a flash. I had my sheet for pickup and off I went. While I went to pay my wife went looking for lamp shades. After checkout is when the disappointment kicked in. 57 minutes later I get called for my item to be picked up. As I'm approaching the counter the attendant points to my box behind the wall. I go over to pick it up and hand her my sheet and I get scolded "get behind the yellow line" when I turned around there were two ladies that heard her and their eyes were huge in amazement. Since it's been 57 minutes I just wanted to leave. 

My experience with this side of the ikea experience was further eroded when I went to return the lamp shades today. I walked in at 10:55. I was number 69, they were on 56. I made an online purchase at 11:33 and they were on 66. At 11:45 I got called. Why does it take this long for a return, I waited 50 minutes in the middle of a Tuesday for a return.  Get outta here ikea. 

IKEAs offer decent stuff at a reasonable price, all of my experiences have been positive when on the sales floor but the return procedure and the pickup area is a disaster and the pickup area need major tending to as they are a horrible last experience at this Ikea.

I took my bff to enjoy a pedicure for her  birthday today and we had the best time!
First off let me just say that I'm a licensed cosmetologist and my friend is a licensed nail tech so we are tough  customers! 
Lari and the receptionist greeted us with a smile and we got to choose our polish from a huge assortment on the wall. Then we were escorted back to the pedi chairs that were very clean and gave a great massage!
I had Jeni and my friend had Rose. What wonderful ladies and we had so much fun with them! They gave an incredibly thorough and unrushed pedicure that was done from beginning to end with expertise and care. We both had the deluxe pedis and I got mine with the paraffin treatment and she got the mask.  It has been a long time since I have felt so pampered and relaxed! 
Thank you for such a wonderful day Lari, Rose and Jeni! You will definitely be seeing us again very soon!

This review is for the main dining room only. We attempted to be put on the waiting list for the ramen room while we were in the main dining room and somehow that didn't happen.  Really wanted to try to ramen too not just the small plates in the main dining room. You can't order ramen in the main dining room and the ramen room is very small.  The food in the main dining room was really good though.
Had 4 teen girls with mom and dad for birthday party. Was a great family activity, tons of fun!!

Jim and Cindy have taken care of all our personal and business insurance needs for many years! They treat us like family and always have the right plan for us. From Automobile  to Home to Rental to Life insurance and everything in between! We recommend them to all of our friends and family!

I have been here a few times and it has been great every time. Great dogs and the itialian beef sandwich is a must also. You are always treated like an old friend when you come there. The Chicago dog is great, you get the Snap from the hot dog like it should be.  I had the slaw dog the other day and had to get extra slaw to take home. Tell him captain Ron sent you.
Been going here for years, love love love this place! Yogart is great and the employees are always nice. Worth the trip from other side of town.

Absolutely one of the most amazing restaurants I've had the pleasure to dine in. This place is why I truly believe hole-in-a-wall spots are the best places to grab a bite. The restaurant is set up more like a take out than anything else. There are a few tables but mostly Pikpon was designed as a take out joint.

It was our first time here and I cannot resist but to get way more than we had the stomach for. Our waitress Aiko was very accommodating and extremely knowledgable of the menu. For appetizers, we got; deep fried spare ribs, steamed crab dumplings, larb with ground pork and Thai fish cakes. We also opted for the lunch special which came with a side of salad with thai peanut dressing and tom yum soup, the entree was Basil fried rice with chicken and I later ordered a bowl of stew noodles with beef. 

The salad came first and was easily the best way to start the meal. The salad mix was fresh and the peanut dressing sweet and delicious. It was gone the minute it hit the table. The larb came next and I was completely blown away. I am a huge fan of larb and it is very hard to find a place to make it authentically. Thankfully, Pikpon delivered in a big way. The fact that the chef was generous with the lime leaf in the salad got me extremely happy. The sauce was on point with the right amount of sweet and salty. Also, they didn't name this place Pikpon (pepper) for no reason, the larb had a strong kick to it. 

The basil fried rice had a lot of flavors, the dish was deceptively small looking as I kept eating but couldn't finish. You can taste all the ingredients here, you can tell it was freshly prepped. The fried rice was spicier than we had anticipated. Even though I didn't wanted to bother them since it was our fault for picking the spice level, the chef insisted on remaking our dish for us free of charge. Talk about excellent customer service!

The spare rib appetizer was crunchy and salty, the steamed crab dumplings were soft and delicate, contrasting the crisp texture of the ribs. I was pleasantly surprised with how flavorful the beef stew noodles was. I was glad they left out pigs's blood from the broth unless requested by more adventurous diner. The authentic version of this is called Boat noodles and they are always served with pig's blood. I was glad to not have it, I don't really like the irony after taste.

We ended the meal with Thai taro custard and pandan custard served with steamed bread for dipping. I checked in and got a free Thai iced tea, the restaurant also treated us to 2 free thai coffee after dinner. The taro pudding was an instant hit, it was a cross of an egg quiesce and a flan texturally and had chunks of taro throughout. The pandan pudding had a very creamy texture, it was definitely everything I wanted in a custard. The steamed bread soaked up all the custardy goodness. It was the perfect ending to a perfect meal. 

Awesome food, amazing service: shout out to Aiko and the talented chef Tommy for an amazing experience. I will be coming back with many many people!!
Best authentic Mexican food in the area. The staff is great and the food is fresh. The price point is awesome as well. Enjoy!!

My favorite place to get my nails done. Diane and her team are friendly and kind. They do whatever they can to keep their customers happy. I have been a loyal customer for 5+ years and will continue to go back. Nails are always done beautifully. Also the only place I trust to get my eyebrows done. Great place for all your needs! Highly recommend
Amazing! Michael was a great tour guide and quite scary stories. Would recommend all day!

Great find for authentic philly cheesesteak adjacent to the Philadelphia Italian Market. On our way to the airport, we diverted to George's to pick up a greasy hoagie to make others jealous on our crowded plane ride home. Despite the sogginess of being knocked around in a luggage bag for an hour, George's sandwich checked all the boxes and we look forward to returning to sit "al fresco" out front.

Given our philly cheesesteak ignorance, the boys behind the window explained the delicate process of constructing a proper cheesesteak, walking us through their choices of cheese, peppers, and onions, and chatting as the steak sizzled on the grill. Service and value were top-notch.

This place was a fantastic find! The fiancée planned a quiet weekend for us to celebrate our engagement and he did a great job in picking this place. It's is a small hotel located right on the beach. This property is very well maintained and it looks like it was recently remodeled( the new name is Hotel Sol.). It has a decently sized pool, grills right on the beach and lots of seating area. Our room had a kitchenette with a pretty good sized fridge.  The room was spotless. The housekeeping service does a fantastic job. The hammocks outside offer fantastic views and you truly feel like you are in paradise. We will definitely be back.

I sent a message through Facebook for a quote and some other information, and was greeted with a reply withing minutes.  I will be checking out the Center City location in the near future to repair a cracked iPhone screen.  And, will be sure to update this review about that service!

Really amazing. Not your traditional bfast place.  Very bright and clean.  Local artist work on display and for sale. Has a hip urban vibe. Food was amazing. Organic fresh ingredients come through. Waffles are some of the best I have ever had.  Grab a bite and walk across the street and your on the beach. Best breakfast brunch place in st Pete's so far.

Introducing YEG's first-ever Phoritto! 

Yes, it's exactly what it sounds like... pho (Vietnamese noodle soup) in the form of a burrito! But first, let's discuss where and when you can get this unique item.

Miss Saigon is the newest Vietnamese restaurant to open in the city. It's located less than 5 minutes from Whyte Ave. What makes this restaurant stand out from other Vietnamese restaurants would be the clear millennial influence and late night hours. On weekends, they are open till 4 AM. Perfect for the late night owls and partiers, considering their location as well! On weekdays, they are open till 12 AM. Their menu has a variety of traditional Vietnamese dishes (pho, vermicelli bowl, and rice dishes) as well as some Thai influenced dishes and Vietnamese fried rice dishes I haven't seen elsewhere. I love their menus! They were styled like a magazine with the history of pho and Vietnam travel tips in the front, followed by the actual food menu.

The bubble tea lightbulbs were probably one of my favorite part about this food adventure! They're so cute and they light up at the bottom as well. Perfect IG opportunity hehe. All of their bubble tea are served in these lightbulbs. For bubble tea, there's milk tea ($5.50), fresh fruit ($6.50), and slush ($5.50). I tried the matcha green tea slush and really enjoyed it. Although it was powder based, the taste of matcha was strong yet creamy at the same time. The restaurant actually gave us an avocado fresh fruit smoothie on the house so my friend was able to have a cute lightbulb drink as well!

Alright, now for the main review... the phoritto! I've seen this item on social media before but never thought I'd have the chance to try it in Edmonton. For $12, the phoritto is a decently filling size and is accompanied by a small bowl of meatball soup. The phoritto is stuffed with pho noodles, rare beef, bean sprouts, onions, and cilantro then wrapped in a tortilla wrap. There's hoisin sauce and sriracha sauce drizzled on the phoritto already. If you can't handle spice, like me, I suggest asking them for no sriracha sauce when you order! As I was eating it, I noticed that there was a bit more sauce throughout the phoritto. It did seem a bit dry towards each end, though. I'd say the meat got a bit dry and the tortilla got a bit boring to eat (if that makes sense??). I tried dipping the phoritto into the soup broth to solve the dryness but it didn't really work. My friend figured out another solution after we ate there, which is to take a bite of the phoritto then slurp up some soup broth with it. The phoritto held up pretty well as I ate it and didn't fall apart. It was certainly a different way to eat pho but I enjoyed it! For the soup, I thought it tasted fine but my friend tried it and said it tasted very salty (different taste buds, I guess?). The meatballs in the soup were very soft and tender, though.

My friend ordered their special beef noodle soup, which comes with slices of rare beef (or steak), brisket, and beef meatballs. There was a good amount of meat in it but the pho noodles were a bit clumpy. It was also lacking the variety of meats that you'd find in Pho Dac Biet at other Vietnamese restaurants such as flank and tendon. He ordered the regular size and said it filled him up. The other sizes offered for pho are large and xlarge. They also offer a "What the Pho Challenge" for those who want to challenge their eating abilities, and a $60 pho bowl for sharing amongst friends and family.

So verdict is: come and try the phoritto and order a cute lightbulb drink as well! Or have some pho when you're not sober on a Saturday night at 3 AM   I can see this place being busy on weekends since there's no other pho restaurant in the city opened past 9 PM I'm pretty sure! Best of luck to Miss Saigon!

Wow! Just wow! Came here with the family to get a variety of cheese and other goodies for our Christmas Eve dinner. We had excellent customer service even with having to wait to get in. The staff seemed very happy to help you. The assortment of meats, cheeses, pasta and so much more was a delight for all your senses. We ended up leaving with a ton of cheese and meats that we will thoroughly enjoy tomorrow night. Looking forward to coming back.

Tried to help my wife out with a bill by paying it while she was in the hospital unable to do it herself. Received another bill after she got out and she proceeded to pay them again. After she paid the bill thankfully she told me and I let her know that I had already paid it. Now they won't give us our money back without getting a statement from our bank and then bringing it to them. Guess they are not up to speed with online banking and email. Also they do not have on records that I paid. Well guess what? My online bank statement has proof. My guess is that they are that lazy, they don't even want to look up the transaction which they were happy to take over the phone with my debit card on 11/22/17. Go somewhere else, trust me they are not trustworthy at all and the headache after the sale/dental work is not worth the hassle here.

Came for a week for a BFF getaway week.  Property GORGEOUS. Our room overlooked pool and mountains!  Lots of places to snuggle down in a corner for quiet reading or playing games. Pool, hot tub (enormous), and cold spring pool all wonderfully relaxing, especially as resort was very empty.  "Flag" on lounge chairs to request bar service and food was GENIUS!

Restaurants clean and food generous!  Special kudos to Lindsey in Espazote restaurant who went out of her way to make up for the grumpy customer service of Gino and Maryann.  

Front desk exceptional. Kept having problem with room keys. They finally gave us a free drink in the bar...very kind.

Spa girls super friendly. Massage excellent.   Free bicycle every day....fun, but sore....next time bring padded bike shorts!  Free hour each day at country club driving range....SUPER fun to try, and pros available for about $85/hour for one hour lesson.  Have never laughed so much...especially intimidated when local young girls (probably on golf team) showed up and easily drove for the fences!  Trying it out was definitely a trip highlight.

Will definitely come again with our husbands.

LOVE THIS PLACE! We were at Perch and stopped by! We tasted all of the flavors and loved it. I now want them to do my wedding cakes and cupcakes!!!! SO AMAZING!!!! The only problem I had was the girl working didn't greet us or engage in selling the cupcakes. SMILE more! It won't hurt anyone:) a place like this needs a person who's happy to be there selling their yummy cakes! Beautiful! Glad we stopped by!

Went eclipse weekend and it was a insane wait and so busy when we were finally sat- food was very good but cold and / burnt.

The waiter noticed we hasn't eaten much and asked why. We explained - and she had the kitchen remade our whole meal again to go for us.
Very nice touch.

My new local go to spot for Indian good that I'm very glad to have it in my life. Pick up usually takes longer than expected but it is worth the wait. All your classics such as chicken tikka masala, lamb korma, naan, samosa and raita are all top notch but there are some more unique items worth trying too. This includes the gobhi manchurian (almost general tsos like) and spinach chaat (crunchy goodness). It's BYOB so looking forward at some point to eating inside too.

An interesting experience. 

Maybe they were busier than they anticipated. The food was good, but we requested salt and pepper upon delivery--20 minutes later we were half finished our meal and it still hadn't arrived. We were also not provided napkins. We watched for our waitress or other staff to grab someone's attention but were sadly unsuccessful. After our meal was cold, a gentleman finally approached to ask us how everything was. We explained our predicament, and without an apology, he righted the lack of salt and pepper and bestowed one napkin upon our group of three. One napkin.

I'm still confused.

They get three stars because the food was decent.

Hands-down the best bread in St. Louis. My favorite fast-casual spot to dine-in or carry out. Friendly, family-owned with a wonderful product. Favorites include: Turkey and Swiss, Salsiccia and the Prince. Their catering division is wonderful as well-they did our wedding welcome party and our guests loved the Chicken Spiedini!

Stoney's is by far my favorite liquor store. They have plenty of choices of craft beer, you can mix and match a bundle of them to try new beers, and they have a wide array of liquors, wines, and other spirits. They also have some juices and other mixers so you don't have to make two trips! They even have a shelf of snacks to choose from if needed. The staff has always been incredibly helpful and willing to listen to needs, as well as provide stories for a great customer service experience. I highly recommend visiting this store and becoming a regular!!!
Fun time. The beer selection was great, live music and a food vibe. We shared different appetizers and the service was good... very friendly.

I've only been here a few times but my gf and I went Friday night to celebrate my new job.  We got there and it was our waitress's first day on the job.  She did extremely well.  She kept our drinks full, the food was extremely good, and the restaurant was clean.  The only think that was a little bit of a disappointment was the price.  I think 30 bucks a person is extremely steep but that's just me.

A++ first time coming to Harrison Beach for a spray tan. Great experience! Wonderful, friendly staff named Emily explained the machine and was extremely nice. They didn't charge extra for the "sticky feet" needed that many places make you buy separately. $38 for spray tan with primer included is a great price. I will definitely come back!

My family is from Texas so I love some good BBQ. We had a pizza and pulled pork plate with Mac and cheese as a side. The flavor of of the food was great! The service was excellent! 

The only major critique of the food was the amount of grease. The pizza was becoming soggy because of the grease below it, and the Mac and cheese was swimming in it. I saw a previous review about the BBQ coming with "grocery store bread" on the side, but I was disappointed not to see that. Good BBQ is meant to be eaten with a solid square piece of white bread. Instead I was served with two small pieces of baguette toasted bread which I could only use with about a quarter of the meat. That being said the flavor of the pizza, pork and Mac and cheese was on point. 

I will go back to try more items because it was a comfortable friendly environment with excellent service and great flavored food!

my favorite place to get my groceries and produce. I do a one stop shop here most of the time since there have a huge variety of products. I also love their delicious food! staff super friendly ! can't get better than this!
Wonderful roll made right in front of you! I found that a great touch. I had the spicy crunchy roll and it was fantastic. Great flavor. Will definitely come back.

I won't return to this restaurant. It's especially not for health-minded eaters. There isn't much of a selection on the food menu. The salads were unique, but the house salad entree I ordered had a bunch of oil on it.  My dressing was on the side like I asked.  The side for almost all entrees is just garlic mashed potatoes.
The service was excellent but our appetizers weren't great. Very cool bar set up with tons of craft brew choices.

Saw this place on the Food network.  Had to try it out for myself.  I wasn't disappointed the sandwiches were very good and there were a lot of sauces to choose from I found 2 that I liked so I mixed them up. The sides were also good.

This place has a special place in my heart.  Arrived at about 2 PM & there were people getting their shaved lunch.  Seriously.   We had plans on going to lunch after eating our sno-bliz, but those plans went out the door.  I got a go-cup of piña colada w/ condense milk & I was full until dinner time.  Locals were hanging out in the mid-day September sun watching cars go by.  They were surprised to find tourist from CA there during the week.  Several people recounted their special long time connections to the place.  Lots of flavor combinations & local eatery recommendations.  It was a lovey time connecting with the locals while enjoying a beautiful afternoon.

Great place! The food was amazing. We got the platters with different meats and falafel. It was well served and delicious. The place is small and cozy, but I feel that if it was full it would feel a little crowded. Also, they were out of a couple things we wanted to get. Regardless, we had a great experience and would recommend it.

Ordered an omelette and was unusually surprised by how awesomely fresh the salsa was and how great my Omelette tasted. The mushrooms were so good too. It was a nice surprise to the usual omelettes that I get at other diners. The hashbrowns (tators) were perfectly done & crsipy! The coffee was good too!

Parks lincoln gave me an estimate of over $1300 just in parts to fix my head lights, I went to Extreme Auto Lights on Waters ave in Tampa and They Diagnosed the problem CORRECTLY and I walked out of there with head lights that worked and a bill of $211!  These guys were great, they did a great job and they were HONEST! They saved me almost $2000. I can't thank them enough for what they did. I can't say enough on how great this place is and the fact they could have taken me for a ride the way the Lincoln dealer was going to and they didn't. 

Thank YOU I love you guys

Fast and friendly service with an ecclectic decor. We were here to visit with friends and had a great time.  They had a terrific prime rib special served with a bad potato. We also ordered a spinach and cheese ravioli with shrimp. The food was great, we look forward to our next visit.

Thank you - thank you - I don't know the ladies name but (she walked with a limp her foot was injured )she was so awesome and helpful - I had been all over town looking for a rim to match my car because I hit an Indiana pot hole and cracked rim. She was the only one out of four tire automotive location willing to search her data base and find the exact tire rim to match the others I am so happy. Thank you service parts lady you are awesome.

This was my first and only experience with The Beer Store. I went in to purchase a gift card. Upon entering, there was no one at the register at the front of the store. I waited around for a little, walked up and down an aisle, and still, no one had come to the register. I then went to the bar area in the back, where no more than 8 people were seated around the bar. There was one bartender, with whom I made eye contact as I stood behind a bar stool. She was conversing with a couple about personal matters - this conversation continued, as I stood there, obviously waiting for initial service. The bartender, after making eye contact with me (seeing I was there, clearly), did not take a moment to step away from her personal conversation to see if I needed anything. After standing there, waiting around for more than a minute, I walked out. There was still no one at the front register area, nor did the bartender ever make any effort to serve me. I went to another craft beer store in the area instead, and received excellent and immediate customer service. I would not recommend The Beer Store to others, solely for the fact that I value customer service, and feel that this establishment is severely lacking in that department.

What a wonderful dinner I just ate! Came here with five friends and the table we had was extremely accommodating. Love the mood lighting and stone tables. Our waitress, Stacey, was extremely lovely and answered all our questions! We had the rock shrimp and edamame as appetizers which both were very delicious! We shared a bunch of special rolls as well as sushi. The fish was very fresh and the soy sauce was very good! Overall a fabulous experience! Will be back soon!!!!
Best brunch I've had in New Orleans. Shrimp bloody Mary's, fried green tomatoes. What more can you ask for.

It was my first visit to this restaurant. I expected the traditional wait to be seated routine. It was totally different. You go up to the desk to order and pay. Then you can choose up to three different rooms to sit in and someone brings your food. Our Service was great and food was hot and very tasty!! We will be back.

Yummy pancakes! I got the peach pancakes and it comes with 3 pancakes with peaches and whipped cream on top. There could have been less syrup on the peaches as it was a little too much sugar, but the peaches were spiced well. The whipped cream was fresh out of a bucket. They scooped it on to the plate right before serving. It was a busy place, but I still got out in about 30-40 minute (it was just a party of one though). I would recommend it!

Great experience with Ben who guided us to the perfect place.  He was very attentive to our needs and guided us to the best apartment for our needs.  We were moving from Vermont and were more than a bit overwhelmed with the search for an apartment.  Ben made the process effortless and enjoyable!

I would highly recommend Nashville Apartment Locators to anyone!

I ate here some time ago, I thought the food was okay when it was fresh, but upon eating the next day, only 1 star. I noticed it was extremely oily that actually defied explanation and then made my stomach hurt. 

I don't mind oil either, but something was off, maybe old oil, to much oil, not really sure, but it didn't become apparent until the next day, then I was just grossed out by the experience. 

I would try them again, so that's why the 3 stars for now. On the plus side the hot mustard was probably the king of hot mustards, I literally had to be super careful on not getting to much, and I did choke. I would give the hot mustard 5 stars. 

Value equation wise, I felt the place was pricey, but if I didn't have the terrible oily experience, I could have seen myself dining again as the flavors were elevated compared to most food in this town.

Bright spot in New Orleans French Quarter. We had an amazing lunch here. Excellent service! Food was so good. Oysters, pasta, shrimp, all cooked perfectly. Please give them a try you will not be dissapointed.

First off I have to say I absolutely love the atmosphere at Joe's Crab Shack! It is a great location, right by the river with outdoor patio seating which is awesome exclamation mark inside it's comfortable you can bring your kids and make all the noise you want because it's loud in there. The volume is the biggest drawback. Also absolutely love the dancing servers!! The music is from my generation which is so cool and when they get down they really do it right!

The prices are competitive, just wish most of the seafood wasn't over cooked every single time I go in there. Everything else on the menu that I've tried is good. Salads are fresh drinks are good lots of options on the menu. Just please stop over cooking the seafood! I know we're inland, but surely someone has to know how to prepare seafood properly. Do that and I'll give you more stars.

The doctors here have hearts of gold, and always go above and beyond for my pups. I wouldn't take Memphis and Hercules anywhere else. 

My dog Memphis has a very painful medical condition, and when he goes into one of his spells, they are always available to help him get some relief. We usually see Dr Hale, but the other vets there are just as caring and thorough. 

Thank you for being so ever caring!

Wow!! What an amazing burger!! I ordered the ESTATE BURGER with Angus and was not disappointed. I asked for the sweet red onion marmalade on the side but ended up eating every last drop! I gave the experience 4 stars due to my truffle Parmesan fries being weak in the truffle oil/Parmesan department. Boo!! Other than that, my burger was phenomenal!
It was my first time coming to this location. The service was a disappointment. We were not greeted at all. Our table was not clean and had to request for it to be cleaned. The food was mediocre.

I just want to let you know that this is my favorite and also highly recommended place for cleaning my vehicle to my friends and family. It's almost therapeutic to me. Stu always gives the best customer service and puts a smile on everyone's face. It's nice to have a place with multiple stations to vacuum my car, that contains little stations for single use items within it, like; Armor All, Tire shine, glass cleaning wipes, and different car scent options. After that, I scrub my rims with a special brush at a different station and I like to use their automatic car wash(Supreme) to keep my car looking new. They also have the option to wash your car by hand. When ever someone tells me my car looks nice and clean, I tell them that I went to Earthwash, where it's located, and that I like to go once a week if I can..and that's because I like quality, and those who are close to me know that. I want them to have the best too!
I love the chicken Parmesan, but i order it with spinach tagliatelle and they never get it right! So check your order if you are doing take out.

Terrible customer service. Employees are racist even though black people keep the store running. I've shopped there for years and I've never been greeted, asked if I needed help or told to have a good day. One thing employees will do is stalk your every move without even welcoming you to their store. They treat black customers as if they are thieves. They don't value their returning customers at all. If you're reading this, take your money somewhere else where you're dollar is appreciated. They're prices are high anyway. I repeat take your hard earned money somewhere else. Zero stars or a negative amount is not allowed, my true rating for hair town is -5 stars.

Who would have known! Food here is delicious. Can't really go wrong. Specials like chicken and waffles are always a nice surprise too. Definitely a unique and fresh menu for a "department store". Staff is friendly, can get crowded on weekends but they provide you with a buzzer so you can shop while you wait for your table. Unfortunately, deserts are amazing too! Be hungry.

Drove 5 hours from San Francisco to Reno to see a specific car at this dealer, and they told me it just sold when I got there. I had been communicating via text with a salesman at this lot the day before, and confirmed that I would arrive at a specific time to test drive this car.  I was never notified that the car sold until I arrived, I am very disappointed to say the least. Just happens to be my birthday today as well, happy birthday to me huh?

Great local bar! I love the portobello sandwich. It's marinated in balsamic too. So yummy! The Hoppy Ass beer is a great IPA at an unbelievable price. Great place to meet with friends for food and drinks. It is also kid friendly. The also have a chess game if you want to play with your friend while enjoying a cold beer!
Great vegan spot in Pottstown. Nice cozy different  interior . They also do vegan cooking classes and smoothies

Rescue is a world class spa and Philadelphia (and now, NYC!) destination. Sublime facials and skin products, wonderful manicures and pedicures that last and last, expert massages, festive events and generous samples, hair and make up applications like no-other. Again and again, I walk in frumpy and tired... and walk out energized, nourished, glowing and polished from head to toe. Thank you Danuta Mieloch and your superb team for creating a place of refuge, calm and beauty in the middle of our metropolis.  

Rescue Spa NYC is gorgeous!

The restaurant was delicious and beautiful place to relax and enjoy the scenery. Our server Steven was outstanding and gave us great advice about what to get. I will definitely be coming back here next time.

I loved the German Christmas market in Chicago and was so excited to hear  Carmel Indiana was going to have one as well. Hubby and I took our two grandkids to have a look.
The setting was cute with their wooden chalets for each vendor.
Each of the little buildings were selling German wares or food. Most all the items were high dollar. Hubby saw a cuckoo clock for several thousand dollars! 
I told the kiddos we would get a hot pretzel and a Christkindle boot mug, but the lines were too long and there were no mugs to be seen.
White Christmas lights adorned the entire area. They had some pretty gas fires along side the ice rink to warm yourself.
The ice rink was small but nicely done. It looked like a two hour wait to skate. I don't know, but I'm guessing they limited time and people on the ice.
Why three stars you ask, it was cute but, very sterile. It did not seem homey or welcoming at all. Seemed like a Stepford wife atmosphere. Lol!The buildings had an emptiness about them even though each one sold a nice product from Germany. $$$$
Parking wasn't too bad. We got there about an hour after it opened and used the parking garage nearby. 
Yes, this is their first year, so hopefully next year will be more inviting. We may go back,  but right now my memories are....meh....

I hate to give 1 star, but in my opinion that was the wash was worth. I paid $16 for the "works" and my car came out as if it just got washed with rain. They don't clean the windows nor vacuum the interior for you, you have to do it yourself, which is ok but not for $16. I took another car to another car wash right after and got it hand washed for $13 and ended up with way better results.

First time and last here.... just ordered 3 drinks and realized I forgot my cigarettes in my truck went grabbed them and upon reentering was told they were over capacity and couldn't reenter, I would have to wait in a line 40 people deep and wait until people left meanwhile my beers I just paid for I could not enjoy.

I am not new to sushi restaurants. I have been to many, and have a definite idea of what good sushi is and what bad sushi is. This was BAD sushi. As a USF student, getting 10% off by showing my ID is very exciting. Unfortunately, I would have rather paid more elsewhere and received an edible dinner. 

The first red flag was showing up at "happy hour" and there being only one other group inside the restaurant. The menu for happy hour sushi was also more expensive than their regular menu for the same items, which was confusing. Another red flag was that most of the rolls listed were marked with an asterisk as cooked...when there is only a handful of raw sushi options, you know your meal is going to be questionable. 

I started with the ginger salad, which was a laughable loose handful of iceberg lettuce, string cut carrots, and a swamping of dressing. I could have poured the leftover, watery dressing into a wine glass. I asked about their special, which I think was called "Smokey", because I am a fan of smoked raw salmon...the waiter cringed and recommended I try something else. I should have left after that. 

The smoked salmon was listed as cooked, which also shocked me because anywhere else I go, restaurants cold-smoke their fish. It shouldn't be cooked at all, just flavored with smoke. After inquiring about the Salmon Lover's smoked roll, the waiter said that yes, it's cooked, but it has the texture of raw fish. Sounds fake, but okay...I ordered it, hoping I was misunderstanding him.

The rolls came out quickly, but the meal itself would have gone quicker had they just thrown it into the trash after making it rather than bring it to my table. The "smoked" salmon didn't taste smoky, and they had the texture of raw fish because it WAS raw--and beyond safe food temperatures! it didn't flake like cooked salmon and was slimy. It tasted spoiled. The tempura flakes inside the roll also had a disgusting, bitter taste that overpowered the entire roll. I didn't eat the rest of it, and hoped they'd take it off my bill. It was $12 for that monstrosity, and I was praying that I didn't get food poisoning from the few bites I risked. I told the waiter I didn't like it, and when he returned with my bill, the nasty roll remained but it appeared he had removed the cost of my $2 salad. Yippee.

Ultimately, the whole experience was absurd and a waste of time. I was there with two other friends, one of which who also eats raw sushi and didn't enjoy her experience either, and one who exclusively eats cooked rolls. She thought her food was good. 
If your frame of reference of good sushi is cooked(?) or store-bought, this is your place.
Otherwise, save your money and avoid food poisoning--STAY AWAY!
I will never be coming back here.

Got in under the wire for their pre fixe lunch deal. Had the goat cheese and shrimp crepe to start. Must admit I've had these before at FQF,, and as usual outstanding. Wifey ordered the fire grilled pork chop with red beans and rice.  I ordered the blackened catfish. Oops, several minutes after ordering told they ran out of the catfish. Oh well, nothing wrong with a pork chop for lunch.  It was fantabulous..tender, and you could tell it was fire grilled by the grill marks and the flavor. Oh we had a curry tomato crab soup, also outstanding. Also included was a glass of wine. $20.00 bucks!!@@ are you kidding me. Going back tomorrow.

My husband and I ate here while shopping in Metairie. We decided we felt like having sandwiches, so I opened Yelp and this spot grabbed my attention. I was very pleased we decided to eat here. There are many sandwich options, as well as a really nice side selection. They also have small plates for those who are not very hungry and also kid options. Not to mention, there is also a full bar. The atmosphere is friendly, inviting and casual. It's not a place to impress a date at, but it is a nice, chill spot with good food. I had the Cuban sandwich with parmesan fries and the hubby had a club sandwich with regular fries. We both enjoyed our quick meal here and have stated we will more than likely be back!

I was unsure of trying this restaurant because it's become such a huge tourist attraction, but I was super impressed. Oh my god, delicious, mouthwatering food! I got the local burger and was blown away. It has lamb in it, which is a huge win for me. If you visit, you have to try this! The fries were amazing, too. Can't go wrong with this spot!

Marie was so charming. You walk in and she greets you warmly. 


Great food and I love the atmosphere. The Capri was delicious and I can't wait to try all their other sandwiches.

They also have some unique sandwiches for vegetarians that look quite filing and yummy. 

During lunch time they were able to keep the lining moving quickly.

Lastly, they had tasteful Christmas music playing like Josh Groban and Michael Buble. Not many places in the city have Christmas music playing so it was very welcomed

UPDATED FOR NEW MENU ITEMS I'VE TRIED:
Since my first visit, Better Byrd has joined my weekly rotation between its other sister restaurants, Fresh kitchen and Ciccios. I have gotten takeout here numerous times and my go to takeout here is the bowls . Of all the bowls (9 dollars), that  I've tried, pesto byrd, Brussels, Bangkok/ thai peanut, the Thai bowl is my absolute favorite.  For my base I get couscous. I have gotten the Bangkok dozens of times now, which has Thai flavors with its peanut sauce, chopped peanuts and pickled carrots. Peanut sauce is so freakin good. I always get an extra one to go with my bowl. Additional sauces and dressings except the peanut sauce  is 25 cent extra.  Was not a fan of their pull roasted chicken so  after my first try Ive always paid an extra 1 dollar to substitute grill chicken .  The pull and roasted chicken  doesn't have much flavor for me.  Doesn't taste seasoned at all, just plain boiled chicken pulled apart is what it taste like. 

I've tried The cheesy chik sandwich which comes on artisanal English muffin, whipped goat cheese spread and  pepper-jelly. This  is my favorite sandwich here. I don't need to try the whole menu to tell you this is my favorite chicken sandwich here, simply because I loooove goat cheese and that spread is  like a goat cheese cream cheese. The texture so smooth. The artisanal English muffin is the best English muffin I've ever had. It ain't no ordinary English muffin! You can tell  just looking at it. The inside is thicker than usual English muffin, but so soft and a little buttery. The pepper jelly is perfect zing but not that spicy and just sweet enough.  I was excited to try it and compare to a similar sandwich I had at Maple Street Biscuit Company. I can say this is my favorite of the two. The  goat cheese spread takes it easily. 

Not a fan of their Mac and cheese. I would not order it again. The cheese sauce was way to thin and barely coated the macaroni shells. It really looks like a macaroni salad with mayo (just look at the pics), and not a cheese sauce because of how thin sauce was. The jalapeños was lackluster and the side just tasted like meh. The Parmesan truffle fries (5 dollars)  on the other hand is great. The portion size is like a large fry order. They do not skimp on their truffle oil! It can be a bit  excessive  on the bottom, but I don't mind it since it doesn't soak too much into the fries and make them soggy. I like the extra pool on the bottom to slide my fried from the top that don't have enough truffle oil. My boyfriend and I always opt to share them because of  portion and richness of the Parmesan and truffle oil. 

My dad got the wings and he said they were good. I liked that they're flashfried instead of breaded and deepdried. I think this is the best of both, where it's a cross between grilled and fried. There's some char to them as well. I think the wings could stand alone without sauce. My dad wanted spicy wings and the server taking our order at register suggested that Nashville hot was their "spiciest." It was not spicy enough for my dad. 

BetterBYrd does not and will not take your order for pick up over the phone! Ive  tried. They explained that the register does not give you the option to leave ticket open and not take payment before closing the order and moving to a new one. You must use their app, which lately has been clitchy. I've only order bowls to go on the app.  Sometimes the bowl doesn't come as described  even when I don't remove ingredients. It specifically states"select to remove" and I never click them to  remove, I just substitute grilled chicken. So I try to type in the special instructions," make as described" but only gives you 25 characters, because I also have to specify I want additional sauces on top of what comes standard with the bowl. There's always some confusion and a lot of times I have to check I got the extra sauce. I could go on and on about my mishaps with the app. But overall I don't find it user friendly in getting the item prepared correctly.

I'd give zero stars if I could. The first time i tried them my car wasn't cleaned very well, but I thought it was just a fluke. I tried again and the second time my car came out with a scratch on the hood. I then decided to try them for auto detailing and requested a hand car wash instead. The detailing was awful. I still had water spots. They didn't fix the hard water spots that I talked indepthly about with the on-site manager. I will never go back, especially for car detailing. Its pathetic.

Fun place to socialize with friends! Lots of fun activities and great service.

I came with a party of 3 on a Thursday night, right before a huge crowd of people. Despite the sudden increase in business, our server was still incredibly prompt about making sure we had what we needed. When we decided to retreat to one of the karaoke rooms and had some technical difficulties, someone was right there to help us out. I will be recommending this place to all of my friends!

This place has a classic feel to it due to the furniture and the layout of the store, which is entirely open without any dividers or nooks. It does appear that many families like coming here. The coffee itself is very mediocre. It is something that I could make in my home kitchen very easily. The French pastries are good enough for what they are. This place is more atmosphere than anything else.
Hands down the BEST Trinidadian restaurant in the area! My wife and I love their vegetable roti. The atmosphere and the entire staff make you feel at home. A true gem on north Broad street!

Here's what we liked:
- family style atmosphere, you feel like you're in their home
- friendly and fast, no fuss service
- portion sizes are decent for what you pay

Here's what we didn't like:
- the burnt ends were too salty and slathered in a sauce - would have been good to taste the smokiness, not the sauce
- the brisket was ok, well cooked but we just didn't care for the honey bbq sauce we asked for and they put all over
- the mac'n'cheese was terrible - overcooked and blend

As a disclaimer, we are new of the area and are accustomed to great KC style BBQ so we realize the southern style sauces are different.

Still rate it a 3 cause it was A-OK and I love to support independent, family-owned and operated places.
Delicious! We had the warm and cold lobster rolls and both were great.  Bread was amazing too!  A little on the expensive side but you get what you pay for and it was quality food.
O my went one time but the dishes we tried were great!  Nice home cooked food experience, home in the wall place

I realize they have not been open that long but the ambience is like a homeless shelter. I agree with a previous reviewer say that they need more than cheap picnic tables for seating, my back is screaming when I leave. Torn scotch taped paper signs on the door is what greets you along with a floor that has seen some wear and tear.
Now all you "beer heads" that are going to say sure but what about the beer? I did like the beer but we now have other craft breweries in the area that are doing a helluva job as well who can match the beer in my very humble opinion. I think that this is the most unappetizing establishment I have ever been in. I am hoping that this will soon change because this is not where I would feel comfortable taking a date.

For a restaurant which just opened, they are doing very well.  Sushi is definitely high standard as are the cocktails.  Sake menu is non existent yet (one house sake on offer when we were there) but should be coming along. 

Loved the lobster fried rice as it was not greasy and cooked to perfection.  The kind where you can taste each rice grain. 

Tuna crudo was clean and tasty and I would definitely order it again when I come back. 

I loved my nigiri pieces, cut well and tasted great.  Not sure why they didn't dab a bit of wasabi under the fish but I adjusted my own wasabi so no biggie..  My wife's Sindy roll was very tasty by fell apart way too easily. 

Very modern casual ambiance and pleasant staff made for a great overall experience. 

Location is great and I hear parking deal (validation) is coming as parking could be challenging. 

Not many places in Philly serving good sushi, this place is and I welcome them.

I wish you guys at the Tuna Bar lots of luck and success and hope you keep the great atmosphere, quality ingredients and quality chefs cutting away for a very long time! Congratulations!

I went there on my birthday in November. Wonderful atmosphere, large rooms. I usually don't like to sit at a booth but this was pretty nice and spacious. Our beer was great, table side guacamole was excellent. My dinner was churrasco burger. Dessert was my least favorite, it was a cake of some sort. A little pricey on the tab...
This was such a fun and great experience. Loved the atmosphere and the food was great! Loved the bread & pasta & appetizers!

I don't like to leave negative reviews, but sometimes it's necessary. I'm sure their food is good although I wasn't able to try it and I'm not sure I'll attempt to again. It seems that they need to work on their organization and professionalism. I called the day before and confirmed a reservation with them over the phone. I had to call several times to get someone to pick up the phone and the voicemail it went to said it was full. I thought that was strange but gave them the benefit of the doubt as they could have been busy. We were running a bit late so we rushed to get there on time. The restaurant was empty and not even open. There was a sign on the door saying it was closed for the holidays. This was on a Saturday the 23rd. I had specifically asked if they were open and confirmed the reservation with them. I read Max's review about them screwing up his reservation and thought maybe that was just a one time error. I guess not. I hope they can improve in this area because it seems that people enjoy the food. If walking in, you should be ok. Just be aware if you are making reservations. The good thing that came out of it was that we were able to try another restaurant close by which was very good (Bakersfield Nashville).

They don't just have great cookies, cupcakes, and puddings! I ordered a salted caramel cake for a birthday party, and it was amazing - four layers of moist cake with caramel buttercream between each layer. I checked before I ordered to make sure that the icing would be from real ingredients. Indeed - it's made from butter and sugar, and it tastes like it. The cake was both elegant and delicious, a rare combination.

It takes me a really long something as big as a tattoo. It took me a month to decide what exactly I wanted, and it took me a week of research to find out where I wanted to go. I made the best decision choosing New Generation Inc. Billy was so nice, and super patient with my indecisiveness: where to place the tattoo, how big I wanted it, how I wanted it faced, Etc. He sat down with me and researched different hummingbirds I would like, and gave me his honest opinion on what would look the best. I love my piece and all the detail he included in such a small tattoo, will definitely be visiting him again!

Finally came here after yelp showed  photos of the 3 feet long dosa! Gotta go where food is as large as an elementary schooler. Also I worked with a phenomenal cook whose day job is an engineer and he recommended Dosa Hut. 
Took my son and texted some friends and we were off to enjoy some Southern India Cuisine. 
The non exciting and kind of hidden building is behind Patel brothers and keeps looking. Next to Subway and the bank. You actually can drive through the Habitat parking lot and see the white building. Door is also non descriptive. 
Maybe at best 9 tables and a RAJ will come out. Both Gentlemen  have the first part of their names as Raj. I worked with one of them too, different guy from above. Water comes out in bottles and the Mango Lassie was one of the best I have had but son said I was over the top on that.
We ordered samosas for a friend, he left so we did not try. Had chicken Tila and the thaili with the non vegan version. So good and ordered more sodas that did not come out as we were full by that time. 
Probably one of favorite Indian restaurants in town. Next time going to get the 3 foot dosa.
Hailey helped me with a large lunch catering order.. went perfect.. easy ordering, beautiful set up and on time. I'd give it a 10 if I could.

A fantastic 1.5 hour walking tour to learn about the history of Nashville - its founding, its capital, its buildings both old and new, Andrew Jackson, women's suffrage, lunch counter sit-ins, the Ryman, Skull's, Printer Alley, and of course its music. Ryan is a great story teller and makes history come alive as we walked the streets of days gone by to the bustling music filled streets of today. Highly recommend.

Awful business model it took forever to even figure out where to order. on top of that the workers actually are not professional at all. on top of THAT my other half sandwhich didn't even have sausage covering even half of the bread. easily worst place i've been in a while

Just when you thought you were gonna be good and stay healthy with the Taco Salad.

Until you get it in their Taco Shell. These taco shells are IT. 

I'm surprised I haven't reviewed TacoSon earlier - I've been going here for years. Their burritos are the best items in my opinion, everything else is standard with some variation.

However... they make fresh tamarind juice (tamarindo). And fresh hibiscus juice. Super hard to find these made fresh, and they nailed it.
I have been going to Gena for over 20 years and I can honestly say she is the best in the area! The salon is run very organized!!! You can't go wrong coming here!!!!

Had ribs, greens & butter beans. The ribs were pulled early so they could clean the grill,  so they mixed their priorities. Delicious beans cooked with ham & the greens we're pretty plain. Found a free place to park. Very spacious,  but noisy.

Called service 5:15 pm Wed and they had appt window narrowed to between 9 and 10 am the next day.  Andy Y  arrived punctually, made diagnosis inside of 10 minutes and provided reasonable options for blocked drain pan n valve leading to recurring locked freezer drawer on 7 yo Samsung reefer.  Got the drawer to open, removed ice, stripped unit down front n back, cleaned dual freezer compartment drain tubes showing both to me, filled with very gnarly, moldy scummy stuff.  I paid the $89 minimum diagnostic fee plus another $54 or so as Andy's work came to $143 which the minimum fee was credited toward.  I could have googled more self repair vids, spent thrice the time making a mess and twice the $$$ for Andy or others to fix my inevitable misadventure.  So naturally I was very happy to get my freezer back in less than 24 hours for $143.  Your mileage may vary!

I got the gator bites and the brisket.
The gator was fantastic, but the brisket was really fattening.
When coming into the restaurant it was freezing.
The service was fantastic and real quick. The place
was packed, but still got seated and got my food right away.
I do think they could reduce the price of gator and brisket. 
My total bill came to $43

Outstanding food and service. The only challenge was that one plate came late so we didn't get to eat together. Overall though a great experience and we will be back!

My wife and I had breakfast combo number one and it was awesome. A lot of food!!!

My son had steak fajitas and he really enjoyed it. 

Can't wait to come back

These guys make great Greek food - not just gyros! I know they have been busy both times we've eaten in...and their food truck party was a success as well!  Today I'm having spanakopita and souvlaki skewers (chicken) served with lemon & toast while my husband is getting the lunch special of gyro, patates (seasoned fries) & a soda!  The chicken is tender & squeezing lemon on it lifts it up further! And I always grab fries - even if I don't have my own order- they are SO good! 
Order at the counter & wait for the goods - and it is worth the wait! If only they were closer to the hill I would come for lunch on a workday, but for now I have to come on my rare days off! 
They do have a few special dessert items...one of these times I'll have to get dessert first so I have room! I've not had room for dessert yet - their servings are generous so I leave feeling full!

The play area is great really huge! Parents don't have to bend over too bad in some areas. I'd say my only complaints is the cleanliness of the place, from stray socks and food in play areas to the huge dust bunnies is places. A lot of staff standing around and gossiping. There are a few good ones walking around at least they look busy. Oh and the washrooms are dirty too, in fact all the clean supplies are on the ground and easily accessible to kids. Also hubby took kid here twice and had trouble with waiting for food. Cause the staff was asking if they ordered it first instead of checking if it was actually for a customer. They were compensated thankfully. All in all great place for your kids to run off steam, be cautious of other kids cause some parents don't watch theirs, and be wary of the food and cleanliness. I mean it is a kids playground after all.

My girlfriend and I order out often. Tonight the girl working takeout (didn't get her name) was a total gem. I forgot to mention on the phone that my girlfriend can't have cheese on her veggie wrap. We had to come back and she took care of us without question, even though it was my fault. Food was great! She deserves a raise!

I had a great experience with Orsini's Auto Body.

Was in a weather induced accident on the evening of December 13th. The next morning I was paging through Yelp to find a local auto body store I could take my car to as my BMW dealer did not do any body work. To my luck, I came across Orsini's. Joe was very pleasant to deal with from the start and was very honest and up front. In a situation where most people would panic and be worried about leaving their car with an auto body that no one recommended them to, I felt completely fine with leaving my car with Joe and his team.

The initial estimate was 14 days but somehow Joe managed to replace my bumper, grill, hood, radiator and some other parts in a matter of 3 days, all using genuine BMW parts(new).

Everything went smoothly with insurance and I did not have to get involved in anything else along the long. I received prompt updates during the week on how everything was going.

Would highly recommend Orsini's to any of my friends or anyone in Delco that is looking for body work for their cars.

Hope I don't need to come back (lol) but if something happens I know who i can go to.

Best cheesesteak period. There is no geno, there is no pat, there is no tony, there is only Dalessandro. If you want an authentic, real cheesesteak with whiz (which, don't lie to yourself, you want it) come over to this side of the river and change your life. You will never regret it, ever. 

PS: bring cash. They don't have time for credit cards.

Beautiful restaurant in a great location!  Came in for dinner before heading to a show at The Straz. Best decision I made that day for sure!  I made reservations for an early dinner so I was seated at a comfortable booth. 

Menu was steak centric for sure so I went with the Ribeye. I also indulge in calamari, raw oysters and a bottle of Groth Cab. Service was top notch and the experience was first class all the way. 

The ribeye was spot on mid-rare. Calamari was the best I've had in Florida and the oysters (blue points) were as fresh as could be. 

And you know what else happened?  The GM, AGM and Executive Chef all stopped by the table to ensure everything was perfect. I felt like a Zagat critic!  

Next time I'm in Tampa I'm making Timpano my first stop. 

Apparently they treat everyone like a big shot there...

My boyfriend and I recently discovered this new restaurant while Yelp-hunting for cheap, filling eats near out apartment. Both of us wanted something warm and satisfying, while I was craving something vegetarian with a brewing Hanger (my boyfriend's greatest fear). Yeeroh was the perfect solution, with the addition perk of finally putting to rest my confusion on how the word "gyro" is pronounced!!

The venue is very hip and clean (exposed brick, twinkle lights, trendy music); there are several tables, but they are obviously catering toward quick meals and takeout. Staff was awesome, very friendly and efficient. Yeeroh's menu offers Classic Sandwiches (set ingredients) as well as build-your-own sandwiches, a variety of starters, and some desserts. Each sandwich comes with a choice of zucchini fries or regular fries - you can choose to have them put into your gyro, or you can opt to have them on the side.

We decided to start with Feta Fries, which are similar in concept to Mozzarella sticks with a less Instagrammable cheese pull. But the feta flavor with the wonderfully seasoned and crispy coating really hit the spot, and successfully stemmed the Hanger while we waited for our gyros. I ordered a lovely vegetarian gyro on a wheat pita. The warm grilled veggies are well seasoned and paired perfectly with fresh spinach, tomato, and cucumber  that I opted for. The zucchini fries were amazing - thinly sliced, crispy, and indulgent but still "healthy" (I.e. guilt-free!). My boyfriend ordered The Diavolo - this monster of a sandwich is perfect for those who are hungry and those who love spice. It's stuffed with chicken, spicy feta sauce, GHOST PEPPER HOT SAUCE, pepperonis, and fries (yes the fries are IN the gyro). My boyfriend loved it, and I definitely had a few bites and many stolen fries. It may be that my boyfriend and I are used to spicy foods and have had our taste buds burned off, but The Diavolo wasn't overwhelmingly spicy. It definitely had a good kick, but anyone who can handle Hot Cheetos would be able to handle The Diavolo.

We ended our meal with Baklava (because when there is baklava, you can't not order it). It was a tad pricey at $5.50 a piece, but it's a decently large piece. I'm a bit of a baklava snob so I wouldn't say it was anything special, but I definitely enjoyed it.

To conclude, I must emphasize how generous the portions are, given the price. For less than $10 a person, you will get both quality and quantity. Definitely planning on returning here if I need a quick take-out meal, regardless of whether I'm feeling more of a #cleaneats or a #treatyoself mood!

I was really looking forward to this spot b/c I love wings. Their wings were not that good and their service sucked. The environment and ambiance was awful. Place felt dirty and outdated, that spotlight lighting has got to go. The only thing that's good about this spot is their beer selection. 

I hated how they put the wings on top of the fries. The fries soaked up all the sauce and made the fries soggy. 

I'll pass on this spot.

We had an office, holiday dinner at Radice recently.  This was my first experience eating there as it was highly recommended by others.  I must admit though, I was a little underwhelmed.  I thought the service was great, and the appetizers our waiter recommended were quite tasty.  For my entrée, I ordered the sea bass filet.  It was cool in temperature and kind of soggy and flavorless.  I love great seafood and I know it when I taste it.  This was not.  Maybe I just ordered the wrong thing - but it did not wow me at all.  The atmosphere is very contemporary and a bit stark and cold with it's white walls and lack of pictures or color.  For the prices, I am not sure I would run back to this place.  Just being honest.

Another year, another new Honda !
Drove just under an hour to get the car I wanted at the price I wanted.  Once again, our local dealer couldn't touch this deal.
Thanks Vince, Tony, and Adam ! !

The food was very good and portions were large. However, the service was not the greatest. 
For that reason, I had to give it four stars. 
And it was not cheap. 
All in all, if they can work on the service, an above average steakhouse.
Everything tasted fresh, wish we'd have ordered the sandwich warm. The garlic parm fries were on point!

Great place to stop in for a sandwich in Broad Ripple. All their food is really flavorful and have a large variety of Cuban food. This was the first time I had even had Cuban cuisine and it definitely did not disappoint.

I would highly recommend stopping in for a quick lunch if you are ever in Indianapolis.

People know that I love QDOBA and I'm thrilled to have them so close to my house.  The crew are always friendly and helpful...  Maybe too helpful?  They give my wife whatever she wants, but it's just so challenging to close that tortilla...  The newer pricing model from when they reopened a few years ago is one set price for all toppings.  Maybe my wife should specify she'll want one of everything...   I dunno...  I don't know if I've ever eaten here though, it's usually just a quick pickup and I'm back home.

Nice little industrial place! The design was super clean and aesthetically pleasing. I loved how the place was an open concept. The kitchen was super exposed. The place was extremely clean. The guy who took my order was probably one of the nicest humans I've ever met. We got two chicken sliders, fries, and 2 donuts. The sliders and fries reminded me of chic fa la, except gourmet. Everything was pretty good. I do wish the food was a tad more flavorful. The donuts were a tad disappointing. They have them out in the open, for lord knows how long. We got the cranberry pomegranate and chocolate glaze. As far as the toppings were concerned they were absolutely to die for. Super fresh and tasty. I haven't tasted chocolate that good in an extremely long time. But the actual donut was cold, dry, and kind of stale. They would have been better if they were warm and fresh. That kind of took me by surprise. They are popular because of their donuts, but because of the way they store them they are stale. Maybe they could see about storing them a different way.

This is by far my most favorite place to go for Asian cuisine. The owner is extremely nice and friendly and he only delivers the highest quality food. The dumplings are made fresh, never frozen out of a bag. He uses fresh veggies and high quality meats. The sauces and broths are amazing. This place is the best around!

Listen. If Kekes up the street can handle a massive line out the door and Still have great service and food delivery at the perfect time, the Village INN can also get it together and provide the same service. They need better management even though we did get the bill paid for by her, we weren't looking for a hand out we were looking for great tasting food as well as a taste of their pies which they claim to be known for. Again, with a change of menu, cooks, and management, this place and totally be eclectic, fun and interesting. There was a server we saw that was Awesome ! She was on point and organized we wished we did have her but instead we ended up with a young lady who really didn't want to work today. I get it but you are working in a industry that is brutal and your customer service and organizational skills is important.
Great spot close to my home!I walked right in and Becca hooked me up with a sweet cut ,will def be back

Stopped in for lunch. This was my 2nd visit. I got a spinach and feta croissant which was yummy. There are several different things to choose from and the prices can't be beat. Last time, I had the spicy shrimp Nolache which is like a bun with spicy shrimp inside. It was yummy too. There are a lot of drinks on the menu but since I'm not really into coffee and tea I didn't order anything to drink. 

The food is fresh and so affordable that you can get a couple of different things if you want.
