Parking can be a challenge, there are a handful of spaces in front of Chef but I'm not sure if there are others on the other sides of the building. 

There were several people sitting working on their laptops so the atmosphere must stay fairly calm and I imagine there is free wifi. 

I'll be back to try something else soon.

I was taken here for Valentine's Day. There was a set menu and it was probably the fanciest food I've ever had. It was very good and complex. The atmosphere could've been intimidating since I don't go to very fancy restaurants often but it was fine. The staff was welcoming and kind.

We took our two fur babies to Petcetera for bathing and Stacy was the groomer.  If you know anything about Yorkies, they are particular little creatures, and these two seem to sense that they're going to suffer at the vet or groomer.  They quiver and shake themselves right to sleep.  However, these two walked boldly into Petcetera (maybe because it's on Magazine Street?) for their extensive bathing, including nail trim, teeth brushing, eyes cleaned and a few other things for $25 each.  

What a great place--they even offer self service for brave pet parents--an elevated tub to wash your fur babies for only $12.  

Petcetera's wide selection of grooming and pet care products, clothing, costumes, accessories, and food items is amazing.  Unique, one of a kind and quality products.

Heard such great things about Sardi's that I planned our flag football team outing here. 15 of us strolled in on a Sunday evening without a reservation and took over the entire middle section of the restaurant. No one minded that we moved and connected the tables, and the vibe was very casual and fun! As for the food, it did not disappoint! I got a 1/2 chicken, the plantains and the fried rice platter and it was enough to last me two full meals! Prices are worth the portions! Will definitely be back and hope to see one move closer into the city at some point!

This place is amazing! The ramen was incredible (by far the best we've had in St. Pete) and the vibe was so much fun. Even after dinner, we hung out in the private lounge for drinks for hours after. Would definitely recommend!!

We couldn't get any service.  It was busy, but there were plenty of open tables.  We sat at a table that had 7 employees posted up on the wall next to it chatting.  Sat there for almost 10 minutes and no one acknowledged us.

It's my first time to try an Arepa and i love it! I had the Pernil y Queso de Mano. The pork was flavorful without being salty and the cheese was delicious! I went during weekday for lunch and the place was not busy.  Will come back to try other items on their menu.

This bar has a great ambiance!  It was decorated for X-mas during this past visit, and included hundreds of handmade origami snowflakes!  The beer and tequila selection were very good.  The service was quick and on point.  The food was delicious.  I highly recommend the pomegranate guacamole.  Our group tried 7 or 8 other items, which were all good, but the guac was the highlight!
My favorite place in philly!! Such a cool theme. Great service, amazing food and fantastic drinks! Can't wait to come back!
Great place to coms and relax. Seaside on the bay of Tampa.  Good food in the bar, and drinks were just as delicious. Atmosphere is real laid back without a lot of tourist.

1. Pizza was excellent. Cheesy breadsticks were excellent.
2. Loved the location.
3. Great atmosphere. Very clean.
4. Only downside was the delayed initial service. We waited almost 10 minutes after we were seated before anyone approached our table to take our drink orders. And the restaurant was almost empty-- less than a dozen customers, so staff should have easily been able to at least take drink orders. This isn't the first time this has happened here. I once visited for lunch with coworkers and we waited so long for our order taker to initially come to the table, that we just had to leave.
5. Front entry host staff could also use some training on greeting/friendliness when customers arrive.
6. Overall, I really like Giordano's pizza, but customer services consistently comes up short at this specific location. I'd give it five stars, if customer service improved.

Dr Clayman is the best Thyroid surgeon in my opinion. His team are first class and so professional. My whole experience was nothing but the best care from my first visit to leaving the hospital after surgery. Dr Clayman spent time with me discussing my condition and made me feel I was his only patient. The best part was that I was virtually pain free after surgery and I had a full thyroidectomy as well as multiple lymph nodes removed. My recovery has been very good and smooth so far. I highly recommend Dr Clayman and his team. There is no other option to consider.

I love this place. I have been here a few times and they have been consistently amazing. I'm hooked on the spaghetti and vegan meatballs with pink sauce. The cannolis are super good too! Their focaccia bread is also delicious. Give me all the caaaaarbs!! Definitely a great place to get a healthy, fresh, and fast bite to eat. Downside is they don't really have any where to eat besides at the counter which is cool but I hope they expand one day to have a seating area. Regardless, this place is awesome. Give them all your money.

We frequented this place long before the remodel and it has only gotten better! We went in on Friday night to an extremely busy place, we thought good for them! Bad for us though for not thinking we needed reservations! That being said, the host was very gracious and even got us some wine for the wait. The food was well worth the wait. Delicious Italian and very good portions. The new ambience is awesome and so is the bar. We will be back!
I just used Rescue Rangers LLC.  It was a great experience. The attendant showed up early, fixed my problem and I was on my way!  Could not have asked for better service.
Fantastic restaurant!  Consistently great food and atmosphere!  Great place for a catered party or a romantic evening with your wife!
Usually here at least once a week and love it. The grits here are awesome as are the biscuits. It's a bit outta my way but entirely worth it!!!

We visited Pho 79 because we're close to Garden City and Pho Bac was closed.
I wish I could say I've found a great pho place, unfortunately it's not the case. The noodles are steak were fine, but the broth was not. They use too much anise, so there's a heavy black licorice flavor. And they char the white onion before adding it to the soup, which at first intrigued me, but ultimately added a strange burnt flavor.
I won't be returning.

Before buying any furniture for our new home in Tucson, we shopped around. We actually shopped around too much, visiting 20+ furniture stores in the area.

Hands DOWN discount mattress barn was the cheapest. 

Steve personally set up my bar stools on one visit, and made 100% sure it was assembled level. And on another loaded my extra large ottoman into my van all by himself.

By purchasing from Discount Mattress Barn, you get so much more than just the best value. You get amazing customer service!!

What an absolutely charming place to stroll. The pathway runs along the water and is filled with wildlife. We had a wonderful time spotting all kinds of local birds. If you can find a hotel along this path, then you will be doubly blessed. There is a Marriott right on the walk.

What a gorgeous walk on a chilly Sunday(Dec10).Usually it doesn't get that cold in Tampa. So much to see and it was a beautiful day. They have rental bikes, so if you don't want to walk, you can ride.

I'd recommend it to anyone that wants to spend a few hours - starting mid day and walking along the water, seeing what downtown has to offer, stopping at Columbia Cafe for lunch, at the Sail for a drink, at Curtis Hixon for some people watching, at Ulele for Happy Hour, etc... And then be sure to wonder along the Riverwalk after the sun sets to see the beautiful light show under the bridges. It's really incredible! And if you are tired of walking - hop onto Pirate Water Taxi's and see it all from the waterside!!

Celiacs in the area def need to check out this place!
They have a number of gluten free options and accommodate to preventing cross contamination to the best of their abilities if you mention your dietary needs.
My fav thing from there is their chicken quesadillas.

After reading the mixed reviews I had my doubts but have to say our group of 5 was pleasantly surprised! We had made reservations, were seated promptly after a warm greeting at the door as we arrived.  

Our group ordered 2 bottles of wine, both half price. I had a Chilean Syrah and found it to be very good.  It's rare to find a special like that for a decent wine, and even more rare on a Friday night!

Our meals included pizza, salad, pasta. All prepared perfectly and quite tasty. 

Our server was friendly and efficient.  I plan to return!

So much potential. We came here in a group, with a reservation.  None of the drinks came out right, the waitress refused to bring us water (she told us that she didn't have three hands), and the pricing was subjective.  

Good points -- the oysters were amazing. 

Bad points -- waitress and runner were incredibly rude, half of the food came out cold or overly salty.

In short, I would say do this only for drinks and apps, don't waste your money on the entrees.

I've been here 3 times before and loved it. But tonight... the kitchen is SO slow. My family and I waited on our food (two sir chicken sandwiches and a cheese omelet) for twenty five minutes. Our server was really nice and apologetic. But it really shouldn't have taken 25 minutes to make two sandwiches and an omelet.

Truly amazing meal. Favorite part by far was the hamachi curry. Cocktails were excellent. Also ordered the smoked tuna tartare, conch croquettes, broiled shrimp and goat curry- the most tender meat I've had in a long time! Our server Claire was very knowledgeable and fun. Highly recommend for a special night out!

The staff top notch. The amount of RVs and boats on display make it a satisfying trip. My sales person, Frank Bailor was so responsive. He attention to me as a customer was unmatched. Would buy there again and again.

We are from S Jersey but are in New Hope and Lambertville every six weeks or so. For the past several years I have wanted to try Nicola's and we finally did. We went on a freezing day with a high of 19 and sat by the fire. The girls had homemade chicken soup and our family shared a large pie. Everything was awesome. The pizza crust is amazing. The sauce was just the right amount of sweet and the cheese was perfect. Can't wait to come back!
This is the best, most consistent Mexican joint in St. Louis. Nothing fancy. Just great authentic food done right. The chicken nachos are wonderful. The service is fast and friendly.
Michael did a great job with my persistent back and neck pain. He seems well trained in shiatsu and some thai techniques. Would definitely go back!

Been here before but yesterday was extra good!They had pasta with garlic olive oil and scallops.It was amazing it wasn't a overly large portion of food but it filled me up!My husband got an item that was on the menu and it was also good.Service was great but I forgot the young lady's name.

This is my go to when I'm in the office for a quick lunch to go. I always order the same thing. Salmon Caesar wrap with a side of fruit. Always fresh, quick and to the point.
There is a seating area with maybe 5 or so tables. They have a full menu of soups, sandwiches, salads and other goodies. If your in the area definitely stop in. I believe they do breakfast also.
I had the best pedicure ever today! The folks in this salon are so nice and friendly. Plus, they do a wonderful job and their prices are great!
This is a pretty decent chain Italian restaurant. Great for a late night meal. They are open til 10pm

Great place for a quick and easy lunch. Super clean and vibrant. Large salads with lots of flavor. Only downfall is having to park in the garage, wish there was more street parking. The prices are a little high as well....

Pros: 

-Food is good and reliable. For a faster food option, I appreciate the effort that Bread Co puts into making the food have healthier qualities. 
-Given the food quality, I believe the price is reasonable and I like that you get regular rewards on MyPanera. 

Cons:

-Whenever I come to this location, it's always unclear where the line is or what the order to being helped is. It's always a game for me to decide which workers are on cashiers and who I should walk up to. 
-My order was wrong (had onions when I asked for them off) and the worker got me a new one without apology or anything to make it right (despite the receipt saying I should get a treat for my trouble). 
-Also, someone was vacuuming the floor and got very close to us at our table for an uncomfortable amount of time while we were eating. 

I enjoy coming to Bread Co occasionally, but slightly disappointed that this location isn't consistently great service.

I ordered the veggie plate via DoorDash and while the food I got was good half of my veggie plate was missing compared to what is listed and the pictured online. I received only 1/4 of the falafel, no rice, and no tabouli. I would give this place another try but only if I was eating onsite to make sure I get everything I paid for.

Recently went to check this place out,In Style salon. It recently opened a couple of weeks ago and it was awesome! Great staff, some of the nicest people you will ever meet. There were four stylists working there. Anson, Inn, May, and Sandy. All were very warm and super friendly. 

The stylists in this establishment are multi-lingual so you don't have to be afraid of not being able to communicate with your favorite stylist. Inn was my stylist, he is very adept with the scissors but understands limited English. He spoke primarily Chinese, but i had no problems communicating with him because Anson and Sandy both are very good with English and helped to convey my requests for how I wanted my hair styled.

In addition to English and Chinese, Sandy is also fluent in Vietnamese. It's quite impressive how a person can have such good command of that many languages.

Another impressive thing is I love how the place is laid out. It was nice and roomy. Not like the other salons in Chinatown where you feel cramped into a small amount of space. 

The design of this store is very sophisticated. The lighting is bright but not overwhelming. Just perfect. There are big mirrors and nice big windows in which we got a lot of passerby stop and stare in intrigue at how nice the place looks. A couple of them even took out their phones to take photos of the place.

This might be just me, but I believe what really sets them apart, besides their fantastic staff, is the design of the walls. It's really intricate and interesting. Nothing like what I have seen in any other salons in Chinatown. You really have to come in and see for yourself what I'm talking about.

Overall, I had a great experience and will definitely be back. I would recommend this place to anyone looking for a great place to hair their hair styled.

I've had to come here a few times, and every experience I've had has been positive. However, nothing tops the experience I had today, Christmas Day. 

I woke up feeling terrible, thinking I might have the flu so I needed to find somewhere to go, STAT and I knew my options would be limited on Christmas. I called to confirm they were opened and headed there immediately. 

Upon entering the facility, EVERY SINGLE PERSON working there was nicer than you can imagine. It was like Pleasantville and these people were working on CHRISTMAS. They were all calm, professional and exceeded my expectations. The facility is impeccably clean, which is also very important to me. 

Hopefully you don't have to make regular trips to Urgent Care, but if you find yourself needing one, I highly recommend this one.

I stop here on my way home from the gym a lot. Good portions, fine prices... really good food. 4 stars because the ambiance could be a little better and the rice was just OK, and the prices could be a LITTLE cheaper. nothing fancy but overall the food is awesome for being in the middle of a strip mall in franklin. I like the gyro mix plate.
Great portions and food! They've got good specials but we did have to wait awhile to be seated

Arrived Sunday at about 11:30am. There were several empty tables, but the hostess didn't want to seat me because I was alone. I guess the tip wasn't going to be big enough for them. Will never go there again.
Live music, nice patio seating, large bar with a second floor seating. Had the shrimp and crab and it was pretty good.  The bloody mary and the home made Pina colada was the bomb.

Fact: It's the number one Children's Museum in the USA. 

(I could finish my review with that alone). 

YES this place is amazing for kids. Complete with hands-on water activities, a carousel, ever-changing exhibits, a huge dinosaur exhibit, a life-size polar bear, amazing glass art, little dollhouses, and a swirl walkway you follow up to see all the exhibits, you will not be disappointed. The best part of the year is around the holidays when the museum puts up a "Yuletide Slide" down their big entrance steps and allow people of all ages to grab a sack and slide down the big (ice-looking) slide. 

Don't be fooled by the name though - this place is also a blast for adults. I love how relevant they stay, by hosting adult "after dark" events here. Museum by Moonlight is a big one, full of cocktails, food, silent disco, and more. I've heard that the Children's Museum also has a great intern program. 

I used to always love the gift store too, as it's filled with hundreds of creative and thoughtful children's toys and gifts. There's a food court with fast food as well.

Not too long ago, my first oyster experience (side note: it wasn't here) was terrible and made me swear off oysters for good. Fast forward to the present and now I'm a convert, thanks to Royal House. I had told a friend about how much I didn't like oysters, so they recommended this establishment. I got  the chargrilled oysters which is topped with Parmesan cheese butter. The seasoning was everything I imagined it would be and then some - bursting with flavor at every bite. Squeeze some lemon on top and you'll be in heaven. 

I got my order to go, so I cannot comment too much on service, but the waitstaff was very kind, attentive, and very pleasant. Highly recommend dropping by for a snack if you're ever in the French Quarter. I will be looking for every excuse to stop by here whenever I'm in town.

You have a choice!  This place is a nightmare for anyone.  Go to the GOLETA COMMUNITY CENTER just a few blocks away on Calle Real.  You can Google to see all great reviews.  AND IT IS NON PROFIT!  You will not be turned away.  The quality of care is wonderful.  This Med Center should be forced out of our city!

We checked in to the hotel later in the evening and commented on the new look and feel of the place. The front desk staff noted they just opened the facility the week before, so it is a brand new hotel!

It was a great experience and fair price. Extra bonus being one of the first to stay in the new facilities.

Breakfast was good and all the staff very friendly. Overall a great experience. Great location with easy access to to major roads and points of interest.
Huge DD fan here but this place is simply the worst. Always understaffed and mess up the order. Better location just ten minutes down the road.

Very disappointed. My eyebrows are the one thing on my face I have going for me, dark, thick and shaped. I've gotten my eyebrows threaded for years and I've never had an experience like this. They look like they've been buzz cut. They're thin, my arch is near gone,  and she took all the length out of them. They're so short they're patchy in places missing so much hair. I may have shed a few tears on the way to the car. It also takes the woman 10+ minutes for each customer. I felt her taking a lot of hair but didn't think I'd lose half my eyebrow. I will not be returning.

Such a nice coffee shop! Lots of space and natural light! The prices are reasonable and the service is excellent. There's a cool selection of coffee and tea, as well as a few food items if you need something to munch on. This is easily my new favorite coffee shop in the city!

Aimee has such high integrity and so helpful! I took my suede shoes there to get cleaned, worrying that they might be looking too dirty, and Aimee assured me that they looked great as it is and that I didn't need to get anything done. It is so rare to find a repair person telling you that the item is fine as it is and that I thus don't need to get anything repaired and thus don't need to pay them anything (since they're not doing anything).

Read all these Yelp reviews!!! 

They are correct! This place has amazing customer service, and Aimee is incredibly kind and friendly. I hope you get to meet her. Talking with her will make your day a happy one.

My sweetheart made reservations for our anniversary dinner for Wednesday at 8pm. To be extra sure they had our reservation, he called the morning of to confirm our table for 2. We arrived at 7:55pm, and were told that since we were early, we could hang out at the bar. The bar seating was at capacity so we kinda just hung out at the corner of the bar. We were given drink menus to peruse but no one took our order; when two seats opened up, we claimed them quickly. Once we were seated, we were greeted by a bartender--I ordered the French rose, and P ordered a "New Kid on the Block". Yall, the tamarind (?) that they burn atop the glass smells HEAVENLY! I need to find the candle version of the drink ASAP! I really enjoyed my wine and the sip I had of the cocktail was very good too -- definitely wasn't too strong of a drink as I had imagined based on description.

While we were at the bar, the hostess came by and said the restaurant was experiencing a delay in table turnovers and gave us the option to wait or dine at the bar. We opted to wait and maybe 5 minutes later (at most), our table was ready. None of this dampened our night but I would just recommend being flexible. 

Andrew was our server and he was attentive. He introduced himself, but did not give an intro to the restaurant or the menu; of course these intros aren't required but it seemed a little abrupt to go directly to ordering. 

We started with the Crabmeat Pudha. I would not recommend this dish. The gram flour (besan) was overpowering and I tasted almost no crabmeat. 

For our main, we ordered a variety of the roti sathis -- the gobi, saag paneer, tomato mirchi masala, and the raita. You can order these a la carte in addition to the 3/$15 or 6/$25. We also ordered two garlic naan -- hands down, the best naan I have ever eaten! None of the other dishes were truly remarkable on their own, but taken together, it was a great meal. Of note, the tomato mirchi masala is served 'room temp' per the owner; he mentioned this when he came to our table which I believe he does with all of his patrons. Personally, the dish was colder than room temp but still enjoyable. I thought the raita had a nice crunch to it, and with the vegetable additions, had a good consistency to it. 

As you've probably heard/read, this is a Indian fusion restaurant. No typical, heavy Indian food like butter chicken to be found here! I'm interested in knowing if the menu will change from time to time. 

Now, on to the ambiance, my favorite. This is a stunning restaurant! From the menu, to the bar set up, to the dark walls, and glass looking into the kitchen, it is a beautiful space. Just FYI -- it is a loud restaurant (but that doesn't ever both us). 

Reservations are most definitely required given this restaurant's newness and popularity. We previously dined at Saffon on the West Bank, and were greeted by the owner then too which I think adds the perfect personal touch to the culinary experience.

We skipped on dessert, but P got a masala chai with the 1 oz of cognac addition to finish off -- what a unique option!

All in all, it was a great night! Certainly will return to try other cocktails and badhi plates.
Second Sixt rental in as many weeks.  Same experience as last time: exceptionally friendly, cars are clean, in and out process is speedy.  Will probably look to start renting more from these guys.

This store is amazing!
There is so much kitchen goodness here.
The tub full of cookie cutters is so fun.  I can see myself purchasing a new cookie cutter each time I visit the store.
When I entered the store in Tucson for the first time it only took me a couple of minutes to realize I'd been in a very similar store.  I first became acquainted with the store in Savannah, GA, though it was a different store name. I spent hours shopping on two separate occasions during our visit to Savannah.  I thought of that store so often over the past few years. 
It's so great that I live in Tucson and my favorite kitchen store ever also lives in Tucson!

Jokers, complete and utter jokers.  Totally unorganized and had the wrong chart in my file, didnt even know why i was there or that they did some work for me ... i hear from new dentist nearby that they are fixing a lot of coast's work later.  Keep scrolling all i can say

This place is one of my favorites in tucson I've worked at pizza restaurants and this is honestly the best in my opinion. My favorite is the calzones they also serve great ice cream sandwiches and have a bar!

So I needed a new belt as my trusty old one bit the dust the day before. So I thought to myself "hey I'll just pop into Leons on my way to work! Quick, easy, in and right back out!" 

How wrong was I! I walked in found the belt in my size. Even grabbed two because I thought the price was reasonable. Went up to the counter lady and was told that she was very busy with a large order. Hey no problem I understand.

Went to the next lady and was told I didn't "sign" in at the door to get checked out. 

Oh okay. Went to the door signed in and proceeded to wait almost an hour for someone to check me out. What should have been a 10 minute in and out visit turned into a 50 minute fiasco. Very sad and disappointing. Will go down to Ed Roehr or better yet Amazon for my quick uniform replacements.

I love Himalayan Yeti!!  Delicious food and the place is cozy and aesthetically pleasing. The menu is diverse and the beer selection is really good. They serve the best naan I have ever had. The tikka masala is better than most. Waiters have limited English so be patient. They are as friendly as can be. Lovely restaurant on Kingshighway in South St. Louis. Wish I lived closer so I could get carry out. I will definitely be back.

Great experience. Food is delicious and the restaurant is nice decorated. My filet mignon was cooked perfectly to medium rare. Mash potato and asparagus are both really good. Do not skip dessert either. Those donut holes are a must!

This place saved us!! We had an earlier booking at a hotel that turned to be "not as advertised". We found a vacancy for a suite to sleep 5 of us (3 kids, 2 adults) for a great price. Upon entering the lobby, we found Christmas decorations, a cheery fire and hot out of the oven complimentary cookies. Jason was working the desk and he may be the hardest working front clerk with the most positive attitude in the hospitality management industry. He got us checked in, recommended eating establishments and produced menus for us to take to our rooms. There were luggage caddies available, making our unloading so much easier. We called down for additional towels and he brought them up between checking in other guests. 
The carpets had seen better days, but the room and bedding were clean. The room was quiet and we did not hear any street traffic. In the morning we went down for the complimentary breakfast and had the choice of waffles, French toast, sausage, scrambled eggs, toast, cereals, coffees and juices. 
VERY good value for a family of five.
One of the Worst pizzas I've ever had,  all cheese and no sauce. This pizza was drenched in oil and layered in gross cheese,  Definitely not going back there.

I have a feeling this place is a bit of a gimmick. There aren't a ton of seafood restaurants on the water, so it's wait here or eat without the water front view. There are only like 8 tables, so not a place for a big group. It's half outdoor seating too. Lots of specialty seafood like urchin and classic shrimps and fish. It was pretty tasty, and little pricey. Staff is kind of snippy, I think thats part of the "show".

The Octopus and Turkey Thigh were great and the small plates of frisee/napa cabbage and marinated beets were a nice surprise. My wife and I enjoyed it very much; however, just be prepared for not the quickest turnaround of service, especially if you're a fast drinker of water and/or iced tea. Cute ol' corner gas station/garage converted into quaint restaurant. Decor is modern/up-to-date with touch of ol' style yellow brick/repurposed wood and bold light fixtures. Will be back.

I first heard the term "pork belly" in the 1983 film "Trading Places", e.g. breakfast bacon. This pigbit has become trendy in recent years, but a recent visit to Asian fusion restaurant Creazion presented more expressions than I've had in a single meal. Along with many other tasty tidbits.

Pork belly pops started us off on a high note, cubes of braised fatty meat on skewers, glazed in maple and ponzu sauce. The sweet was matched with salt and spice, with lightly crisped, tender, succulent meat ($9). Next, orders of calamari--tempura-fried baby squid mantle and tentacle--both tender and crispy, tossed in sweet chili, lemongrass, scallion, and chipotle aioli ($8). Loved 'em.

Stir-fried chicken, mushroom, and crispy noodles were served with leaves of iceberg lettuce to make lively chicken lettuce wraps ($6). Flavors of garlic, ginger, soy, and a hint of fish sauce were enhanced by a side of cilantro and scallion. Next, a rice flour and turmeric crepe--banh xeo--stuffed with pork belly, prawn, bean sprout, scallion, with a side of cilantro, basil, and pickled daikon/carrot ($9). Usually a light, savory dish, the crepe itself was sweet and quite oily. A pair of steamed lotus buns stuffed with braised pork belly, cucumber, pickled daikon/carrot, possessed a near perfect contrast of flavors and texture ($7). If you've got room for just one appetizer, don't skip this.

My sister-in-law's banh mi sandwich of French baguette with BBQ pork, Vietnamese pork sausage--cha lua--cucumber, cilantro, jalapeno, pickled daikon/carrot, and house spread, was just OK ($7). The bread was nicely crusty, but the pork was a bit dry and included more than a few gristly bits. 

Her husband's seafood noodle soup--pho do bien--with prawns, calamari, blue crab, veggies, egg noodle, and chicken broth was pretty satisfying ($13). The seafood was tender, the broth hearty, the noodles and veg on par. A kid's order of beef pho with rare steak, flank, brisket, veg, rice noodle, and beef broth was well received and quickly consumed ($9).

My bowl of tonkatsu ramen with soft pork belly, 7 minute egg, wood ear mushroom, garlic chip, and scallion was close to being great ($12). The broth was rich, the fungi and meat plentiful, but the noodles were in a bit of a knot requiring disassembly. Worth it. The egg yolk was a bit runnier than the jammy consistency I love with proper Japanese ajitsuke tamago, but still yummy. 

A pair of poke bowls were ordered by our friend and her son, one salmon, one ahi tuna ($12). The fresh, cubed fish was available on a choice of rice--brown or white--or organic mixed greens. Toppings included crab salad, seaweed salad, edamame, sweet onion, jalapeno, wasabi, chipotle aioli, and ginger ponzu sauce. The fish tasted fresh and the seaweed salad was quite good. Both enjoyed their meal.

A goi ga salad of thin-sliced chicken breast, cabbage, cilantro, basil, pickled daikon/carrot, crushed peanut, and nuoc mam dressing was my wife's selection ($8). The fish sauce dressing was fine, but the chicken was dry and the shredded lettuce quite limp. I think this dish works best when the traditional cabbage is used for more crunch. Orders of lo mein for the niece and nephew were a hit; thin egg noodles loaded with plenty of stir-fried chicken, pork, prawn, broccoli, bok choy, and carrot ($11). The veggies had crunch and the meats were tender. As it should be. Overall, our lunch invited a shot at the dinner menu.

I'm a big fan, I've dined as a family with kids, had business functions ranging from 8-30 pp.  Staff is very professional and accommodating.  Had brunch and dinner as well as the personalized price fix menu from Paul.  Definitely one of the best restaurants in town.  Portions are decent too, unlike some fancier restaurants in town.

Had expectations for a fresh meal based on menu choices and advertising in the restaurant. The whole wheat roll for my chicken sandwich was both stale and rubbery at the same time- go figure. Sweet potato fries clearly had been rewarmed. My friend's salad was less pathetic but nothing special. This place is selling itself as fresh, healthy and from the farm.... yuck!

Very disappointed!!!! Made reservations early in week. When we arrived we were seated in bar area in the corner. It took an hour to get a glass of wine. 2 hours later our food arrived. Steak over cooked and all food was cold. Lobster was way over cooked (couldn't get out of shell). Food was compted but was not worth it. Bad service and bad food all in 1 visit.
This place is legit. Ive eaten food from here many times and it is ALWAYS good. If you are in the mood for authentic Mexican food this is the spot to go to.

I would give piree's 5 stars if it wasn't for the nachos. I ended up with chips, a few pieces of cheese, and a bunch of lettuce. 
Aside from the nachos, everything else is also delicious, fresh, and flavorful

Heard this was one of the best BBQ joints in Nashville and was a little disappointed after trying it out. The brisket sandwich was delicious but the sides fell short for me. I got the mac & cheese and cornbread and they were both pretty mediocre. My family also thought their sides weren't great but we all thought the brisket was very well cooked.

I definitely recommend this place for the brisket, but I wouldn't waste your money on their sides.
The pad Thai sauce does not taste like the pad Thai sauce that makes pad Thai glorious.

Had a Groupon and went for whole body cryotherapy and a massage.  Staff was welcoming and Katie made me feel comfortable experiencing cryotherapy for the first time.  Also she was an excellent massage therapist.  Recommend to everyone to come check this place out.

Delicious, authentic food with service that makes you feel like family! Our server, Nancy, truly cared about our experience. She was friendly and attentive and made us feel like we were the only table in the restaurant despite being a busy evening. I visited for the first time in early December, already returned, and am sure this will be a new common stop for dinner.

Crazy good food. Not the fastest service but totally worth the wait. I had the savory spinach and mushroom bread pudding and it was ridiculously good. Probably the best coffee that I have had while in New Orleans. On top of that the prices are very inexpensive. A definite "must do" while in New Orleans.

First time at HS. It was difficult getting a reservation. It always is after great reviews from patrons and the most recent 3 star out of 4 from CL. HS really steps it up for Collingswood. Once inside if you close your eyes one would think they were in a major city in the US. Love the open kitchen. Beautiful inside and out. Now for the food. Kale salad with hazelnuts was fantastic. Even if you don't like kale you will love this. Next the octopus. Perfectly done and one of the best I have tasted. This next dish they hit it out of the park and should make it permanent on the menu. Pasta cups with red meat gravy aka bolognese sauce. It was so good and had a little spice to it. And last a table share of a pork shoulder that they crisped up which was fantastic. Believe it or not our friends made a reservation for this Wednesday so we can't wait to go back. Staff was great and steered us in the right direction for ordering. Merry Christmas and Happy New Year!

Folks may disagree with me, but I have to be the first to not give this restaurant the five stars that it is used to getting. I will first state the positives. The flavors of the curries and other stews are simply delicious; they are doing everything right with what seemed like very authentic tastes and aromas. Now here is my particular issue: this restaurant chooses to curry salmon. It is my fault, really, as I should have asked what fish was to be used in the curry fish dish. Had I known it was salmon I would have passed. Salmon is not a fish for curry, in my opinion. With that said, please note that this is a rather personal opinion and is based completely on the one issue. The restaurant is clean and the service provided is that from good people, no qualms on those points.

I'll keep this brief. I came in for an oil change and a half hour later they return to me letting me know they cannot service the car because the engine needs replacing. Yes, the engine. So I drove to the dealership and they changed the oil for $40. No engine replacement necessary.

Excellent ambience and concept! The BBQ is good but the tikka masala curry was very bland, it is missing flavors! Their mango kulfi is too good! The service is very good and everyone at the restaurant is very friendly! Their black daal is delicious and biryani is the best! There is no consistency in the taste of food though, sometimes it is delicious and sometimes it is just ok! For instance one day the biryani tasted just amazing and the other day it was just ok...hence reducing one star! Samosa chaat and pav bhaji are very good too!
This place is the westbank's best kept secret. Everything i have eaten there was fantastic. The service is good and the food comes out fast. I would definitely recommend this place to anyone!
This is a pretty decent chain Italian restaurant. Great for a late night meal. They are open til 10pm

We have been here a few times and we love it! Their manager, Mike, came to our table a couple time to check on us and he was very pleasant. The service is always great and the food is really good. Prices are decent too. This is one of our go to spots that we can count on for great food, service and atmosphere! Thank you Glory Days! We will be back soon.

Horrible service and food. Service was terrible. The management staff seemed to congregate at the wait station and chat with the servers in an unprofessional manner. At 8:30 on a Friday night the clean up guy was dragging rug mats thru the dining area.

I've only eaten here twice. Both times were excellent. Ate there tonight with my bestie. We had chicken nachos. She had Linguine Alfredo and I had Steak Modiga with Alfredo pasta. All good was very flavorful and cooked perfectly. Service was fast even though they were super busy. We are going back next week to try the lunch buffet. Tonys is a new favorite !

I'm so happy we found Viviano's. Their tortellini is out of this world, and the tiramisu is not far behind. Delightful staff who treat you like family and a deli meat selection that makes my heart skip a beat. Delicious.

Went to Soma on Sunday for Brunch. The food was great but the coffee? Yikes! Get a new blend, a new brand, a new roaster - something. Nasty. Even had them make a fresh pot because the first cup was so awful. It helped a tiny bit. No one at our table could finish their cup. But really - Brunch without good coffee? Doesn't work for me.

If you're looking  for a place to get a real workout in and actually feel like you accomplished something, Orange Theory is the place to go! This particular location is amazing. The staff and trainers are all incredibly nice and really care about you accomplishing your goals. I would recommend to anyone and everyone to give it a try and see for yourself why Orange Theory is THE BEST!!!
I have had at least 3 oil change appointments that have taken 3 hours each, others were over 2 hours.  Just a terrible experience with service department.  Don't ever come here!!!

I finally got there! I'll start with the beginning. The only problem was parking but we did finally find it around the block in front of a church. We were treated wonderfully by the servers. I had the beet burger. Let me just say it was fabulous and satisfied that burger craving. My daughter had the Korean Bowl and really liked it. It was colorful, flavorful, and filling. I want to try that next time. There is a good variety of foods. Gluten free items are available. The sodas are natural, I had the ginger ale and it is excellent. Definitely going back. Love it!

AW MAN...I hate when you recommend a place based on the yelp reviews and end up disappointing yourself and your friends. Especially when you're an avid yelper, it deals a serious blow to your street food cred. I mean will my friends ever let me recommend a place to eat again!? I'll probably have to grovel and beg my way back into their cold hearts! Lol kidding, I'm thankful to have nice friends, but if any of your friends bully you prob need some new friends!! 

Anyways back to the review. SO Dalessandro's, first of all I like this name it's snazzy it's sassy, and it's italian-y. It gave me good vibes, and the 1000 reviews helped to push expectations higher. WELL, I will say Dalessandro's had amazing service, shout-out to the girl behind the counter who wasn't a jerk and treated us like human beings. 

The order: Sharp Provolone, Fried Onions, Cheesesteak. 
The friend's order: SAME THING but added mushrooms. 

The execution:  A-OK, greasy, HUGE PORTION, decent philly cheesesteak but honestly it didn't do it for anyone, and we still had the itch to move on and find the greatest philly cheesesteak that ever existed...

Will we ever find that?! To be continued.......
SNS powder they only dipped twice, got cracks after 2 days

Super disappointed. I'm from California, and the first few times I went to Steak 'n Shake I thought of it like the in n out of the Midwest. The last two times I have been overwhelmingly disappointed. Last time it took over 20 minutes before the waitress asked us for our drink order. This time, I cannot tell the difference between the Steak 'n Shake burger and a McDonald's burger! The picture is of a Steak 'n Shake DOUBLE burger with grilled onions. Seriously Steak 'n Shake? You can do better.

Love love love this place! I don't ever eat inside the restaurant so I don't have much to say about the building other than it is really small. But I work nearby and we always order their food to go. 

The food always tastes fresh. My favorite thing here is the chicken pecan tart! Sooo good and it comes with a mango chutney on top, heavenly! Another favorite is the chicken salad croissant sandwich with the best ever tomato basil bisque! 

The bakery next door is also amazing. I usually just get the cupcakes. I'm sure the other stuff is good too but their cupcakes are my fav. But inside the main restaurant they also give free samples of the bakery goods. 

I definitely recommend this place for breakfast or lunch. But not dinner because they don't serve dinner, only open for breakfast and lunch lol.
Sabrina is so cool, eat here just to have an honest experience. The food is really damn good

I had an almost flat tire that fix a flat was spewing out of at 4:00 on a Friday afternoon. I stopped by a place near this company & they refused to help me saying they'd "already put some stuff up" because they closed in 40 minutes.

Enter Best Used Tires! They were the next place I saw and I immediately stopped. Not only did they have a tire for me, they had it replaced in under 30 minutes. They looked over my other tires & told me I probably needed to replace the other within the next few months. No sales pitch, no pressure. Just genuinely helpful! Great place- will come here again!

I went in today with a possible broken leg. Walked in with pain but thought no way. I was brought in in a very timely fashion. Every one treated me with concern and sympathy.  From the ladies in the front office to the nurses. Especially brian the np. It's the 2nd time I've needed them and i will never hesitate to use them again.

Such a unique place in the heart of Midtown. Not super large, so recommend getting there earlier if you want to get in, cause it will fill up. Good beers for $4 and plates that are great to share. Highly recommended for a date or with friends who like to share.

Nice little spot in a very unexpected little plaza. We started with the lamb tartare which was yummy with the little pieces of cut up beet. I had the fish tacos which were just ok but I should have asked what kind of fish came on them because it was salmon which I'm not a huge fan of and had I asked i would have ordered something else. The toppings were great but salmon just isn't my fave. We also had an order of chicken tenders and the fried chicken (thigh) sandwich which were all delicious. Our server was great and overall a cool spot. I'd def give it another go.
John is a great guy... service has been on time and very thorough. There's many times a special so that helps my budget. Thanks for keeping me on the road Team Fred Beans!

I had a really good experience with these guys. The guy I worked with, Keith, took care of me and fixed a part of the car that wasn't part of the work my insurance covered. Car looks great and it was ready a day early.

I'm a big fan of Whisk Bakeshop and generally buy their products at the Tower Grove Farmer's Market. The number one reason I visit their stand is for the goat cheese popsicles. It sounds totally weird but it's literally the best thing ever. I buy at least four every week we go through so many of them! They are creamy with whole seasonal fruit in the bottom (my favorite is the blackberry). I always ask for the frostiest ones so they will make it home to my freezer before melting. Another unique item I love are the popcorn cookies. They are deliciously crispy and buttery. Today I visited their storefront during the Cherokee Street Cookie Spree. I bought a white chocolate peppermint cookie that was to die for. Next time I think I'm going to try one of their homemade pop tarts!

We stopped in to pick up some late night take out and we're pleasantly surprised with the low prices and serving sizes. The only downside was how thirsty the noodles made us. Must have been the salt or msg. I would not stop by without having something to drink at your side. Other than that, we looking forward to stopping by again!

Very nice place in a very quaint downtown Franklin Tennessee. Downstairs is a fun bar like atmosphere. Upstairs and more quiet dinner setting. The food was excellent only prepared with very good presentation. The downside was the portions were pretty small for a larger than average price tag. Overall good experience but if your hungry you'll pay for it

We just had the best experience at Brick City Eatery! We sat at the bar area and watched the workers make the pizzas....so much fun. The pizzas were delicious! We will definitely be back! The staff was friendly and helpful!

We actually found Al's when we moved to the area 2 years ago. It's amazing. Don't expect anything but great service and fantastic food.  Meat is perfectly bbq'd, sauce is mildly spicy and cole slaw is fresh and tangy!! Servings are huge and don't forget a slice of cake. They do alternate desserts and expect a line on Fridays.

This place is doing the dip nails (SNS) completely wrong..you're getting played! This is a VERY HONEST review and i neverrr give bad reviews..this is a first for me. 

I got the dip nails done here and they turned out terrible from the color not matching what was on the sample to the application. But the worst part is that THEY DONT USE THE VITAMIN BASE which is the whole point of the dip nails. Dip nails or SNS nails is supposed to be healthy for your nails bc it doesn't ruin your nails like acrylic and shellac do and the powder has vitamins that helps your nails grow stronger and healthier. Except this place DOESNT EVEN USE the base which is what has the vitamins in it!!! They don't apply the vitamin base, there should be two different clear polishes for dipping (one for the base that is thicker and then one for the color powder that is thinner) but they just use the thick one so your nails are super thick, and then they don't even and smooth everything out after. ALSO, they ARE NOT supposed to file the top of your nails with the rough, harsh electric filter like they do for acrylic. For the dip nails, you are only supposed to VERY LIGHTLY buff the nails. Your nails should be smooth before they apply anything and smooth when they remove the dip nails. Idk how they remove the dip nail here bc I wasn't even gonna try it here based on how they were done in the first place. 

If you're wondering how I know all of this and how it should be done, it's bc afterwards, I did my research AND got them redone at a place that knew what they were doing and actually answered a ton of questions I had before doing my nails. 

I just think it's wrong that people are getting the dip or SNS nails done here thinking that they're getting this healthy, good new nail product/system and they're not. They're not using the most important products (probably bc it's cheaper and faster) and not doing the process correctly. 

Everyone was nice, though..I'll give them that much.
Great dive bar. Sure, the place was a little dirty, but compared to the rest of the block, it felt like walking into an oasis. They had good music, good food and they pour heavy.

Wow!   Soooo full!    Great staff!   Delicious food!   BYOB!   Good times!      I loved the wings, tofu, and the catfish!     I can't wait until I'm back in town to visit.    It's slowly becoming my undisputed go to restaurant when I'm philly!   Also heard from a patron that Uber eats started delivering.    Wish I lived closer so I could enjoy more frequently.    Absolutely one of my favorite spots for a good meal!

The limited menu offered for soft opening was very good. I had the bourbon salmon which was very tasty. Daughters coconut shrimp and cherry cocktail was very good. The salads we were told had homemade dressing and they definetly taste homemade. Bleu cheese had chuck of cheese.
Can't wait to try the full menu.
12/20/2017 was scheduled for grand opening.

New favorite place to eat in Nola added to the list. The fish tacos, mac and cheese and shrimp grits were amazing. If I could, I would have ordered everything on the menu. I will definitely be going back.  

The drinks will not disappoint either

Sure, it was my first time at Capitol Cellars. So no, I haven't tried all of their cultivated selection of wines on offer. And I haven't delved into their delectable dinner offerings including prime rib and faux scallops made of trumpet mushrooms. 

But oh, I can speak to their happy hour! 

2C wines are bogo between the hours of 4-6, a healthy little window to dip into the restaurant for an early evening treat. Sip on your Sauvignon Blanc or a red blend while you look around. Take in the classy, dark but cozy feel of the place. I was there around Christmas time and they had the joint decked out with lights and a tree. It felt swanky but unpretentious. Just lovely. 

I enjoyed my wine but LOVED my small plate. I had the Borah Slider. It was a kobe beef patty with mozzarella and tomato, basil and balsamic reduction. Only a few bites big, but priced right at $5 with a few fries riding along. The meat was superb. My dining companion ordered another and she's not much of a red meat eater. I'd go back in a heartbeat for that kobe. And next time I'll try a full dinner entree. 

Head here for a romantic date or a very nice meal for a special occasion. Service was attentive, yet unobtrusive. Highly recommend it!!

Rude sales lady! I walked in just to look at the sales since I'm always into buying sunglasses but the rude sales associate approached me with attitude and was incredibly rude... after that encounter I immediately walked out!!

I checked in on to 12th stayed till the morning of the 14th was told that I would be charged$85 I asked to have a mini fridge and microwave brought to my room for my granddaughter who is only 15 months old to keep her milk cold and warm her milk at night was told no problem I never got either of them
The room was dirty with a funny smell kept spraying my perfume so I didn't have to smell it I never got a receipt for the room
So I leave come home check my account only to find that they over charged me for the room and tacked on an extra $250 said I was smoking in the room I DON'T smoke around my granddaughter 
They also said that I'd have free WiFi never could connect to it.
   I'd NEVER STAY at another Hampton inn I'd rather sleep in my car they did nothing but lie to me from the start 
I should have asked for another room because of the dirtiness of the room along with the smell of the room but it was close to the elevator and easy to come and go with my granddaughter 
Don't expect to get any help with your bags there's no one to help 
If I could have given a minus star that's what I would have given them

YES! YES! YES!   A nice, simple Taqueria.  When I go for my tacos, I want it simple and to the point... the way I always got them as I grew up in L.A.   Some meat, onion, cilantro, chile, and 2 small corn tortillas, served up with an Horchata, period.   

Given that we are in Tampa, this place came pretty close to nailing it.  The tortillas are a little bigger than "home", and they were not double... but the flavor speaks volumes.  It is, without question, the closest I have come to finding the real deal here in Tampa.

Now, if someone knows of a place that meets this criteria, AND hand-makes corn tortillas (not with a press), please let me know!!!!!!  That is the dream!

Until then, this is my go-to place!
Kudos!

Just went in to grab a bite. I asked if the Shrimp and snow peas had other vegetables in it. The counter guy said yes. I asked if he could leave the other veggies out and I was told NO. He said snow peas are expensive. I told him I didn't want extra snow peas I just didn't want the other veggies. I was still told NO!!!!  Very rude!!! Will never go back!!!

I think this newly re-designed Walmart Supercenter is just fine. Sure, the typical complaint is not enough registers open. They claim they can't get people to work certain hours or they don't show up. Wellll... pay more and give benefits, Walmart. 

Otherwise, I think the store is excellent. I get MUCH lower prices on brand name groceries and dairy products. The big produce section is terrific. The staff is almost always courteous and helpful - REALLY helpful. I've written to corporate about a few individual store associates who really went out of their way to help me.

I can get my groceries AND other regular stuff in the same place. I save on all those things, too. The rest rooms are (pretty) clean and well maintained. The pharmacy is EXCELLENT! Want reasonably priced prescriptions? Come here!

I do wish more of their products were made in the USA - like the old days of Walmart.

It's so typical to bash Walmart, but, other than how Walmart compensates the employees*, it's really a great store.

* Many of the staff are retirees, and the system works just fine for them.

This place is SO good. The sweet crepes are amazing. Service has always been great every time i love gone.  One time, my friend noticed it was closed but the open sign was still lit. So we got their attention to turn it off and they let us in and allowed us to order a crepe, which was very nice of them.

Although this shoe section is very big. i rarely find anything here. Not to mention, these shoe department salespeople did not provide basic customer service at all. After bringing me the shoes, not once did she ask if they fit, if I needed a different size or if I needed help with anything else. She just stood behind the counter and waited for me to come up to pay for the shoes or I guess walk away if I didn't like them. In all of the Macys I have been in, these people were the worst. The one tall guy just stared at me, never even saying hello. I am not sure if they just act like that because they know they will make the commission regardless because it is a high traffic store or what.

I understand that it's after  11pm, but if you're going to serve food, then it should be edible. Barely warm, dry burgers that needed washing down to be able to swallow them and cold shoestring fries. Plus the shake was so glutinous that it was undrinkable.

Apparently the server was so busy being friendly with other tables that he didn't bring us any silverware or napkins. 

Not a pleasant dining experience.

We here for a birthday party. Great atmosphere and great people that work here. The food is good. There is a mixture of Japanese and American culture in the sushi rolls. Some rolls were good and some where not too good. For example the dragon roll is amazing but there Mexican roll was not right... also the prices were a little higher than I would expect from a sushi restaurant. Definitely a place to try once.

I wrote this review under " I Wear" and wanted to share my wonderful experience at this location !


My fiancé and I first stopped in as we saw many eye catching frames ! He purchased a pair of sun glasses that were very unique. Alex was very helpful and the prices were reasonable. He really knows the brands that are sold( material, lens, how it's made , style, etc).

I decided to go for my two year eye exam since I thought the frames offered were very stylish and different. The  ophthalmologist had the best manner I've ever encountered which made having my eye dilated less torturing.

Now, I'm not very decisive  and have a petite face .
Alex pulled out so many frames with such patience. He was the first person to offer me glasses that fit my face without my eye lashes brushing on the lens (which I thought were normal and no one from my usual eye wear store noted or made such a recommendation ). This was life changing ! I can now blink without my lashes lightly brushing against the lens! He noted the bridge of my nose to help steer me on frames that wouldn't fit correctly on my face.

I then decided to try on sun glasses, again, Alex was so patient ! He took the time and effort to help me decide on a stylish,comfortable, and right size frame for my face!

If you're looking for new glasses or eye frames -- I would recommend to stop by. This place really pays attention to the profile of your face to help you find your perfect frames !
Bank of America--- takes Customer Service Failure to a whole new level each and every day they are in business..

I went to my usual tire store Tire pros to get my tires changed but they only had three so I called Sears just to see if they were competitive with the price Tire Pros had quoted me. They were and so I had them done plus alignment. In the past I have been reluctant to do the alignment because every one says its a rip off but my car has never run better. one negative point, I wanted them to be precise about how long it would take. They said 2 hours but that turned into 2 45. The staff were straight-forward and courteous and the price quoted was out the door, no surprises. I will definitely go back if the tires hold out as promised.

This place is amazing!! The service is always excellent. The hot & sour soup is the best. There are also awesome lunch specials! We drive 30 minutes past many other Asian restaurants to come here because it's our favorite ! Keep up the good work Pinang!

I love the Han Dynasty in Manyunk so was happy to see one in the area.  I went there once and the food was ok but not what I expected.  I ordered takeout from there again (thinking maybe it was just that one time) and the food was horrible.  The Dandan noodles were way over cooked and a bad texture, the honey shrimp had no flavor and the general tsos was really soggy.  I paid $50 for bad chinese takeout.  I will still go to the one in Manyunk but I'll never go to the Exton one again.

Also, the service wasn't good.  I was just picking up an order and they barely acknowledged me and seemed annoyed that I didn't remember the order number they provided me over the phone.
A bit expensive but the food is worth it. Portion sizes are smaller. The shrimp pizza is BANGIN'

First five star that I have ever given. On my way to Miami and this is truly a surprise! We ordered two gyros and an large plate of eggplant. The taste is better than most of the high-end restaurants we have been. The owner is awesome too. He suggested to have pita go with the eggplant and that is the best idea. We will definitely visit this place again if we are in this region.

My husband and I found this on yelp and reviews were great, and thought I would try something different. I ordered the biscuits and gravy with eggs and sausage. While the biscuits were fluffy and delicious the sausage gravy was ok. The sausage patties on the side was terrible. Had a real sweet spicy taste to it didn't go well with the sage in it.  I couldn't even eat it. The chef came out and walked around to tables to ask customers about their food they ordered. He came by ours, and I asked about the sausage.  He seemed very proud of his recipe, and not interested in toning it down a bit.  Maybe his sausage sales will explain that it's time to change the recipe.  My coffee was very bitter, chose not to have a second cup.  The service was wonderful. But, will go elsewhere for my breakfast.

Hate leaving a bad review on such a local classic but I am fairly certain that I have had food poisoning form Merritt's twice in the past. The food is cheap and the portions are big, but you get what you pay for. 

I hope that they have got their kitchen staff figured out, but still I think I am going to be sticking with their amazingly good scones from now on. They are always a safe bet...

Had an awesome experience at bark life! Super friendly staff, and gave my little girl, Bijou, the best haircut she has ever had! I have become fairly picky because she has had so many odd cuts over the years, but what i described they delivered and I'm so happy! Janelle did the cut in only took 2 hours, and they even honor a military discount! They have a mobile punch card as well so that's nice to work towards even more discounts! I'm very happy and so glad to have tried you guys out!

I've had my fair share of tacos from Chicago to Phoenix to San Diego to San Francisco. The tacos here have topped all of those places! I've had the grilled fish, chicken, carnitas, and shrimp...each one was pretty exceptional! And yes, the fish tacos here are better than any fish taco I ever had in San Diego/La Jolla/Encinitas! The portions are on the larger size, the flavors are delicious, and the spicy salsa that's house-made is downright drinkable! 

Do your belly a favor and get into Buena Onda :)

ordered online for pickup. the loco burrito salad wasn't terrible, but it was supposed to come with bread and they did not include it, and there was not a napkin or a fork included in the bag. They hide them behind the counter too, so if they're busy you'd better hope you've got your own utensils somewhere!

I ordered the Spicy Tuna bowl and thought it was just ok and I was hoping it would be better. The tuna chunks were cut inconsistently. I had some small pieces that were bitesized while others I had to cut up myself with a knife. Also, it didn't seem like the tuna was pre-seasoned or marinated so it was bland. I'm used to tuna poke tasting more flavorful. The brown rice was good but it was clumpy and not loose at all. I had to break it up to mix it up better. The fried onion was kind of strange, reminded me of thanksgiving green bean casserole or a bbq dish, should have ordered it without.

Went here for the first time on taco Tuesday and ordered the birria, pescado, and Tocino tacos. They were delicious. Guacamole was super fresh and so was the salsa. Chips came out warm and crispy. This is authentic Mexican cuisine at its best.

Finally I get to write a good review. 

Went to Pietro's a couple of nights ago and had a really good meal.

I had clams in a wine, butter sauce to start. Nice balance of seasonings and broth. The bread selection was a bit old school and they gave me rock hard butter but all in all it was very tasty.

The main came with soup or salad and I chose the later. Standard ok oill and vinegar fare but served ice cold so I knew it had been in the box. But it was okay.

For the main I had lamb chops with prawns. Lamb was perfect and the compliment of prawns was excellent. It had a nice wine reduction sauce with was amazing 

Desert was Tiramasu which was moist and delicious. 

Good for you Pietro's.. I shall return. Something I find I don't say often in Reno.

Loved the coffee. This was my first time having a draft latte. I guess I'm late to the party. Awesome building, too. While waiting for my drinks and food, I watched baristas; the cooks working the big fancy, copper oven; and someone doing some baking in the back behind the roasters. The bread was also stand out.
The service was incredibly slow when we went. The place was not packed so I'm not sure what was taking so long. The traditional margarita was so sour it tasted like straight lime juice.

Arrived an hour before Man of La Mancha at the Temple of Music and Art (an outstanding performance by the way!) to grab a sandwich.  My son got the soup of the day in one of Don's bread bowls.  I got a caprese sandwich.  Both were just right. I've said this before, but Don's bread is an expression of love! I ordered a brownie with my meal, as did my father from a different server and he was told they were out.  When I went back up to inquire, my server confirmed that they were out.  I asked if they had anything sweet and our server went into the back and materialized with 2 brownies! We were thrilled. It was  a great way to fill our tummies before the show.  I had read that Barrio Sandwiches was initially a pop-up restaurant- hope it becomes a permanent fixture.

Compelled to visit because of the sushi burger.  It delivered and more!  I had the Oolong tea (guava) and it was delicious.  The wait staff are excellent and the restaurant has a funky, cool ambience.  Now, on to the burger--it exceeded my high expectations.  It was savory, sweet, umami, as well as crunchy (in the right places) and overall delicious.  Nicely balanced.  Plus, I am full!  Highly recommend you try this place.  I will be back!

Overall a pretty great experience. The booths they have set up are nice and the products seem pretty legit. The atmosphere is wonderful, too, with the Palladium overseeing everything. 

We went on a Thursday night and it was actually kind of dead, not very lively. For some reason I expected a little bit more to be happening but it was really just ice skating and booths. I assume it's more lively on the weekends but probably WAY busier. 

The reason I am giving this event 3 stars is because most of the staff we encountered for the ice skating were pretty miserable. I know not everyone has Christmas cheer but eeesh. 

Also 3 stars because my skates smelled horrible, they were extremely uncomfortable, and the staff I encountered to get them were a drain.
We found this place by fluke and LOVED it. Amber was amazing with the drinks and fun personality. We had burger and fries for $5 with cheese $6, totally with a stop. We'll be back!

Everything I dreamed and more. There are spots to pull up. Water views of the bay. Some trash. Some trash cans. Birds. Some trees and scrub. Great place to launch a watercraft or grill some hotdogs. In comparison to the French Riviera, the crowd here is also fabulous but only men go topless.

We took their Oak Alley Plantation tour. It was so much fun. Our driver Dionne (like the singer) was hilarious. She was so knowledgeable and kept up a great commentary when we were stuck in traffic. 

I definitely recommend doing the single plantation. It gave us ample time to take the plantation house tour, walk through the exhibits and have an great lunch at their restaurant. It was totally worth the price.

This establishment is filled with wonderful food as well as integrity! This review which will be posted everywhere is worth the read.

Being from out of town, decided to google best bbq in Nashville. Edley's popped up with 4.5 stars and 600 reviews. They have earned the reputation of best for a reason! Food is delicious, I recommend the brisket as well as the pulled pork! Melt in your mouth and absolutely delicious!

On to the integrity and my restored faith in humanity. Jumped back on the road, headed home, about 3 hours later I realized I didn't have my wallet. I called them and the manager Michelle Davis informed me that they did find my wallet. I asked if there was anyway she could have it shipped to me, to keep the cash inside as a thank you gift for going out of her way to help a complete stranger. She said she would be happy to ship it to me, but that she will not accept any payment. I recieved my wallet in the mail today,  with all the cash inside all my cards, licence, insurance, you name it.  Anyone who has lost a purse or wallet knows what a pain in the butt it is to replace everything.... I am so grateful to Michelle. I hope she recieves many blessings from her kindness. Thank you Edley's for hiring such an honest and good hearted person. She truly saved me from many headaches for her kindness.

Warning!  DANGER,....They broke off three lug nuts from my wife's van and did not replace them or tell her what had happened.  I had to have the van towed to a REAL tire store, Olin Mott & had them fix the issue.  ALL of the lug nuts on all four wheels were not torqued properly.  One rear tire had all four lugs loose...

We've been to zahav twice, once on a first date and the both of us really love the branzino. We then came for a small event for our residency Retreat, we had 8 people there and really enjoyed the private seating and amazing Wine and Food.

I've never had a great experience with Old Navy but this store saddened me. It was in disarray, I mean really really disorganized and out of order. They didn't even have any boot cut khakis which I am certain is a staple at old navy. I would've been less irritated if they had some in the wrong sizes, but there was zero. I also couldn't find a soul to help me. I know it's pretty typical for an Old Navy to be disorganized, but, this one really takes the cake.

I'm sure that  the stress and hardship experienced by those affected by the CA wildfires will limit their Yelp reviews of restoration services, but I want to say how impressed I have been with this company.  Between Jeannine on the phone, Chasen to estimate and the team that showed up to clean - this company has been incredible.  Given that we were  a couple weeks late to requesting post-fire service due to serious family health issues, the response to our plea for help was just great.

I ordered from this place through the new app called Slice that allows you to order from local pizza shops. I ordered the largest size they had the xx-lg just because I've never seen the option before. It ended up being around $20 for something that was the diameter of about half a queen size bed! Woof it was massive. I ordered the meat lovers pizza with a pan crust and under special instructions asked for the pizza to be well done (I like my cheese to have some brown spots). It was delicious! And I'll probably have left overs for a week! The toppings were very fresh and they were very generous, each bite I had at least 2-3 toppings. At no point was there ever a bite with just cheese. The dough and crust was pretty good. I ordered the pan so it was pretty thick and pretty doughy. It tasted nothing like the pizza chain dough. It had its own original taste and texture that I personally really enjoyed. The sauce was very good too. Compared to the cheese and toppings it wasn't the star ingredient and I didn't taste much of it but I knew it was there. Next time I might ask for them to add a bit extra. I was initially worried about delivery time as the Slice email said it would take 60mins on a Friday night but they came at 40mins later and their delivery driver was SO NICE! most pizza delivery guys are just not very happy and always seem like it's your fault they're in a bad mood. This guy though was an angel and it made the whole experience a positive one where I felt I should help them out with a positive help review. I also had a canolli and cheesecake slice. I highly recommend the cheese cake slice over the canolli but that may just be personal preference. Give local pizza shops a try, this one at least is really good. I want to order from them again and try their NY style crust.

I placed my order online and I had added 5 extra wings. They had the order ready to go on time. Unfortunately when I got home my five extra wings weren't in there. The same night I submitted a survey letting them know I did receive my wings. A few hours later I got a email from the owner apologizing about the inconvenience and she had left me a five dollar gift card to resolve the issue. They definitely got my business back. On top of that the food was great

I have never been so disappointed in a restaurant in my life. 
This restaurant was not worth our time and probably gotten better service at mc donalds.
First off they advertise as habachi, but they have no tables to cook at. 
The food we did get was ok, pretty good. Not worth calling home about.
The worst part was the service. It was the worst!
Waitress came to the table said less than 5 words to us. We ordered and she left only to return with the food, which she just dropped off and walked away. She never can back to the table, no one ever acknowledged us. We couldn't get refills on our drinks because there was no one to be found. When the check was dropped the other waiter put it on the table and walked off. Our waitress was standing there doing nothing, just looking at us.
I don't think we heard more than 10 words from both of them together.

HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE WILL NEVER GO BACK

Wish I could give this place negative stars. My husband purchased a slice of devils food cake and a bread pudding. The bakery items looked less than enticing. I decided to give it a shot. The devils cake literally tasted like mud pie. The bread pudding had a weird, moist green film on the bottom. I was disgusted and have been suffering from stomach pains since consuming the few bites. I wish I had read some of the previous reviews before trying this place. It is obvious that this place has some sanitation issues. I'm big on recommending great spots to friends, family and random strangers. This place will definitely be on my "do not" list.

My wife and I have visited this location many times.  For quite a while, we stopped eating here because the service was spotty. Over the last year or so, there have been numerous management changes.  We are aware of the tragic loss of their GM and we were hoping that the increased level of service would continue with the new GM.  that didn't happen.  Last Sunday we showed up around 1pm and they were almost out of bagels.  We placed our order, paid and then waited....and waited.... and waited!  Employees walked by us many times but no one thought it was odd that we were the only ones with no food!  After 30 minutes, my wife went to the counter.  The confused expressions told me that they lost our order.  It was NOT that busy!  10 minutes later, an employee tried handing us a TO GO order as we told her we were leaving after they credited my card.  She handed me cash and I asked her if she even read my receipt.  She stated that she didn't notice!  At that point I asked who the manager was.  She stated that she was in charge of the store at that time.  I DID tell her exactly what I thought of her management skills.  She apologized and apparently thought our irritation was amusing because she kept smirking.  I asked her remove herself and get someone else to get my credit.  The only bright spot - BETH - who knew how to give me a credit with a sincere apology.  Einstein needs to make sure they only put people in positions of authority who can handle it.  We will not go back.  When we did what we were supposed to, which is to pay for food and service, excuses aren't acceptable.  We were approached by another customer and told that the current GM was as useless as the girl who blotched this.  Poor management trickles down!

This place is absolutely legit. Normally if you go to sushi bar you want larger pieces but here it's nice to get smaller ones so you can enjoy more during the AYCE. EVERYTHING here is so good!! Added bonus: come here on your bday for free AYCE!

Came here with a serious craving for barbecue and not wanting to travel far. I would have to say although they did satisfy my craving for BBQ, it wasn't exactly what I'd hoped for. The ribs were fall off the bone good and the sauces were great.... but something just seemed like they were sitting under a heat lamp for a while. the baked potato I ordered was rock hard on the bottom where I could only eat the top flesh of the potato. Rib tips we ordered were also good but not as good as the ribs.... more reminiscent of beef jerky. Margarita had a heavy pour so that was enjoyable. Overall good if you don't mind sacrificing a little bit of quality for convenience and speed.

I enjoyed this place. The Devil Crab Arancini was delicious and the service was great! The ambience was great for the nightlife. I will say this place is a bit expensive but very modern. I will definitely be back but next time it will be for brunch! I heard they have a great brunch selection on Saturdays and Sundays.

The calzones from Sauce On The Side are crazy delicious!  After my first visit, I promptly returned to another Sauce On The Side because I loved it so much.  My favorite is the $9 "Meat Me in St. Louie" that has pepperoni, Italian sausage, provel, mascarpone-ricotta blend, garlic oil with a side of meat sauce.  The Cock-A-Doodle Noodle comes with Buffalo butter saunce and was fun, but not as tasty as the meat one.

Parking was hard to find at this location.
