I had a terrible experience dealing with the management of this hotel. I had to cancel my hotel reservation two weeks in advance of my New Year's eve and New Year's day reservation. They refused to offer me a refund despite the fact that they could easily rent that room or probably even more than what I paid for it. I would not suggest booking this hotel for in advance of your stay date. They have zero flexibility with their cancellation policy. Do not expect reasonable management decisions from this hotel. I promised the manager I was talking to that I would leave a review and they said go for it so here it is. For such an expensive hotel this is the worst customer service I've ever encountered.

*Update

After posting this same review on Tripadvisor, the hotel first attempted to have my review removed. When Tripadvisor refused to remove the 100% legitimate review they then posted a response im which they publicly asked me to email them to assist in the matter. I emailed Alfred L Groos, the general manager who responded to me and received ZERO response. This hotel is far overrated because they attempt to have negative reviews removed. 

This hotel caused a tremendous amount of stress for me over Christmas all over the fact that they didnt want to rebook a room 2 weeks before the stay date on NYE. Its downright shameful how this supposedly high end hotel treats people. Their GM who responds to reviews is just a stooge who doesn't actually contact people back. 

Look closely at this hotels negative reviews from the past...bed bugs, uncleanliness, construction issues, bad management. Just be careful if you decide to stay here when there are great hotels at much better prices just down the street.

Came here for dinner with my family on Saturday night. Got seated right away. But the food and service was horrible. Will never come back here again. Too overpriced and horrible food. This restaurant has gone down the hill.
And the manager should be fired the way he handles customer care.

YUM! Incredible crispy pizza! Anti-pasta salad is also delicious and a necessity for a true Italian meal! The staff is friendly and always working to meet your needs. Definitely the go-to place for pizza in Spring Hill!

ordered 3 packs of cookies in the drive through only was charged for one pack but ended up not getting any. went back to the drive through and explained that i needed one for free because i didnt receive it and two more that i would pay for. i got to the window payed 2.12 and left with only 2 packs of cookies. people at the window werent even friendly about it as i tried to make light of the situation. will not visit this location again.

Rudest management staff ever! Ripped my holiday decorations down and than got into a screaming match with me over the absurdity of it all! Nothing was offensive and further more who the he'll tells someone to take down holiday d edcorations?

I really want to like this place so I keep going back but I just can't. Their burgers are never to my expectations in a burger. I look for a juicy burger with flavor on a soft bun i just good bread. The burger is always dry and never has good flavor - no matter how I get it done and how many toppings I get. Bread is also dry. I can barely finish it and I really love burgers. 

Tater tots are just okay as well. The dip they give you with is salty is a bit salty. 


However, i do love their fries!! I'd go back for some good fries! And their service is great.
Affordable, highly customizable, friendly wait staff and ultimately delicious food. Great ambiance and location. Would recommend if you are looking for quality ramen.
Great food fast, not quite like a cook in front of you restaurant but next best thing

I walked in to get a djambe (spelling) drum for my husband for Christmas. I dont know much about them but wally was there happy and willing to help. He helped me pick out the perfect instrument and offered it hold it for me until christmas as well as offered to find a box so I could wrap it. I also asked about flute repairs since mine is in need of some maintenance and he was happy to walk me through the pricing guide of that as well. I was super pleased with the excellent customer service and look forward to working with this company in the future.

Not sure why people give this gas station such high reviews. Yes, it's conveniently located. But it also takes advantage of that location to the tune of about 20 cents per gallon! I guess one man's convenience is another's price gouging. 

Oh, and they have that new-fangled, annoying TV screen that plays ads and announcements as you pump. Sure, play ads on your own time or play them in the convenience store. But don't force me to watch them. What's more, the ads didn't even really work. One started, but it appeared cut out before it finished and before I could really find out what it was selling. Then another started, and it happened again. Basically, there's some kind of computer glitch. Gosh, if only they put some of the revenue from the inflated gas prices into the advertising system. Yes, it would still be annoying. But at least they'd be peddling with quality production values.

Also, the station isn't really conveniently placed. You've got to turn off the main road and then make a few more turns, going around and then under the turnoff. No, that's not a big deal; and it might not even be the gas station's fault, strictly speaking. But they still bear responsibility. And you'd think that with all the planning that went into having a service plaza at a location like this, they'd have figured out how to do it right.

They can't charge as much as they do back east. Tom repeated this to me, then quoted me a price over three times what I would have paid back home in Chicago. Completely pitiful that he preaches that while in the third largest city in the country prices for a basic shower door are roughly a third of what this clown is trying to get away with. Avoid these guys at all costs, not a legit company at all.
Awesome locals bar with a cool vibe and great cocktails. The owner tends bar some evenings and is super friendly. Great spot for a drink or a dinner date.

Don't knock it til you try it. I was treated to a pineapple upside down donut and my sugar went through the roof. I had to cut myself off from eating the whole thing but it truly was an amazing treat.

My husband and I had our 12/23/17 at Kimberton Inn. We worked with Jason and Jeff from the very beginning, and they were extremely helpful and accommodating. The restaurant was beautifully decorated for Christmas and the ceremony and dinner were absolutely fantastic. The service was phenomenal and the food was even better. Our guests could not stop raving about the food and the atmosphere. We will be back every year for our anniversary and will look back on our special day as completely perfect.

I order huancaina potatoes not to good the potatoes was raw and the sauce nothing close to the real huancaina and watery ; the fish ceviche not fresh lot of red onions on top and the lemon juice was bitter; the chaufa rice with a lot of sesame oil; I want to thanks the manager of the restaurant that came to the table and apologized with us for the mistakes and offered free picarones.

Called them on 12/16/2017
Due to the forest fire they evacuated the Alpacas and will not be in operation this week.

Please avoid going until everything is back to normal

The front left speaker we were sitting next to was crackling loudly whenever there were loud sound effects and was ruining the movie so we moved from our front row seats up to the back middle. Could still hear it along with the squeak from every seat in the place. Really ruined our movie.

The food is terrific, but the service is horrible.  They do not have enough people working.  Tables are not cleared in a timely manner, there are no refills on drinks and people wait to be seated even though there are many tables open.  It is the same every time I come here.

When my white friend suggested me an Indian restaurant to visit while in NOLA, I was like ya sure but Saffron blew my mind and in more ways than one! First of all so tough to get a reservation - Saffron was playing hard to get with me and I wanted it even more ‍
Finally got in, entered in and witnessed the classiest decor and lighting! The bar is full and the bartenders definitely know what their shit. 
The family owned restaurant has taken Indian fine dining experience to another level! The food is 
All sorts of Ah-mazing!
The service was impeccable, the servers had so much knowledge and were smart. The owners were warm n welcoming and super genuine. One of the best meals, especially Indian, I've had in my life. Very soon I see it becoming an institution in New Orleans
Love the new look of the place. Definitely more spacious, open and bright. Outdoor seating available. Full bar. Oysters and fried seafood plate was good!

I'm so happy there's poke in South Tampa, and that I can get it at a drive thru (when you have kids, it's so much easier not having to get out of the car)  

I had the Alaska bowl. A small is more than enough for lunch, and it is full of fresh salmon.  It was very good. I wish there was a little less quinoa and more seaweed salad or edamame, but I liked it otherwise. 

I also had the avocado wave smoothie. It was tasty. There were some unblended chunks of mango, but it was still good with good avocado flavor.  

Service is pretty fast, although I imagine cooked items would take longer.

It's a little ridiculous. I basically live at Porch. They indulge my addiction to their space. I've been known to perch there for an hour, but the benefit is that my home now feels wonderful with all of the little treasures I've discovered there over the past few years--soy candles that smell like freshly cut grass, a smokey glass votive that casts the most wonderful glow from my nightstand, a prehistoric succulent peeking from a spikey white ceramic planter--Porch is helping me to live my life that much more beautifully. 

I have a bargain with myself that I can only buy one item when I'm there; otherwise, I'd buy the whole store and my house would look like . . . Porch. 

See why I live there?

California rolls were exceptionally tiny and made mostly of cucumber. 
The tempura in the Vegas roll was burnt and awful and again, tiny little baby rolls. 
And they charged me for an extra roll I never ordered. 
 2 stars is too good honestly

Dr Clayman and his team were very professional. From our first discussion, he put my mind at ease about my thyroid cancer diagnosis. The whole experience at Tampa General was very positive and I believe all that helped in contributing to a smooth recovery. He is definitely the best thyroid surgeon in Tampa as far as I am concerned.

Been to Birchwood a few times now and they have been nothing but helpful. Willingly answering my questions. We love the raw cheese and farm fresh eggs. There has never been any political discussion when I've been there. I recommend this farm.

I really like going to the Italian Market office. Highly recommend Dr. Romano. The receptionists have always been very helpful when calling in scripts needed at the last minute. Thank you all for being so pleasant! :)
I love this restaurant! Not only do they have an amazing space with a great bar but, awesome fire pits outside and live music on weekends. The food is yummy too- you won't be disappointed!

The papaya salad was delicious. The soups are packed with flavor. I also split the yellow curry with my mom. It was a little sweet for my taste, but I enjoyed it nonetheless. Atmosphere is cozy and casual. Overall, loved this place. Would definitely recommend it.
I've always had a good experience here. The meat and bread are always very fresh. Love the classic Italian. My four year old loves it here too

Aimee Olexy and Stephen Starr must not have gotten the news that people like to relax and converse over their food or that people don't like excruciating noise. This one is louder than Jones, Buddakon, and Talulah's Garden. I don't care how good the food is -- and it was fairly good here -- I will not return to a restaurant that is deafening. Are you trying to turn the tables over faster or just clueless. I was here at the invitation of a friend last night and couldn't wait to leave. Having said that, the decor is quite nice. Too bad I couldn't spend more time enjoying it.

2.5 stars for mediocre food.

It really wasn't as flavorful as any other Cajun food I've had (even in California). I was disappointed by almost everything (shrimp creole, jambalaya, bread roll, portion size, seafood quality). The crawfish etouffe was okay, but not memorable. It's a bad sign when I have to use the seasonings and hot sauces at the table to give the food enough flavor. The jambalaya was entirely mushy like it was sitting for hours and just got microwaved. The crawfish and shrimp were tiny and the meat disintegrated in my mouth as if the meat was previously frozen and thawed out. I would say the combination plate of crawfish etouffee, jambalaya, and shrimp creole was more than 50% rice...the rice was hiding under the shrimp and crawfish which was pretty disappointing. For an entree that's nearly $20, it was small, mostly filled with rice, and had underwhelming flavor to say the least. I had high hopes because of the long line but I guess it's just not my cup of tea.

Winner!! This is a nice little place!  A great menu selection, great service, and really great food.  They even gave us a snickerdoodle pancake as a first time visitor and boy was it amazing. If your looking for a small, hometown style diner with great food, this is the place!

We had a great dinner experience here on a Saturday night. It was really busy but we only had to wait about 10 minutes for a table. We ordered the alligator bites, crab mac and cheese, and house salad. They were all appetizers but it was a perfect amount of food for the two of us to share. All the food was delicious and Kiki our server was wonderful. Good choice!
Great service, awesome atmosphere, and the best food in Nashville. Mac and Cheese is great.  Nice selection of Moonshine cocktails and local beers.
Very good for a chain. Nice gluten free options. The service was good. Prices not bad.
The absolute best brunch I had in a while. The bread is delicious the eggs Benedict with salmon was perfect. The coffee was excellent. Next time I'm in Philly, I'm coming back for sure.

Went there for lunch today for the first time and had the chicken, brown rice, and eggplant.  It was delicious!  The eggplant (which is more of an eggplant tomato compote) is so flavorful!!!  I can already see myself coming back for their fresh prepackaged meals to have at least once a week.  Great price, healthy options, and great flavor.

They also have some hot and fresh meal options on top of the fresh prepackaged meals.

I'm a patient of Dr. Amy Singer and I have to say that this has been a horrible experience. 

Referrals don't get made, you'll have to do that legwork yourself. I called and asked about a referral (left a message that is), they called back and told me that I had received a call about it on some such date. That call never showed up on my phone or at&t bill. 

Then I dropped a car jack on my foot one Monday night. It wasn't better by Wednesday so I called Dr. Singer's office. They couldn't get me in but were nice enough to order an X-ray. I got the X-ray done Wednesday. Didn't hear anything. Finally called Dr. Singer's office Monday morning. Still haven't heard from them Monday eob. 

These people do not take their job seriously. Which is a horrible thing for health care. I can't speak to the rest of Banner Medical, but avoid this place if you can.

Just so people know, I sent an email to the address Banner provided in the response, detailing, again, what happened. I have had no response as of 10/12/18

The restaurant smelled dirty, like oily body odor. The service was great...the food on the other hand was mediocre. Typical chain restaurant taste, bland. Everything needed salt including the carbonara, which has bacon in it. This restaurant needs to be cleaned.

While I don't frequent La Collina on a usual basis, I stopped off tonight with a few family members. 

We came in at 6:30 PM, but we had a 7:00 PM reservation. However, the host was very kind and seated us a bit early. 

Soon after that, our waiter, Mike came over. Throughout the entire dinner he was very polite, professional and courteous. 

Mike started off being bringing us a variety of quick starters including an Italian style bread, peppers and eggplant. They were all very fresh and tasty. 

At the same time that the bread and vegetables came out, we ordered our drinks. I got a ginger splash with a Maraschino cherry. 

Eventually, we ordered our appetizers. I got the calamari and also had a little of the minestrone soup. The calamari was pretty good. It was nicely grilled though it was a little hard. The minestrone soup was nice as well. It had fresh, tasty vegetables. 

We then had our entrees. I got an absolutely excellent ribeye steak! The steak was moist, full of flavor and was tender. It also had a great side of potatoes and some other vegetables. 

Finally, it was time for dessert. Mike brought out a giant cart full of fresh desserts including chocolate and vanilla cakes, cannolis and fresh berries. I decided to get the vanilla cake. It came out very fast with a nice side of strawberries and chocolate shavings on the side of the icing. The cake itself was solid, but not spectacular especially compare to other nice restaurants in the area. Looking back on it now, I wish I went with the cannoli. 

Also, many other reviews complain about the price of La Collina. I will say it is expensive, but for the quality of the food, wait staff and ambiance, it is very good. 

Speaking of the ambiance, La Collina is just great. The view of the Schuylkill River is absolutely amazing as well. 

Also, La Collina has complimentary valet, which is great. The valet worker remembered my car perfectly and was very personable. 

Altogether, I had a great experience at La Collina. The wait staff, ambiance and food made the experience worthwhile!

waited one and half hours for my order and have never got it. People coming much later than me got their order earlier. Asked the guy who sticked that I am someone he called earlier, which is not me. Have to cancel my order after one and half hour waiting. Bad experience.

I joined this gym after seeing an advertisement for a nutritional challenge on Facebook. Figured what have I got to lose? Well this wasn't some ordinary gym. These coaches helped me reach my goals and stay motivated. I have belonged to many gyms in the past and this one, by far, has been my favorite. They are knowledgeable and motivating and bossy and pushy and make you sweat and simply, make you want to do well!! Nothing but positive things to say about this gym, the trainers and the programming!!
I had Caitlyn Williams cut my hair and had an amazing experience! She is super friendly, fast, and professional -- and I love my haircut. Highly recommend!
Food was quick and delicious. Brisket, ribs and pulled pork were great. Excellent service. Definitely coming back!
Very disappointed to watch a server release helium balloons right outside their front door. Not environmentally friendly.

This restaurant could've easily gotten 4 or 5 stars from me if the service wasn't so poor. We tried to call to make reservations, but we're denied. So we decided to walk-in anyway. We waited about 10 minutes for a fairly empty restaurant. There just seemed to be a lack of communication between servers. Multiple servers asking us the same thing over and over, but forgetting to bring it out. Our food came out separately almost 10 minutes apart. And we didn't get one of our appetizers until we were ready to leave  (given to to us complimentary for the wait)

The food....AMAZING!!!! we order the Thai chili wings and mussels for appetizers... did I say amazing??? I wished the wings came in larger order so we could've taken some to go! For the entree we had the curry salmon with white rice. Sooooo good. Not too thick and chalky, but just right with a bit of a kick. We also ordered the shrimp scampi with spinach..eh. it was just ok, but I'd probably try another curry dish instead.

Maybe it was just an off night for service,  but the food made up for it.
Delicious pizza and friendly people! Short wait time and the food is always prompt and great!
Sugar, sugar and more sugar best describe this pizza sauce.  Veggies were mushy and protein was full of filler.
Jean Claude  is the man.. best service I've had in Tampa yet!! A ten player and a true good server .. very happy w my party!!!

Last year I was new to the area and had no clue where to start looking for a dentist. Luckily I found Dr. Mach! He's everything you look for in a dentist. He's gentle, thorough, patient, knowledgeable and has patient friendly equipment. He's done several procedures on me and I'm extremely satisfied!  The office is super clean and the two girls that work in his office are awesome! They are so sweet and helpful! I highly recommend Dr. Mach and his staff!!

The only reason I'm giving this place 5 stars is because of Denise! I have been trying to contact corporate on her behalf to let them know how lucky they are to have an employee like her (guess I'll have to wait until I buy more there and get another receipt) it's impossible to take a survey when you don't have one and with a 11 month old I can barely keep track of my shoes! Anyways I had a horrible experience with a girl with yellow hair and a bad attitude (she's there "Human Resources person") the guy manager didn't even do anything when I called it to his attention! Luckily I called the next day after I cooled down and spoke to a Norah she was so nice and helpful and told me to come in before she left she had Denise help me! Because of Denise I will continue to shop at that location! I just love her attitude and the love she has for babies and kids everyone else here seems to hate there job! except for the two younger guys (spider man and the one with curly hair) there very pleasant as well!

I ate here last night and ordered a fried chicken sandwich. Food was great, but it was after my meal that I saw little roaches all over the wall. I told my server about this and she was extremely dismissive and got a napkin and killed the roach. All she said was "the building was old". I explained to her my concern about quality and she told me not to worry about the bug issue. I would be extremely selective when deciding on eating here. Had the waitress been more empathic and less dismissive about the issue I would be more keen to eat here again.

I think Westin Hotels have passed their expiration date. My previous two stays at different properties have been a disappointment and this one was the final straw.  The price for the quality of the room was outrageous.  I would have expected a room like this to be in the $75 - $80 range not $279. I don't mind paying more money for a room but the quality needs to match. Check in was supposed to be at 3:00 and I didn't get into my room until 4:15. They had one employee taking care of both valet and bellhop and he did a terrific job but I felt bad for him.   The room was very dated and the carpet need to be replaced and the layout of the room was horrible.  I will say that the bathroom was nicely done. Lastly I ordered a $9.00 desert that had a $12 surcharge for room service. Never, never again will I stay at a Westin.
Really good coffee with a great mellow atmosphere.  Saw them at an event in Brandon so had to see the coffee shop in person.

I've been meaning to come here for a while, as I heard their happy hour was tasty. The boyfriend and I got one of each off the menu. It was delicious! Great martinis, and Gabrielle our server was so sweet and humble. We loved the entire experience!

I like DiFabio's. Love the concept and the food is always good. Brings something different to Media.Great rolls for sandwiches and good enough pasta for a low key place as such. Highly recommend the cheesesteak egg rolls. Only negative is the service. It's not necessarily awful, but on our three in restaurant visits bartender always disappears. Ordered Uber Eats tonight and they sent ranch dressing with a Caesar salad. We go out a lot and I think we would come more if the service was consistent, warm and welcoming.

I have always been nervous to try a skin treatment (facial) and finally decided to gice it a shot. Not knowing much about the services and what to expect the staff at Spa Solai were extremely helpful and friendly! I scheduled an appointment with Sammie, from the minute she greeted me she was very friendly and focused on making sure I was comfortable. She explains the entire process ans what to expect, she gave me excellent tips and advice for skin care. I am glad I decided to try it, after one visit I think I am hooked! Can't wait for the next one! Thank you Spa Solai, especially Sammie!

The dinner buffet was ok. Some spicy some aromatic dishes. Naan was hard and dry - or very greasy (there were two batches). For around $18 a reasonable value. The wine per glass was also budget  - but barely potable. The staff was uniformly grumpy and unfriendly, and overcharged on the bill (added a buffet dinner). Decor was nice. Modern but friendly. Not terrible but certainly not worth more than 2 stars

My husband had eaten here once and said the food was tasty.  I never got the chance to taste the food, however, because of the slow service.  

When we walked in, some people were leaving, saying to us "Don't bother - we waited 45 minutes for our food and it never came, so we left."  I should have listened to them!  We ended up sitting next to another group that seemed upset about their food taking so long.  Another family at a large table seemed to have an incomplete order and hadn't gotten any silverware yet.  

Someone finally came to take our drink order, so we had a beer while we wondered whether it would be worth waiting for food.  Then the waitress (?) (maybe the hostess?) eventually came by and said "Is everything going OK?"  We told her no one had taken our order.  By the time someone came to take our order, we just asked for the check so we could leave.

Adding insult to injury, we couldn't leave because our car was blocked in.  The parking lot is a disaster - they allow double parking, and customers have to go back inside to find out who the f&%* is blocking their car so they can leave this crazy place.  Ugh.  Not going back.

It was a cold, windy, city morn when we reached Washington Avenue, and I still hadn't had my first cup of java. I was trying to maintain my good mood, but it would be a losing battle without some caffeine soon. 

Desperate times called for desperate measures. 

I remembered there was this Bambu shop nearby, so I Yelped it and realized it was right across 6th Street from where we were. We walked over and found it in the inner corner of the shopping center. It was a small shop, with short red sofa, three cafe tables, and a few chairs along the window. The walls were covered in menus and photos of their signature Che fruity concoctions. 

Colorful, but I needed something stronger and hotter. Farther down the drinks list was the coffee. I asked for Vietnamese coffee, hot. I normally drink it in VN cafes or after meals, so this was my first takeout. 

It was exactly as expected. Strong, hot and sweetened by condensed milk. I missed the whole drip experience but it was great to be able to shop the market with java in hand.

The first time I came to iDope six months ago, I was immediately helped and my cracked screen was fixed within 5-8 minutes. Today, I returned to get a replacement and was delighted to see that iDope's quick and easy service hasn't changed at all. You can tell the people there, especially Pat, truly care about helping you with your screen issues and really know their stuff. One of the great things about iDope is that they have no ties to Apple or other phone companies, so their advice is always honest and they're not just trying to make a quick buck off of your hard earned money!

I would highly recommend iDope for anyone who is having issues with their broken phone screens.
Delicious little place! Didn't think much from the outside but the food is sooo good! Big proportions too!

Very happy we found Paul! I've been on the lookout for a dresser for forever but had something so specific in mind that it could not be found. But Paul met with us, listened, and drew up a wonderful design. He kept us in the loop and we collaborated throughout the building stage. Great communicator, nice guy, wonderful business! We couldn't be happier with the dresser.

Stopped by here for a quick weekday lunch. The place is chic; a small little place with a food bar seating and right across from Jefferson University.

The food review was mixed. I had ordered Rangoon samosas and spicy Sichuan noodles. The samosa (fried dumplings) were very good to my surprise. It is served over some sweet jelly which at first struck as a bit odd. The flavors very well balanced and I have to say, this was very good. The spicy Sichuan noodles on the other hand were too salty and after a few bites, I couldn't feel my tongue due to the spicy. This doesn't mean that the food was poorly prepared; maybe it wasn't what I expected. This the 4 stars. I would definitely recommend you check it out.

The interior is decent. It is not a place for groups to go. I liked the small place, cozy eating set-up at the bar. There are a few tables.

The service was pleasant. They checked on me often and were very polite. Overall, I say exceeds service. The only thing is, I had left my entire entree, it would have been good if they asked "was everything OK?" Again, this is a high bar set for expectations. This shouldn't stop you from trying this place out.

I've been here twice, once with my husband for dinner and once alone for the lunch buffet. Unfortunately, I don't think I'll be back.

First off, when my husband and I ordered dinner, I ordered the lamb curry. I was told "no no no" by the waiter and that "it was too spicy for me" and that I should order "butter chicken." I was honestly insulted. My husband is Indian and I've eaten at countless indian restaurants. When the lamb came out, it wasn't too spicy for me, so there's that. We were instructed to order the vegetable korma as well. The vegetables in there didn't seem fresh, as if they were frozen or something of that nature.

I decided to give it another try for the buffet. I found that the buffet was overtly spicy. I was told that it was "Southern Indian cuisine" which is spicier. I've travelled allover the world and come from a city that has hundreds of Indian/Pakistani restaurants, I've NEVER eaten at a buffet with so many items that were beyond spicy.

Unfortunately, we won't be back.

Blackberry beer, 'nuff said. 

Seriously, you guys, it was delicious and so was everything else we tried.  They seem to have a lot of limited release and specialty beers, so I'd recommend coming often. 

Very casual vibe and they had an almost too cool live DJ the night we went. Tons of puppies and around, too, so bring yours. 

I think they could use a few more games like ping pong or foosball, etc., but we will be back regardless!

Attempted a fry eating contest, we ended at two but farm were those fried tasty. I personally
Went for the vegan option the beat salad and it did not miss a beat. My company had devoured the quite fantastic chicken noodle pasta thing. My other friend had some tuna and kimchi and shrimp cakes. Great wine and beer selection. Bon appetite

Very expensive for what you get. A croissant and a coffee with run you for around $6.50 with tips. Sorry but the croissant was dry and really not tasty. I'm french so i believe i know how  a croissant should taste :) Kind of disappointed about it. The place is great though. The staff is pretty friendly but i will not go back. I'm pretty sure if they don't change the quality and the price they will be gone quickly!

From the start they were pretty shady, their prices are significantly higher than you can find for better quality diamonds elsewhere. I try to support local businesses but refuse to be blatantly ripped off. Never the less I purchased a setting from them in an effort to somewhat support local businesses and I got a higher quality certified diamond elsewhere. I returned to look at wedding bands, again their prices were at least double. So I simply made the purchase else where. I returned to see them about soldering them together (the setting I purchased from them and the band I found at a much better price elsewhere). It's then they will inform you that the will only work on items from their store. Meaning if you decide to buy the same band elsewhere they won't solder it for you. Furthermore if you have another professional jeweler solder it the "Lee Read Diamond Warranty" will be void and they will no longer honor it. So if you want to pay excessively for buying local and have a company that wants to lock out competitive pricing then Lee Read has your name written all over it.

Great food!! Good service! Nice place... and a happy tummy...all that makes for a great Saturday morning! SoBro skillet was an absolute delight...So many flavors in one skillet. The french toast was just right served with real maple syrup.

I'm really torn and have mixed emotions about this place. I really wanted to like it because I loved the look and ambiance of it but had lots of disappointments unfortunately. 

I came here with a couple girlfriends because we wanted to come for happy hour. Happy hour here is a joke and the website lied. I'll start with that. Online it says "select half off appetizers" when we got there that was not the case. Happy hour is now just half off personal pizzas, which none of us wanted, and $1 off some select beers and wines. If it was straight forward in the first place I wouldn't of  expected something else and this negative would of been avoided. 

Now for positives. I loved the look of this place! We had a "private" booth that had beaded curtains that came down and a little personal chandelier on our wall with a dimmer switch so we could set it at the lighting that worked for us. Such a smart idea! The booth was truly adorable and would make for a great date night! 

Our waitress was also a sweet heart. But now for the food. I was set on ordering appetizers because that's what we came for, so even though they were full price I still got them instead of an entree. Big mistake. I ordered the charbroiled oysters (5 in an order) and the cremini mushrooms with blue cheese fondue. Both sounded amazing but both lacked flavor. The oysters promised rep peppers, bacon and Parm cheese. All I tasted was breadcrumbs and they were very dry, no sauce to them. The fondue was very under seasoned and bland and had very little actual mushrooms. With a name of the starter as "cremini mushrooms" I expected a mushroom heavy dish. I actually didn't even eat much of the fondue at all so my waitress took it off the bill which was very nice of here to do.  

I would give 5 stars for our waitress and the ambience of the restaurant but the food just fell flat for me. I may come here again and order something different. My friend had a pasta dish that was actually quite tasty. So this place is worth coming to and checking out but order wisely here!

Three Brothers Pizza was definetly one of the best pizzas I've had since coming down to Florida! The staff overall were really friendly and accommodating. The delivery was surprisingly fast, and the pizza was still warm despite the long distance! The dining area was very comfortable and one of the servers there is pretty cute too!

My favorite grocery store for many reasons!! 1. Healthy food and ingredients are easy to find and located everywhere in the store. 2. The staff is friendly, helpful, and fast. 3. There are seasonal items that are seriously amazing! It's always sad to see them go when the season ends, but there are always more surprises coming in. 4. The store is small and personal! 

I seriously love Trader Joe's.

This review is only for the white pizza.  The staff was very friendly and the prices were right.  I found my pizza to be too greasy  but did have a great garlic flavor.  There is a large selection of pizzas available so you can definitely find something you like.

I have had all positive experiences with two different counselors here. Jill Freeman, has been helping me since July after a traumatic experience. A medical condition prevented me from being able to get there physically so she helped me over phone conferences during those few months. I greatly appreciated her willingness to work with me over the phone despite the fact that it may not be the way she's used to working with people.  

My son ran into some issues at school being bullied to the point where he chose to say "just kill me". I burst into tears while even inquiring about getting an appt with him. Denise the receptionist was so sweet over the phone and told me to just take a deep breath (I was actually driving) so she said she would have Matt call me back (he was in a session) and she took it one step further by texting me his number to make it easier for my to call and leave a voicemail with my info.  He called right back, set something up for the first available time he had.  

My son also went to speak with another counselor closer to home, but we kept our appt with Matt to see who my son felt most comfortable. Of course Matt won my son over as soon as he mentioned football and used sports analogies so my son could better understand the concepts and strategies Matt was teaching us.  The other counselor we met with just listened and gave his opinions, Matt on the other hand got up, drew out a diagram that we could see and immediately was giving strategies on how to stop, walk away, and other pointers to get him in a more positive direction other than acting on his feelings and saying bad things he doesn't mean and will regret.  

We will continue sessions with both counselors as needed in the future.  Obviously these other reviews are either old or biased. There's three sides to every story!  I would recommend Matt and Jill to others.
The food is very good everyone that works there is very friendly give Gloria the best in town

Wow! What a great experience! Visiting family for Thanksgiving and we came here to celebrate a family birthday - as if we didn't need more food after the Thanksgiving feast!

Fresh sushi all around! The rice for the rolls and nigiri were just enough to give it heft but not too much that you get full eating 3 pieces! 

Had some Udon - freshly made with whatever toppings you want! The soup base was delicious. Great flavor and nice and hot for a cold day! 

Delicious Chinese food items available as well. Clams in ginger sauce, mussels in a tomato base (not Chinese but yummy), tempura vegetables (I put this in my Udon), fish, beef sautes.

Needless to say, I over ate!

To end the lunch, I had green tea/match soft serve...the best!

If ever I find myself back in Philly, I'm making my way to Minado!

Came here for a dose of Eggs Benedict, some smoked salmon and a good old fashioned Bloody Mary. Environment was chill and not crowded which always makes for better service. Food was hot and fresh with a tasty kugel fried style shredded potato pancake brick. "Fare" pricing for the quality, will be back another time. Good service too.

Great place for breakfast! The food was excellent and the service was too. I had the biscuits and gravy with eggs and my wife had an omelette. Solid home fires and the rye bread toast is fab, I think baked on site. Cute little place and worth a stop. Enjoy!

Party of four ordered boodae jigae and boolgogi. Boodae jigae was yummy - I liked trying all of the different parts of the stew. Neat experience since having read up on the history of the dish the week before. Banchan was plentiful (the fish cakes were addictive!). And boolgogi was a great sweet/savory dish to help cut back on the kimchi-based stew. We were stuffed and satisfied after this delicious meal!   

The owner was sweet and delighted to serve us. I enjoyed a lot of the antique decor throughout the restaurant. Though the modern fire pit was quite the showstopper.    

Next time I come, I would like to try their roasted mackerel and another stew!

This is a great barber shop with lots of qualified barbers and several chairs to get you in and taken care of quickly.  The staff is top notch and the atmosphere is relaxed and friendly.   Great place to get a real haircut.

My family and I eat at this restaurant on a fairly regular basis. The man who I believe to be the owner or the general manager (middle-aged, Asian man) runs a quality operation. The front counter people that he hires are outstanding. Their friendliness and helpfulness are outstanding. The service and the way that the employees interact with customers rivals that of Chick-fil-a (that's a compliment). The food is always fresh, hot and delicious. I really enjoy Panda Express and especially this particular store.

In town for the Eclipse of 2017, these guys were open late the night before. Vegan + BBQ? Who knew? Great barbecue that my kids loved - sausage was particularly outstanding. Pro tip: this joint is a bar and a restaurant adjacent. We went into the bar side, not realizing there was another half with bigger tables.

When we finally pull the trigger on a vacation home in some outlying area around Boise, this place will get lots of business from us!

3.5 really. The concept is really neat. It's a wide open area with bowling darts and pingpong, and it never feels too crowded. However, the food is incredibly bland and for such a high price (13 for a burger). It's not bad, but not good which is why I put a 3.5. Check it out, but eat before you go.
You get five stars because my daughter said that the prices are reasonable they are age friendly and she loved the atmosphere. Also we had a wonderful waitress can't remember her name.

It's sad to come to NOLA and have bad gumbo...no depth. And overpriced at $14 each for a bowl to go. On the other hand, the Bloody Mary olive infused vodka is good, I would have it in a dirty martini.

I had a very good experience with Dr. Bingham. He took the time to listen and to address all my concerns. Because of Dr. Bingham, I will go back and refer my family. The gentleman that helped me pick out frames was also very friendly and knowledgeable. However, the receptionist had horrible customer service. I nearly cancelled my appointment when I had to reschedule and felt like I was a huge inconvenience. And though she was friendly enough with me at my appointment, I witnessed her completely belittle another customer for being late, in a way that I would NEVER be a customer there had she talked to me that way. So, Dr. Bingham is wonderful!! however I would really look at who you have representing you at the front counter. My guess is you are losing clientele due to her attitude. Or, maybe she just has more bad days than most :)

I can say I will not be back at this place. Kevin was our waiter n he was bad. Took forever to take our order forever to bring our drinks. And the way he spoke to us we couldn't understand one word. He needs to pickup his jeans I don't need to see his underwear 
We asked for more fries n never got them n no refills on our drinks 
I will not be going back

This place has a lot of potential to be really good, I just didn't, like my meal. It was fried plaintain with carnitas. I wasn't expecting it to be a barbecue meal, I was just looking for something adventerous. I guess I bit off more than I could chew..literally. I would still go back and try something else because the salsa was banging and for there to have only been two servers working, the service was really good. The lounge could use a little febreeze tho..lol.

Stopped in here on a whim to meet up with some friends for drinks, very cute inside (hard to figure out if it is the right place since they have no sign on the door, but I kindof like that). It was a Friday night and it wasn't too crowded which was great. I would like to go here again and actually have dinner, seemed to be good.

WOW!!!!!!
This place is amazing!!! Food is flavored just right and you get PLENTY for the price. The have a few salsas to choose from from a mild Pico to a very hot one ( didn't try so can't comment on the hotness). They have good variety of condiments to choose from as well. I have eaten at many Mexican food places in a variety of states including Mexico and this is hands down in the top 3 only being out done by a place in Mexico and well.......my own mamas kitchen!!! The staff is friendly and provide excellent customer service, so if you want good food and great customer service go see Victor and the chef down at Baja Fish on Wetmore!!!

The bar service was excellent, always had a drink and never had to sit with an empty glass! However, the reason I didn't give this place 5 stars was the waitress. The older waitress we had took our order, forgot an item we ordered and didn't even check up on us to see how everything was. She wasn't even polite when she approached us..... she actually seemed a little annoyed. Its took over an hour after eating for her to come back and see if we wanted our check. Had being a waitress myself I understand things can get hectic if your overwhelmed, however it didn't seem that overwhelming there at the time.

Had a craving for a good bagel.... my Google search brought up All Star Bagel. Unfortunately I was a little disappointed because they don't make a true kettled bagel. Instead they only offer what we call a pan bagel. If I wanted that I could have just gone up the street to Dunkin Donuts and probably for less money. Truth be told the bagels were good but I'm kind of old school and truly enjoy a real kettled bagel. Don't think I'll be going back I'll probably just stick to getting my Bagels from either Upper Dublin Bagel Squad or Manhattan Bagel. Thanks for reading my rant.

There's finally a new Starbucks drive thru open further down Hillsborough that's probably worth the drive. This location is frustrating. On the corner of extremely congested Memorial and Hillsborough, and paired with GameStop, in the smallest plaza ever. If you can squeeze past the drive thru line to enter the parking lot, you'll be lucky to find a spot. Going inside is typically faster but who wants to risk getting trapped? Exiting is tricky because if you park you basically have to exit right onto Memorial. If you drive thru, you can loop around the building again to turn right onto Memorial -or- turn right onto Hillsborough. Very rarely does either option go smoothly. On more than one occasion they were unexpectedly closed for unknown reasons. It's too bad because the staff is super friendly, and do a fine job prepping drinks and breakfast sammiches. I'd only recommend this Starbucks if you travel during times of little to no traffic.

I needed to quit combustible tobacco... I made the switch to Vaping at a local shop in my hometown. It was similar to Level Vape Shop in that the employees cared about helping make the transition as easy as possible with education, patience with my rookie questions without making me feel like an idiot and turned me on to high quality products.
When I first met Kelly I knew she ran the same type of operation, despite all of her competition turning to competing on price alone, LVS provides great prices and more importantly a non intimidating environment that is focused on helping smokers make the switch. I highly suggest and recommend LVS to my friends and family that want to give quitting a try...

this is not to complain about the food...because we didn't get any.  Our reservation was for 3, we were seated at 3:20, didn't get even water until 3:45...then another 15 to get our drinks, had to ask twice to get a basket of bread. we walked out at 5 because we never got our food and never saw our waitress.  the servers were each out for themselves, never worked as a team, never smiled.  i know it sucks to work on christmas, i've done it myself, but this was such a mess.  one star is generous.

Bad service, happy hour burger tasted like cruddy old beef, salmon burger tasted like canned tuna, order got messed up, and the place is overpriced (outside of HH which is the only redeeming quality). I would not recommend, but given the shortage of options around, I can see why people would go here.
Fantastic experience! Very friendly staff and beautiful venue. I was recommended Dr. Nabors upon moving to Nashville and I'm very happy with the choice!

An institution - quick service, delicious coffee and fresh beignet. I recommend coming here outside of peak times just to save waiting in line (time you could spend drinking!). Perfect place to hit after your done with bourbon street and need some something in your belly!

As a Hilton Diamond member, I found this property to be the worst one that I have stayed at. The front desk didn't recognize by membership status, the digital key feature that Hilton is so proud of never worked (I only got messages to expect it to be enabled soon), the bath tub diverter was stuck in the shower position, and the whirlpool water was barely warm and the jets did not work.   On the positive side the room was clean.
I have been coming here for 20 years. If you want real New Orleans food, before you head to The Quarter, stop here. This is home.
I have tried most of the Pho places in town and this is my "go to" place on this end of tow. Really good broth and people there are really nice. Definitely recommend to everyone.

While this is a great place to entertain yourself with electronic games and things. Think twice about eating here. The fare is sub par to other local restaurants and along the lines of mediocre chain restaurant food. While I don't like to pick on the wait staff because I've worked in the service industry. I will just say it was less then attentive. The food was edible but room temperature by the time it got to the table. Luckily we were not in a rush because everything was a slow process.

Great family place during the day and a great low key place for adults at night. Great views from every seat and usually a good band or dude with a guitar. Our last visit on 10-17 was marred by excruciatingly slow service (even slower than usual) and my Cuban sandwich .  How can you screw up a Cuban? Well, they have that perfected. DO NOT ORDER THE CUBAN.  The 'ground pork' is Spam and the meat is 2 paper thin slices with pickles stuffed on the ends. Terrible. Grouper cheeks were great!  The picture is the Cuban.

Although the place is cool and smells amazing, we were excited cuz it looked amazing too and expected great treats. We wanted dessert and picked up 2 pralines and two chocolate covered gophers. The pralines tasted stale and the gophers were not bad, but not great. To top it all off, the 4 pieces of treats we bought (2 pralines and two gophers) was $18.21.
For over $18.00 for 4 pieces of candy, it better come with a happy ending!!!
It didn't.  Don't let the looks fool ya!!!
Slammer!!!
Food was great and very reasonable. Got in before a concert with no wait. Service was good as well

I was happy to bring out of town friends to the Rose Petals Cafe & Lounge today for a nice breakfast.  They were seeking between the Savory & Sweet, but wanted it to provide that "comfort food" appeal.  I immediately felt Rose Petals would meet this picky bunches punch list.  

We called ahead because we had a group of five (5) and the seating is limited.  As we arrived, we had a table awaiting us and our greeter- Malcolm.  Wow, Malcolm was awesome and made our experience a wonderful one, he was pleasant and attentive to our requests.  

Food:  The group ordered coffee, tea, waffles, french toast and a few other menu favorites. The food was good, everyone was pleased with their orders.  

Service:  The wait for the meal was a bit long-over 15 minutes.  I am not sure of the set-up in the kitchen, but they may need more chefs to get the food out quicker, but that is my only note for this special place.

Price:  Reasonable for the portions offered.

Decided to do something different with my 12 year old son, and came to Arrowhead to try archery for the first time.... What a fun and personal archery experience. The owners are casual and welcoming of the inexperienced. Highly recommend.

Saw the Halal Guys as we walked down canal street. Got so excited and sure enough it's the same guys from NYC. Had a combo with beef and falafel and everything was on-point. Made our night! Next time we are in NOLA this is a must!

After our awful experience at Tapped, we were both still starving and wanted something fast. I have heard great things about Hi Pointe so we figured let's give it a shot.

You walk in and up to the order counter. The man who took our order was very nice and moved quickly. The girl that checked us out was also very nice.

It was busy but not super crowded, it was very easy to find a table. 

The food came SO fast. It was delicious and affordable! A little greasy but We both expected that going in. It would be the BEST hangover remedy! 

Overall the experience and food here was just great! I will definitely be back again the next time I want a burger! Do yourself a favor and check this St Louis staple out!

This is amongst the best Indian food I've had on the East Coast. The chicken has been perfectly tender on each of the dishes I have ordered and the dal makhani deserves SPECIAL praise!
Delivery folks don't come up to my apartment even when there is place to park; which is a bit of a downer - but for food alone, this is an easy 5/5 for me. Keep it up please!

If you want to wait two weeks for your computer to be fixed and get daily excuses why it's not ready you should bring your computer here, Then when  you are told it's ready, you show up and still have to wait a half hour.

I've been here more than a dozen times and have ordered almost everything off the menu. Everything that I have ordered has been fantastic! I definitely would recommend the brisket cheesesteak and the roast pork. The owners are welcoming and outgoing. Easily the best sandwich spot in Abington!

This restaurant has really delicious food and very pretty decor. We had mixed tandoori grill, palak paneer and naan. Probably the best Kashmiri naan we've had. Very pleasant atmosphere and good service.
I don't understand all the great reviews here. The food is amazingly horrible. Very bland!

Just don't do it.

ROACHES everywhere. This place is nasty. It is also very old.
It shouldn't be a Hampton Inn. It is more like an old worn out Holiday Inn from 1978!

The staff is very understanding of the issues. That is the sad part.

Really good Neapolitan wood fired pizza ; friendly service, nice ambiance. Like others, offered a free glass of a decent house wine when we dropped in without having BYOB'd. Salads are terrific, ricotta stuffed meatball and eggplant appetizers phenomenal and beautiful salads big enough for two. Good, fresh food with a variety of toppings - I had the broccoli rabe and salciccia pie. Good value compared to the only other place in the region (Liberty Hall Lambertville) that makes good Neapolitan pies. Will become a definite addition to our regular restaurant rotation.
Cute place just opened. Super friendly staff. Great ribs and pulled pork. Yummy cornbread & homemade pie. They managed to pull off a large to-go order in 15 mins on opening weekend. Thumbs up.

Love this studio and the instructors.  Parking situation sucks but get there early for the class you want to take and plan on having to walk as there is no accommodating parking in the nearby lot.  It's worth it for the amazing yoga you will receive.

Konan has some of the best bbq I've ever had. Their ribs are amazing but the sausage was unreal and the pork was delicious. Mac n cheese is tasty. Probably the best greens my wife and I have ever eaten. And the staff is super friendly. Great for take out or eat in.
What a great place!  Friendly staff.  Fresh ingredients and lots of choices.  Try the hot pot if you have not before.  It wonderful.  Highly recommend

Food is good, service is great.  Price is reasonable.  Number one reason to come here though is the little Cheerios in 2 oz containers that preoccupies your little ones while you wait for food in peace and hold a semi-reasonable conversation with your spouse.  Easy parking is also a plus.  Seriously, we love it here!
Brought my jeans here to have them hemmed and I'm very pleased with the result! They were beautifully hemmed and the pricing seemed reasonable - I paid $11.
I'm so pleased with how clean and sparkling my windows are! This is a fantastic local company that is conscientious and thorough, prompt and clean.

We didn't have a reservation but the host was polite and accommodating. While we sat at the bar waiting for a table, decided to just eat at the bar. The bartender, Daniel, was incredible. He made the best Manhattan I've ever had and was extremely polite and attentive. Prime filet was worth every penny, and Brussels sprouts side dish was fantastic. I'd come back anytime.

Had a great experience at the Crow's Nest.  Our group had the wings to start followed by the steak biscuits, cheese burger, French dip and the fish sandwich.  The food was great and the service was on point.

Excellent homemade Italian with a great presentation. Custom drinks are great, try stormy Monday. Service is excellent. Does take out and local delivery. Highly recommended. 

Homemade pasta and motz was excellent.

Extremely reasonable prices 

Great discovery

You walk by this place near Opryland. Very loud but the locals love it. Music was so loud couldnt even talk to each other. I opted for smoked chicken. Did not care for it at all. VERY expensive for a small piece of meat and a handful of fries. Also their drink prices are ridiculous!  It was like 12.00 or something like that for one mixed drink. I would expect that at a very luxe resort not a country western bar. Would rather just buy a bottle and some soda and kick back in my room.

Omg the tofu pad see ew is amazing - so many vegetables and they actually managed to make it spicy enough for my taste. The massaman curry was also nice and flavorful - and had papaya, so interesting! but could have maybe used a little more coconut milk. Nice staff too. Glad to have found this place on our long drive through the South.

My family and I came here for Christmas Eve for dinner. The service was terrible, very slow, the staff had to be asked to bring silverware repeatedly. Had a 6:30 reservation and our food didn't come out til 9:00. They obviously overbooked reservations and were understaffed. Some of the dishes looked like they had been microwaved, yet the food wasn't even hot! A real disappointment for a Christmas Eve dinner. The one thing that was flowing at the table was wine. Sure, lots of $ to be made on wine!!

My favorite local town grocery and more. Ridley's has everything the grocery stores in town have and then some. Bakery, Deli and even an Ace Hardware Store! 

If you need it they've got it. Good selection among the dry goods as well as produce. 

Staff are helpful and friendly and know their stuff.

Will be returning for sure! Don't let anyone ever tell you that corn doesn't belong in ice cream. I got that and the fruit cup, which were both very good. My only improve would be for a bigger dining area for people who would like to relax there.

Very simple menu but make no mistake, the coffee is A-M-A-Z-I-N-G!!!! Staff was very polite and facility was super clean! The mocha coffee was very creamy but not heavy and not too sweet. My drink was perfectly made  with a heart on topDefinitely a revisit tomorrow :)

Sushi Ya is my most favorite sushi place ever! I am from Germany, my husband is American and grew up in Boise.
Once a year we come to Idaho and can't wait to enjoy the Sushi at this restaurant.
Their AYCE special is amazing value!
Go for the 18.95$ one as this includes the specialty rolls. Those are so delicious!!
Best ones are Playboy, Mountain, CK and Hurricane - big, special and so tasty!!
Only thing to improve: the interior design/atmosphere - it is pretty basic. If they pimped it up a little bit more, they could attract even more customers.

The food here was pretty good. The tacos were kind of blah mage with ground beef. Chili queso dip was outstanding. Prices were a little high but probably about average for oro valley. Service was ok but nothing special. Nothing special about this place at all really.

5 stars for my first time attending. Boudain balls, head hog cheese, double chop pork chop, and the venison. Everything was so good. The chef even came out and introduced our entree's. The dirty rice with the chop is probably the BEST dirty rice here!

I came here last night with my boyfriend. We sat at the chefs counter which was great! We got to see all the orders being made and all the delicious food. My boyfriend ordered the meatballs and spaghetti - he said it was good. I ordered the branzino- I didnt like it. It was very fishy, almost inedible. I didn't think it was cooked all the way and over seasoned. I ate maybe half of it. The waitress was friend and the ambiance was nice. However the food was ehh and it is expensive for what it is.

My husband received an undercooked burger & oninon ring topping with a burnt bun via a postmates order. We were offered no refund & the "rawness" was explained away. They said they do medium rare, but my husband disagrees. Won't be returning. We contacted Postmates for a refund.

There are many great Thai places in town. I have no problem trying new places, so when my wife said that the curry was good, I thought I would try their food. 

We ordered take out. $38+$6 tip for tom ka gai soup, corn fritters, Penang and Pad se ew. The Panang was good and the fritters were good.

The soup was very watered down and had very little flavor. The Pad se ew was oily, flavorless and had no spice! I ordered it hot and it was very bland. I called and they offered to credit the Pad se ew. Also, very small portions compared to the other Thai places in town. 

my wife can eat here if she wants, but I think I'm done with Thai Island.

Make sure to make a reservation a few days in advance because they tend to book up. Made a reservation for a Friday night for 5 people and when we went in, got seated right away. Got 5 pizzas, the crust is thin so it's easy to have multiple slices....plain, Margherita, pepperoni, the special (white with tomatoes and spinach) and peppers and sausage. All delicious and able to take home whatever we didn't eat! Definitely recommend!

Not sure if they should just make spiral staircases because the rest of what they do is not done well, the customer service is very weak, sales people make the sale and then act like they have no communication with the production dept.
I you want it to be real late and missing parts then mylen stairs is the right place.

If this is the same guy...My dad and I were swayed by his slick presentation and hired him.  He "regrouted" all the tile--kitchen, bathrooms.  Left a mess, grout smeared everywhere.   Yeah, he told me how to clean it before it got too hard.  Too late.  The grout is now cracking and discolored.  Worse than before he started.   Can't find his card.  It has been 6 months now so a little late.

Will not return. I waited an hour in the waiting room before being taken back just to wait another 15 minutes for the doctor to see me. He spent 2 minutes with me, never introduced himself and did not address my problem.

Good food; friendly staff all working together to make the dining experience a really good one. Cheese dip and chips were one of the best that I have had. Definitely would come back and order it. Burrito bowls were good but had a lot of lettuce, probably more than necessary. We also had the street corn which was good because of the seasonings and the cheese.

Stopped in for breakfast with my son. Was welcomed right away with yummy smells and smiles. Our waitress was amazing. Our food was yummy and cooked to perfection.Prices are reasonable and large selection. Definitely will be returning.

I can't say enough about this place I live in West Chester and the new location is right below where I live so I took an employee there  to try it out and it was absolutely delicious! The owner was so incredibly nice to me and the staff as well. It is very inexpensive for what you get and is really fresh ingredients. Everytime I am there they are so incredibly kind and friendly. They even offered to bring pizza to me since I live so close. If you havnt tried this place you should. I have never written a review about anywhere before but I had to for this place. They deserve it.

Terrible!! Terrible service!! Terrible management. Cold, overdone food! Ordered the 1/2 chicken, got two burned pieces after a 45 minute wait!!! My roast beef poor boy was cold, soggy and did not come with the gravy that was advertised!
Best Tortellini ever! YUM! Great Service, Karaoke on Friday nights, Love it!

Great setting, fantastic service, amazing quality. I'm so satisfied with this cute ice cream parlor!! Also, they let you sample as much as you want, with eco-friendly spoons. Overall, it's a little pricey, however, 100% worth it! I have found my favorite ice cream destination!

A uniquely New Orleans concept with cream puff like donuts (lot of icing/filling), sliders and high quality coffees and food/ingredients. 

Staff is knowledgeable and well trained and the shops are generally cozy and well decorated. A good spot for a casual meal or just to hang out.
The tacos are amazing! I love the shrimp tacos! The chicken tinga is amazing too. The staff is always very friendly and the owner is awesome! Never have I had a bad morsel from Taco Buddha!
I had the pleasure of getting one of the best haircuts ever, today while visiting Philly on business at Meister's.  Also, a very trendy - cool vibe and far from the ordinary experience!  Bravo!

It pains me to leave Cafe Equator such a low rating but I did not enjoy my experience here. My fiancé and I went for an early dinner on Saturday. We were seated fairly quickly by the hostess who apparently was also the only waitress in the restaurant. It took a while before we got some service. My house Cab was surprisingly pretty good. My fiancé got a coke and at $3.25 it better have been the best coke of his life. I don't consider myself cheap but that's a bit steep for a fountain drink. We ordered the calamari as an appraiser and it was really good. It wasn't warm but the flavors were there. Perfectly fried. As an entree my fiancé ordered the drunken noodles and he reports it was OK. Spicy, but no flavor. My stuffed peanut chicken was cooked to helllll. Omg. Dry and tough! The peanut sauce looked incredibly unappetizing however it didn't taste so bad. The side of steamed veggies were seasoned nicely. The waitress was kind enough to offer me another meal and I ordered the chicken pad Thai which was underwhelming. For some reason the dishes we ordered lacked color and appeal. Everything was brown and sad. If I ever come back I'll stick to the appetizers.

Came for the Christmas show and was not disappointed. I would say that dusk would be the best time to come as you get to see the sun in the garden, and then afterward you still get to see all the nighttime outside decorations. 

We came on a freezing Wednesday and ended up staying inside for the majority of our visit. It was beautiful, especially the children's garden section. My favorite part must be the carolers though. There was a man playing an organ in the front of a large room and everyone was encouraged to sing Christmas carols along with him. 

Food's a little overpriced.

Not happy that they charged $15.00 to give my granddaughter a manicure!  The woman never soaked her hands in warm water and never massaged her hands with lotion! Unacceptable and was not happy with the sloppy results!! Never will I come back here again!!
First time ordered Vietnamese hoagies and Pho  via Postmates. It was good! Btw, please use code: 6uldb to get $100 off delivery fee on postmates.com

Went here for lunch one Saturday. Ordered a chicken cesar salad which was absolutely delicious. 'Oven tomatoes' are just baked tomatoes. Salad had a mexican twist to it. Everyone in my party loved their dish. The chorizo quesadilla looked amazing!
The blue crab burger! Crab cake and burger in one. You can't go wrong. Pasta was good too. Pretty rich cream sauce.

Decent vibe. Divey but clean. Cool place to have a drink. BUT  better know what you like!no room for trying new things. they are big on their variety of local beers, which I'm into! I tried one that I did NOT like at all and could not drink. I asked to switch for a lighter beer and I was denied. I left the entire beer undrunk.(sp? Weird). I also witnessed a bartender explaining the menu on arrival to another party and I receive nothing like that. Not even the occasional bar service. It seemed like they only tended to regulars :(

Wow I would say get the Pho with beef and make sure you breathe between shovelful, it is so good you can get caught up just shoving it in your mouth. There are so many flavors to be enjoyed, slow down is my advice and enjoy the fresh flavors.

My partner and I walked into Trinity, attracted to the idea of a happy hour menu, for which they delivered perfectly.  The general manager, Robbie, welcomed us in, which I thought was very thoughtful for a GM to actively be monitoring his restaurant.  That's how a GM  is supposed  to operate, right?  Anyway, we were personally escorted to two bar stool seats by Robbie, and then we met the bartender, who subsequently served us perfect martinis.  This is New Orleans, so the bar was set kind of high for a new restaurant.  It delivered.  Our drinks were spot on, on point.  They had several tempting appetizers on the happy hour.  We will be back for a formal dinner.  A refreshing upset from the typical New Orleans restaurants that ride on a reputation - this place is new, and trying to prove itself.  And it worked 100%.  5/5.  Highly recommend.

DO NOT EXPECT YOUR DEPOSIT BACK NO MATTER HOW IMMACULATE YOU KEEP THE HOME.
My family and I lived in a rental property managed by The Nordstrom Group for 5 years. They are great while you are renting with them for the most part but lack compassion and basic human decency, for example while we lived there the home got broken into with the door being kicked down and they took 2 weeks to replace the front door so our family was living in an unsafe environment through that time. If minor issues arise they are quick to get them taken care of as long as you stay on them about it BUT they are awful once it's time to move. 
I was given a 30 day notice that the house would be put up for sale and we had to move. That in it self is frustrating but at the time I had just had twins who were living in the NICU so it couldn't have come at a worse time. They could not have been less empathetic to our situation. So we did what we had to do and scrambled to move out in time. 
We kept that place in great condition we repainted the house interior every year, and had the carpets professionally cleaned every 6 months or so (and freshly done for the move), we reported every issue we ever had with the house and got things promptly taken care of.  We cleaned the house very well when we moved out with the exception of the oven and a couple of tiny crumbs left in a kitchen drawer and on the floor in front of it because my toddler was eating as I was waiting for Vanessa to arrive for inspection. I figured it wasn't a big deal and they could take it out of our nearly TWO THOUSAND DOLLAR deposit. I was wrong. Vanessa came to inspect and said they would need to have a cleaning service go in and re clean the entire house because of the crumbs left. She was extremely rude and passive aggressive with comments like "I understand your babies are in the hospital but this place is unacceptable, it truly is filthy your husband should have hired a professional cleaner if you couldn't get it done." When it came time for the deposit not only did they refuse to give it back but they tried to charge me $500 more for 2 air filters to be replaced when I just replaced them 3 months prior! So I asked for them to compare the home to when I was given the keys at move in. I wrote down every issue with the home how the walls were filthy, how they left ice in the sink and a full plate of food in the microwave, and crumbs and stains everywhere on the tile  along with tons of pet hair but they refused to do a comparison. Funny thing is in their listing of the home they mentioned how well maintained the home was kept and how move in ready it was using the photos they took during inspection. 
The Nordstrom Group is not a place I'd recommend to anyone they scam you out of your money for the simple reason that they can get away with it. It's a moral-less company with zero integrity.
Great food & service. Small menu but executed well, definitely with the trip! Parking is a little wonky and traffic kinda stinks but the food is totally worth it.

Service was awesome here! Same dude who took our order also served the food and took our trash once we were done. They seem to get regulars here too as the staff was overly friendly with certain customers.

It was around 1:30 when I came with my family and it wasn't even packed at all. I saw two or three other groups here finishing their lunches.

My dad and I both got the chicken gyro. I got fruit as a side while he got basmati rice. It was good but could've been more flavorful. I've had better. My mom and sister got the lamb gyro with basmati rice. My sister thought it was just okay and that the rice had too much lemon. My older sister got the mezedes platter which came with hummus, tzaziki sauce, pita, and grape leaves with rice in it. The grape leaves weren't wrapped well. She said it was just okay.

It was clean though! And service was a selling point.
